- ISSF News – Sydney 2000 wrap-up (mentions equipment of winners):contentReference[oaicite:35]{index=35}', null, '### Daina Gudzinevičiūtė', 'Olympic Medals > Daina Gudzinevičiūtė', '["olympic-medals","daina-gudzinevi-i-t"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('009fdd3e-9414-43da-b177-5163a04b75a5', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '2', '36', '- **Perazzi (brand)**  
  The brand is framed as an **identity and legacy**, not just a manufacturer of shotguns. Owning a Perazzi is presented as entering a lineage of mastery, artistry, and emotional transformation.

- **Perazzi Identity**  
  The idea that a Perazzi is "not something you merely own — it''s something you earn, embody, and ultimately become." The gun becomes a life-defining companion.

- **Legacy**  
  A multi-generational concept of excellence. A Perazzi connects champions, aspirants, and future shooters through a shared lineage. Every scratch is treated as history in the making.', null, '2.1 Core Brand Concepts', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Core Brand Concepts', '["2-1-core-brand-concepts","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-core-brand-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('00c071ce-9eb9-4ff1-b2da-7b80171da192', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '6', '58', '- **1957** – Daniele Perazzi founds **Armi Perazzi** in Brescia, Italy, after working as a teenage apprentice gunsmith. His goal: build the world’s finest competition shotguns.[1][2]
- Early 1960s – Perazzi partners with ex-Fiat engineer **Ivo Fabbri** to modernize traditional designs.  
- Together they develop an O/U prototype for **Ennio Mattarelli**, who wins **1964 Olympic Trap gold** in Tokyo with a Perazzi. This victory establishes Perazzi on the world stage and validates the emerging MX architecture.[3]', null, '3.1.1 Origins', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Company History and Ownership Timeline > 3.1.1 Origins', '["3-1-1-origins","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-1-company-history-and-ownership-timeline-3-1-1-origins"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('00c3cb82-7d8c-4bc8-ad61-f2ff5a6ce8fa', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '19', '50', '### Kim Rhode
**Country:** United States
**Event:** Women’s Double Trap
**Medal:** Gold
**Olympics:** 2004 Athens
**Perazzi platform:** MX12
**Highlights:** Rhode won gold in women’s double trap at Athens 2004, again with her Perazzi MX12:contentReference[oaicite:68]{index=68}. This made her a two-time Olympic champion with Perazzi. *(Double trap was discontinued for women after 2004, prompting Rhode’s switch to skeet – she continued her medal streak in skeet, also initially with Perazzi.)*
**Sources:**
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:69]{index=69}
- NRA Shooting Journal – History of Perazzi (mentions Rhode’s 2004 win):contentReference[oaicite:70]{index=70}', null, '### Kim Rhode', 'Olympic Medals > Kim Rhode', '["olympic-medals","kim-rhode"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('00c9a50e-65b7-4fa4-ab86-39dd6c1033b7', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '37', '51', '- **Description:** Very hard or very soft walnut behaves differently under tools.  
- **Diagnosis:** Response of first cuts: chatter on hard wood, mushy or fuzzy edges on softer wood.  
- **Mitigation & Repair:**  
  - On hard wood: sharpen tools more frequently; may reduce cutting speed.  
  - On softer wood: cut with very sharp tools and lighter pressure; may plan a light recut or clean-up after finishing once the surface is stiffened.

---', null, '3.6.8 Hardness/Softness of Wood', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.8 Hardness/Softness of Wood', '["3-6-8-hardness-softness-of-wood","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-8-hardness-softness-of-wood"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('00ebbb38-838b-4340-8f98-d466a0f910a4', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '24', '40', '- **Rasps & Files**  
  - Coarse to fine (e.g., cabinet rasps) for shaping grips, combs, and butt contours.

- **Spokeshaves**  
  - For smoothing convex curves along comb and wrist.

- **Sandpaper**  
  - Range of grits (e.g., from ~80 up to 320+), often used with backing blocks for even surfaces.', null, '3.5.2 Shaping & Smoothing Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.2 Shaping & Smoothing Tools', '["3-5-2-shaping-smoothing-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-2-shaping-smoothing-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('01028760-24d0-423a-92d1-6b5601b41a09', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '235', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 20 | Base model: high-tech-s-20 | Platform: HT | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat', null, '### High Tech S 20', 'Models > High Tech S 20', '["model-details","high-tech-s-20","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('0138dbfb-5044-4e7e-b85a-626a51dda481', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '23', '45', '- Deciding to use **stain or alkanet-tinted oil** vs leaving wood natural:

- When to stain:  
  - To enrich a lighter or grayish blank.  
  - To **match stock and fore-end** or match a replacement part to an existing gun.  
  - To align with a brand or model signature tone.

- When not to stain:  
  - When walnut has naturally rich, desirable color that responds well to clear oil.

Care is taken to avoid blotchiness and maintain a **natural look**, not an opaque color coat.', null, '3.4.4 Color & Tint Choices', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Color & Tint Choices', '["3-4-4-color-tint-choices","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-color-tint-choices"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('02058fa6-5f38-4d1f-9352-efe52a5bd493', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '22', '35', 'Mastery at this station manifests in **consistent, precise receivers** and in the subtle decisions that make life easier for downstream craftsmen.', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('0263a0ea-c51f-4304-a555-ac0e50f11165', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '3', '56', '- **Lock-Up**  
  - Engagement of **locking bolt** with barrel **bites** and monobloc.  
  - Determines whether the gun closes solidly, with no play (“on the face”).

- **Top Lever Position**  
  - At rest, a new gun’s top lever typically sits **right of center** (e.g., around “4 o’clock”) to allow for future wear; centered lever on a new gun can indicate insufficient engagement.

- **Headspace**  
  - Distance between the chambered cartridge base and breech face; checked with **go / no-go gauges**.

- **Cocking & Opening Effort**  
  - Effort required to open the gun and cock hammers; must be smooth and not excessive.

- **Ejector & Extractor Function**  
  - **Ejectors**: throw fired hulls clear of the chambers.  
  - **Extractors**: raise shells for manual removal.  
  - Timing and strength are critical: fired shells should eject smartly, unfired shells should extract only.', null, '2.2 Mechanism Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Mechanism Concepts', '["2-2-mechanism-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-mechanism-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('02836191-e357-43b7-b303-ff47bfe913bd', '4ae532ea-bef9-47fe-9bd9-051858902e2f', '16', '23', 'Imagine the flow of **information and decisions** as a loop:

1. **Customer specifications** (fit measurements, discipline, aesthetic preferences) →  
2. **Design / Build Sheet** (dimensions, chambering, barrel specs) →  
3. **Machining & Fitting** (CNC programs and hand fitting guided by the build sheet) →  
4. **Pattern test & fit check** (output data on POI, pattern, shooter feedback) →  
5. **Final adjustments** (comb height, stock bend, rib, chokes) →  
6. **Delivery & real-world feedback** (competition results, user reports).

This loop emphasizes that the process is **customer-centric and iterative**, not one-way.', null, '3.3.3 Information & Decision Loops', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Mental Models & Diagrams > 3.3.3 Information & Decision Loops', '["3-3-3-information-decision-loops","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-3-main-content-3-3-mental-models-diagrams-3-3-3-information-decision-loops"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('0297d07a-05b9-44b8-a482-9201613e08f4', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '22', '53', '- Uses fit to **mitigate recoil** by:  
  - Adjusting pitch so pad fully contacts the shoulder.  
  - Ensuring pad shape and mounting avoid hotspots.  
- Balances shooter’s desire for “less recoil” with realistic limits of gun weight and load choice.  
- Decides when to adjust pitch immediately (e.g., clear toe dig and bruising) vs when to suggest trying the gun more before chasing minor comfort issues.', null, '3.4.3 Fit vs Recoil Management', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Fit vs Recoil Management', '["3-4-3-fit-vs-recoil-management","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-fit-vs-recoil-management"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('02cf30e9-2740-439b-8d49-1ba106510104', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '24', '39', 'When the **customer is present** (e.g., for a made-to-measure build):

- Pattern testing becomes a **joint diagnostic** for:
  - Gun POI.
  - Shooter mount and technique.

Process:

1. Shooter fires at the pattern plate using their typical mount.
2. Fitter observes:
   - Mount consistency.
   - Head position and cant.
   - Pattern impact relative to aiming point.

Distinctions:

- If the gun is patterning straight from a rest but shooter hits left consistently:
  - The issue may be **stock cast** or head alignment, not barrel regulation.
- Corrections can include:
  - Adjusting cast (stock bending, comb shims).
  - Changing comb height.
  - Coaching mount and head position.

By the end, the goal is:

- **Gun and shooter together** produce centered patterns at intended POI.', null, '3.3.3 Pattern Testing as Fit Diagnostic', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Patterning & On-Range Performance > 3.3.3 Pattern Testing as Fit Diagnostic', '["3-3-3-pattern-testing-as-fit-diagnostic","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-3-patterning-on-range-performance-3-3-3-pattern-testing-as-fit-diagnostic"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('02ee8625-8a52-407a-8290-a808ca8f93c1', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '18', '38', 'George’s relationship with Perazzi is depicted as a search for the perfect tool to match extraordinary talent.

Key equipment timeline:

- Switched to Perazzi in 2001, adopting a Perazzi MX2000S with 32″ barrels and fixed Full chokes[56][57].  
- With the MX2000S, he won championships for roughly 15 years; the gun became almost as legendary as George himself.  
- In 2016, he tried the newer Perazzi High Tech model and captured three World Championships in a single year[58][59].  
- Ultimately returned to the MX2000S, stating that its balance and feel were uniquely suited to him[59].

Customization details:

- Parallel stock for a consistent mount.  
- Tapered rib for a precise focal plane[60].  
- Fixed chokes (Full and Full) used in all situations, reflecting his philosophy that if he does his job, the tight pattern will do the rest[61][62].

The source highlights the synergy between George and his Perazzi: smooth mount, intense focus, and decisive shooting, with observers describing his performances as a “master class in calm concentration.”

---', null, '3.1.6.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Sponsored Shooters (Perazzi USA Team) > 3.1.6 George Digweed MBE – Sporting Clays (Great Britain, Sponsored Shooter) > 3.1.6.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', '["3-1-6-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-1-sponsored-shooters-perazzi-usa-team-3-1-6-george-digweed-mbe-sporting-clays-great-britain-sponsored-shooter-3-1-6-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('030a3bfb-39c0-4998-9789-e867ac2c144b', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '10', '26', '- Emotional and visual confirmation that:
  - This gun is **not ordinary**.
  - The brand understands their desire for **presentation and distinction**.
- A sense that:
  - The gun is part of their **personal aesthetic** and identity, not just a tool.', null, '3.2.3 What They Are Seeking', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.2 Prestige > 3.2.3 What They Are Seeking', '["3-2-3-what-they-are-seeking","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-2-prestige-3-2-3-what-they-are-seeking"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('037f5f4f-a8f3-42db-a3a2-b3a154801270', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '69', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 2020 (Scaled Frame) | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 28ga, 410ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### High Tech S 2020 (Scaled Frame)', 'Models > High Tech S 2020 (Scaled Frame)', '["model-details","high-tech-s-2020-scaled-frame","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('03fb7a71-cac1-44a4-979e-1ca5f61c217d', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '0', '39', '- Source: Internal Perazzi USA Document - The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun
