  - Pros: preserve design lines; provide precise wood-to-metal junction.  
  - Cons: can feel sharp and less forgiving in handling.

- **Slightly Broken Edges**  
  - Pros: more comfortable to handle; less prone to chipping.  
  - Cons: can soften design language if overdone.

**Practical approach:**  
- Preserve design-defining edges (e.g., receiver perimeter) as crisp as possible.  
- Gently break only selected edges (e.g., loading port, areas of frequent hand contact) to remove the sharpest corners.', null, '3.4.3 Edge Preservation vs Handling Comfort', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Edge Preservation vs Handling Comfort', '["3-4-3-edge-preservation-vs-handling-comfort","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-edge-preservation-vs-handling-comfort"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('05d4b1b2-e9bb-4165-a520-da7ac529e2dc', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '34', '45', '- Engraving appears **sharp and lively**, not softened by polishing.  
- Raised scroll or lettering may be gently brightened without losing definition.  
- Background surfaces around engraving are clean and uniform.', null, '3.7.2 Engraving Preservation', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.2 Engraving Preservation', '["3-7-2-engraving-preservation","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-2-engraving-preservation"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('06082767-e283-4cf9-98eb-78373eb392e7', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '6', '32', '- **Action Types (Examples)**  
  - **MX8**: classic removable-trigger competition action.  
  - **MX12**: fixed-trigger variant.  
  - **High Tech / High Tech S**: updated receiver family with heavier, stiffer construction and slightly different weight distribution.  
  - Many MX and High Tech barrels are modular and can be interchanged on the same action frame with appropriate fitting.[5]

- **Trigger System Options**  
  - **Leaf-Spring Trigger**[6][7]  
    - Very crisp and light pull.  
    - Potential failure mode: leaf spring can break suddenly; failure usually halts trigger operation.  
    - Favored by many top competitors for feel, often backed up by carrying spare trigger groups.
  - **Coil-Spring Trigger**[6][8]  
    - Typically slightly heavier and longer pull.  
    - Extremely durable; more tolerant of long-term usage.  
    - If a coil spring fails, the system often still fires at least once, providing a safety margin.

- **Single vs Double Trigger**  
  - Single trigger (selectable or non-selectable) vs two separate triggers.  
  - Configured based on discipline, shooter preference, and model constraints.', null, '2.5 Actions, Triggers, and Modularity', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.5 Actions, Triggers, and Modularity', '["2-5-actions-triggers-and-modularity","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-5-actions-triggers-and-modularity"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('0695949d-8c93-4c68-a513-a65aabde66ee', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '174', '238', 'Model name: MX20 SCO Sideplates | Base model: mx20 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX20 SCO Sideplates', 'Models > MX20 SCO Sideplates', '["model-details","mx20-sco-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('0699db65-9c04-4693-a0da-907fa10397c6', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '42', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 5 Gold | Base model: high-tech-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 5 Gold', 'Models > High Tech 5 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-5-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('072a3dfd-6517-4b86-bd24-18761a8b0816', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '13', '51', '- Understand required proof markings for the jurisdiction (e.g., Italian proof codes), including:  
  - Year codes.  
