- Recognize when a faint or partially polished‑off proof mark would require re‑stamping and, if necessary, re‑proofing.', null, '3.3.2 Proof Law & Marking Knowledge', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Proof Law & Marking Knowledge', '["3-3-2-proof-law-marking-knowledge","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-proof-law-marking-knowledge"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('07e5b8a9-5370-4dc0-97e5-e945e5ca0ed4', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '29', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 RS | Base model: high-tech-rs | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: 2020 | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: unsingle | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 10.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 2020 RS', 'Models > High Tech 2020 RS', '["model-details","high-tech-2020-rs","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('07fec2d4-9528-4910-ae45-95723944396c', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '36', '45', '- Master finishers manage multiple sets of barrels and parts through rust cycles without losing track.  
- They anticipate tricky steels and adjust recipes and cycle counts instinctively.  
- They rarely need to re-do work; most parts finish correctly on the first full process.', null, '3.7.4 Process Control & Efficiency', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.4 Process Control & Efficiency', '["3-7-4-process-control-efficiency","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-4-process-control-efficiency"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('08f4450f-1d8d-46ca-a401-a1b87eb06604', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '36', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Gun fires with safety engaged; safety too loose or too tight.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Misfitted or misassembled safety bar; weak detent; mechanical interference.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Test repeatedly with safety on; inspect safety linkage.  
  - Correct bar alignment, adjust detent and travel; verify safety cannot be bypassed by normal trigger pull.', null, '3.6.6 Safety Malfunction', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.6 Safety Malfunction', '["3-6-6-safety-malfunction","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-6-safety-malfunction"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('0974fd4e-a426-412c-8af1-9c751c5ebc3d', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '2', '49', '- **Patterning & Performance Testing Station (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Patterning Range*, *Test-Fire Range*, *Performance Test Station*.  
  - Definition: Station where completed guns are fired at pattern plates or paper targets to verify POI, regulation, and pattern quality, and to confirm functioning under live fire.

- **Pattern Tester / Performance Tester (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Test-Fire Gunsmith*, *Patterning Specialist*, *Range Technician*.  
  - Definition: Craftsperson responsible for setting up tests, firing the gun, interpreting results, and deciding whether the gun passes or requires adjustment.', null, '2.1 Roles and Station', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Station', '["2-1-roles-and-station","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-station"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('098a3032-04be-4db1-b933-77c7e500a4a7', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '139', '238', 'Model name: MX12 | Base model: mx12 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX12', 'Models > MX12', '["model-details","mx12","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('0997efa4-3507-4ed3-b834-82dff0afed98', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '39', '51', '- Masters work with **steady, fluid tool strokes**, often appearing relaxed.  
- They brace hands and tools so that slips are rare.  
- Muscle memory guides the cutter along existing grooves with minimal conscious correction.', null, '3.7.1 Smooth, Confident Motions', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.1 Smooth, Confident Motions', '["3-7-1-smooth-confident-motions","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-1-smooth-confident-motions"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('0a1fc6bc-ac4b-472a-ba6c-1b8cea89af89', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '46', '58', '- Factory showroom functions as a **mini-museum** with extensive displays of models and engraving examples.[146][147]
- Customers often describe visits as a key emotional milestone in their Perazzi journey.  
- Perazzi hosts or supports gatherings at major shoots, reinforcing a sense of **family and community** among owners.
- Online owner communities (forums, social media groups) actively discuss fitting, maintenance, and configuration choices.', null, '3.9.4 Factory Visits and Owner Community', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.9 Events, Community, and Legacy > 3.9.4 Factory Visits and Owner Community', '["3-9-4-factory-visits-and-owner-community","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-9-events-community-and-legacy-3-9-4-factory-visits-and-owner-community"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('0a4524e0-a6bb-4cf3-bd32-11675bfa0c45', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '25', '32', 'This section consolidates non-standard scenarios and caveats that require extra care at the Design & Specification stage.', null, '4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', '["4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('0aea4f68-343b-41e6-b18d-707245002197', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '17', '32', 'The tools at this station are largely **measurement and design tools**, rather than heavy machinery.

**Fit Tools**

- **Try-Guns / Adjustable Stocks**  
  - Used to empirically find the shooter’s optimal dimensions.  
  - The fitter adjusts length, cast, drop, and sometimes pitch while the shooter mounts and fires at a pattern plate or test targets.

- **Measurement Devices**  
  - Stock-measuring jigs, calipers, inclinometers, or specialized gauges.  
  - Used to record cast, drop, LOP, pitch, and toe angle from the final try-gun settings.

**Design and Simulation Tools**

- **CAD Models and Digital Design Tools**  
  - Standard parts and model families are represented in CAD.  
  - Engineers can simulate:  
    - Center of gravity and overall weight for specific barrel/stock combinations.  
    - Impact of different barrel lengths and wood densities on balance.

- **Specification Checklists**  
  - Internal checklists ensure that key parameters are set and validated, including:  
    - Chamber length (e.g., 70mm vs 76mm for 3" shells).  
    - Choke types and constrictions.  
    - Rib style, POI guidance, and proof requirements.

- **Reference Patterns and Templates**  
  - Physical pattern stocks (e.g., trap Monte Carlo vs field stock) used as starting points for custom dimensions.  
  - Engraving patterns and grade references.

**Communication Tools**

- **Direct Communication with Dealers and Customers**  
  - Telephone, email, and in-person discussion to clarify ambiguous points.  
  - Used to verify preferences, priorities (timeline vs aesthetics), and tolerance for trade-offs.

**Key Measurement Focus**

- Stock fit dimensions (LOP, DAC, DAH, cast, pitch, toe).  
- Barrel specifications (length, rib type, choke system, wall thickness constraints).  
- Target POI (e.g., 60/40 at 40 yards for trap).  
- Balance and center of gravity targets, often inferred rather than explicitly measured.

The design station also communicates intended POI and handling goals to downstream barrel regulators and stockmakers so they can align soldering, rib placement, and stock shaping with the original intent.

---', null, '3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual)', '["3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('0afc3b03-7625-4e03-a42e-ce0a734ebb14', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '28', '32', '- **Customization Complexity vs. Production Throughput**  
  - The high degree of customization inherently limits volume (approx. 7 guns/day).  
  - Attempts to increase production without compromising hand assembly would conflict with the brand’s ethos.

- **Competition vs. Field Use**  
  - Perazzi shotguns are optimized for **clay target competition** and high round counts.  
  - While they can be used for game, they are not designed as ultra-light field guns and may feel heavy for all-day carry.

- **Comparisons with Other Makers**  
  - References to mass-market and English best-gun makers are **generalized** and not exhaustive.  
  - When using this document in AI responses, treat these comparisons as **directional characterization**, not brand-specific criticism.

- **Rebuildability and Wear Parts**  
  - The assertion that a Perazzi can be rebuilt indefinitely assumes:
    - Access to appropriate wear parts (springs, pins, lugs).  
    - Skilled gunsmiths familiar with the platform.  
  - This is a design intent, not a guarantee of infinite life without proper maintenance.

---', null, '4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', '["4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('0b19d532-e1ca-4991-be5d-185daa5a6740', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '29', '51', '- **Examples:**  
  - Wrong engraving pattern or initials.  
  - Incorrect barrel length or choke configuration vs order.  
  - Different trigger type than specified (e.g., coil vs leaf).

- **Diagnosis:**  
  - Compare gun against order sheet line by line.

- **Response:**  
  - Escalate to management and relevant department (engraving, barrel shop, trigger assembly).  
  - Remedies may be complex (e.g., re-engraving, new barrels, or remake); often require customer consultation.', null, '3.6.1 Specification Mismatch', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.1 Specification Mismatch', '["3-6-1-specification-mismatch","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-1-specification-mismatch"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('0b5ca6d5-7c47-443e-ade1-7e024cad6210', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '138', '238', 'Model name: MX12 | Base model: mx12 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX12', 'Models > MX12', '["model-details","mx12","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('0b7eabcc-d892-4ee1-8c0d-182321660fa5', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '14', '38', '- **Inertia Trigger**  
  - Pros: mechanically simple; widely used and proven.  
  - Cons: requires sufficient recoil to reset; may struggle with ultra-light loads.

- **Mechanical Trigger**  
  - Pros: resets independent of recoil; works reliably with very light loads or during dry-fire.  
  - Cons: more complex; may have more parts and potential points of failure.

**Practical approach:**

- Follow model design (many Perazzis are inertia-based, with mechanical as specialized or optional where applicable).  
- Ensure inertia block mass and spring tension are tuned to work reliably with intended loads.  
- If an application demands extremely light loads, consider mechanical options or specific tuning strategies.', null, '3.4.2 Inertia vs Mechanical Second-Shot System', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Inertia vs Mechanical Second-Shot System', '["3-4-2-inertia-vs-mechanical-second-shot-system","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-inertia-vs-mechanical-second-shot-system"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('0b97eefa-88a0-4aba-bb0a-b52c6546e09d', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '33', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Shallow primer dent; occasional misfires.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Weak hammer/striker springs.  
  - Short or misaligned firing pins.  
  - Excessive drag (dirt, thick grease) in hammer/pin channels.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Compare strike marks with standard; measure protrusion if needed.  
  - Replace or adjust springs; clean and lightly lubricate channels; correct pin alignment.', null, '3.6.3 Weak Primer Strikes', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.3 Weak Primer Strikes', '["3-6-3-weak-primer-strikes","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-3-weak-primer-strikes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('0c071378-c1ad-477e-b7d1-060f3ef86693', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '3', '32', 'This section describes the main **site areas** from the user’s point of view. PerazziGPT should use these concepts when helping a user figure out where to go.', null, '2. Site Structure & Area Concepts', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 2. Site Structure & Area Concepts', '["2-site-structure-area-concepts","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-2-site-structure-area-concepts"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('0c10788f-9752-422b-bb04-ad505ee6613d', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '40', '50', '### Fehaid Al-Deehani
**Country:** Independent (Kuwait)
**Event:** Men’s Double Trap
