---', null, '5.2 External References', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 5. References & Cross-Links > 5.2 External References', '["5-2-external-references","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-5-references-cross-links-5-2-external-references"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('0fd8aef5-95b3-41c2-8cbe-ccec32e5e35c', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '34', '51', '- **Description:** Grain breaks out in or near checkering, leaving pits or lifted fibers.  
- **Diagnosis:** Visual/tactile detection of pits or rough defects in pattern.  
- **Mitigation & Repair:**  
  - Use very sharp tools and light cuts in challenging grain.  
  - For minor issues, compress fibers or re-cut adjacent diamonds to blend.  
  - For larger chip-outs, carefully fill and re-cut, leveraging wood figure to hide small repairs.', null, '3.6.5 Tearing & Chip-Out', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.5 Tearing & Chip-Out', '["3-6-5-tearing-chip-out","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-5-tearing-chip-out"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('0fe42716-abde-4688-8c35-e4573852e8b5', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '24', '50', '### Marko Kemppainen
**Country:** Finland
**Event:** Men’s Skeet
**Medal:** Silver
**Olympics:** 2004 Athens
**Perazzi platform:** MX2000/8
**Highlights:** Kemppainen took skeet silver in 2004 using a Perazzi MX2000/8:contentReference[oaicite:84]{index=84}. He shot a perfect 25 in the final round to tie for gold, only losing in a shoot-off. The MX2000’s precision contributed to his record-equaling score of 149/150, proving its worth in the most tense moments:contentReference[oaicite:85]{index=85}.
**Sources:**
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:86]{index=86}
- ISSF – Athens 2004 Skeet Men Finals report (notes Kemppainen’s Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:87]{index=87}', null, '### Marko Kemppainen', 'Olympic Medals > Marko Kemppainen', '["olympic-medals","marko-kemppainen"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('0feb6370-a107-40cb-9022-6b8316e7721a', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '24', '45', '- **Case Colors**  
  - Pros: traditional look; hard surface.  
  - Cons: process complexity; potential for distortion; aesthetic preference.

- **Blue (Rust or Hot)**  
  - Pros: classic, durable protective finish; familiar to competition shooters.  
  - Cons: can rust if neglected; shows wear on high-contact areas.

- **Coin Finish**  
  - Pros: displays engraving clearly; bright, modern or traditional look depending on treatment.  
  - Cons: requires protective coatings; more susceptible to visible rust spots if not protected.

**Practical approach:**  
- Choose finish based on model identity, engraving style, and customer preference.  
- Coordinate with engravers and product engineering when choosing which finish best highlights engraving and meets usage expectations.', null, '3.4.4 Case Colors vs Blue vs Coin Finish', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Case Colors vs Blue vs Coin Finish', '["3-4-4-case-colors-vs-blue-vs-coin-finish","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-case-colors-vs-blue-vs-coin-finish"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('103e3242-1a29-42e0-8b31-9ef4859762b2', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '5', '32', '- **Barrel Length**  
  - Common sporting/trap lengths: ~29.5", 32", 34".  
  - Longer barrels: smoother swing, longer sighting plane, more forward weight.  
  - Shorter barrels: quicker handling, faster acceleration.

- **Rib Configuration**  
  - Includes rib height, taper, and style (e.g., low vs high rib).  
  - Affects sight picture, POI, and handling.

- **Chokes**  
  - Types: fixed constriction vs interchangeable choke tubes.  
  - Dimensions: often expressed as constriction in millimeters or thousandths of an inch (e.g., extra full ~0.040" constriction for long-range use).

- **Monobloc Design**  
  - Barrel assembly style where tubes are joined to a monobloc (block containing the chambers and locking surfaces).  
  - Barrel profiles and wall thickness must stay within safe limits for desired choke constrictions.

- **Point of Impact (POI)**  
  - How high or low the pattern centers relative to the point of aim (e.g., 60/40 pattern for trap, meaning 60% of the pattern above the point of aim at a given distance).  
  - Influenced by stock fit, rib design, and barrel regulation.

- **Balance / Center of Gravity**  
  - The point where the gun naturally balances when supported.  
  - Critical to how the gun feels in the hands: front-heavy vs neutral vs back-heavy.', null, '2.4 Barrel and Performance Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Barrel and Performance Concepts', '["2-4-barrel-and-performance-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-barrel-and-performance-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('10405909-d4a3-48a3-9d2d-8fbd8a8caa62', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '37', '58', '- Basic guidance:[35][110]  
  - Keep action surfaces clean and lightly lubricated (oil on pivots, grease on locking surfaces).  
  - Clean barrels regularly; avoid corrosion and moisture.  
  - Use snap caps if dry-firing to protect firing pins.  
  - Do not store with top lever or springs excessively tensioned; relax tension where practical (e.g. leaving removable triggers in fired state during long-term storage).

- Service intervals:  
  - Routine inspection annually or as usage dictates.  
  - Major overhaul (springs, pins, locking bolt) only after high round counts (often 30,000–100,000+ shells), depending on wear.[35][36][112]

- Service network:  
  - **Perazzi USA** gunsmiths in Azusa.  
  - Factory-trained specialists (e.g. Giacomo Sporting, Whiz White in the U.S.).[111]  
  - Factory refurbishment options: rebluing, wood refinishing, checkering recut, and general mechanical refresh.', null, '3.7.3 Service and Maintenance Practices', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.7 Parts, Accessories, and Service > 3.7.3 Service and Maintenance Practices', '["3-7-3-service-and-maintenance-practices","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-7-parts-accessories-and-service-3-7-3-service-and-maintenance-practices"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('1061b45b-7290-422e-b7f7-83183ce7ab51', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '26', '39', 'Perazzi’s competition focus leads to **extra emphasis** on pattern quality:

- Many other high-end shotguns pattern-test mainly for regulation; Perazzi also prioritizes:
  - **Uniform coverage**.
  - Shot-to-shot consistency.
- Barrels are designed with:
  - High-quality steel.
  - Long forcing cones.
  - Carefully developed chokes to avoid fliers and uneven patterns.

Shooters who pattern their guns extensively with their preferred ammo often corroborate the **consistency and quality** of Perazzi’s patterns.

Performance feedback over time:

- If a shooter later reports POI issues (e.g., gun hitting too high in Olympic trap doubles), Perazzi or a qualified gunsmith can:
  - Adjust adjustable ribs/comb.
  - Make small balance changes.
- The **cross-cutting nature** of patterning and performance:
  - Factory establishes a solid baseline.
  - Adjustable systems (ribs, combs, chokes) allow ongoing tuning as needs evolve.', null, '3.3.5 Ongoing Performance & Comparisons', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Patterning & On-Range Performance > 3.3.5 Ongoing Performance & Comparisons', '["3-3-5-ongoing-performance-comparisons","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-3-patterning-on-range-performance-3-3-5-ongoing-performance-comparisons"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('10789b52-dd1d-46fc-9a92-80b1b7acb8ec', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '14', '58', '- **TM1** – Classic single-barrel trap gun introduced for American trap in the late 1960s.  
- Subsequent TM models (TMX, TM9, TM9X) offer higher ribs, adjustable ribs, and refined barrel dynamics.[128][129]
- The TM series is iconic in ATA trap and has been widely used in the Grand American and other major events.
- **Grand America 1 & 2** – TM-based unsingle and top-single trap guns named after the Grand American tournament; optimized for handicap trap.[8]', null, '3.2.4 TM Series – Single-Barrel Trap Guns', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Product Platform Architecture > 3.2.4 TM Series – Single-Barrel Trap Guns', '["3-2-4-tm-series-single-barrel-trap-guns","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-2-product-platform-architecture-3-2-4-tm-series-single-barrel-trap-guns"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('10d31c9d-c2c0-49f5-856b-10e4559bc17e', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '2', '56', '- **Assembly & Mechanical QC Station (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Final Assembly Bench*, *Mechanical QC Bench*, *Assembly & Test*.  
  - Definition: Station where all major components are assembled into the complete shotgun, and where mechanical testing and tuning are performed.

- **Assembler / Mechanical QC Specialist (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Final Assembler*, *Assembly Gunsmith*, *Mechanical Inspector*.  
  - Definition: Craftsperson responsible for final assembly, mechanical tuning, and systematic QC checks before the gun is passed to patterning and final fitting.', null, '2.1 Roles and Station', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Station', '["2-1-roles-and-station","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-station"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('10fd1073-ed1b-4a4d-97e4-2e28e0d309ea', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '27', '38', '- Assembles complex trigger groups quickly due to experience.  
- Spends disproportionate time on final sear polishing and tuning—never rushed—because this is where feel and safety are locked in.', null, '3.7.4 Efficient, Focused Workflow', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.4 Efficient, Focused Workflow', '["3-7-4-efficient-focused-workflow","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-4-efficient-focused-workflow"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('110505b3-1c16-45cf-b1f7-f3e77c707838', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '171', '238', 'Model name: MX20 SCO | Base model: mx20 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SCO | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX20 SCO', 'Models > MX20 SCO', '["model-details","mx20-sco","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('110f8c60-88f9-4678-b1c3-9eefcb87661e', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '28', '39', 'While Perazzi is function-first, aesthetics and identity are **integral to the ownership experience**:

- A competition gun must:
  - Inspire confidence.
  - Reflect the owner’s identity and story.
- Perazzi’s aesthetic language is:
  - **Italian artistry** – refined and purposeful.
  - Generally not gaudy or overly ostentatious on competition models.
  - Capable of scaling up to **high-art engraving and wood** for those who desire it.

Aesthetics become a **cross-cutting system** because they:

- Influence emotional connection to the gun.
- Reinforce brand identity.
- Often support performance by boosting confidence.', null, '3.4.1 Role of Aesthetics in a Competition Gun', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Aesthetics & Identity > 3.4.1 Role of Aesthetics in a Competition Gun', '["3-4-1-role-of-aesthetics-in-a-competition-gun","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-4-aesthetics-identity-3-4-1-role-of-aesthetics-in-a-competition-gun"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('11770e54-d38d-4bd5-97ce-46ae9ed3f101', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '57', '58', '- **1. High-Level Overview** – Purpose of this document and its scope.  
