- **5. References & Cross-Links** – How this station interacts with upstream design and downstream assembly, plus narrative transition to trigger and furniture stations.', null, 'Appendix A. Section Index', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > Appendix A. Section Index', '["appendix-a-section-index","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-appendix-a-section-index"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('1211a179-5e5d-49c8-a659-b3979cef06fd', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '19', '39', 'Relative to other makers:

- **English “best guns”**
  - Often lighter side-by-sides built for game shooting.
  - Balanced slightly more **butt-heavy** for fast mounting and comfortable all-day carry.
- **Perazzi competition guns**
  - Typically 8–9 lbs (for 12-gauge O/U).
  - Built for:
    - High-volume clay shooting.
    - Recoil moderation over long sessions.
    - Smooth, controlled swings.
  - Often balanced neutral to slightly muzzle-forward to encourage follow-through.

The **removable trigger group** and **low-profile Boss-style action**:

- Concentrate weight **between the hands**.
- Lower the **bore axis** relative to the shoulder.
- Contribute to:
  - Stability without sluggishness.
  - Reduced muzzle flip on recoil.
  - A characteristic “between-the-hands” Perazzi feel.[4]', null, '3.2.6 Comparative Handling Philosophy', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Fit, Balance & Handling Characteristics > 3.2.6 Comparative Handling Philosophy', '["3-2-6-comparative-handling-philosophy","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-2-fit-balance-handling-characteristics-3-2-6-comparative-handling-philosophy"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('123d6701-e92c-4f69-af96-74621a6f1c53', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '19', '39', '- **Tight Ejector Fit**  
  - Pros: less gas blow-by, crisp movement.  
  - Cons: risk of sticking when dirty.

- **Looser Ejector Fit**  
  - Pros: more tolerant of fouling, higher reliability.  
  - Cons: potential for more movement, slightly less refined feel.

**Design response:**

- Barrel makers aim for reliable function, erring slightly toward tolerance rather than overly tight ejectors while still ensuring good support and timing.

---', null, '3.4.6 Ejector Fit and Reliability', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.6 Ejector Fit and Reliability', '["3-4-6-ejector-fit-and-reliability","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-6-ejector-fit-and-reliability"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('128146e2-8307-402f-a4a4-75933ece0726', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '65', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S', 'Models > High Tech S', '["model-details","high-tech-s","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('1282c98a-6018-4dbf-8fbb-932ab9bf27fb', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '186', '238', 'Model name: MX2005 | Base model: mx2005 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: 2000 | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: unsingle | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### MX2005', 'Models > MX2005', '["model-details","mx2005","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('12958c07-73ff-44d8-a1b3-bbc1ddd34f06', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '3', '48', '- **Walnut Blank**  
  - Dried, rough-sawn block of walnut prepared for stock or fore-end.  
  - Often high-grade Turkish or French walnut, air-dried and later conditioned in controlled rooms (e.g., 3–4 months at controlled humidity).

- **Figure / Grain Figure**  
  - Visual patterns in the wood (curl, fiddleback, marblecake, burl, etc.).  
  - Strongly influences aesthetics and grade (e.g., SC2, SC3, SCO).

- **Grain Flow / Grain Direction**  
  - Orientation of wood fibers.  
  - Critical for strength, especially through the **wrist** (narrow section behind the receiver).

- **Sapwood**  
  - Lighter outer wood that can indicate different mechanical or finishing behavior.  
  - Sometimes avoided in critical or highly visible areas.

- **Burl / Knot / Defect**  
  - Localized grain irregularities that can be visually striking but may weaken structure if placed in critical zones.

- **Wrist**  
  - Narrow section of stock behind the receiver where breakage risk is highest if grain orientation is poor.

- **Fore-end Blank**  
  - Smaller walnut blank for the fore-end; ideally matched to stock (same log or set) in color and figure.

- **Moisture Content**  
  - Degree of remaining water in the blank; ideally at a stable level (often around 8–10% conceptually).  
  - Affects stability and risk of warping after cutting.', null, '2.2 Wood & Material Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Wood & Material Concepts', '["2-2-wood-material-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-wood-material-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('12c78f08-4bea-4e79-b671-2c1fcd0382a4', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '3', '51', '- **Checkering**  
  - Crossed sets of parallel grooves cut into wood to form small **diamonds** (pyramidal points) that provide texture and grip.

- **Lines Per Inch (LPI)**  
  - Count of checkering lines per inch.  
  - Lower LPI (e.g., ~16–18): coarser, more aggressive grip.  
  - Medium LPI (e.g., ~18–22): common on competition guns; balance of grip, comfort, and durability.  
  - Higher LPI (e.g., ~24–28): finer, more decorative, but more delicate and prone to wear/clogging.

- **Diamond Points**  
  - The peaks between grooves formed where lines intersect; should be sharp and consistent across the pattern.

- **Pattern Layout**  
  - Overall shape and angle of checkered area (e.g., point pattern on pistol grip; diamond/triangular panels on fore-end).

- **Borders**  
  - Lines (single or double) cut around the pattern to frame it and terminate diamonds cleanly.', null, '2.2 Pattern & Geometry Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Pattern & Geometry Concepts', '["2-2-pattern-geometry-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-pattern-geometry-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('1302e7be-6923-4b4c-abf2-6205be44a91e', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '7', '51', 'The **Final Inspection, Proof Marks & Sign-Off** station exists to:

- Provide a final **holistic quality control gate** before the gun leaves the factory.
- Ensure **full compliance** with:
  - Customer’s order.  
  - Internal Perazzi standards for craftsmanship and finish.  
  - Legal requirements (proof marks, serial numbers, documentation).
- Catch and correct **any remaining defects**, however small, from any previous stage.
- Prepare the gun for **delivery or shipment** in a state that preempts complaints, returns, or negative reviews.', null, '3.1.1 Purpose', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.1 Purpose', '["3-1-1-purpose","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-1-purpose"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('1366d49e-5d25-4bdf-b46d-57b9bafd5eda', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '8', '39', 'The **Barrel Fabrication & Regulation station** is responsible for producing a barrel set that is:

- Structurally safe under high pressure and repeated firing.  
- Dimensionally accurate in **chamber**, **bore**, **forcing cone**, and **choke**.  
- **Straight** along its entire length.  
- Properly **joined** to the monobloc and ribs, with no voids or loose sections.  
- **Regulated** so both barrels shoot to the intended POI at the specified distance.  
- Within target **weight and balance** parameters for the model and/or customer.

Barrels are treated as a **paramount craft** at Perazzi. This station combines high-precision machining with hand skills that few manufacturers still maintain (e.g., manual straightening).', null, '3.1.1 Purpose', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.1 Purpose', '["3-1-1-purpose","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-1-purpose"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('137e4da3-f1bd-4fa6-a78b-062a5f918249', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '25', '32', '- **Goal**  
  Live-fire test the shotgun to ensure **point of impact** and **pattern density** meet the intended specifications.

- **Inputs**  
  - Assembled shotgun.  
  - Proof/test ammunition.  
  - Indoor patterning tunnel or outdoor range.  
  - Pattern board (paper or steel plate) at set distance.  
  - Aiming bench or rest.

- **Outputs**  
  - Verified pattern results for each barrel:
    - Both barrels hitting to the same point.  
    - Appropriate pattern spread for the choke.  
  - Data on **regulation and POI** (e.g., trap gun intentionally shooting high, ~70/30).  
  - If out of spec, barrels can be adjusted (e.g., barrel bending or additional regulation).

- **Owned by**  
  **Test-firer / ballistics technician** (experienced gunsmith who knows expected standards).

---', null, '3.3.14 Patterning & Performance Testing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.3 End-to-End Production Process Map > 3.3.14 Patterning & Performance Testing', '["3-3-14-patterning-performance-testing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-3-end-to-end-production-process-map-3-3-14-patterning-performance-testing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('1387e660-0b0c-4edf-9fc9-1c0454aba5a1', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '12', '32', '- **Purpose:** Support owners in keeping their guns safe, functional, and well cared for.
- **What the user can do here:**
  - Find recommended service centers and gunsmiths authorized by Perazzi.
