**Caveat:** In such cases, extra attention is paid to wall thickness, thermal behavior, and how the barrel set will balance with the chosen action and stock.', null, '4.1 Unusually Light or Heavy Barrels', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Unusually Light or Heavy Barrels', '["4-1-unusually-light-or-heavy-barrels","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-unusually-light-or-heavy-barrels"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('17f2a294-ddb4-4269-86fa-20d62c971c67', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '14', '26', '- Answers to:
  - “What is the functional difference between these platforms or configurations?”  
  - “How will this choice affect recoil, balance, sight picture, or endurance?”  
- A brand that:
  - Respects their curiosity.
  - Helps them build a **mental model** of why a given Perazzi setup makes sense.', null, '3.3.3 What They Are Seeking', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.3 Analyst > 3.3.3 What They Are Seeking', '["3-3-3-what-they-are-seeking","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-3-analyst-3-3-3-what-they-are-seeking"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('18074466-abfe-43bc-bbf5-4fc8b0cc9d4f', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '229', '238', 'Model name: MX8 SCO Sideplates | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX8 SCO Sideplates', 'Models > MX8 SCO Sideplates', '["model-details","mx8-sco-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('180a0ab7-e542-4524-898c-53944bfd59e2', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '8', '35', 'A successful outcome at this station means:

- **Dimensional Accuracy**  
  - Critical features (hinge pin/trunnion holes, locking lug recesses, firing pin holes, sear and trigger pin bores, water table, standing breech) are within tight tolerances (often thousandths of an inch / hundredths of a millimeter).

- **Controlled Allowances for Hand Fitting**  
  - Key surfaces, especially those that interface with barrel and locking parts, are left slightly **oversized** for hand filing and scraping later.  
  - No critical dimension is unintentionally undersized (no premature looseness).

- **Material Integrity**  
  - Machining does not introduce cracks or severe stress concentrations.  
  - If heat treatment occurs after initial machining, warpage is controlled and accounted for.

- **Fit-Ready Surfaces**  
  - Surfaces that will be left as-machined in the finished gun (e.g., certain internal walls) have appropriate surface finish and do not contain stress risers or deep tool marks.

- **Downstream Compatibility**  
  - Barrel fitters, stockmakers, and assemblers can achieve perfect final fit with normal amounts of hand work.  
  - A properly finished gun will close with the characteristic **tight, solid feel** and maintain that fit over years of use.

When this station operates perfectly, later craftsmen can refine and assemble the gun without encountering unfixable machining errors.

