  - Confirm that gun closes correctly on go gauge and not on no-go gauge.

- **Trigger Pull Gauge**  
  - Measure and verify pull weights for each barrel; compare with spec or customer request.

- **Alignment & Strike Checks**  
  - Use primed cases or specialized snap caps to examine firing pin strike **position and depth**.

- **Visual & Alignment Tools**  
  - Use lights, mirrors, and eye judgment to confirm that barrels align correctly on the action (coarse boresighting, with fine POI confirmed later in pattern testing).', null, '3.3.2 Precision Instrument Use', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Precision Instrument Use', '["3-3-2-precision-instrument-use","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-precision-instrument-use"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('1897298d-28db-4413-9b25-cc1a4362990c', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '38', '51', '- Master inspectors follow a **consistent, methodical path** during inspection, for example:  
  1. Start at muzzle: inspect finish, choke marks, rib, beads.  
  2. Move to fore-end: latch fit, wood-metal joints.  
  3. Inspect action exterior: engraving, finish, marking clarity.  
  4. Open gun: inspect chambers, bores, extractors/ejectors, interior finish.  
  5. Check triggers and safety with snap caps.  
  6. Verify stock fit, pad fit, and wood finish.  
  7. Confirm accessories and case presentation.  
  8. Confirm proof marks, serial numbers, and paperwork.

- This routine ensures no area is forgotten, even after inspecting many guns.', null, '3.7.1 Systematic, Repeatable Process', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.1 Systematic, Repeatable Process', '["3-7-1-systematic-repeatable-process","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-1-systematic-repeatable-process"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('18b463b2-b005-411c-94fb-85d773abd06b', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '14', '35', '- **Faster Machining Cycles**  
  - Pros: higher throughput.  
  - Cons: higher heat, potential for rougher finish, faster tool wear.

- **Slower, Controlled Cuts**  
  - Pros: smoother finishes and cooler steel, especially important for surfaces that will not be hand-polished later.  
  - Cons: longer cycle times.

**Station practice:**

- Use slower, more careful passes on critical or visible surfaces.  
- Accept more aggressive cutting on hidden or non-critical surfaces when safe.', null, '3.4.2 Cutting Speed vs. Tool Life vs. Surface Finish', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Cutting Speed vs. Tool Life vs. Surface Finish', '["3-4-2-cutting-speed-vs-tool-life-vs-surface-finish","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-cutting-speed-vs-tool-life-vs-surface-finish"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('18c213b7-71ed-4b7b-b614-3802279e4f24', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '161', '238', 'Model name: MX16 SCO | Base model: mx16 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SCO | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 16ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX16 SCO', 'Models > MX16 SCO', '["model-details","mx16-sco","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('18c374f8-5c7f-4bb9-b4b3-6beed525088f', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '20', '56', '- Confirm presence and correctness of **proof marks** and required legal markings.  
- Understand that barrels and actions are proofed earlier, but verify that post-proof work has not altered safety-critical elements.  
