- "Which platform should I look at for sporting clays?"
- "Where can I compare MX8 and High Tech?"', null, '2.3.2 Shotguns / Platforms', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 2. Site Structure & Area Concepts > 2.3 Site Area Concepts > 2.3.2 Shotguns / Platforms', '["2-3-2-shotguns-platforms","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-2-site-structure-area-concepts-2-3-site-area-concepts-2-3-2-shotguns-platforms"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('1fc2b06f-e4e1-4ed0-a1c8-5e1091223f46', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '16', '45', '- Protecting checkering from heavy finish build:  
  - Masking checkered areas when spraying synthetic finishes.  
  - Carefully brushing a **thinned finish** into checkering when sealing, then removing excess (e.g., with a toothbrush) so diamonds remain clean.

- Maintaining clean borders:  
  - Scoring lightly around checkering borders before finishing to minimize finish bleed.  
  - Avoiding puddling at edges between smooth and checkered areas.

- Recuttering or cleaning checkering after finishing:  
  - Lightly re-cutting or brushing checkering to sharpen any softened detail or remove residual finish.', null, '3.3.6 Checkering Protection & Sealing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.6 Checkering Protection & Sealing', '["3-3-6-checkering-protection-sealing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-6-checkering-protection-sealing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('1fdd6cdf-aa82-4319-873e-029b75f14494', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '191', '238', 'Model name: MX28 SC3 | Base model: mx28 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 28ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX28 SC3', 'Models > MX28 SC3', '["model-details","mx28-sc3","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('1fe41f4b-8fc2-404d-9786-51493644b7be', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '17', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech 2020', 'Models > High Tech 2020', '["model-details","high-tech-2020","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('203d0c6f-51ca-4856-ab7e-3028b4942010', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '48', '53', '- Significant fit problems identified at this stage (e.g., hopelessly wrong base measurements) may necessitate more serious work such as:  
  - A new stock.  
  - Substantial barrel or rib adjustments.  
- Such situations are rare but must be handled honestly and with a clear plan.', null, '4.3 Major Changes Discovered Late', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.3 Major Changes Discovered Late', '["4-3-major-changes-discovered-late","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-3-major-changes-discovered-late"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('206f1ad1-2d06-4b14-a5f2-563068938df4', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '14', '45', '- Applying very **thin coats** of oil:  
  - Rubbing in with hand or pad to generate slight warmth and promote penetration.  
  - Wiping off all excess to avoid sticky build.

- Managing **coats and timing**:  
  - Allowing each coat to dry fully, often overnight or longer, depending on formulation and environment.  
  - Building 10–20+ thin coats for a traditional oil finish when time allows.

- Using controlled environments:  
  - Dust-free, warm, dry rooms or cabinets to promote even curing.

- Judging **finish build**:  
  - Knowing when enough is enough to avoid a thick, plasticky film.  
  - Stopping when pores are filled to the desired degree and a soft, deep sheen is achieved.', null, '3.3.4 Application Techniques – Oil Finishes', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.4 Application Techniques – Oil Finishes', '["3-3-4-application-techniques-oil-finishes","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-4-application-techniques-oil-finishes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('20b78f58-411d-4d31-8654-ff63459717b7', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '27', '50', '### Juan Miguel Rodríguez
**Country:** Cuba
**Event:** Men’s Skeet
**Medal:** Bronze
