- Always keep the answer grounded in the Perazzi ethos: long-term relationship between shooter and gun, craft, and serious competition use.', null, '5. Processing Guidelines (for AI Use)', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 5. Processing Guidelines (for AI Use)', '["5-processing-guidelines-for-ai-use","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-5-processing-guidelines-for-ai-use"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('20d3ea0f-685e-48dd-8477-ceebb171a678', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '14', '36', '- Messaging is **reflective and intimate**, addressing the shooter’s inner life and aspirations.  
- The brand sees itself as **inviting people into a journey**, not pushing a product.  
- Copy makes heavy use of **metaphor, introspection, and sensory storytelling** to create an aspirational emotional experience.', null, '3.3.2 Deeply Emotional & Personal', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Brand Tone & Personality > 3.3.2 Deeply Emotional & Personal', '["3-3-2-deeply-emotional-personal","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-3-brand-tone-personality-3-3-2-deeply-emotional-personal"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('20ffb3b6-c253-4471-bb06-c456fa5e39fb', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '31', '39', 'This section consolidates special scenarios that require extra care in barrel fabrication and regulation.', null, '4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', '["4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('2105d42d-5a42-4ebe-b694-7046eaea25e9', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '172', '238', 'Model name: MX20 SCO Gold | Base model: mx20 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX20 SCO Gold', 'Models > MX20 SCO Gold', '["model-details","mx20-sco-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('2190b6b7-b9d2-4466-8148-f0cd9eeab701', '500269f5-9624-4f5b-9ded-8de9740793b2', '0', '7', 'Perazzi takes great pride in crafting premium, high-performance shotguns, each meticulously designed and assembled to the highest standards of quality, precision, and authenticity. To preserve the warranty, the integrity and value of your Perazzi shotgun, please be aware of the following potential risks:', null, 'Consumer Warning Notice', 'Consumer Warning Notice', '["consumer-warning-notice","consumer-warning-notice"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:16.184829+00', null), ('21b0cb79-fd89-4a30-afbd-781080cd504b', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '0', '238', 'Model name: DC | Base model: dc | Platform: DC | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: side-by-side | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### DC', 'Models > DC', '["model-details","dc","platform:dc"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('21b16ecc-17f1-45d2-839f-ccdaf76b7502', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '168', '238', 'Model name: MX20 SC3 Gold | Base model: mx20 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX20 SC3 Gold', 'Models > MX20 SC3 Gold', '["model-details","mx20-sc3-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('21b60c8d-fcaf-481e-a33c-64946f076bac', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '29', '48', '- **Straightedges & Rulers**  
  - Used to represent bore/rib axis and measure drop to comb/heel.

- **Protractors / Angle Gauges**  
  - Used conceptually to define pitch and cast angles, especially during layout.

- **Templates & Patterns**  
  - Butt, comb, and grip outline templates; metal or wood patterns to trace outlines.

- **Marking Tools**  
  - Chalk, pencils, and marking gauges to lay down lines on rough, uneven blanks.

- **Calipers & Compasses**  
  - Spot-check thickness of wood left in critical areas (e.g., comb, wrist) after roughing.

- **Moisture Meter (conceptual)**  
  - To verify blanks are within desired moisture content range.', null, '3.5.2 Layout & Measurement Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.2 Layout & Measurement Tools', '["3-5-2-layout-measurement-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-2-layout-measurement-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('220c855d-aa5b-44c5-be63-b0c2a7e83059', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '32', '50', '### Zuzana Štefečeková
**Country:** Slovakia
**Event:** Women’s Trap
**Medal:** Silver
**Olympics:** 2012 London
**Perazzi platform:** MX2000/3
**Highlights:** Štefečeková earned trap silver in 2012 with a Perazzi MX2000/3:contentReference[oaicite:113]{index=113}. This model is a rare variant with a removable trigger unit; she favored it for its crisp trigger pull. Štefečeková continued her success in 2021 (Tokyo) where she upgraded to gold – again with a Perazzi (High Tech 2020):contentReference[oaicite:114]{index=114}, confirming a long-term pattern.
**Sources:**
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:115]{index=115}
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:116]{index=116}', null, '### Zuzana Štefečeková', 'Olympic Medals > Zuzana Štefečeková', '["olympic-medals","zuzana-tefe-ekov"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('2246565a-cb9f-437f-9ef8-2ba6ba78c290', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '11', '53', '- Understands relationships between **stock dimensions** and **shot placement**:  
  - Left/right hits vs cast.  
  - High/low hits vs comb height/drop and sometimes pitch.  
- Interprets pattern and target results in light of fit rather than only shooter technique.  
- Uses an iterative approach similar to an optometrist: small changes followed by **“better or worse?”** checks.', null, '3.3.1 Shotgun Fitting Expertise', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.1 Shotgun Fitting Expertise', '["3-3-1-shotgun-fitting-expertise","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-1-shotgun-fitting-expertise"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('22cda9e3-546a-4c20-b086-d7095a44575e', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '19', '39', '- All European makers adhere to **CIP proof laws**:
  - Guns must pass proof tests (e.g., 1370 bar for many modern 12-gauge magnum shells).[12]
  - Proof marks are stamped onto barrels/actions.
- Regulation:
  - Double-barrel makers (O/U and SxS) must regulate barrels to hit a proper POI.
  - Techniques:
    - Trial soldering and shooting.
    - Adjustment using wedges or partial resoldering.
- Perazzi’s difference is largely in **degree and emphasis**, not in principle:
  - They invest heavily in fine regulation for competition accuracy.
  - Mass producers may accept wider POI tolerances for field-grade guns.', null, '3.2.3 Proof and Regulation Standards', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices > 3.2.3 Proof and Regulation Standards', '["3-2-3-proof-and-regulation-standards","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices-3-2-3-proof-and-regulation-standards"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('232ef043-57bc-456e-8ef9-e987b72553a6', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '5', '53', '- **Point of Impact (POI) vs Sight Picture**  
  - Relationship between where the shooter **sees** the target over the rib and where the pattern centers.  
  - Final fitting ensures POI matches the shooter’s desired sight picture (e.g., floating targets vs covering them).

- **Comfort & Recoil Management**  
  - Distribution of recoil across shoulder and cheek.  
  - Fit can significantly reduce perceived recoil by aligning pad and comb with the shooter’s body.

- **Natural Mount & Swing**  
  - The gun should come to the shoulder and cheek **without conscious adjustment**, and track targets smoothly.  
  - Final fitting tunes stock geometry until mount and swing feel intuitive.', null, '2.4 Performance & Experience Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Performance & Experience Concepts', '["2-4-performance-experience-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-performance-experience-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('2353d79a-ad86-4d92-a39f-02771d2ab75d', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '2', '51', '- **Checkering Station (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Checkering Bench*, *Grip Checkering Station*.  
  - Definition: Station where the stock and fore-end receive hand-cut checkering.

- **Checkerer (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Checkering Technician*, *Checkering Specialist*.  
  - Definition: Craftsperson who lays out and cuts checkering patterns. At Perazzi, this work is reportedly done by a small group of highly specialized technicians (e.g., “three skilled female technicians” working full time).', null, '2.1 Roles and Station', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Station', '["2-1-roles-and-station","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-station"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('2366e9b5-1a9a-4b0d-9ed8-0fba5d689e87', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '3', '32', '- **Fitting Session**  
  - A session where a shooter is measured and test-fires an adjustable gun (try-gun) to determine stock dimensions and sometimes balance preferences.

- **Perazzi Experience Visit**  
  - A structured visit (often half-day or longer) where a customer works with a fitting specialist using adjustable test guns to dial in **stock dimensions**, **intended use**, and **model options** for a bespoke build.

- **Try-Gun (Adjustable Test Gun)**  
  - A special, highly adjustable shotgun used during fittings.  
  - Adjustable for: length of pull, cast, drop, sometimes pitch and comb height.  
  - The fitter adjusts the try-gun until the customer’s mount, pattern, and perceived recoil behavior align with the target use.', null, '2.2 Customer & Fitting Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Customer & Fitting Concepts', '["2-2-customer-fitting-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-customer-fitting-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('23799c02-0ee1-4fc4-88cc-d67e8ca1b11c', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '18', '35', '- **CNC Milling Machines**  
  - Multi-axis machining centers (Perazzi reportedly has several high-value CNCs, some around $1M each).  
  - Used for roughing, semi-finishing, and finishing passes on the receiver.

- **EDM (Electrical Discharge Machining)**  
  - Potentially used for hard-to-cut or tight internal features (e.g., precise slots) in hardened steel.

- **Lathes and Gun Drills (adjacent processes)**  
  - More relevant to pins and barrel components, but may be used for turning small action-related parts.

- **Custom Jigs and Fixtures**  
  - Purpose-built fixtures to hold the forging in different orientations (e.g., machining the top latch recess, drilling firing pin holes).

- **Hand Tools**  
  - Files, stones, and hand reamers to deburr, refine, and bring selected bores or surfaces to final size.', null, '3.5.1 Machines and Cutting Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Machines and Cutting Tools', '["3-5-1-machines-and-cutting-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-machines-and-cutting-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('237f2c7b-a187-4d4f-84eb-6580da7d1f11', '177a681e-a602-4d92-af07-b17c98816feb', '6', '13', 'Perazzi writing uses a highly intentional tone of voice with the following characteristics:

1. **Deeply Emotional and Reflective**  
   - Consistently emotional, introspective, and profound.  
   - Deliberately invokes strong feelings of inspiration, aspiration, reverence, and authenticity.  
   - Focuses less on mere information and more on evoking a genuine emotional response.

2. **Authentic and Personal**  
   - Frequently uses personal, emotionally charged language and anecdotal framing.  
   - Emphasizes a strong personal connection to the brand.  
   - Creates an impression of sincerity and heartfelt engagement rather than detached marketing.

3. **Quietly Confident and Aspirational**  
   - Confident without boasting or loud claims.  
   - Positions Perazzi as uniquely prestigious and aspirational.  
   - Suggests an implicit, inherent superiority rather than explicit self-praise.

4. **Philosophical and Thoughtful**  
   - Often includes philosophical nuances and reflective ideas.  
   - Invites the reader to think about mastery, legacy, personal transformation, and values.  
   - Treats ownership and craftsmanship as vehicles for deeper meaning, not just performance.

5. **Reverent and Respectful**  
   - Expresses reverence for Perazzi’s craftsmanship, history, and ethos.  
   - Uses a tone of admiration and deep respect.  
   - Frames Perazzi as more than a product—an embodiment of deeply held values.', null, '3.1 Tone of Voice', 'Perazzi Writing Style and Tone (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Tone of Voice', '["3-1-tone-of-voice","perazzi-writing-style-and-tone-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-1-tone-of-voice"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:49.998824+00', null), ('239216b6-fcc4-4889-93cb-3a893e9be4f4', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '190', '238', 'Model name: MX28 B | Base model: mx28 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 28ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX28 B', 'Models > MX28 B', '["model-details","mx28-b","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('23cc2b97-57be-42da-9176-86cc234c1003', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '76', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 2020 Gold | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S 2020 Gold', 'Models > High Tech S 2020 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-s-2020-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('23df91ee-2056-4f13-bb83-896ed796a6eb', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '31', '45', 'Representative failure modes at the wood finishing station:

1. **Uneven Color / Stain Blotchiness**  
   - *Cause:* variable absorption in walnut, uneven stain application, lack of conditioner.  
   - *Diagnosis:* patchy dark/light areas after staining or first coats.  
   - *Mitigation:* pre-testing on offcuts; using wash coats/conditioners; blending with additional dye; in severe cases, stripping and re-staining.

2. **Dust Inclusions / Nibs**  
   - *Cause:* dust or lint landing on wet finish.  
   - *Diagnosis:* tiny bumps or cloudy specs visible under raking light.  
   - *Mitigation:* sanding or nib-sanding between coats; keeping environment and rags scrupulously clean.

3. **Runs or Sags (Sprayed Finishes)**  
   - *Cause:* heavy application, improper viscosity, poor technique.  
   - *Diagnosis:* visible drips, curtains, or thicker streaks.  
   - *Mitigation:* allow to cure, then level-sand and re-coat with thinner, more controlled applications.

4. **Orange Peel Texture (Sprayed Finishes)**  
   - *Cause:* improper atomization, too-thick coats, or incorrect solvent balance.  
   - *Diagnosis:* pebbled surface resembling citrus skin.  
   - *Mitigation:* carefully leveling with fine abrasives, then adjusting thinning and spray technique.

5. **Finish Not Curing / Remaining Tacky**  
   - *Cause:* thick oil coats, insufficient driers, low temperature or high humidity, or incorrect poly mix.  
   - *Diagnosis:* persistent tackiness; fingerprint imprints; lingering solvent smell.  
   - *Mitigation:* increased drying time or warmth; wiping with solvent and re-applying thinner coats; discarding compromised batches.

6. **Cloudiness / Blush**  
   - *Cause:* trapped moisture (especially in humid conditions), incompatible solvents.  
   - *Diagnosis:* milky or cloudy appearance in film.  
   - *Mitigation:* controlled warmth and ventilation; stripping and reapplying in severe cases.

7. **Cracks or Crazing in Finish (Long-Term)**  
   - *Cause:* overly thick, brittle film; wood movement; climatic changes.  
   - *Diagnosis:* fine surface cracking, often around pores or at edges.  
   - *Mitigation:* prevention through thin, flexible finishes on high-use guns; repair may require partial or full refinish.

8. **Interaction with Recoil Pad or Adhesives**  
   - *Cause:* pad installation after finish causing chipping at butt edges.  
   - *Diagnosis:* visible white line or chipped edge where pad meets wood.  
   - *Mitigation:* careful pad fitting; sometimes fitting pad before final coats; touch-up or sanding pad edges to maintain flush transition.

9. **Checkering Clogging**  
   - *Cause:* excessive finish in checkering valleys.  
   - *Diagnosis:* rounded, muted diamonds; slippery feel in checkered area.  
   - *Mitigation:* minimal finish applications in checkering; brushing out with stiff brush; light recutting to restore diamond sharpness.

10. **Gloss Inconsistency**  
    - *Cause:* uneven sanding, variable film thickness, or partial rub-out.  
    - *Diagnosis:* patches of differing sheen under raking light.  
    - *Mitigation:* uniform rub-out with fine abrasive or steel wool; additional targeted coats or polishing to equalize.

11. **Edge Seal & Fit Issues**  
    - *Cause:* inadequate sealing at edges, or finish swelling inletting areas.  
    - *Diagnosis:* visible raw lines at metal/wood seam, or too-tight fit after finishing.  
    - *Mitigation:* extra sealing attention on end grain; keeping inletting mostly unbuilt or lightly sealed; careful relief if fit tightens slightly.

---', null, '3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis', '["3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('23e7c74a-f10d-4ca2-9ac3-b76318b48e57', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '16', '51', '- Working at close range with good light and sometimes magnification to see minute deviations.  
- Detecting line drift or spacing irregularities early and **nudging lines back** gradually while cuts are still shallow.  
- Maintaining consistent motifs in border areas and across panels on both sides of the gun.', null, '3.3.6 Visual Acuity & Early Correction', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.6 Visual Acuity & Early Correction', '["3-3-6-visual-acuity-early-correction","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-6-visual-acuity-early-correction"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('240351e7-8a15-415f-8d29-271e9be07579', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '11', '49', '- Ability to **aim and fire consistently** at the aiming mark, minimizing human error:  
  - Use of bench rests or supports to stabilize the gun.  
  - Understanding that pattern spread tolerates some aiming variation, but POI evaluation still requires care.

- Selecting appropriate **distances** and setups for:
  - POI and regulation checks (often 15–20 m or 35–40 m depending on desired insight).  
  - Full pattern spread analysis (typically at 35–40 m).', null, '3.3.1 Marksmanship & Setup', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.1 Marksmanship & Setup', '["3-3-1-marksmanship-setup","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-1-marksmanship-setup"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('24275724-832e-498b-850b-488c49569b52', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '10', '39', '- At Perazzi, **bespoke is the default**, not the exception:
  - Custom stock measurements.
  - Barrel lengths and configurations.
  - Chokes, ribs, triggers, engraving, and wood grade.
- Production characteristics:
  - Output: roughly **1,500–3,000 guns/year**.
  - Organization resembles a **flexible workshop** rather than a high-speed assembly line.
- Comparisons:
  - Other makers often separate “standard line production” from a smaller **custom shop** (e.g., Beretta SO line).
  - For Perazzi, customization is built into the core production model, not bolted on.
- Consequences:
  - Serial-number matching and individual fitting of major parts (barrels, actions, fore-ends).
  - Reduced interchangeability of major components between guns.
  - Enhanced individuality and fit at the cost of easy mix-and-match.', null, '3.1.5 Customization as Standard Production', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations > 3.1.5 Customization as Standard Production', '["3-1-5-customization-as-standard-production","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations-3-1-5-customization-as-standard-production"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('242b6a34-61d1-4c40-8802-82eacd3e6a63', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '21', '50', '### Maria Quintanal
**Country:** Spain
**Event:** Women’s Trap
**Medal:** Silver
**Olympics:** 2004 Athens
**Perazzi platform:** MX2000/8
**Highlights:** Quintanal earned trap silver in 2004 using a Perazzi MX2000/8:contentReference[oaicite:74]{index=74}. A veteran shooter, she benefited from the MX2000’s reduced recoil and custom fit, as she battled windy conditions to secure a medal for Spain.
**Sources:**
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:75]{index=75}
- ISSF Newsletter 2004 – highlights of women’s trap (mentions Quintanal’s equipment):contentReference[oaicite:76]{index=76}', null, '### Maria Quintanal', 'Olympic Medals > Maria Quintanal', '["olympic-medals","maria-quintanal"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('2517955a-5ee6-44f6-9392-46cf6ef510ce', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '20', '49', '- **Fewer Shots (1–2 per barrel)**  
  - Pros: faster throughput; sufficient when upstream quality and regulation are reliable.  
  - Cons: patterning has inherent shot-to-shot variability; fewer samples mean less statistical certainty.

- **More Shots**  
  - Pros: higher confidence in pattern consistency and POI.  
  - Cons: more ammo and time; usually unnecessary if no anomalies are seen.

**Practical approach:**  
- Fire **at least one** well-aimed shot per barrel; shoot follow-up patterns if results are questionable.  
- Use experience to determine when a second or third pattern is needed for confirmation.', null, '3.4.2 Number of Shots per Barrel', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Number of Shots per Barrel', '["3-4-2-number-of-shots-per-barrel","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-number-of-shots-per-barrel"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('253f49a1-a94e-4992-95a4-778eb9666ac2', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '10', '38', 'Ian’s firearm of choice is described as a Perazzi trap shotgun that gives him absolute trust in every shot. Additional points:

- One of his major handicap victories occurred in an event presented by Perazzi – framed as a fitting nod to the brand he now represents[12].  
- While many top competitors switch equipment, Ian is portrayed as having found his perfect fit with Perazzi, whose balance and precision match his fast yet smooth shooting style.  
- With his Perazzi, Ian maintains an aspirational outlook: he approaches each target with focus and humility, always striving for the next milestone.

The source notes that the “wide-eyed kid” who once outshot the field at Sparta is now a quietly confident young man intent on carving out a lasting legacy in American Trap, “one target at a time.”

