Key elements from the source:

- Nicknamed the “Shooterina” (shooter + ballerina).  
- Spent childhood training in dance, including a Juilliard summer program, before discovering her true “stage” on the skeet range[67][68].  
- Became ISSF Women’s Skeet World Champion in 2017, winning gold in Moscow[69].  
- First woman ever to win both a Junior World title (2014) and an Open World title in Women’s Skeet[70].

Additional achievements:

- Multiple World Cup medals, including a silver in Lonato[71].  
- Several USA National Championships.  
- Pan American Games gold medal in Mixed Team Skeet (2023)[72].

Dania typically trains with high frequency (source notes: six days a week, ~250 targets a day)[74][71]. She narrowly missed the 2016 Olympic team but later made the Tokyo 2020 (held 2021) Olympic team as an alternate.

The source underscores her role as an inspiration, particularly for young women, and notes her work speaking about mental health in sports and encouraging youth at clubs[68][73].', null, '3.2.1.1 Biography & Background', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Supported Shooters > 3.2.1 Dania Vizzi – International Skeet (Supported Shooter) > 3.2.1.1 Biography & Background', '["3-2-1-1-biography-background","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-2-supported-shooters-3-2-1-dania-vizzi-international-skeet-supported-shooter-3-2-1-1-biography-background"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('290aeb07-45de-4a81-97d2-5be1326f7d48', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '23', '51', '- **Hand-Cut**  
  - Pros: adaptable to varying grain hardness; allows on-the-fly corrections; has subtle visual “sparkle.”  
  - Cons: labor-intensive; requires highly skilled specialists.

- **Machine/Laser Cut**  
  - Pros: faster, consistent over large runs.  
  - Cons: less adaptable to unpredictable grain; may look too uniform; error correction harder.

**Practical context:**  
- Perazzi emphasizes **hand checkering by specialized technicians**, reflecting a conscious choice of tradition and quality over maximal automation.', null, '3.4.5 Hand-Cut vs Machine / Laser Cut', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.5 Hand-Cut vs Machine / Laser Cut', '["3-4-5-hand-cut-vs-machine-laser-cut","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-5-hand-cut-vs-machine-laser-cut"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('295a2151-a548-42ad-9bcf-159d81040394', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '12', '38', 'Trigger assembly involves recurring trade-offs among **lightness, safety, reliability, and feel**.', null, '3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs', '["3-4-decisions-trade-offs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('29ba463f-fcca-47c9-814e-94154115124d', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '11', '39', '- **Finished Barrel Set (In the White)**  
  - Two tubes joined in a monobloc, with top and side ribs installed.  
  - External surfaces polished and ready for finishing (e.g., bluing).

- **Proofed Barrels**  
  - Barrels stamped with proof marks (e.g., gauge, chamber length, proof code) after passing proof tests.

- **Regulation Data / Test Results**  
  - Pattern and POI records from test-firing or optical alignment.  
  - Confirmation that adjustments (if any) were successful.

- **Intermediate Fit-Ready Features**  
  - Prepared ejector channels and monobloc features for later ejector fitting.  
  - Barrel weight marks (e.g., in kg) if used internally or stamped.

These outputs feed into **action fitting**, **stockmaking**, **ejector fitting**, and final **assembly and finishing**.

