ver","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('2b9d3d9a-4e03-449d-b73b-bdc385e676c7', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '10', '36', '- Acquiring a Perazzi is positioned as a **rite of passage**.  
- The emphasis is on **who the owner is** and who they are becoming, not on the commercial act of buying.  
- The customization and build journey is framed as a **personal evolution**, strengthening the connection between shooter and shotgun.', null, '3.2.1 Transformation Over Transaction', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Emotional & Philosophical Brand Pillars > 3.2.1 Transformation Over Transaction', '["3-2-1-transformation-over-transaction","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-2-emotional-philosophical-brand-pillars-3-2-1-transformation-over-transaction"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('2bae84ca-8459-4d3e-a908-6b18374500f6', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '4', '45', '- **Pore-Filled vs Open-Pore**  
  - *Pore-filled*: pores filled to create a flatter, more reflective surface.  
  - *Open-pore*: pores partially visible; more natural feel and microtexture.

- **Sheen Levels**  
  - *Matte*: minimal reflection; low glare.  
  - *Satin / Semi-gloss*: gentle luster, common on competition guns.  
  - *High Gloss*: mirror-like reflection, often for presentation guns.

- **Chatoyance**  
  - The 3D depth effect in figure; appears to move under changing light.  
  - Enhanced by good pore filling, color choice, and thin, clear film/oil layers.

- **Grain Raising / “Whiskering”**  
  - Deliberately wetting wood to raise grain, then sanding or cutting it back.  
  - Reduces grain-raising later when finish is applied.', null, '2.3 Surface & Sheen Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Surface & Sheen Concepts', '["2-3-surface-sheen-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-surface-sheen-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('2c05cf3d-4f12-4175-b6f1-5fda057ea0ed', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '110', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S X | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: X | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S X', 'Models > High Tech S X', '["model-details","high-tech-s-x","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('2c1a4c6f-c3c8-4785-8f17-ad34554836a8', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '14', '48', '- **Pantograph/duplicator operation**:  
  - Tracing pattern stock smoothly and evenly to avoid over-cutting.  
  - Adjusting cut depth and offset to leave specified oversize.  
- **CNC operation**:  
  - Setting up blanks with correct orientation and fixturing.  
  - Using or adjusting programs to reflect individual customer dimensions.  
  - Selecting feeds and speeds that minimize tear-out, especially in highly figured areas.', null, '3.3.3 Machine Operation (Duplicator / CNC)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.3 Machine Operation (Duplicator / CNC)', '["3-3-3-machine-operation-duplicator-cnc","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-3-machine-operation-duplicator-cnc"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('2c5ef6a4-f179-4e84-aa7b-6065167ad292', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '4', '32', '- **Build Sheet / Blueprint**  
  The technical document capturing the customer’s specifications (dimensions, options, configuration) and guiding all subsequent manufacturing steps.

- **Stock Blank**  
  A dried walnut block (of specified grade) from which the shotgun’s stock and fore-end are carved.

- **Fore-end Iron**  
  The metal structure under the fore-end wood that interfaces with the barrels, houses the latch, and often the ejector mechanism.

- **Lockwork Specialist / Master Assembler / Test-Firer**  
  Specialist roles in Perazzi’s production: trigger and lockwork assembly, final mechanical assembly and adjustment, and live-fire pattern and performance testing.

---', null, '2.3 Production & Craft Terms', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Production & Craft Terms', '["2-3-production-craft-terms","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-production-craft-terms"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('2c6e01b0-8568-4e4f-9541-5fe55ec21525', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '5', '39', '- **Engraving**  
  Decorative cutting and inlay on metal surfaces. Ranges from simple scroll to full game scenes with gold inlay, often hand-executed on higher grades (e.g., SC3, SCO).

- **Walnut Grade**  
  Visual and structural classification of stock wood (from standard to exhibition), reflecting figure, color, and grain.

- **House Style**  
  Perazzi’s default aesthetic for competition guns: generally **understated, purposeful, and modern**, with an emphasis on function-forward design.

- **Personalization**  
  Bespoke engraving, wood selection, initials, crests, and other visual choices that align the gun’s appearance with the owner’s identity and legacy.

