- Regularly sharpening cutters to maintain crisp cutting rather than tearing.', null, '3.3.4 Grain Awareness', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.4 Grain Awareness', '["3-3-4-grain-awareness","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-4-grain-awareness"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('2f9a226a-c1b9-4b27-a4bd-cc4271186d33', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '18', '39', '- Decide the distance at which barrels should effectively coincide (e.g., 35–40 m).  
- Over-unders are typically set nearly parallel, sometimes with subtle vertical convergence to accommodate different barrel positions relative to sight line.

**Design response:**

- Use standard internal distances and reference setups (e.g., a particular convergence at 11 m to achieve desired effect at 35 m).  
- Modify approach for special customer requests (e.g., slightly higher second barrel POI for longer-range follow-up shots).', null, '3.4.5 Regulation Distance and Strategy', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.5 Regulation Distance and Strategy', '["3-4-5-regulation-distance-and-strategy","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-5-regulation-distance-and-strategy"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('2fb36ece-fba2-4ca0-aaae-7518fddc5832', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '20', '45', 'Metal finishing involves repeated balancing decisions between **appearance, durability, fit preservation, and process time**.', null, '3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs', '["3-4-decisions-trade-offs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('2fc3b739-92c3-45f4-b053-6357141f883c', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '180', '238', 'Model name: MX2000/8 | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2000 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib height: 4.0 mm | Rib style: ramp', null, '### MX2000/8', 'Models > MX2000/8', '["model-details","mx2000-8","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('30525aa5-5ba5-40e8-aa8d-121962199380', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '9', '32', '**Primary Inputs**

- **Customer Order Data**  
  - Dealer order forms with option selections.  
  - Direct customer specifications for bespoke builds.

- **Fitting Results**  
  - Measurements taken from try-gun sessions (e.g., during a Perazzi Experience visit).  
  - Dimensions: LOP, DAC, DAH, cast at comb and heel, pitch, toe angle.  
  - Observations on handling preferences and recoil behavior.

- **Model Baseline Information**  
  - Selected family: e.g., MX8, MX12, High Tech, High Tech S.  
  - Known compatible barrel and trigger options for that action family.  
  - Standard vs special configurations.

- **Historical Records**  
  - Past Perazzi builds for the same client (when available).  
  - Previously successful parameter sets for similar shooters, disciplines, or performance goals.

- **Regulatory and Competition Constraints**  
  - Market-specific requirements (e.g., US import marks).  
  - Discipline rules: maximum weight, trigger guard dimensions, minimum bore/chamber requirements, etc.

**Primary Outputs**

- **Build Sheet / Dossier**  
  - A complete specification document that contains:  
    - Customer identity and serial number.  
    - Model family and action type.  
    - Barrel specifications (length, rib type, choke system, chamber length, gauge, POI notes).  
    - Trigger system choice (leaf vs coil; removable vs fixed; single/double; selectable/non-selectable).  
    - Stock dimensions and configuration (including adjustable features if present).  
    - Engraving grade and style; wood grade and requested figure.  
    - Any custom or non-standard features and their implications (e.g., special engraving motifs, stock designs, or inlays).

- **Digital and/or CAD/CAM Instructions**  
  - CNC setup data and notes for non-standard dimensions or barrel profiles.  
  - Recorded parameters for center-of-gravity targets and balance planning when required.

- **Reference Materials**  
  - Sketches, mock-ups, or pattern templates for:  
    - Unique engraving requests.  
    - Non-standard stock shapes or rib configurations.  
  - Internal notes for downstream craftspeople (e.g., instructions for engravers, stockmakers, or barrel regulators).

These outputs travel with the project through every subsequent station.

---', null, '3.2 Inputs & Outputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs', '["3-2-inputs-outputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('3058b246-ef11-472f-bc18-cbf418dfeb55', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '40', '51', '- They follow a practiced sequence:  
  - Layout → first light lines → deepen systematically → cross-lines → borders → final clean-up.  
- They develop a working rhythm that keeps quality stable from the **first line to the last**, even over long sessions.', null, '3.7.2 Consistent Rhythm & Pace', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.2 Consistent Rhythm & Pace', '["3-7-2-consistent-rhythm-pace","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-2-consistent-rhythm-pace"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('305bb23a-79bb-4846-8f66-8d306780002e', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '9', '56', '- **Finished Components**  
  - **Receiver/action**: polished, finished, and engraved as applicable; internal lockwork and trigger group pre-fitted or ready for installation.  
  - **Barrel set**: blued and proofed, with ribs and ejectors fully installed and regulated.  
  - **Stock and fore-end**: fully shaped, checkered, and finished, with associated hardware (trigger guard, fore-end iron, latch).

- **Small Parts & Hardware**  
  - Screws, pins, through-bolt (stock bolt), springs (top lever spring, locking bolt spring, ejector springs, etc.), and minor fittings that may be installed at this stage.

- **Lubricants & Compounds**  
  - Grease for hinges, locking lugs, cocking cams, and other high-load interfaces.  
  - Light oil for sears, triggers, and internal linkages.  
  - Assembly pastes as needed.

- **Testing Tools & Gauges**  
  - Snap caps / dummy shells (with or without fired primers).  
  - Trigger pull gauge (mechanical or digital).  
  - Headspace gauges (go / no-go).  
  - Firing pin protrusion gauge (or visual/functional equivalent).  
  - Bore light or borescope for final bore inspection.  
  - Balance scale and weight scale for overall gun weight.

- **General Gunsmithing Tools**  
  - Hollow-ground gunsmith screwdrivers (often custom-ground for individual screws).  
  - Torque wrench or calibrated T-handle for stock bolt (if used).  
  - Pin punches and small hammer.  
  - Rubber or leather-faced mallet for gentle taps.  
  - Inspection light and mirrors.', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('30616409-4656-42ac-8163-6a6d533c6c9a', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '7', '39', '- **Monobloc** – breech block that barrels are joined into.  
- **Chamber Reamer** – tool used to cut chambers.  
- **Forcing Cone** – chamber-to-bore transition.  
- **Choke Constriction** – amount bore is reduced at the muzzle.  
- **Ribs** – top and side joining structures.  
- **Solder / Flux / Spelter** – joining materials and flux agents.  
- **Regulation** – alignment of barrels’ POI.  
- **POI** – point of impact.  
- **Pattern** – pellet distribution on target.  
- **Proof Pressure** – elevated test pressure during proof.

