  - **3.1.3 Tom Seay – Sporting Clays** – Regional titles, Team USA roles, lifelong Perazzi use.  
  - **3.1.4 David Radulovich – Sporting Clays** – World titles, psychological approach, Perazzi High Tech and MX12 usage.  
  - **3.1.5 Paul “L.P.” Giambrone III – American Skeet** – World titles, NSSA Hall of Fame, Perazzi High Tech 3 skeet configuration.  
  - **3.1.6 George Digweed MBE – Sporting Clays (Great Britain)** – Multi-decade world dominance, MX2000S and High Tech history.  
  - **3.1.7 Tamás Jeri – Sporting Clays (Hungary)** – World and European titles, 200/200 world record, Perazzi High Tech Sporting.  
- **3.2 Supported Shooters**  
  - **3.2.1 Dania Vizzi – International Skeet** – Ballet-to-skeet journey, world titles, Perazzi MX2000 and High Tech 2020.  
  - **3.2.2 Mike Simpson – All Disciplines & Coach** – Coaching legacy, national honors, long-term Perazzi advocacy.  
  - **3.2.3 Keith Ditto – American Trap** – ATA Grand Slam, Kentucky dominance, Perazzi trap combo with PFS.  
  - **3.2.4 Michael Wengard (Wengerd) – American Trap** – Early Hall of Fame induction, Grand Slam, Perazzi MX-series combo.  
  - **3.2.5 Annabelle Ayres – Sporting Clays** – Women’s national and world titles, advocacy, Perazzi High Tech Sporting.  
  - **3.2.6 Amber English – International Skeet** – Olympic gold, World Cup and Pan Am results, Perazzi MX8.  
  - **3.2.7 Josh Poole – American Skeet** – 500×500 collegiate record, 400×400 state titles, Perazzi High Tech skeet.

This structure is designed so that AI systems can easily locate an athlete by name or discipline and retrieve their biography, achievements, and Perazzi equipment details without losing any of the original document’s information.', null, 'Appendix A. Section Index', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > Appendix A. Section Index', '["appendix-a-section-index","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-appendix-a-section-index"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('344fd611-1dda-4185-aaff-aef920913f1f', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '4', '32', '- **Length of Pull (LOP)**  
  - Distance from the trigger face to the center of the butt end.  
  - Key for mount comfort, eye alignment, and recoil distribution.

- **Drop at Comb (DAC)**  
  - Vertical distance between the line of sight (or rib) and the top of the comb at a defined reference point.  
  - Influences eye height relative to the rib and therefore **point of impact (POI)**.

- **Drop at Heel (DAH)**  
  - Vertical distance between the line of sight (or rib) and the heel of the stock.  
  - Influences how the gun sits in the shoulder and the general sight picture.

- **Cast-Off / Cast-On**  
  - Lateral offset of the stock from the barrel centerline.  
  - Cast-off (for right-handed shooters) moves the stock to the right; cast-on (for left-handed shooters) moves it to the left.  
  - Often specified at both comb and heel.

- **Toe Angle / Toe-Out**  
  - Orientation of the lower corner (toe) of the butt plate relative to the shooter’s chest.  
  - Affects how the gun interfaces with chest/shoulder and perceived recoil.

- **Pitch**  
  - Angle of the butt plate relative to the barrels.  
  - Adjusted to change how recoil is distributed into the shoulder and to manage muzzle rise.', null, '2.3 Stock Fit Dimensions', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Stock Fit Dimensions', '["2-3-stock-fit-dimensions","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-stock-fit-dimensions"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('34562c56-a591-43b2-94bf-ee4e43a86fad', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '7', '35', 'The **Action & Receiver Machining station** shapes a **raw steel forging** into a nearly complete action body that will:

- Withstand the stresses of repeated firing.  
- Provide precise geometry for barrel pivot and lock-up.  
- Accept the trigger group, top latch, and forend components with correct clearances.  
- Allow stockmakers to inlet the stock accurately.

This station executes the majority of the material removal, transforming a rough forging into a highly precise but intentionally **slightly oversize** receiver in certain areas, ready for hand fitting.', null, '3.1.1 Purpose', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.1 Purpose', '["3-1-1-purpose","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-1-purpose"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('3578c773-71aa-4d1b-a56b-7aa38f88f76c', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '14', '40', '- Fits **fore-end iron to wood** with internal screws and inletting.  
- Ensures latch hook engages barrel loop correctly and closes with appropriate effort:  
  - Not so tight that closing is difficult or stresses latch.  
  - Not so loose that fore-end rattles or unlatches under recoil.  
- Relieves wood around moving parts (ejectors, rods) so they operate without drag or binding.  
- Shapes fore-end exterior for comfortable grip, often flared near receiver and slimming toward tip in a visually balanced way.', null, '3.3.4 Fore-end Fitting & Function', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.4 Fore-end Fitting & Function', '["3-3-4-fore-end-fitting-function","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-4-fore-end-fitting-function"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('35930b2e-323b-437b-8752-53133cb468d4', '500269f5-9624-4f5b-9ded-8de9740793b2', '3', '7', 'The mixing and matching of components from different Perazzi models or assemblies may result in improper fitting, reduced performance, or mechanical issues. Only Perazzi factory-fitted components ensure optimal function, safety, and resale value. Beware of altered serial numbers on barrels, forends and especially when illegally changed on the action.', null, 'Mixed and Matched Components', 'Consumer Warning Notice > Mixed and Matched Components', '["mixed-and-matched-components","consumer-warning-notice-mixed-and-matched-components"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:16.184829+00', null), ('35abd572-5ab8-4012-a2de-6fb247240ece', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '162', '238', 'Model name: MX16 SCO Gold | Base model: mx16 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 16ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX16 SCO Gold', 'Models > MX16 SCO Gold', '["model-details","mx16-sco-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('35f1c33c-7f87-43ee-a53e-4a55780576d7', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '12', '45', '- Ensuring **all sanding scratches** are removed before final finish:  
  - Multiple whiskering cycles: wetting the stock to raise grain, then sanding it back.  
  - Inspecting under raking light to reveal hidden scratches or swirl marks.

- Deciding where to leave very slight texture (e.g., comb top) vs ultra-smooth (e.g., show-grade butt).', null, '3.3.2 Surface Preparation & Grain Raising', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Surface Preparation & Grain Raising', '["3-3-2-surface-preparation-grain-raising","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-surface-preparation-grain-raising"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('35f87a2a-3b2a-472b-b6a0-88131cebfc34', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '23', '39', 'Beyond POI, testers analyze **pattern quality**:

- Patterns are evaluated for:
  - Even pellet distribution.
  - Absence of large voids.
  - Expected spread for choke type.

For fixed-choke guns:

- If a customer specified choke constrictions (e.g., IC / IM for sporting clays):
  - Testers verify that patterns **behave like those chokes** at the intended distances.
- If an IC-pattern appears too tight (closer to Modified), they can:
  - Lightly re-hone the choke to open it a few thousandths of an inch.
- Such corrections are infrequent due to precise bore and choke work, but they remain possible.

For multi-choke (tubed) guns:

- Factory typically tests with:
  - Known-good target loads (e.g., popular Italian target ammunition).
  - Standard choke tubes to verify performance.

Barrel and choke design choices (e.g., smooth internal finishes, gradual constrictions) are intended to produce **dense, uniform patterns** without “donut” profiles.', null, '3.3.2 Pattern Quality and Choke Verification', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Patterning & On-Range Performance > 3.3.2 Pattern Quality and Choke Verification', '["3-3-2-pattern-quality-and-choke-verification","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-3-patterning-on-range-performance-3-3-2-pattern-quality-and-choke-verification"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('36058c15-3de3-4978-949e-c42fac7ecea4', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '20', '53', '- Focus first on **comb height/cast** and **LOP**, as they most directly influence POI and comfort.  
- Decide whether cast should be changed via:  
  - Adjustable comb offset (affects cheek position), or  
  - Full stock bending (affects both cheek alignment and pad placement).  
- Consider whether the shooter can adapt to a small cast or drop discrepancy vs subjecting a finished stock to bending risk.', null, '3.4.1 Which Adjustments to Prioritize', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Which Adjustments to Prioritize', '["3-4-1-which-adjustments-to-prioritize","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-which-adjustments-to-prioritize"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('3612cd39-f6b1-443c-b1c3-316cb6606028', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '7', '56', 'The **Assembly & Mechanical QC station** is responsible for:

- Assembling **all finished components** into a complete shotgun:
  - Receiver/action with internal lockwork and trigger group.
  - Barrel set with ejectors installed and regulated.
  - Finished stock and fore-end with their iron/metal parts attached.
- Performing thorough **mechanical and functional tests** to:
  - Verify that every mechanism behaves as intended.
  - Fine-tune the feel of the gun (opening, closing, trigger, ejectors, safety, etc.).
- Catching and correcting any issues before:
  - Pattern testing and POI confirmation.
  - Final fitting with the shooter (for bespoke guns).
  - Delivery to customer.

It is the **final internal gate** for mechanical integrity.', null, '3.1.1 Purpose', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.1 Purpose', '["3-1-1-purpose","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-1-purpose"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('3617c48d-ca4b-4019-a1f1-39a1df84d6e4', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '19', '32', 'Mastery in the Design & Specification role is often invisible: it is evident by the **absence of downstream issues** and by small, intelligent choices that make a gun feel exceptional rather than merely “correct.”', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('362ac501-f603-4145-8774-970df72f2bd4', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '49', '51', '- **Upstream:**  
  - **Stock Inletting & Final Shaping Station (Part II.F)** – provides fully shaped and fitted stock and fore-end with final geometry ready for surface detailing.

- **Downstream:**  
  - **Wood Finishing Station** – applies oil or varnish finishes that protect and highlight walnut and may require final checkering clean-up or sealing.  
  - **Metal Finishing Station** – runs in parallel; while checkering is completed, metal parts may be polished and blued.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With checkering complete, the tactile character of the stock and fore-end is established. Next, the focus moves to **metal and wood finishing departments**, where the visual depth and protective surfaces of a Perazzi—its bluing, gloss, or satin sheen—are brought to life.

---', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('362d8ee5-a2aa-4bcc-8cad-f562240ea333', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '31', '39', 'Perazzi’s competition **house style**:

- Tends toward **“understated excellence”**:
  - Clean lines.
  - No default ornate sideplates on many competition models.
  - Simple polished blued or nickel action with “Perazzi” script.
- This appeals to shooters who view themselves as:
  - Serious competitors first.
  - Less concerned with overt display.

The aesthetic restraint can itself be a **statement**:

- “I don’t need gold birds to prove anything; my Perazzi and my scores speak for themselves.”

For customers who want more visual expression:

- Higher grades (SC3, SCO, sideplates with full-coverage engraving and gold inlays) offer:
  - **Full artistic expression** comparable to classic British best guns.
- Real-world patterns:
  - An Olympic-level shooter might run a fairly standard engraved gun.
  - A recreational shooter with a strong appreciation for art and legacy might invest in a highly engraved, exhibition-grade build.

The key is **alignment**:

- The gun’s aesthetic positioning matches the owner’s self-image:
  - Pure performance tool.
  - Dual-purpose performance and heirloom piece.
  - Primarily a legacy showpiece that still shoots at a world-class level.', null, '3.4.4 House Style vs. Customer Expression', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Aesthetics & Identity > 3.4.4 House Style vs. Customer Expression', '["3-4-4-house-style-vs-customer-expression","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-4-aesthetics-identity-3-4-4-house-style-vs-customer-expression"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('36802f77-59e5-47f7-90c7-e1dd787a24ef', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '10', '58', '- **1957** – Company founded in Brescia.[2]
- **1964** – Ennio Mattarelli wins Olympic Trap gold with a Perazzi prototype.[3]
- **1968** – MX8 introduced for Mexico City Olympics.[4]
- **1973** – U.S. market entry via Ithaca; American Trap-specific models follow.[5]
- **1981** – DB81 O/U developed with Ray Stafford and Dan Bonillas.[6]
- **1990** – MX10 adjustable-rib trap model launched.[6]
- **1999–2000** – MX2000 series and MX2000/RS unsingle introduced.[7]
- **2012** – Daniele Perazzi passes away; Perazzi guns dominate London Olympics.[3][15]
- **2023** – CSG majority acquisition with family retaining control.[12][13]

