  - Soot, dye, or colored paste applied to metal surfaces so that high spots transfer to wood, guiding incremental wood removal.

- **Hook Scrapers & Rifflers**  
  - Curved scraping and rasping tools used to refine internal and external contours.

- **Spokeshave**  
  - Small plane-like tool for shaping convex curves (comb, grip arcs).

- **Cabinet Rasps**  
  - Coarse-to-medium shaping tools (e.g., #49 and #50 style) used to rapidly refine stock contours before finer finishing.', null, '2.4 Tools & Transfer Media Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Tools & Transfer Media Concepts', '["2-4-tools-transfer-media-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-tools-transfer-media-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('37f5020d-8d78-477a-bf8c-06bf68bc2d7b', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '48', '51', '- Over time, checkering may wear or fill with finish.  
- Masters can refresh patterns by carefully recutting original grooves, restoring diamond sharpness.

**Caveat:**  
- Depth must be managed to avoid weakening wood or altering stock dimensions; excess re-cutting can leave overly deep, fragile diamonds.

---', null, '4.4 Re-Cutting or Refreshing Checkering', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.4 Re-Cutting or Refreshing Checkering', '["4-4-re-cutting-or-refreshing-checkering","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-4-re-cutting-or-refreshing-checkering"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('380425b1-d7a2-4960-9448-2d42b7bd71e4', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '51', '53', '- **Upstream Stations (conceptual):**  
  - **Assembly & Mechanical Quality Control (Part II.J)** – delivers a fully assembled, mechanically verified gun for fitting.  
  - **Patterning & Performance Testing (Part II.K)** – supplies POI and pattern information that informs final fit decisions.

- **Downstream / Related:**  
  - **Final Inspection & Sign-Off (conceptual next stage)** – verifies that all processes are complete, proof marks and serial numbers are correct, and documentation matches the finished gun before casing and delivery.  
  - **Warranty & Service / Future Adjustments** – later changes or repairs refer back to the fitting records created here.

- **Narrative Context:**  
  - Final fitting is the **capstone** of the hands‑on build process. After this stage, the gun is essentially ready for final inspection, documentation, and presentation or shipment to the customer.

---', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('38077df3-f770-46a6-bc85-6dc5b204500b', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '8', '40', 'This station is considered successful when:

- **Wood-to-Metal Fit**  
  - Action seats in stock with **no wobble** and no hidden stress points.  
  - Wood-metal joint lines are **hairline-thin**; no daylight visible.  
  - Traditional benchmark: with careful fitting, the action and stock can hold together under gentle handling even before bolts are fully tightened.

- **Structural Integrity**  
  - No cracking, chipping, or crushed fibers in critical zones (stock head, wrist, tang areas, fore-end latch region).  
  - Bearing surfaces are well-supported; relieved areas avoid random stress concentrations.

- **Dimensional Accuracy & Ergonomics**  
  - LOP, drop at comb/heel, cast, and pitch match fitted specifications within fine tolerances.  
  - Comb, cheekpiece (if present), grip, and butt are symmetrically shaped (except where intentional asymmetry like cast exists).  
  - Shooter’s eye naturally aligns with rib when mounting; stock “comes up” intuitively.

- **Functional Freedom**  
  - All moving parts (triggers, safety, top lever, ejectors, fore-end latch) move freely with no wood interference.  
  - Fore-end snaps on securely without excessive force and has no rattle.

- **Preparation for Finishing**  
  - External surfaces are smooth and shaped correctly, ready for final sanding/finishing steps.  
  - Edges and profiles are appropriate for the intended finish (rounded vs crisp where required).

---', null, '3.1.2 Success Criteria', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.2 Success Criteria', '["3-1-2-success-criteria","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-2-success-criteria"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('381f23b4-d74f-44d2-abc7-207880b2b356', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '36', '38', '- The numeric references `[1]`–`[109]` represent unspecified sources cited in the original text. This document **does not** include the corresponding bibliography.  
- For AI/RAG usage, these citation markers can be treated as internal anchors indicating that a statement in the original source referenced an external article, interview, or record.  
- This document is intended to be used alongside other internal Perazzi materials (e.g., product specifications, brand voice guidelines) but does not itself reference specific file paths beyond the metadata header.', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('382b341f-5831-418b-a067-ac709e8dbae0', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '8', '51', 'Final inspection is successful when:

- **Specification Conformance**  
  - Model, gauge, barrel length, choke markings, engraving pattern and grade, wood grade, stock dimensions (LOP, cast, drop), handedness (e.g., left-hand cast-on), adjustable comb presence, and pad type all match the order sheet.  
  - Any special options (e.g., personalized initials on oval, special trigger type) are present and correct.

- **Identity & Legal Compliance**  
  - All serial numbers on barrels, action, and fore-end iron match exactly and are clearly legible.  
  - Required proof marks are present, correct, and readable.  
  - Proof certificate and any ballistic test documents, if supplied, match the gun and its markings.

- **Fit, Finish & Cleanliness**  
  - Wood and metal surfaces are pristine: no visible handling marks, scratches, dents, or finish defects.  
  - Checkering is sharp and tidy, with no fuzz or stray fibers.  
  - Bores are spotless and lightly oiled; internal working areas are clean and free of debris.  
  - External surfaces are clean but not greasy (lubricated where needed internally, dry to the touch externally).

- **Function & Safety**  
  - Safety functions correctly; triggers and ejectors behave as already verified in mechanical QC.  
  - No new issues have emerged since earlier testing.

- **Accessories & Presentation**  
  - All accessories and tools specified for that model/order are present in case and correctly arranged.  
  - Case is correct for the gun (size, logo, internal layout) and is clean and free of debris.  
  - Any included cards (manual, warranty, inspector card) are present and correctly filled out.

- **Documentation & Records**  
  - Internal QA checklist is complete and signed off.  
  - Serial number and configuration are logged for warranty and legal purposes.  
  - Export or shipping documents are initiated or verified for accuracy.

