- Pricing reflects craftsmanship, customization, and competition pedigree, but is generally below ultra-boutique makers (e.g. Fabbri, high-end British “best guns”).[138]', null, '3.8.1 General Positioning', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.8 Pricing Structure and Value > 3.8.1 General Positioning', '["3-8-1-general-positioning","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-8-pricing-structure-and-value-3-8-1-general-positioning"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('407e4a0a-1e91-491b-8867-b2ffa16343e3', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '37', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - One ejector weak, inconsistent, or non-functional.  
  - Both ejectors firing when only one barrel is fired, or vice versa.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Unequal spring tensions; dirty or rough ejector channels.  
  - Incorrect ejector sear engagement or trip timing.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Test each barrel independently with snap caps.  
  - Clean and polish channels; adjust springs or sear surfaces; verify equal strength and correct timing.', null, '3.6.7 Ejector Issues', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.7 Ejector Issues', '["3-6-7-ejector-issues","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-7-ejector-issues"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('4082a686-d810-4a3e-afb0-0699143498b0', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '3', '26', 'This is a quick reference summary. Detailed descriptions follow in section 3.

