---', null, '2. Archetype Overview Table', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 2. Archetype Overview Table', '["2-archetype-overview-table","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-2-archetype-overview-table"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('40bc75d0-e5c5-49c3-ac49-0d71045b58d8', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '13', '45', '- Choosing whether to:  
  - Leave pores partially open for a traditional, natural look.  
  - Fill pores fully for a **glass-smooth, reflective surface**.

- Techniques:  
  - **Slurry fill**: wet-sanding oil into the wood to form a paste of oil + fine wood dust that fills pores, then wiping off surface residue.  
  - Using commercial grain fillers, tinted or clear, applied and sanded back between coats.

- Understanding trade-offs:  
  - Fully filled pores emphasize grain contrast and facilitate cleaning.  
  - Mildly open pores can feel more “alive” and may provide microtexture at the fore-end.', null, '3.3.3 Pore Filling Strategies', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.3 Pore Filling Strategies', '["3-3-3-pore-filling-strategies","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-3-pore-filling-strategies"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('40c17650-f3d8-4b04-88c5-74b63fa34b67', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '17', '56', '- Develop a **calibrated sense of feel**:  
  - Opening: smooth camming, no grinding or sticking.  
  - Lock-up: authoritative but not harsh click.  
  - Cocking: consistent resistance throughout motion.  
- Recognize “wrong” sounds (scraping, rattles, asymmetrical ejector noises) as indicators of problems to investigate.', null, '3.3.6 Smoothness, Sound, and “Feel”', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.6 Smoothness, Sound, and “Feel”', '["3-3-6-smoothness-sound-and-feel","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-6-smoothness-sound-and-feel"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('40c39a28-18e1-4d05-8051-d2dac814b428', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '23', '38', 'Mike Simpson is presented primarily as a coach whose legacy in shooting sports spans over 25 years.

Key points:

- Based in Georgia and known as “Coach Mike.”  
- Integral part of USA Shooting’s coaching cadre since 1996[77].  
- Named USA Shooting’s National Coach of the Year in 2013[78].  
- Has coached athletes across American Trap, Skeet, Olympic Bunker, and International Skeet.

His coaching philosophy centers on fundamentals, mental focus, and confidence in equipment. As assistant national coach, he has traveled with Team USA to numerous World Championships and Olympics. Many athletes credit his calm demeanor for their success, describing a sense of “calm confidence” when Mike is behind them on the line.

Mike’s own background includes competition in American trap, skeet, and sporting clays. The source portrays him as a “true student of the shotgun” who experimented extensively and now passes that knowledge to students. In 2023, he was inducted into the NSSA–NSCA Hall of Fame as a coach, an honor he accepted humbly, crediting his students[79][80].', null, '3.2.2.1 Biography & Background', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Supported Shooters > 3.2.2 Mike Simpson – All Disciplines & Coach (Supported Shooter) > 3.2.2.1 Biography & Background', '["3-2-2-1-biography-background","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-2-supported-shooters-3-2-2-mike-simpson-all-disciplines-coach-supported-shooter-3-2-2-1-biography-background"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('40ca8fda-cfff-4d80-9e03-5f4a567e149a', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '25', '26', '> This section is for AI behavior and retrieval purposes. It is safe to keep in the corpus but should not be recited verbatim.

- Use these archetypes **implicitly** to:
  - Choose which **aspects of Perazzi** to highlight (heritage, artistry, specifications, performance, legacy).
  - Choose what kind of **examples and stories** to offer (champions, factory, multi-generational ownership, event experiences).

- Do **not**:
  - Tell a user “You are a [Archetype].”
  - Insist that a user “fits” one of these categories.
  - Change the **facts** of an answer based on archetype—only the framing and emphasis.

- When users ask questions like:
  - “Why would someone choose Perazzi early in their career?”
  - “What type of shooter tends to gravitate toward Perazzi?”
  
  You may draw on this document to explain that:
  - People who choose Perazzi often care about:
    - Long-term relationship with their gun (Loyalist, Legacy).
    - Distinction and craft (Prestige).
    - Clear logic and serious competition (Analyst, Achiever).
  - Different aspects of the brand speak more strongly to different motivations, but all are anchored in:
    - Craftsmanship,
    - Serious competition use,
    - The idea of a gun as a long-term partner.

- Always keep the explanation focused on **Perazzi and the shooter**, not on internal AI mechanics or scoring systems.', null, '5. Guidance for PerazziGPT (AI Use Only)', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 5. Guidance for PerazziGPT (AI Use Only)', '["5-guidance-for-perazzigpt-ai-use-only","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-5-guidance-for-perazzigpt-ai-use-only"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('411db42a-9fbc-4475-bde5-b86ce99e5adf', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '33', '48', 'Mastery in this station is expressed in **intuitive wood judgment**, **confident machine use**, and **thoughtful coordination with downstream craftspeople**.', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('41426fe1-e2a8-4366-a317-6ef97e03b360', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '20', '36', '- Perazzi avoids competing on **price, volume, or advertising saturation**.  
- It emphasizes **rarity, elite access, and personalized experiences** (e.g., bespoke builds, invite-only events like the Perazzi Invitational).  
- The brand’s power comes from **selectivity**, not ubiquity.', null, '3.5.1 Exclusivity Over Accessibility', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Strategic Brand Themes > 3.5.1 Exclusivity Over Accessibility', '["3-5-1-exclusivity-over-accessibility","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-5-strategic-brand-themes-3-5-1-exclusivity-over-accessibility"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('414c464b-8d89-4573-8b7d-026f3a1575e3', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '27', '58', 'Perazzi’s brand identity extends beyond engineering into legacy, exclusivity, and transformation.', null, '3.5 Brand Philosophy and Ethos', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Brand Philosophy and Ethos', '["3-5-brand-philosophy-and-ethos","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-5-brand-philosophy-and-ethos"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('41554df0-3016-4e5d-a6bf-d96e2b44c90b', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '3', '45', '- **Walnut Stock & Fore-end**  
  - Air-dried and conditioned walnut, already shaped, inletted, and checkered, typically sanded to ~320 grit or finer before finishing.
  - Variability in color, density, and figure (curl, marblecake, etc.) affects how finishes behave.

- **Oil Finish (Traditional)**  
  - Often based on boiled linseed or tung oil with **driers** (e.g., cobalt salts) and sometimes small amounts of varnish/resin.  
  - Examples: “London oil finish,” custom stock oils.  
  - Pros: warm, natural look; easy to repair; can be built up to satin or semi-gloss.  
  - Cons: slower to build and cure; requires periodic maintenance.

- **Polyurethane / Varnish / Lacquer (Synthetic Film Finishes)**  
  - Sprayed or brushed catalyzed finishes that cure to a more durable film.  
  - Can be formulated or rubbed to **matte, satin, or high gloss**.  
  - Pros: high water resistance; low maintenance.  
  - Cons: film-like if applied heavily; localized repairs are harder to make invisible.

- **Stains and Color Agents**  
  - Dyes or stains used to adjust walnut tone (e.g., warmer brown/red).  
  - **Alkanet root oil** (traditional) can impart a subtle reddish cast.  
  - Used to even out color or reach a brand-specific tone.

- **Pore Fillers**  
  - Materials used to fill open pores for a smoother surface:  
    - Traditional **oil + wood-dust or pumice slurry**.  
    - Commercial grain fillers.  
  - Affects texture and sheen (glass-smooth vs lightly textured).

- **Waxes**  
  - Final surface treatment (e.g., beeswax blends) providing a soft sheen and extra moisture resistance over cured oil/film.', null, '2.2 Wood & Finish Types', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Wood & Finish Types', '["2-2-wood-finish-types","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-wood-finish-types"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('416a1831-273a-4780-8830-16ed959dc1b6', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '25', '49', '- Whether to:

- Provide a **physical test target** to the customer.  
  - Record pattern data internally only.  
  - Use pattern photographs or brief written notes as proof of testing.

---', null, '3.4.7 Documentation & Customer Artifacts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.7 Documentation & Customer Artifacts', '["3-4-7-documentation-customer-artifacts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-7-documentation-customer-artifacts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('41e0795f-9653-43bc-90cc-e958c3ab4620', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '28', '45', '- **Rust Bluing Setup**  
  - Rusting solutions and application gear (swabs, pads).  
  - Humidity cabinet or controlled area to induce uniform rusting.  
  - Boiling tanks for conversion of rust to black oxide.  
  - Carding brushes or wheels to remove loose oxide between cycles.

- **Hot Salt Bluing Tanks (where used)**  
  - Temperature-controlled chemical baths for bluing compatible parts.  
  - Thermometers and possibly hydrometers or titration methods for bath control.

- **Case Hardening & Plating (when applicable)**  
  - Furnaces and quenching setups for case hardening.  
