- **Rubber / Leather Mallet**  
  - For gentle tapping to seat parts or simulate recoil.', null, '3.5.1 Assembly Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Assembly Tools', '["3-5-1-assembly-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-assembly-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('45eea243-bca7-4e22-b24b-a03c8da8753e', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '55', '238', 'Model name: High Tech P 3 | Base model: high-tech-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: P | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech P 3', 'Models > High Tech P 3', '["model-details","high-tech-p-3","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('45fe270c-ec50-47a4-8b46-02deb7b89c41', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '37', '39', '- **Upstream:**  
  - **Design & Specification Station (Product Engineering)** – provides barrel length, rib type, chamber length, choke specification, and target weight that guide barrel fabrication and regulation.

- **Lateral/Related Stations:**  
  - **Action & Receiver Machining** – defines locking geometry and monobloc design that barrels must integrate with.  
  - **Ejector and Lockwork Stations** – rely on correctly formed ejector cuts and monobloc features.

- **Downstream:**  
  - **Action Fitting & Assembly** – mates barrels to the action, confirming lock-up and headspace.  
  - **Stockmaking & Balance Tuning** – works with barrel weight to achieve final gun balance.  
  - **Final Testing & Inspection** – performs final pattern and function checks to validate the barrel shop’s work.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With the barrel set complete—straight, regulated, and proofed—and the action waiting in the white, the next focus in the handbook is on **trigger mechanism specialists and furniture (stock and fore-end)**, the components that form the "connective tissue" between mechanical performance and the shooter.

---', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('46710470-2180-4634-8b29-4b7d9d5d660e', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '3', '238', 'Model name: DC Extra Super | Base model: dc | Platform: DC | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: Extra Super | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: side-by-side | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### DC Extra Super', 'Models > DC Extra Super', '["model-details","dc-extra-super","platform:dc"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('469f905c-c187-43bc-bd9a-556f2c36faa7', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '28', '39', '- Converts POI requirements and distances into practical adjustments at the muzzle and monobloc.  
- Often regulates barrels correctly in a single soldering pass by combining measured geometry with experience-based rules of thumb.  
- Has mental reference tables (formal or informal) for how small angular offsets translate into inches of shift at typical shotgun distances.', null, '3.7.4 Regulation Expertise', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.4 Regulation Expertise', '["3-7-4-regulation-expertise","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-4-regulation-expertise"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('46bbc332-7b29-43eb-974a-eddd50468288', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '5', '45', '- **Degreasing**  
  - Thorough removal of oil and contaminants before bluing (e.g., detergent baths, solvents).  
  - Essential for preventing patchy or rejected bluing.

- **Rust Cycle (for Rust Bluing)**  
  - Sequence of:
    1. Polishing and degreasing.  
    2. Applying a rusting solution uniformly.  
    3. Allowing controlled rust to form (e.g., multiple coats per day over several days).  
    4. Boiling in water to convert red/brown rust to black oxide.  
    5. Carding (using brushes) to remove loose rust.  
    6. Repeating until desired color depth and evenness are achieved.

- **Carding**  
  - Gentle brushing with soft wire or carding wheels to remove loose oxide after boiling, leaving the adhered black oxide layer.

- **Neutralization**  
  - Stopping the rusting process after final cycles (e.g., via boiling in an alkaline solution and thorough rinsing), then oiling.

- **Buffing**  
  - Using rotating wheels with abrasives to refine surface finish; requires careful control to avoid rounding edges or creating waves.', null, '2.4 Process & Chemistry Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Process & Chemistry Concepts', '["2-4-process-chemistry-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-process-chemistry-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('473875c6-3b70-4ce4-8d8c-1b921d1294b5', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '28', '49', '- **Pellet Count Reference**  
  - Knowledge of approximate pellet counts per load (e.g., 1 oz #7.5 ≈ known pellet count range) to relate pellet hits to pattern percentages.

- **Visual Estimation**  
  - Experienced testers often rely on **visual assessment** rather than exhaustive pellet counting for routine QC.', null, '3.5.3 Counting & Estimation Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.3 Counting & Estimation Tools', '["3-5-3-counting-estimation-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-3-counting-estimation-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('47387959-143c-4465-9b48-2c1513353782', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '4', '49', '- **Pattern Distance**  
  - Typical distances used:  
    - **35–40 meters** for full pattern evaluation.  
    - Sometimes shorter distances (e.g., 15–20 m) for more precise POI/regulation checks.

- **Pattern Plate vs Paper**  
  - **Pattern Plate**: steel plate coated with whitewash/paint; pellet strike leaves visible marks.  
  - **Pattern Paper**: large paper sheets (e.g., ~1 m²) used to capture patterns for detailed analysis or customer presentation.

- **Indoor Patterning Board**  
  - Long dark room with a **moving steel plate** that can be set at different ranges; allows controlled, all-weather testing.

- **Outdoor Range (Test Range Behind the Factory)**  
  - Used for longer range or final tests, including gunsmith evaluation with live fire.', null, '2.3 Test Environment & Distance Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Test Environment & Distance Concepts', '["2-3-test-environment-distance-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-test-environment-distance-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('474ac4a4-4677-4c0b-b3ab-1fa5b54560d9', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '23', '39', '- All fine shotguns are designed with **long service and rebuildability** in mind:
  - Perazzi: replaceable locking bolts, bushings, triggers, and other wear parts.
  - British best guns: intentional extra material on hook surfaces and locking lugs to allow tightening.
- Shared mentality:
  - A high-end shotgun is a **multi-decade or multi-generational tool**, not disposable.
  - Service centers and parts pipelines are integral to the product offering (e.g., Perazzi USA, Krieghoff USA, H&H service departments).
- Differences:
  - Perazzi leans more toward **user-accessible service** for some parts (trigger groups, springs).
  - Some traditional makers historically preferred **gunsmith-only service**, though this has evolved.', null, '3.2.7 Focus on Longevity and Service', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices > 3.2.7 Focus on Longevity and Service', '["3-2-7-focus-on-longevity-and-service","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices-3-2-7-focus-on-longevity-and-service"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('47617c12-80ef-4937-9769-072608bc1d31', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '19', '49', '- **Shorter Distance (e.g., 15–20 m)**  
  - Pros: easier to see precise POI and differences between barrels (smaller pattern; center easier to locate).  
  - Cons: less information about full pattern spread and choke behavior.

- **Standard Pattern Distance (e.g., 35–40 m)**  
  - Pros: standard reference for pattern density and spread; aligns with conventional pattern metrics.  
  - Cons: patterns are broader; small POI differences are a bit harder to assess visually.

**Practical approach:**  
- Some testers may use **both**: shorter range for fine POI/regulation checks and standard distance for full pattern analysis.  
- Others may rely mainly on the standard distance, trusting upstream barrel regulation and focusing on confirmation.', null, '3.4.1 Test Distance Choices', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Test Distance Choices', '["3-4-1-test-distance-choices","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-test-distance-choices"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('47b23d29-6eff-4183-8ac0-634aa341ae06', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '125', '238', 'Model name: High Tech X | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: X | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech X', 'Models > High Tech X', '["model-details","high-tech-x","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('47d2e331-173c-4d09-a784-3ac3534e5fc1', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '2', '39', '- **Removable Trigger Group (Drop-Out Trigger)**  
  A self-contained trigger and firing mechanism unit that can be removed from the receiver as a module. Perazzi pioneered this in competition O/Us, allowing shooters to carry a **spare trigger group** and swap in seconds if needed.[15]

- **Boss-Style Low-Profile Action**  
  A compact over-under action inspired by Boss & Co. designs, featuring a **low receiver height** and locking geometry that keeps the barrels close to the hinge, reducing muzzle flip.[4]

- **In-House Barrel Making**  
  The practice of producing barrels internally (from steel bar to finished tubes), rather than buying prefabricated barrel tubes. Enables tight control over **steel choice, internal dimensions, and straightening**.

- **Customization-as-Standard**  
  Production model in which **bespoke builds** are the default: stock dimensions, barrels, chokes, engraving, springs, and more are tailored per order, rather than treating customization as a rare special case.

- **Leaf vs Coil Spring Choice**  
  The option, designed into Perazzi triggers, to use either **leaf (V) springs** or **coil springs**, or to convert between them via parts kits.[6][8]', null, '2.1 Perazzi-Specific Systems & Design Choices', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Perazzi-Specific Systems & Design Choices', '["2-1-perazzi-specific-systems-design-choices","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-perazzi-specific-systems-design-choices"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('47efd619-6330-43e6-9ffe-8e0dbce73a7d', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '23', '32', '- Acts as the **orientation point** for all users.
