    - 3.7.4 Balancing Tradition and Innovation.  
    - 3.7.5 Example Vignette: World Champion Fitting Session.  
- **4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats** – Non-standard requests, regulatory constraints, and communication caveats.  
- **5. References & Cross-Links** – How this station connects to other handbook sections and where key concepts are defined.', null, 'Appendix A. Section Index', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > Appendix A. Section Index', '["appendix-a-section-index","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-appendix-a-section-index"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('499e2fe5-4e48-4a9f-9a77-893a5585a9ef', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '29', '39', 'Engraving is the primary **visual identity canvas** on metal:

- Standard competition models (e.g., MX12, High Tech):
  - May have simple, machine-applied or minimal scroll.
  - Present a **businesslike, function-focused** look.
- Higher grades (e.g., **SC3**, **SCO**):
  - Feature elaborate **hand engraving**:
    - Fine English scroll.
    - Game scenes.
    - Gold inlays.
  - Often executed by **Italian master engravers** whose signatures appear on the receiver.
- Motifs:
  - Catalog designs (house patterns).
  - Fully bespoke works:
    - Scenes of a champion breaking clays.
    - National symbols.
    - Personalized iconography.

Perazzi collaborates with multiple engravers:

- Factory had ~15 engravers working in the front workshop.
- Family traditions in engraving are common (e.g., father-daughter teams).

Engraving functions as:

- Storytelling (visual narrative about owner’s achievements or values).
- Self-expression (sleek competitor vs connoisseur of art).
- A key contributor to the feeling: **“this is my gun, unlike any other.”**', null, '3.4.2 Engraving and Personalization', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Aesthetics & Identity > 3.4.2 Engraving and Personalization', '["3-4-2-engraving-and-personalization","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-4-aesthetics-identity-3-4-2-engraving-and-personalization"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('49e64e71-8083-4898-b01f-ea15149a1445', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '43', '45', '- **Upstream:**  
  - **Barrel Fabrication & Regulation Station (Part II.C)** – supplies barrel sets in white, straightened and proofed, ready for polishing and bluing.  
  - **Action & Receiver Machining / Fitting Stations (Part II.B, etc.)** – provide machined and fitted actions and small parts requiring final finishing.  
  - **Engraving Station (if treated separately)** – finishes engraving before coin or case-color finishes are applied and before any final light polish.

- **Lateral / Parallel:**  
  - **Checkering Station (Part II.G)** – can run partly in parallel as wood is prepped for finish while metal is being blued.

- **Downstream:**  
  - **Wood Finishing Station** – applies oil or varnish finishes to walnut, with some coordination regarding masking and final assembly.  
  - **Final Assembly & Inspection** – confirms that metal finishes meet visual and functional requirements when the gun is fully assembled.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With metal finishing complete and wood finishing often proceeding in parallel, the shotgun is nearly ready for delivery. The next section focuses on **wood finishing**, where the carefully shaped walnut stock and fore-end receive their color, depth, and final protective sheen.

---', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('4a0a7fdd-bcd2-4cf7-80ad-2f88eb465a52', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '10', '39', 'Quality is also reinforced by **sign-off culture** and peer expectations:

- Each station **signs off** on its work.
- Downstream craftspeople immediately feel upstream errors:
  - A burr from machining is obvious to the fitter.
  - A misaligned surface becomes apparent in assembly.
- This creates **peer accountability**:
  - No one wants their work to be the “flaw” someone else finds.
- In final assembly:
  - An inspector can sense issues by:
    - Cycling the action.
    - Feeling for clicks, play, or binding.
  - Example check:
    - Using a feeler gauge (or simply sight and feel) to ensure **no gap** between barrel breech and action face.

Anything suspect is returned for corrective work before the gun is allowed to leave the factory.', null, '3.1.5 In-Process Documentation and Peer Accountability', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Quality Control & Tolerances > 3.1.5 In-Process Documentation and Peer Accountability', '["3-1-5-in-process-documentation-and-peer-accountability","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-1-quality-control-tolerances-3-1-5-in-process-documentation-and-peer-accountability"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('4a58e9f8-8964-40c1-8cf4-33f0b2a2fd09', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '160', '238', 'Model name: MX16 SC3 Gold | Base model: mx16 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 16ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX16 SC3 Gold', 'Models > MX16 SC3 Gold', '["model-details","mx16-sc3-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('4a91243e-4964-42e2-91a9-779f5cae45dd', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '20', '40', '- Choosing whether to incorporate features like:  
  - Slight cheekpiece.  
  - Monte Carlo comb for trap shooters to combine high comb with dropped heel.

**Practical approach:**

- Use shooter’s measurements and discipline to decide:  
  - A high comb height and lower heel for recoil clearance may suggest Monte Carlo geometry.  
  - Cheekpieces are less common on typical Perazzi competition guns but may be added for custom or aesthetic reasons.', null, '3.4.4 Cheekpiece & Monte Carlo Choices', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Cheekpiece & Monte Carlo Choices', '["3-4-4-cheekpiece-monte-carlo-choices","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-cheekpiece-monte-carlo-choices"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('4aa67305-c50d-4621-ab74-190720b61006', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '14', '51', '- Evaluate all **wood-metal joints**:  
  - Around the action, trigger guard inlet, fore-end iron, and butt pad.  
  - Ensure no proud edges, gaps, or unevenness.  
- Inspect checkering:  
  - Borders clean; no fuzz or roughness; no finish buildup in diamonds.  
- Inspect metal finish:  
  - No scratches, dings, or blemishes on visible surfaces.  
  - Even color and polish; no visible touch‑up lines or patchy areas.  
- Inspect wood finish:  
  - No drips, sags, or visible sand-throughs; no new handling marks.', null, '3.3.3 Fit & Finish Standards', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.3 Fit & Finish Standards', '["3-3-3-fit-finish-standards","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-3-fit-finish-standards"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('4ab5fe62-528d-4d4c-9db0-0219a48d2a48', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '22', '38', 'The trigger station actively prevents and diagnoses potential malfunctions before guns leave the factory.

Representative failure modes and responses:

1. **Doubling (Both Barrels Firing at Once)**  
   - Cause: too light sear engagement on second hammer; inertia block or selector issues; incorrect timing.  
   - Diagnosis: dry-fire or live-fire tests with simulated recoil; both barrels firing upon first trigger pull indicates a problem.  
   - Remedy: increase sear engagement or spring force, correct inertia block or selector function, re-test until doubling is eliminated.

2. **Failure to Fire Second Shot**  
   - Cause (inertia triggers): insufficient recoil to move inertia block (especially with very light loads); block or linkage too stiff.  
   - Cause (mechanical triggers): mechanical selector or linkage not resetting.  
   - Diagnosis: simulate recoil with mallet; test dry-fire with varying force; pattern tests with light loads.  
   - Remedy: adjust inertia block mass or spring tension; refine mechanical linkage; in some cases, advise on appropriate ammunition if design is inertia-based.

3. **Sluggish Trigger or Creep**  
   - Cause: rough sear surfaces; misaligned parts; insufficient lubrication.  
   - Diagnosis: feel-based assessment of take-up and break; visual inspection of contact surfaces.  
   - Remedy: additional polishing, stoning, and correct lubrication; check for burrs or misalignment.

4. **Light Primer Strikes**  
   - Cause: weak or incorrectly seated hammer springs; friction in hammer pivot; overly lightened hammer.  
   - Diagnosis: shallow primer indent on snap caps or test rounds; misfires.  
   - Remedy: stronger or correctly installed spring; cleaning and polishing of hammer pivots; adjusting hammer weight within safe limits.

5. **Safety Malfunction (Too Tight or Too Loose)**  
   - Too tight: shooter cannot reliably disengage; risk of “dead trigger” mid-competition.  
   - Too loose: safety may move inadvertently under recoil.  
   - Diagnosis: repeated cycling of safety, feel of detent “click,” and attempts to intentionally move safety under simulated recoil.  
   - Remedy: adjust safety detent spring and groove; refine fit so safety stays in position yet operates smoothly.

6. **Barrel Selection Issues**  
   - Cause: misassembled or rough selector linkage; insufficient travel.  
   - Diagnosis: dry-fire sequences with selector set to each side; verifying correct first-barrel each time.  
   - Remedy: adjust and polish selector mechanisms; verify full travel and repeatability.

7. **Premature Wear (Predictive Concern)**  
   - Cause: improperly hardened sear or hammer; rough surfaces causing accelerated wear.  
   - Diagnosis: hardness “file test” (if a file bites too easily, part may be under-hardened); visual inspection of contact surfaces.  
   - Remedy: replace suspect parts with properly hardened components; avoid shipping triggers that might rapidly degrade.

8. **Assembly Errors**  
   - Cause: missed or mis-seated spring, pin, or part.  
   - Diagnosis: systematic function testing; checking against known assembly order.  
   - Remedy: disassembly, correction, and re-testing.

The station emphasizes thorough testing so that **no trigger-related issues appear for the customer under normal use**.

---', null, '3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis', '["3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('4b0a79cf-c308-4fea-83cc-fe816f0848bc', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '28', '35', 'This section consolidates non-standard scenarios and caveats that require extra care in action machining.', null, '4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', '["4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('4b191be7-1c19-4b77-8d24-ae4b617d938d', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '47', '58', '- Perazzi supports top athletes primarily via guns, custom configurations, and priority service rather than large cash stipends.  
- Sponsored shooters across trap, skeet, sporting, and live-pigeon disciplines serve as **brand ambassadors**, bridging elite performance and aspirant shooters.

---', null, '3.9.5 Sponsored Shooters and Ambassadors', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.9 Events, Community, and Legacy > 3.9.5 Sponsored Shooters and Ambassadors', '["3-9-5-sponsored-shooters-and-ambassadors","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-9-events-community-and-legacy-3-9-5-sponsored-shooters-and-ambassadors"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('4b1aa954-e9e0-485a-88e4-079b0090f51a', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '22', '39', 'Perazzi uses its **indoor pattern range** as a key performance validation step:

- Guns are typically test-fired at **~32–40 yards (30–36 m)**.
- Firing is done from a **rest** to eliminate shooter error.
- Pattern boards are examined for:
  - **Point of impact (POI)** relative to aiming mark.
  - **Barrel regulation** (where each barrel’s pattern centers).
  - **Pattern density and uniformity**.

For O/U guns, they verify:

- The two barrels’ **centers of pattern coincide**, or
- Follow the **intended design**, e.g.:
  - On a trap combo, the bottom barrel may be set to shoot slightly higher than the top barrel, if that is the shooter’s preference for rising vs flatter targets.

If the gun was ordered to produce a **70/30 high pattern** for trap, testers confirm this outcome. Deviations from the requested POI can trigger:

- Minor rib adjustments (on adjustable-rib models).
- Stock adjustment (bend or comb tweaks).
- Reassessment of earlier regulation steps.', null, '3.3.1 Factory Pattern Testing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Patterning & On-Range Performance > 3.3.1 Factory Pattern Testing', '["3-3-1-factory-pattern-testing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-3-patterning-on-range-performance-3-3-1-factory-pattern-testing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('4b43137a-d2aa-47aa-a28c-ad1088b9724a', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '26', '49', '- **Pattern Plate**  
  - Steel plate, recoated between shots with:
    - Whitewash.  
    - Paint (e.g., roller-applied).  
  - Shot impacts leave visible marks for quick assessment.

- **Pattern Paper**  
  - Large sheets with central aiming mark.  
  - After shooting:
    - Identify densest area and draw **30" circle** around it to judge coverage.  
    - Optionally divide into quadrants for more detailed uniformity checks.

- **Marking Tools**  
  - Pens, chalk, and markers to:
    - Indicate barrel used, distance, load, date.  
    - Draw circles and record measurements.', null, '3.5.1 Patterning Targets & Marking', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Patterning Targets & Marking', '["3-5-1-patterning-targets-marking","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-patterning-targets-marking"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('4b625bec-c4db-4cd6-9048-416fab073b67', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '20', '45', '- **Oil Finish**  
  - Pros: traditional appearance; easy to spot-repair; ages gracefully; feels “warm” and organic.  
  - Cons: slower build and cure; requires occasional user maintenance (re-oiling).

- **Polyurethane/Lacquer**  
  - Pros: tougher, more water-resistant; low maintenance; controllable sheen.  
  - Cons: can appear plasticky if heavy; hard to repair locally; may chip or craze over long term.

**Perazzi practice (conceptual):**

- For **hard-use competition guns**, a **thin, oil-like synthetic** or robust oil finish may be preferred to balance durability and appearance.  
- For higher-grade, bespoke guns, a **true hand-rubbed oil** finish may be chosen for tradition and repairability.', null, '3.4.1 Oil vs Polyurethane/Synthetic Film', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Oil vs Polyurethane/Synthetic Film', '["3-4-1-oil-vs-polyurethane-synthetic-film","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-oil-vs-polyurethane-synthetic-film"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('4c844bcc-3adb-40d3-b9a8-8dd763b954a1', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '13', '39', 'Perazzi’s tolerance philosophy blends:

- **Modern metrology**
  - CNC precision.
  - Gauges and reference standards.
- **Old-world hand-fitting**
  - Craftsmen resolving micro-tolerances by feel.
  - A cultural expectation of zero-play where it matters.

The result:

- New Perazzis share a **consistent, solid feel**.
- If a rare issue surfaces in the field (e.g., POI concern, screw backing out), Perazzi addresses it promptly under warranty.
- The aim is to catch all such issues **in-house** before final sign-off, ensuring compliance with internal and CIP standards.

---', null, '3.1.8 Summary: Measured and Felt Quality', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Quality Control & Tolerances > 3.1.8 Summary: Measured and Felt Quality', '["3-1-8-summary-measured-and-felt-quality","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-1-quality-control-tolerances-3-1-8-summary-measured-and-felt-quality"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('4ca90e6b-01be-43a3-9868-543035a1b5e6', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '87', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 3 SCO | Base model: high-tech-s-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S 3 SCO', 'Models > High Tech S 3 SCO', '["model-details","high-tech-s-3-sco","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('4cb4938e-6ab6-46ea-909e-9ff59cd5df20', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '41', '58', '- **Wood grade**:[81]
  - Standard Grade 1: included.  
  - SC2: ~US$1,000–1,500 upgrade.  
  - SC3: ~US$2,000–3,000 upgrade.  
  - SCO: ~US$5,000+ upgrade, depending on blank quality.

- **Engraving**:[117][118][131][134][135]
  - SC3 scroll: ~US$8,000–12,000 over base.  
  - SCO full-coverage: ~US$20,000+ over base.  
  - SCO Gold and sideplate designs can raise total gun prices into the **US$70k–80k** range.

- **Barrels & sub-gauges**:[31]  
  - Extra small-gauge barrel set: ~US$1,680 (on 12-ga frame).  
