  - They support final fitting sessions (e.g., Perazzi Experience) by making small mechanical tweaks as needed.', null, '3.7.4 Collaboration with Pattern Testers & Fitters', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.4 Collaboration with Pattern Testers & Fitters', '["3-7-4-collaboration-with-pattern-testers-fitters","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-4-collaboration-with-pattern-testers-fitters"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('4d4b115c-7494-4a15-afaf-da498161b542', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '49', '53', '- Even with excellent fitting, shooters may need a **few hundred targets** to fully adapt.  
- Fitter may deliberately avoid micro‑tuning based on first impressions and instead schedule follow‑up adjustments after the shooter has gained experience.', null, '4.4 Break-In Period for Shooter', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.4 Break-In Period for Shooter', '["4-4-break-in-period-for-shooter","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-4-break-in-period-for-shooter"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('4dbfea07-9f21-4ab0-b8ab-2a5382802196', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '30', '45', '- **Touch Tests**  
  - Finger or fingernail test in inconspicuous area to judge hardness and tackiness.

- **Visual Checks**  
  - Viewing from multiple angles to detect dull spots, glossy pits, or sanding lines.  
  - Comparing stock and fore-end side-by-side under identical lighting.

- **Moisture & Environment Awareness**  
  - Although formal moisture meters are used earlier in process, finishers maintain a sense of whether wood was properly seasoned before finishing.

---', null, '3.5.4 Informal Checks & Cues', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.4 Informal Checks & Cues', '["3-5-4-informal-checks-cues","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-4-informal-checks-cues"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('4dc32a03-6d6a-48c9-b9e6-b89177ab1bf6', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '33', '35', '- **Upstream:**  
  - **Design & Specification Station (Product Engineering)** – defines model family, dimensions, and critical tolerances that guide action machining.

- **Downstream:**  
  - **Barrel Fitting and Regulation** – depends on precise hinge pin and locking geometry from the receiver.  
  - **Stockmaking and Inletting** – relies on action bar dimensions and contour accuracy.  
  - **Trigger Group Fitting** – depends on internal receiver geometry and pin/bore placement.  
  - **Final Assembly and Test** – confirms that the action closes with the desired feel and maintains tightness in firing tests.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With the receiver machined to near perfection, the next major focus in the handbook is the **barrel department**, where steel tubes are turned into regulated barrel sets, often described as the "soul" of the shotgun.

---', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('4e4f3976-f668-4eb4-afcf-f2c7ce8cb0eb', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '13', '38', '- **Lighter Pull**  
  - Pros: easier, faster shooting with less disturbance to aim.  
  - Cons: if sear engagement is too shallow, higher risk of jar-off, doubling, or unintentional discharge.

- **Heavier Pull**  
  - Pros: greater margin of safety, more resistant to accidental discharge.  
  - Cons: can feel heavy or “creepy” if not tuned carefully.

**Practical approach:**

- Set competition triggers to a range that balances performance and safety (e.g., ~3.3–3.5 lbs, unless customer requests otherwise).  
- Use crisp sear geometry so that slightly heavier pulls still feel light and clean.  
- Adjust sear engagement to ensure safety while achieving minimal creep.', null, '3.4.1 Pull Weight vs Safety', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Pull Weight vs Safety', '["3-4-1-pull-weight-vs-safety","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-pull-weight-vs-safety"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('4f4be8a2-3c9a-445c-a219-294f1c80e826', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '104', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S SC3 Gold | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: SC3 Gold | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S SC3 Gold', 'Models > High Tech S SC3 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-s-sc3-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('4f72f61e-ccaf-4024-b18a-2f6fa7816a29', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '167', '238', 'Model name: MX20 SC3 | Base model: mx20 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX20 SC3', 'Models > MX20 SC3', '["model-details","mx20-sc3","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('4f9c74c9-a0dd-4210-bc4a-34da920a6fda', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '13', '48', '- Orienting the stock within the blank in 3D, accounting for:  
  - Cast (often by tilting the stock shape within the blank for “natural cast”).  
  - Drop and pitch relative to a reference line representing the rib axis.  
- Marking side and top profiles using chalk/pencil and templates.  
- Visualizing how curves (butt, comb, grip) will emerge from the slab and ensuring sufficient margin for final shaping.', null, '3.3.2 Layout & Template Use', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Layout & Template Use', '["3-3-2-layout-template-use","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-layout-template-use"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('501e1826-8eb6-4cb0-9fea-1d8eca4b10ca', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '14', '39', '- Perazzi’s factory is relatively **open to visitors**, which is unusual in the industry.
- Practices:
  - Customers can:
    - Walk through the factory.
    - Observe operations.
    - Participate in fitting and testing sessions on-site.
  - On-site pattern range allows:
    - Immediate feedback on POI and pattern.
    - Direct adjustments by factory staff.
- Cultural effects:
  - Transparency encourages **accountability and pride** among craftspeople.
  - Close feedback loop between:
    - Customer experience.
    - Factory fitting decisions.
- Leadership involvement:
  - Company leadership (e.g., Mauro Perazzi) has been known to participate in made-to-measure sessions.
- Overall:
  - Factory culture is part of the **Perazzi “product”**: owners feel involved in the making of their gun.', null, '3.1.9 Factory Culture & Customer Interaction', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations > 3.1.9 Factory Culture & Customer Interaction', '["3-1-9-factory-culture-customer-interaction","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations-3-1-9-factory-culture-customer-interaction"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('501fb79d-10ed-4161-b4fe-553301796f5d', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '17', '39', '- **High-Temperature Joints** (e.g., monobloc to barrels)  
  - Strong, structural joints typically done with brazing alloys.  
  - Risk of warpage if not controlled.

- **Low-Temperature Joints** (e.g., ribs)  
  - Use softer solder to reduce distortion risk.  
  - Require compatible finishing processes (e.g., rust bluing instead of high-heat salt bluing).

**Design response:**

- Choose solder/brazing alloys and sequences to balance strength, warpage risk, and downstream finishing requirements.  
- Use fixturing and controlled heating to maintain alignment.', null, '3.4.4 Solder Temperature and Method', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Solder Temperature and Method', '["3-4-4-solder-temperature-and-method","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-solder-temperature-and-method"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('503314ba-eed7-4117-9e09-0f5c3712fa53', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '16', '26', '- Seeks **progress, performance, and measurable growth**.
