  - "Which gun is right for me?"
  - "What’s the difference between these platforms?"', null, '3.3.2 Shotguns / Platforms – Structured Exploration', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 3. Core Experiences & Main Site Areas > 3.3 How the Main Site Areas Work > 3.3.2 Shotguns / Platforms – Structured Exploration', '["3-3-2-shotguns-platforms-structured-exploration","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-3-core-experiences-main-site-areas-3-3-how-the-main-site-areas-work-3-3-2-shotguns-platforms-structured-exploration"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('5517f7b6-d8c1-4959-b761-b4455eb85ed0', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '15', '32', 'PerazziGPT should understand that the site is built around a handful of **core experiences**, not just pages.', null, '3.1 Core Experiences Being Built', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 3. Core Experiences & Main Site Areas > 3.1 Core Experiences Being Built', '["3-1-core-experiences-being-built","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-3-core-experiences-main-site-areas-3-1-core-experiences-being-built"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('551fe2e4-abbc-45e2-a9d8-a97a7cab57bc', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '123', '238', 'Model name: High Tech X | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: X | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech X', 'Models > High Tech X', '["model-details","high-tech-x","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('554d4a94-00c8-41c3-8818-32548972b6ff', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '14', '32', '- **Leaf-Spring Trigger**[6][7]  
  - Very crisp, light trigger pull; often preferred for peak competition performance.  
  - Failure mode: if a leaf spring snaps, the trigger may stop working entirely. Though rare, this is a catastrophic-style failure.

- **Coil-Spring Trigger**[6][8]  
  - Slightly heavier and longer trigger pull.  
  - Very robust; more tolerant of long-term use and abuse.  
  - Failure mode: even if a coil spring fails, the trigger often still fires at least once.

**Design response:**

- Match trigger system to shooter priorities:  
  - Some top competitors accept leaf-spring risks and carry a spare drop-out trigger group.  
  - Other shooters prioritize reliability (e.g., for hunting or long tournaments) and prefer coil springs.', null, '3.4.3 Trigger System Choice: Leaf vs Coil Springs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Typical Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Trigger System Choice: Leaf vs Coil Springs', '["3-4-3-trigger-system-choice-leaf-vs-coil-springs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-3-main-content-3-4-typical-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-trigger-system-choice-leaf-vs-coil-springs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('55accd58-6e4a-41d7-8fde-5908714bb780', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '9', '45', '- **Wood Components**  
  - Fully shaped and inletted stock and fore-end, sanded finely (often to ~320 grit or higher).  
  - Checkering cut and cleaned; may be completely bare or lightly sealed.

- **Finishing Materials**  
  - Oil finish mixtures (linseed/tung-based with driers, possibly with varnish/resin).  
  - Synthetic finishes (polyurethane, lacquer) in matte, satin, or gloss formulations.  
  - Stains/dyes or alkanet root oil when color adjustment is desired.  
  - Grain fillers (pumice, commercial fillers) or fine wood dust for slurry filling.  
  - Waxes for final sheen (e.g., beeswax-based blends).

- **Surface Prep Consumables**  
  - Sandpapers in fine grits (e.g., 320–600+).  
  - Steel wool (e.g., 0000) or fine abrasive pads.  
  - Tack cloths, clean lint-free rags.

- **Tools & Equipment**  
  - Rubbing pads or bare hands for oil application.  
  - Spray equipment for poly/film finishes (guns, compressors, thinners, viscosity cups).  
  - Drying racks or cabinets in controlled, low-dust environment.  
  - Buffing cloths and compounds (e.g., rottenstone, automotive finishing compounds).  
  - Light and inspection setups for raking-light viewing.

- **Reference Information**  
  - Shooter/use case (competition, field, presentation).  
  - Brand and model guidelines for standard color and sheen.  
  - Notes from earlier stations (e.g., “keep comb matte,” “fore-end and stock from different blanks – color match”).', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('55b809cb-0bed-49a8-b6fa-96f016cb753e', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '24', '56', '- **Chasing Minor Imperfections**  
  - Pros: can yield near-perfect aesthetics (e.g., wood-metal flushness).  
  - Cons: risk of damaging finish or wood when trying to correct negligible issues at final stage.

**Practical approach:**  
- Correct issues that are **visible and meaningful** to function or aesthetics.  
