- Inspecting both pieces under the same light and angle to confirm match.', null, '3.3.7 Matching Stock & Fore-end', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.7 Matching Stock & Fore-end', '["3-3-7-matching-stock-fore-end","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-7-matching-stock-fore-end"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('579f43da-ed94-4299-9621-85591583a904', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '24', '26', 'Most real users will not fit a single archetype cleanly. Common blends include:

- **Loyalist–Achiever**  
  - Has already committed to Perazzi and cares deeply about performance.  
  - Responds to both continuity and serious training language.

- **Prestige–Legacy**  
  - Cares about visual distinction now and heirloom value later.  
  - Responds to stories about craft and future significance.

- **Analyst–Achiever**  
  - Wants to understand the mechanics behind performance.  
  - Responds well to detailed explanations that connect setup to results.

- **Loyalist–Legacy**  
  - Often tied to family or mentor history with Perazzi.  
  - Sees the gun as part of a multi-generation story.

PerazziGPT should treat these archetypes as **motivational lenses**, not labels. They are helpful for choosing emphasis and examples, not for deciding what is true or what the user “is.”

