---', null, '0. Metadata', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 0. Metadata', '["0-metadata","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-0-metadata"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('57f58def-75e3-469e-a294-6228f2e4050b', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '5', '58', '- **Monobloc**: Solid breech block into which barrel tubes are fitted and soldered; contains locking bites and lugs. Key to Perazzi’s Boss-style low-profile action.[21]

- **Drop-out (detachable) trigger group**: Self-contained trigger-plate unit removable from the bottom of the receiver for fast service or replacement (MX8-style action).[32]

- **Leaf springs vs. coil springs**: Alternative mainspring types driving the hammers. Leaf springs provide very fast lock times; coil springs emphasize durability and easier replacement.[33][36]

- **Point of impact (POI)**: Vertical distribution of pattern relative to point of aim (e.g. 50/50, 70/30, 80/20), tunable via rib height and stock geometry.

- **Try-gun**: Adjustable “fitting” gun used to measure and confirm ideal stock dimensions before building the customer’s final stock.[75]

---', null, '2.4 Technical Concepts', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Technical Concepts', '["2-4-technical-concepts","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-technical-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('5825b83f-a824-4972-8088-662678b38721', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '8', '38', 'Wendell is described as trusting Perazzi shotguns to perform at the highest level. His competition gun of choice is a custom-fitted Perazzi MX2000 with 34″ barrels and fixed chokes (Improved Mod and Full)[9].

Key points:

- The MX2000 is described as a combination he “wields with deadly effect.”  
- With this Perazzi, Wendell exudes a steady, quiet authority on the course, allowing results to speak louder than words.  
- Each time he shoulders his MX2000, the source frames it as the culmination of years of experience and as an embodiment of Perazzi’s ethos of excellence.

The source presents Wendell’s story – from country music to world-class clays – as an example of passion and perseverance, highlighting how he continues to inspire shooters to chase their dreams with humility and unwavering dedication.

