  - Measured on a try-gun to dial in exact stock dimensions.  
  - Allowed to choose their own walnut blank from the stock room.[82][83]  
  - Fire test patterns in the underground tunnel to verify POI.  
  - Stock may be adjusted or remade to achieve precise fit.
- The process often takes place mid-build (after metalwork, before final finishing).  
- Experience is positioned as a “pilgrimage” and key component of the Perazzi ownership story.[43][96]', null, '3.6.3 Factory Fitting and Perazzi Experience', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Customization and Ordering Process > 3.6.3 Factory Fitting and Perazzi Experience', '["3-6-3-factory-fitting-and-perazzi-experience","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-6-customization-and-ordering-process-3-6-3-factory-fitting-and-perazzi-experience"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('5a1e0e91-0179-4b5f-ad6c-144390ff20de', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '21', '45', '- **Fully Pore-Filled**  
  - Pros: glossy, mirror-like surfaces possible; easier to wipe clean; maximum chatoyance.  
  - Cons: more time and coats; risk of overly thick film if not carefully controlled.

- **Partially Open-Pore**  
  - Pros: natural look and feel; can provide microtexture; less time-consuming.  
  - Cons: slightly more susceptible to moisture ingress if not sealed carefully.

**Practical approach:**

- Competition guns often end up **sealed and largely pore-filled**, but with a **satin sheen** rather than extreme gloss.  
- Some fore-ends may retain a hint of texture for grip.', null, '3.4.2 Pore Fill vs Open-Pore', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Pore Fill vs Open-Pore', '["3-4-2-pore-fill-vs-open-pore","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-pore-fill-vs-open-pore"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('5a5eb9cf-76cb-4807-b010-5f4d60f5ca8e', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '9', '238', 'Model name: DC SCO Sideplates | Base model: dc | Platform: DC | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: side-by-side | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### DC SCO Sideplates', 'Models > DC SCO Sideplates', '["model-details","dc-sco-sideplates","platform:dc"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('5abab824-a93f-4720-bc7e-78a2af22c4f4', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '15', '56', '- Confirm that safety effectively blocks firing when engaged:  
  - With safety on, triggers should not release hammers.  
- Verify selector operation (if present):  
  - Selected barrel must fire first; second shot must follow correctly.  
- Confirm configuration (auto-safety vs manual-only) per model and order.', null, '3.3.4 Safety & Selector Verification', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.4 Safety & Selector Verification', '["3-3-4-safety-selector-verification","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-4-safety-selector-verification"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('5b0c05bb-dca0-4d46-9595-9329e9f88a81', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '29', '45', '- **Degreasing Tanks**  
  - Hot detergent or solvent baths for pre-bluing cleaning.

- **Rinse Tanks**  
  - Clean water, possibly demineralized, to avoid deposits.

- **Neutralizing Baths**  
  - Alkaline solutions to stop rusting reactions after rust-bluing cycles.', null, '3.5.3 Cleaning & Neutralization Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.3 Cleaning & Neutralization Tools', '["3-5-3-cleaning-neutralization-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-3-cleaning-neutralization-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('5bba2c9b-5b90-4625-9a58-2cb8d5961f89', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '46', '49', '- Customers may be sensitive to small perceived POI offsets or pattern nuances.  
- Testers must balance technical confidence in results with clear explanation and, when needed, **small adjustments** that align gun behavior with customer comfort.

---', null, '4.4 Customer Perception vs Objective Results', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.4 Customer Perception vs Objective Results', '["4-4-customer-perception-vs-objective-results","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-4-customer-perception-vs-objective-results"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('5bf680e1-26e5-4508-8726-f2f4eb30bf99', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '6', '51', '- **QA Checklist / Spec Sheet**  
  - Line‑by‑line list used to verify each required feature and accessory.

- **Warranty Registration / Internal Record**  
  - Record linking serial number to customer/dealer and captured specs; used for future service and legal compliance.

- **Presentation Standard**  
  - Expectation that gun and case appear immaculate when opened by the client or reviewer, reflecting the brand’s standards.

---', null, '2.5 Administrative & Presentation Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.5 Administrative & Presentation Concepts', '["2-5-administrative-presentation-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-5-administrative-presentation-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('5bfe1f92-0a80-4c1a-a461-50f097462774', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '29', '38', '> **Example vignette (composite, illustrative):**  
> Luigi, a senior trigger artisan at Perazzi, has a ritual: at day’s end, he dry-fires every trigger group he completed that day a dozen times in rapid succession—click-click, reset, click-click—alternating barrels with practiced rhythm. He listens for absolute consistency.  
> One day, a new apprentice hears Luigi reject a unit because “the second click sounded weak.” To the apprentice, it seems fine. Luigi insists on opening it: inside, he finds a slightly rough spot on the inertia block’s path that is slowing the hammer just enough to change the sound. A few careful strokes with a fine file, a light polish, reassembly—and now even the apprentice hears the difference: two strong, sharp clicks. Luigi nods, “Now it has the voice of a Perazzi.”  
> This captures the almost musical ear and intuition a master has for the mechanism’s behavior.

Masters may also develop quiet innovations—small refinements like polishing specific pins or surfaces—to improve long-term stability and consistency, even when such steps are not formally specified.

---', null, '3.7.6 Example Vignette: “Voice of a Perazzi”', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.6 Example Vignette: “Voice of a Perazzi”', '["3-7-6-example-vignette-voice-of-a-perazzi","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-6-example-vignette-voice-of-a-perazzi"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('5c1c523b-31ca-4924-b45d-c65060458984', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '9', '35', '- **Forged Steel Receiver Blank**  
  - Pre-formed steel block shaped roughly like a Perazzi receiver, with extra material throughout.

- **Model-Specific Machining Specifications**  
  - Digital models and/or drawings for different action families (e.g., MX8 vs. MX20, drop-out trigger receivers vs. fixed-trigger receivers).  
  - Instructions derived from upstream design/specification work.

- **CNC Programs and Setup Information**  
  - Multi-operation CNC programs defining tool paths and sequences.  
  - Fixturing and datum definitions for each operation.

- **Cutting Tools, Jigs, and Fixtures**  
  - End mills, drills, reamers, and specialized tools for milling complex shapes (e.g., curved fences, trigger slots).  
  - Custom fixtures to hold the forging at precise orientations for different cuts.

- **Coolant, Speeds, and Feeds**  
  - Defined cutting parameters to balance tool life, surface finish, and thermal stability.', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('5c2ba3a9-b2e1-4d72-9578-de83afc5ac18', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '196', '238', 'Model name: MX28 SCO Gold Sideplates | Base model: mx28 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 28ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX28 SCO Gold Sideplates', 'Models > MX28 SCO Gold Sideplates', '["model-details","mx28-sco-gold-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('5c5ea152-9acd-4594-95f5-1cd5a5acbfec', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '9', '26', '- They see Perazzi as:
