---', null, '0. Metadata', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 0. Metadata', '["0-metadata","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-0-metadata"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('6106a4de-06c8-4a22-b43c-3ec1e3956586', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '3', '39', '- **Barrel Tubes**  
  - Long steel tubes that form the bores of the shotgun. Created by deep-hole drilling and reaming solid bar stock.

- **Monobloc**  
  - Breech block containing chambers, locking lugs, and interfaces to the action. Barrel tubes are joined into the monobloc.

- **Chamber**  
  - Enlarged rear section of the bore that holds the cartridge (e.g., 70 mm / 2¾" or 76 mm / 3").

- **Bore**  
  - Main cylindrical interior of the barrel, between forcing cone and choke.

- **Forcing Cone**  
  - Tapered transition area between chamber and bore. Its length and angle influence pressure curve and pattern.

- **Choke**  
  - Constriction at the muzzle to control pattern density. Can be **fixed** (machined in) or **removable** (threaded choke tubes).

- **Ribs**  
  - **Top Rib**: sighting plane atop the barrel set (flat, raised, or adjustable).  
  - **Side Ribs**: lateral strips joining the tubes, adding stiffness and providing a finished aesthetic.', null, '2.2 Core Barrel Components', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Core Barrel Components', '["2-2-core-barrel-components","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-core-barrel-components"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('6111746c-9a93-4426-97b2-33b6dff22141', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '8', '51', '- **Wood Components**  
  - Fully shaped stock and fore-end, **sanded and ready** for checkering.  
  - Typically still “in the white,” with either no finish or possibly a light sealer coat.

- **Layout Information**  
  - Checkering pattern layout, including:  
    - Pattern shape and coverage (grip area, fore-end panels).  
    - LPI specification (often standardized per model).  
  - Pencil or scribed guide lines marking main pattern angles and boundaries.

- **Checkering Tools & Fixtures**  
  - Single-line cutters for initial grooves.  
  - Double-line or spacing cutters to maintain even spacing.  
  - V-tools/veiners for deepening cuts and forming borders.  
  - Safe-sided cutters for border work.  
  - Flexible straightedge or simple gauges to define initial layout lines.  
  - Checkering cradle or padded vise to hold stock/fore-end at comfortable angles.  
  - Good lighting and, optionally, magnification.', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('61326a5e-a97c-4cae-b8da-244b5ebdeeaa', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '34', '50', '### Massimo Fabbrizi
**Country:** Italy
**Event:** Men’s Trap
**Medal:** Silver
**Olympics:** 2012 London
**Perazzi platform:** MX8
**Highlights:** Fabbrizi earned trap silver for Italy in 2012 using a Perazzi MX8:contentReference[oaicite:120]{index=120}. A protégé of earlier Italian champions, he maintained the tradition of Italian trap shooters with Perazzis. He tied the world record in qualification (125/125) and only narrowly lost gold in a shoot-off, attesting to the MX8’s world-class pedigree decades after its debut:contentReference[oaicite:121]{index=121}.
**Sources:**
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:122]{index=122}
- ISSF Press Release – London 2012 Men’s Trap (mentions Fabbrizi’s equipment):contentReference[oaicite:123]{index=123}', null, '### Massimo Fabbrizi', 'Olympic Medals > Massimo Fabbrizi', '["olympic-medals","massimo-fabbrizi"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('615a87be-b718-4ad6-9b7f-56b089e92f79', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '11', '26', '- Emphasize:
  - **Craftsmanship and artistry** (wood selection, engraving, hand work).
  - **Presentation and presence** (“how the gun lives in the hand and in the eye of others”).
  - **Curation** (“Your gun can be built as deliberately as your taste.”).
- Tone:
  - Refined, composed, visually descriptive.
  - Avoid anything that feels flashy or loud; prestige here is quiet, not ostentatious.

---', null, '3.2.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Prestige-Oriented Users', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.2 Prestige > 3.2.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Prestige-Oriented Users', '["3-2-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-prestige-oriented-users","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-2-prestige-3-2-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-prestige-oriented-users"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('616db9dd-54d1-41f4-ad3d-30e9158cac6f', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '45', '49', '- Some combinations of barrel and load may show unusual but repeatable behavior (e.g., certain wad/shot types).  
- Where anomalies seem load-specific, the gun may still be within spec if it performs normally with standard loads.

**Caveat:**  
If a customer intends to use such loads, testers may recommend alternative ammunition or caution about that specific combination.', null, '4.3 Ammo-Specific Performance', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.3 Ammo-Specific Performance', '["4-3-ammo-specific-performance","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-3-ammo-specific-performance"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('618ae452-a0d3-4a8c-982c-32df01ad85ad', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '28', '48', '- **Band Saw**  
  - Used to cut rough side and top profiles following layout lines.

- **Stock Duplicator / Pantograph**  
  - Copies pattern stock shape into blank, leaving predetermined oversize.

- **CNC Stock Machine**  
  - Uses digital models and parameterized inputs (LOP, drop, cast) to carve stock and fore-end.

- **Hand Tools** (for touch-ups)  
  - Rasps and coarse files for local adjustments.  
  - Chisels and gouges for specific rough inletting or detail refinement.', null, '3.5.1 Cutting & Shaping Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Cutting & Shaping Tools', '["3-5-1-cutting-shaping-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-cutting-shaping-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('619a715f-71a6-453d-ab02-2603a6df8aef', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '23', '40', '- **Inletting Black / Soot**  
  - Applied to metal surfaces to reveal high spots in wood.

- **Chisels & Gouges**  
  - Short, sharp chisels (including fishtail and skew patterns) for precise control.  
  - Light mallet used for controlled cuts.

- **Scrapers (Flat & Curved)**  
  - For shaving thin curls of wood and smoothing contact surfaces.

- **Hook Scrapers & Rifflers**  
  - For reaching and refining tight internal corners and complex external curves.', null, '3.5.1 Core Inletting Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Core Inletting Tools', '["3-5-1-core-inletting-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-core-inletting-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('61a124d0-e0fc-4f18-97d1-089b4b28dd6c', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '12', '51', '- Starting lines with **very light incisions** to avoid slips.  
- Keeping the cutter aligned and at a consistent angle, especially for the first few reference lines.  
- Using previous cuts as guides: once initial lines are established, later cutters “ride” in them.  
- Applying consistent pressure to avoid depth variation and chatter.', null, '3.3.2 Tool Control', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Tool Control', '["3-3-2-tool-control","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-tool-control"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('61ad30ae-8ef4-4675-8ee2-1941897009de', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '7', '49', 'The **Patterning & Performance Testing station**:

- Verifies that **both barrels hit where they should** at typical pattern distances.  
- Confirms that **pattern density and evenness** align with choke designations and intended use.  
- Tests the **functional reliability** of ejectors, triggers, and other systems under **live-fire recoil**.  
- Provides data to support **final fitting and adjustments** (e.g., comb height, adjustable rib position) when the customer or fitter is involved.

It is the final **ballistic and functional validation** of the shotgun.', null, '3.1.1 Purpose', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.1 Purpose', '["3-1-1-purpose","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-1-purpose"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('61d4af2e-3b4a-456a-8f52-ccdf80795d20', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '36', '39', '- **Perazzi-specific practices & architecture** – see also:  
  - Part I: §3.2 (Platform Architecture)  
  - Part II: Process deep-dives by station  
  - Part III: §3.1–3.3 (Quality, Fit, Patterning)

- **Customization, fitting, and user experience** – see:  
  - Part I: §3.1.3  
  - Part II: Stock & fitting sections  
  - Part III: §3.2 (Fit & Handling)

- **Serviceability and longevity** – see:  
  - Part III: §3.1.6–3.1.7 (Tolerance management, cosmetic QC).', null, '5.1 Internal Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 5. References & Cross-Links > 5.1 Internal Cross-Links', '["5-1-internal-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-5-references-cross-links-5-1-internal-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('61e4e5bd-71f4-4ee2-9b45-fed46891d106', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '50', '58', '- Because Perazzi actions and barrels share similar geometry, some gunsmiths or owners assemble **“parts guns”** from mismatched receivers, barrels, and forends.  
- Risks of mismatching serialized components without factory fitting:[21]  
  - Incorrect headspace.  
  - Improper locking-bolt engagement.  
  - Ejector timing issues.  
  - Potential safety hazards.
- Factory policy: barrels, receivers, and forends with different serials should only be paired when properly fitted and verified by the factory or authorized experts.  
- Using mismatched components may void manufacturer responsibility.', null, '3.10.3 Mixing Components and “Parts Guns”', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.10 Counterfeits, Grey Market, and Service Integrity > 3.10.3 Mixing Components and “Parts Guns”', '["3-10-3-mixing-components-and-parts-guns","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-10-counterfeits-grey-market-and-service-integrity-3-10-3-mixing-components-and-parts-guns"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('621d4032-4a4f-41db-a825-b9e7e95735e9', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '13', '35', '- **Tighter Machine Tolerances**  
  - Pros: parts may fit together almost out-of-the-box.  
  - Cons: if too precise, fitters have little or no material left for custom tailoring.

- **More Allowance for Hand Work**  
  - Pros: allows expert fitters to achieve perfect lock-up and mating surfaces.  
  - Cons: too much extra material creates excessive work at later benches.

**Design response at this station:**

- Decide which features to machine to near-final size (e.g., ejector channels) and which to leave oversize (e.g., locking surfaces, some barrel/action contact areas).  
- Determine typical allowances (e.g., leaving a few thousandths of an inch or ~0.1 mm for fitting on critical surfaces).', null, '3.4.1 Machining Tolerance vs. Hand Fit', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Machining Tolerance vs. Hand Fit', '["3-4-1-machining-tolerance-vs-hand-fit","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-machining-tolerance-vs-hand-fit"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('62285bce-5d0b-4116-9b86-0aea39995154', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '31', '50', '### Jessica Rossi
**Country:** Italy
**Event:** Women’s Trap
**Medal:** Gold
**Olympics:** 2012 London
**Perazzi platform:** MX8
**Highlights:** Rossi dominated the women’s trap in 2012, winning gold with a Perazzi MX8 and shattering the world record with 99 hits out of 100:contentReference[oaicite:109]{index=109}. Her performance was one of the most dominant in Olympic shotgun history. Rossi’s MX8 – essentially the same model first used to win Olympic gold in 1964 – proved its timeless efficacy almost half a century later:contentReference[oaicite:110]{index=110}.
**Sources:**
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:111]{index=111}
- ISSF News – London 2012 (Rossi’s world record, mentions her Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:112]{index=112}', null, '### Jessica Rossi', 'Olympic Medals > Jessica Rossi', '["olympic-medals","jessica-rossi"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('62a52657-5494-4e1d-ab4c-7afe23068a29', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '2', '35', '- **Action & Receiver Machining Station (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Action Shop*, *Receiver Machining*, *Action Machining*.  
  - Definition: The station responsible for machining the receiver (action body) and closely related steel parts (e.g., top latch, forend iron, possibly trigger plate) from forged blanks.

- **Receiver / Action (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Frame*, *Action Body*.  
  - Definition: Central structural component that houses the locking system, trigger group, firing pins, and provides attachment points for barrels and stock.

- **Downstream Partners**  
  - Examples: barrel fitting and regulation, stockmaking, assembly, engraving, final inspection.  
  - These stations rely on the receiver’s geometry and surface quality.', null, '2.1 Roles and Components', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Components', '["2-1-roles-and-components","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-components"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('62abe37e-e1b2-41da-b15e-3340b3602452', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '24', '48', '- Leaving more oversize:  
  - Pros: maximum safety margin for final shaping and fit; easier to correct minor errors or movement.  
  - Cons: more labor later for hand shaping.

- Leaving less oversize:  
  - Pros: less hand work; higher efficiency.  
  - Cons: little room to correct errors or accommodate wood movement; high risk with expensive blanks.

**Practical approach:**  
- Err on the side of leaving safe oversize (e.g., a few millimeters externally and undersize in inletting), especially for high-grade blanks, since extra labor is preferred over scrapping costly wood.', null, '3.4.3 Oversize Dimensions vs Efficiency', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Oversize Dimensions vs Efficiency', '["3-4-3-oversize-dimensions-vs-efficiency","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-oversize-dimensions-vs-efficiency"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('62f29f26-fd32-4b3f-bb8f-09f10343e814', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '31', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2024 | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2024 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech 2024', 'Models > High Tech 2024', '["model-details","high-tech-2024","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('6309f00d-08e8-47ab-b824-302fb255e64d', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '38', '45', '- Masters think beyond initial sale, aiming for finishes that **age gracefully**:  
  - Bluing that can be maintained and refreshed if needed.  
  - Coin finishes that resist rust with proper protection.  
  - Engraving that remains legible decades later.

Their work is often **unconsciously appreciated** by customers who simply see a beautiful gun, without realizing how many hours of meticulous surface work and chemical control were required.

---', null, '3.7.6 Long-Term Mindset', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.6 Long-Term Mindset', '["3-7-6-long-term-mindset","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-6-long-term-mindset"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('6332154f-c6c6-43ae-8313-a7c47f5e77f0', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '20', '48', '- Recognizing wood that may still be “green” or unstable.  
- Using intuition and experience (feel, sound when tapped) to assess if a blank is truly seasoned.  
- Knowing when to set aside a blank for additional drying instead of rushing into shaping.

---', null, '3.3.9 Moisture and Stability Awareness', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.9 Moisture and Stability Awareness', '["3-3-9-moisture-and-stability-awareness","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-9-moisture-and-stability-awareness"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('6337f1a8-a77e-44e8-b320-f029df72f725', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '25', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 5 Gold | Base model: high-tech-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 2020 5 Gold', 'Models > High Tech 2020 5 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-2020-5-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('63423013-4971-4a49-96bb-864c15bfd172', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '14', '56', '- **Lock-Up & Top Lever**  
  - Evaluate initial tightness:  
    - Lever far right and difficult to close → may require minimal polishing or lock-bolt adjustment.  
    - Lever near center on new gun → may require fitting slightly oversize locking bolt or adjusting bites to ensure long-term tightness.

- **Cocking Effort**  
  - Detect excessive resistance when opening; trace to cocking rods, cams, or springs; polish or adjust as needed.

- **Ejector Timing & Strength**  
  - Ensure both ejectors trip at appropriate time and with balanced force.  
  - Adjust by very small sear surface changes or spring selection.

- **Trigger Tuning**  
  - Confirm crispness and pull weights; minor adjustments (via sear geometry or springs) when within safe design limits.  
  - Ensure second-shot function (especially inertia triggers) under realistic simulated recoil.

- **Fore-end & Latch Fitting**  
  - Adjust latch engagement to achieve a **positive but not excessive** snap-on and secure fit with no wobble.', null, '3.3.3 Fine Adjustment & Micro-Fitting', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.3 Fine Adjustment & Micro-Fitting', '["3-3-3-fine-adjustment-micro-fitting","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-3-fine-adjustment-micro-fitting"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('6354912d-9237-430e-aeff-4662475e1ab4', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '18', '36', '- Seek **aspirational excellence** and emotional validation through exclusivity.  
- Attracted to Perazzi as a **symbol of status and refined taste**, not just performance.', null, '3.4.2 Prestige Buyers', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Audience Connection > 3.4.2 Prestige Buyers', '["3-4-2-prestige-buyers","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-4-audience-connection-3-4-2-prestige-buyers"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('636395f1-f1ad-4c3d-9333-b38347b0476f', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '64', '238', 'Model name: High Tech RS SC3 Gold | Base model: high-tech-rs | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: SC3 Gold | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 10.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech RS SC3 Gold', 'Models > High Tech RS SC3 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-rs-sc3-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('63744e05-21bb-42a9-a3e1-b6cc6739784e', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '50', '56', '- Guns built for extreme high-volume shooting or unusual disciplines may have:  
  - Higher or lower trigger weights.  
  - Different lubrication strategies.  
  - Specific ejector or extractor configurations.

**Caveat:**  
Assemblers must respect these requirements while ensuring all safety and reliability margins remain intact.', null, '4.1 Custom & Extreme Use Cases', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Custom & Extreme Use Cases', '["4-1-custom-extreme-use-cases","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-custom-extreme-use-cases"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('639a8b38-ccfe-40d4-bf2a-c6d774df269f', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '8', '58', '- **1973** – U.S. importer **Ithaca Gun Co.** begins importing Perazzi shotguns, catalyzing Perazzi’s penetration into American trap and skeet.[5]  
- Perazzi develops **American-specific models**, including:  
  - **TM1** – Single-barrel trap gun optimized for ATA trap.  
  - Later TM- and MX-based trap guns tailored to U.S. preferences.  
- Collaborations with American champions drive further model evolution:  
  - **DB81** O/U (1981), developed with **Ray Stafford** and named for shooter **Dan Bonillas**.[6]  
  - **MX10** (1990), a high-rib top-single trap gun with adjustable rib and stock.[6]  
  - **MX2000/RS** unsingle (around 1999), with “RS” referencing Ray Stafford’s initials.[7]
- **Grand America 1 & 2** – Special TM-derived models for ATA shooters:  
  - Grand America 1: unsingle.  
  - Grand America 2: top single.  
  Both aimed at handicap trap performance.[8]', null, '3.1.3 Expansion into the U.S. and Discipline-Specific Models', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Company History and Ownership Timeline > 3.1.3 Expansion into the U.S. and Discipline-Specific Models', '["3-1-3-expansion-into-the-u-s-and-discipline-specific-models","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-1-company-history-and-ownership-timeline-3-1-3-expansion-into-the-u-s-and-discipline-specific-models"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('64078883-e896-4224-88ae-97f60f462e06', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '28', '38', '- At major competitions, master triggersmiths may support shooters by diagnosing issues in minutes, often with minimal tools (e.g., on a truck tailgate).  
- Their deep familiarity with the Perazzi trigger system allows quick fixes such as spring replacement or sear adjustment under time pressure.', null, '3.7.5 Field Diagnosis and Support', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.5 Field Diagnosis and Support', '["3-7-5-field-diagnosis-and-support","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-5-field-diagnosis-and-support"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('644178f6-173a-4053-8f61-995e822895c7', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '25', '39', 'Perazzi shares with other top-tier makers:

- Commitment to **skilled labor and hand fitting**.
- Use of **high-grade materials**.
- Adherence to **proof and regulation** norms.
- Deep **engraving and stock-craft traditions**.
- Integration of **CNC** with artisanal finishing.
- An emphasis on **longevity and rebuildability**.

Where they diverge is primarily in their **competition-focused emphasis** and certain distinct design choices outlined in §3.1.

---', null, '3.2.9 Summary: Shared Foundations', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices > 3.2.9 Summary: Shared Foundations', '["3-2-9-summary-shared-foundations","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices-3-2-9-summary-shared-foundations"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('64615de5-28b0-4fcd-afc6-544c4d35866f', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '3', '45', '- **Rust Bluing**  
  - Controlled rust cycles followed by boiling and carding to build a deep blue-black magnetite layer.  
  - Especially suited to **soft-soldered barrels** (low heat, does not melt solder).

- **Hot Salt Bluing (Hot Caustic Bluing)**  
  - Immersing parts in hot caustic salt bath (around ~290 °F / ~140 °C).  
  - Efficient for parts without soldered joints and compatible steel alloys.

- **Coin Finish (French Gray / Bright Steel)**  
  - Highly polished or satin-brushed steel left essentially “in the white” but protected by clear coats or oils; often used on engraved receivers.

- **Case Hardening / Color Case (conceptual)**  
  - Cyanide or similar case-hardening processes used historically to create a hard surface with subtle color patterns.  
  - Applied to certain Perazzi actions/eras for aesthetic and surface-hardening purposes.

- **Plating (Nickel, Gold, etc.)**  
  - Electroplated or coated finishes for corrosion resistance or aesthetics (e.g., nickel receivers, gold-plated trigger blades).  
  - Requires carefully controlled thickness so as not to affect fit or obscure engraving.', null, '2.2 Finish Types', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Finish Types', '["2-2-finish-types","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-finish-types"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('64f8852e-3e34-4b6b-a12c-da678553364e', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '20', '51', '- More coverage:  
  - Pros: more contact area for grip; highly functional.  
  - Cons: more labor; may obscure attractive wood figure.

- Less coverage:  
  - Pros: allows more exposed wood to showcase high-grade figure.  
  - Cons: reduced grip area; may be less secure in some holds.

**Practical approach:**  
- On competition guns, prioritize coverage where hands naturally rest.  
- On highly figured exhibition stocks, patterns may be sized and positioned to **frame and complement** figure rather than dominate it.', null, '3.4.2 Pattern Coverage', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Pattern Coverage', '["3-4-2-pattern-coverage","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-pattern-coverage"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('652cd656-6a64-4983-8445-bb2ee18967d8', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '22', '36', '- Competitors may buy visibility through broad sponsorships; Perazzi instead creates **signature experiences**.  
- Events like the **Perazzi Invitational** are framed as **transformative gatherings** where participation itself equals belonging.  
- The focus is on **curated, high-impact interactions**, not logo volume.', null, '3.5.3 Experience Over Sponsorship', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Strategic Brand Themes > 3.5.3 Experience Over Sponsorship', '["3-5-3-experience-over-sponsorship","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-5-strategic-brand-themes-3-5-3-experience-over-sponsorship"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('654fd369-154d-4ced-a72e-58e89b7a5c9f', '177a681e-a602-4d92-af07-b17c98816feb', '2', '13', '- **Canonical name:** Perazzi Writing Style  
