- **Definition:** A deeply emotional, sophisticated, reflective storytelling style crafted to quietly inspire, authentically engage, and resonate with an aspirational, thoughtful, and discerning audience.', null, '2.1 Perazzi Writing Style (Canonical)', 'Perazzi Writing Style and Tone (AI-Optimized Reference) > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Perazzi Writing Style (Canonical)', '["2-1-perazzi-writing-style-canonical","perazzi-writing-style-and-tone-ai-optimized-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-perazzi-writing-style-canonical"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:49.998824+00', null), ('6552a7d9-4101-49e8-8e22-485b9f987213', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '15', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 10 | Base model: high-tech-10 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 17.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 10', 'Models > High Tech 10', '["model-details","high-tech-10","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('657e4efd-b28c-4162-9712-82a9a0be6287', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '19', '58', '- **Detachable trigger groups (MX8-style)**:[32][33]  
  - Entire trigger-plate assembly removes from the bottom of the receiver via latch.  
  - Contains hammers, sears, springs, and safety/barrel selector (if present).  
  - Advantages: Quick serviceability, ability to carry a spare group, and compact receiver design.
- **Spring options**:  
  - **Leaf (flat) mainsprings** – extremely fast lock time and crisp feel; can eventually break from fatigue.[36]  
  - **Coil mainsprings** – slightly slower lock time but high durability and easier replacement.  
  - Many MX8 triggers can be ordered with either system; fixed-trigger guns (MX12, HTS) generally use coil mainsprings.[16][33]
- **Trigger characteristics**:  
  - Simple, robust design with relatively few parts.  
  - Emphasis on large working surfaces and minimal linkages for reliability.[32]  
  - Mechanical triggers (not inertia-dependent) are common in competition builds.  
  - Non-selective triggers (bottom barrel first) are typical for trap; selective triggers are standard or optional on skeet/sporting models.
- **Release triggers**:  
  - Not installed by the factory but often fitted by specialist gunsmiths for trap shooters.  
  - Factory stance: supported by design simplicity but not covered under warranty if modified.', null, '3.3.3 Triggers and Lockwork', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Technical Design and Manufacturing > 3.3.3 Triggers and Lockwork', '["3-3-3-triggers-and-lockwork","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-3-technical-design-and-manufacturing-3-3-3-triggers-and-lockwork"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('65b73913-c421-4ca3-8e78-6eaa093c7766', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '31', '32', '- **1. High-Level Overview** – Scope and goals of Part I of the handbook.  
- **2. Key Concepts & Glossary** – Definitions for core entities, shotgun design concepts, and production terms.  
- **3.1 Perazzi’s Competition Shotguns and Their Heritage** – Origins, mission, competitive breakthrough, and customization philosophy.  
- **3.2 Architectural Hallmarks and Brand Positioning** – Core mechanical design traits and comparisons vs. mass-market and English best-gun makers.  
- **3.3 End-to-End Production Process Map** – Step-by-step flow from design and machining through fitting, finishing, testing, and final sign-off.  
- **4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats** – Important contextual notes and limitations.  
- **5. References & Cross-Links** – Internal navigation and preserved reference markers from the original text.', null, 'Appendix A. Section Index', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > Appendix A. Section Index', '["appendix-a-section-index","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-appendix-a-section-index"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('666fb0d7-5ad7-4de6-b9e0-8134f84d0664', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '21', '45', '- **Rust Bluing**  
  - Pros: safe for soft-soldered barrels; produces a beautiful, durable blue-black; low-heat process.  
  - Cons: labor- and time-intensive (multiple cycles over days).

- **Hot Salt Bluing**  
  - Pros: faster; efficient for small, non-soldered parts.  
  - Cons: temperatures high enough to endanger traditional soft solder; not suitable for soldered barrel assemblies.

**Practical approach:**  
- Use **rust bluing** for barrels and any soldered assemblies.  
- Use hot salt bluing selectively for compatible parts when appropriate and when uniformity of appearance can be maintained.', null, '3.4.1 Rust Bluing vs Hot Salt Bluing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Rust Bluing vs Hot Salt Bluing', '["3-4-1-rust-bluing-vs-hot-salt-bluing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-rust-bluing-vs-hot-salt-bluing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('6690fc38-c133-41a4-bf41-69ff73aa6509', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '53', '238', 'Model name: High Tech Lusso | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Lusso | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech Lusso', 'Models > High Tech Lusso', '["model-details","high-tech-lusso","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('66a32d20-a95d-44e1-a662-2a6b92a7d67f', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '30', '48', '- **Try-Gun / Adjustable Stock**  
