- Experienced technicians can work for many hours while maintaining the same standard of precision, taking short, strategic breaks to avoid fatigue-induced errors.', null, '3.7.5 Stamina & Focus', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.5 Stamina & Focus', '["3-7-5-stamina-focus","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-5-stamina-focus"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('685fe318-3d57-49b9-b2a5-9c0f7190dfd7', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '13', '40', '- Understands practical implications of fit metrics:  
  - How small changes in comb height, cast, or pitch impact eye alignment, recoil feel, and mount consistency.  
- Measures and confirms:  
  - Drop using bench or simple fixtures (sight plane reference and vertical measurements).  
  - Cast using straight references along rib and measuring butt offset.  
  - Pitch using simple angle or wall-based methods.  
- Adjusts comb height, cast and toe by controlled wood removal (e.g., shaving one side more than the other).  
- Shapes grip to fit typical or custom hands:  
  - Can subtly adjust grip swell, relief behind trigger guard (e.g., for shorter thumbs), and palm circumference based on spec or experienced judgment.  
  - Ensures trigger reach remains comfortable and aligned.', null, '3.3.3 Ergonomics & Fit to Shooter', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.3 Ergonomics & Fit to Shooter', '["3-3-3-ergonomics-fit-to-shooter","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-3-ergonomics-fit-to-shooter"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('68a657f1-2846-4bf6-9e0f-29e57c0c2276', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '51', '58', '- Any Perazzi drop-out trigger group will **physically fit** into any compatible receiver, but:[32]  
  - Triggers “wear in” with their original receivers; swapping can accelerate wear.  
  - Trigger pull characteristics may change in a different receiver.  
  - Minor generational differences can affect safety and reliability.
- Perazzi’s stance:  
  - Swapping triggers for an **emergency backup** in competition is fine.  
