- Design goals:
  - Enable **rapid replacement** of the entire trigger unit during competitions if a spring or pin fails.
  - Simplify maintenance and cleaning of the lockwork.
- Competitive advantages:
  - Shooters can carry a **spare trigger group** at major events.
  - Repairs can often be done by swapping units rather than disassembling the entire gun.
- Comparison:
  - Only a few high-end brands offer similar systems (e.g., Krieghoff has removable lock plates), but Perazzi’s implementation as a compact trigger-plate module is distinct.', null, '3.1.1 Removable Trigger Group', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations > 3.1.1 Removable Trigger Group', '["3-1-1-removable-trigger-group","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations-3-1-1-removable-trigger-group"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('6b2a1413-9731-4f1f-a561-bbe759c5809b', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '18', '53', '- Helps shooters trust their gun by:  
