> Franco, a senior finisher, inspects a set of barrels after the final rust-bluing cycle. With gloves on, he runs a fingertip along the steel; the glove comes away clean, with no hint of red dust. Satisfied, he wipes a thin coat of oil along the barrels, and the blue deepens into an almost liquid black.  
