- Part I introduces:
  - Bespoke manufacturing and competition focus.
  - Major stages of the build.  
- Treat it as **the map of the territory**, so you can orient yourself before diving into specifics.', null, '3.1.1 Step 1 – Part I: Product & System Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Recommended Reading Order & Strategy > 3.1.1 Step 1 – Part I: Product & System Overview', '["3-1-1-step-1-part-i-product-system-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-3-main-content-3-1-recommended-reading-order-strategy-3-1-1-step-1-part-i-product-system-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('6e547bf1-0fd6-4aed-8bc7-c45bae0c29c1', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '3', '32', '- **Over-Under (O/U)**  
  A shotgun configuration with one barrel stacked above the other.

- **Action / Receiver**  
  The central metal body of the shotgun where the barrels hinge, lock, and where the firing mechanism is housed. Often called the “heart” of the gun.

- **Trigger-Plate Mechanism**  
  A design in which the firing mechanism (sears, hammers, springs) is built on or around a plate that forms the base of the action. Perazzi uses a trigger-plate, coil-spring mechanism influenced by classic British designs.[4]

- **Removable (Drop-Out) Trigger Group**  
  A complete trigger and lockwork assembly that can be removed from the receiver as a self-contained unit. This allows quick swap or maintenance and lets competitors carry a spare trigger assembly to matches.[3]

- **Boss-Style Locking System (Modified)**  
  A low-profile locking geometry inspired by Boss & Co. designs, adapted by Perazzi. Provides a strong, low-action profile with robust engagement between monobloc and receiver.

- **Monobloc Barrel Construction**  
  Barrel construction method in which a single steel breech block (the monobloc) is machined with two chamber holes and locking lugs, and barrel tubes are inserted and attached into this block. Perazzi uses this method for strength, consistency, and simplified regulation (alignment of the two barrels).

- **Regulation (Barrels)**  
  The process of aligning both barrels in an O/U set so their patterns converge correctly to the same point of aim at a specified distance.', null, '2.2 Shotgun & Design Terms', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Shotgun & Design Terms', '["2-2-shotgun-design-terms","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-shotgun-design-terms"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('6e5d0ceb-39af-45d1-b289-7f0ee95f6616', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '30', '38', 'Annabelle has used various shotguns throughout her journey but ultimately committed to Perazzi.

Key equipment details:

- Currently shoots a Perazzi High Tech Sporting model.  
