  - Direct from Assembly & Mechanical QC, with all systems functioning and finishes complete.

- **Test Ammunition**  
  - Standard target loads (e.g., typical shot size and payload for clays).  
  - Additional specific loads if requested by customer (e.g., a brand/load they intend to use).

- **Patterning Facilities**  
  - **Indoor pattern board** (moving steel plate in a long dark room) for controlled-range testing.  
  - **Outdoor test range** behind the facility for longer-range or final verification.

- **Pattern Targets**  
  - Steel pattern plate coated with whitewash or paint, or  
  - Large pattern paper sheets marked with aiming point and reference circles.

- **Support Equipment**  
  - Bench rest or sandbag rest; sometimes a dedicated patterning rig to reduce human aiming error.  
  - Ear and eye protection for the tester.  
  - Marking tools (paint, chalk, pens) and measuring tools (tape measures, rulers).

- **Reference Information**  
  - Customer specifications: desired POI (e.g., 60/40), choke selection, typical discipline.  
  - Internal QC expectations for regulation and pattern behavior.', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('73644889-8bbc-4a98-91e1-02d9e3b216ab', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '17', '51', '- For minor runovers or spacing issues:  
  - Incorporating the deviation into a slightly modified border (e.g., making a border line fractionally thicker).  
  - Sanding out shallow mistakes outside the pattern area when possible.  
- For small chip-outs:  
  - Compressing nearby wood fibers or performing tiny fill-and-recut operations, particularly where wood figure can help disguise repairs.', null, '3.3.7 Problem Correction Techniques', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.7 Problem Correction Techniques', '["3-3-7-problem-correction-techniques","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-7-problem-correction-techniques"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('7376b83f-ae15-40d8-96c3-eb729e307bcd', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '25', '48', '- Heavier machine inletting:  
  - Pros: saves time if perfectly aligned.  
  - Cons: risky if slightly off; wood cannot be added back.

- Minimal inletting:  
  - Pros: more flexible and safer for custom fit; more work later.  
  - Cons: requires more hand chiseling and scraping.

**Practical approach:**  
- Frequently perform partial inletting by machine (e.g., rough central cavity and stock bolt path) and leave final close fit to hand inletting.', null, '3.4.4 Inletting Now vs Later', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Inletting Now vs Later', '["3-4-4-inletting-now-vs-later","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-inletting-now-vs-later"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('738779ee-6f4c-4f80-b775-0d654a9d4e50', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '19', '51', '- Evaluate the gun through the eyes of a client or reviewer:  
