- Machinists may add or adjust minor operations to remove flash or reconcile deviations before critical cuts.  
- In rare cases (e.g., suspected inclusions), forgings are rejected before machining.', null, '4.2 Variations in Forgings', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.2 Variations in Forgings', '["4-2-variations-in-forgings","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-2-variations-in-forgings"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('75290186-c1ef-4951-a690-fdfbbc68c2f6', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '13', '49', '- Knowing how to correct POI issues:

- **Barrel Bending (Small Corrections)**  
    - Using a bending vise to make small horizontal or vertical POI corrections.  
    - Reserved for minor adjustments; more substantial misalignment may require re-regulation.

- **Adjustable Rib Use (Where Present)**  
    - Adjusting rib height at muzzle or other points to move POI up or down.  
    - Setting factory “baseline” positions for standard POI ratios (e.g., 60/40 for certain trap models).

- **Stock & Comb Adjustments**  
    - Using adjustable combs to raise or lower POI, or alter lateral POI via cast.  
    - Understanding approximate relationships: e.g., small comb changes (on the order of fractions of an inch) correspond to several inches of POI shift at 35–40 m.

- Using **iterative testing**:
  - Adjust, re-test, confirm.  
  - Keeping track of changes to avoid overshooting target POI.', null, '3.3.3 Adjustment Methods & POI Tuning', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.3 Adjustment Methods & POI Tuning', '["3-3-3-adjustment-methods-poi-tuning","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-3-adjustment-methods-poi-tuning"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('755f1691-8019-4017-aaf5-4e67de1081db', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '11', '45', '- Reading walnut’s natural **color, density, and figure** to decide:  
  - Whether stain is required to reach a Perazzi-consistent tone.  
  - How much oil and pore filling will be needed to achieve desired depth.  
- Testing stains or oils on **offcuts** when possible to predict behavior.  
- Avoiding blotchiness by:  
  - Using wash coats or conditioners on sensitive wood.  
  - Applying stain evenly and wiping back consistently.', null, '3.3.1 Understanding Wood Grain & Color', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.1 Understanding Wood Grain & Color', '["3-3-1-understanding-wood-grain-color","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-1-understanding-wood-grain-color"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('7595ae18-feb6-4c44-8946-66f28e77300c', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '9', '38', '- **Machined Trigger Components**  
  - Trigger blades.  
  - Sear components (primary sears and any related parts).  
  - Hammers.  
  - Springs (leaf or coil, depending on configuration).  
  - Pins and axles.  
  - Safety slide and barrel selector components.  
  - Trigger housing (for drop-out designs) or the receiver/action (for fixed triggers).

- **Pre-Treated Parts**  
  - Components that have been heat-treated or case-hardened (especially sears and hammers) for wear resistance.  
  - Some parts may be wire-EDM cut (e.g., sear edges) for precision.

- **Specification Data**  
  - Desired trigger pull weights for first and second shots.  
  - Inertia vs mechanical trigger configuration (model- or customer-dependent).  
  - Spring type preferences (leaf vs coil) where options exist.[6]  
  - Any special requests (e.g., heavier pull preferences, release triggers – noted as specialized/possibly aftermarket).

- **Tools and Consumables**  
  - Fine stones, files, and polishing tools.  
  - Trigger pull gauge.  
  - Lubricants and assembly grease or oil.  
  - Thread locker (for screws that must not loosen).  
  - Snap caps / dummy rounds.', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('75a52412-451e-443a-9976-d10b4beb3740', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '47', '51', '- When the customer is present at delivery, final inspector or a delivery specialist may:  
  - Demonstrate basic disassembly and maintenance.  
  - Explain included tools and spare parts.  
  - Reinforce best practices (storage, oiling, what not to do).', null, '4.4 Customer Presence at Final Handover', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.4 Customer Presence at Final Handover', '["4-4-customer-presence-at-final-handover","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-4-customer-presence-at-final-handover"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('75db7211-6fea-4e79-9e3d-5540d5a70053', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '68', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 2020 | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S 2020', 'Models > High Tech S 2020', '["model-details","high-tech-s-2020","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('7605c78e-9fb5-4d89-adca-c5b690a4d59b', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '8', '45', 'A metal finisher’s work is successful when:

- **Surface Preparation**  
  - All machining marks, scratches, and unevenness are removed from visible surfaces.  
  - Flats remain flat; curves remain true; no “dishing” around screw holes or lettering.  
  - Engraving is preserved with crisp edges; no “washed out” details.

- **Edge Treatment**  
  - Design edges remain crisp where intended (e.g., receiver-to-wood lines).  
  - Dangerous or handling edges are subtly broken without altering design language.

- **Finish Quality & Uniformity**  
  - Bluing (rust or hot) is even in color and depth, with no streaks, spots, or mottling.  
  - Matching parts (e.g., barrels and receiver if both blued) share the same tone unless intentionally contrasted.  
  - Case colors or coin finishes appear uniform and coherent across the receiver.  
  - Plated parts exhibit uniform coverage with no flaking, bare patches, or visible buildup.

- **Functional Integrity**  
  - Polishing has not changed critical geometries such as locking surfaces or hinge pins beyond tolerance.  
  - Soldered ribs remain solid; no loosening due to inappropriate heat.  
  - All markings (serial numbers, proof marks) remain legible and unblurred.

- **Cleanliness & Protection**  
  - Parts are free of residual polishing compound or contaminants.  
  - Freshly finished metal is oiled or otherwise protected so fingerprints and moisture do not etch marks into the finish.

When assembled, the gun should display **matching, flawless metalwork** that passes both visual inspection and functional tests.

---', null, '3.1.2 Success Criteria', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.2 Success Criteria', '["3-1-2-success-criteria","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-2-success-criteria"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('7652b1d2-f2e7-4986-8016-b6e622dda497', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '29', '32', '- Many orders arrive through dealers rather than directly from shooters.  
- Information can be compressed or altered when transmitted.

**Caveats:**

- Ambiguous or incomplete dealer orders must be clarified before finalizing specs.  
