- Reuters – London 2012 trap event report (mentions Al-Deehani’s Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:134]{index=134}', null, '### Fehaid Al-Deehani', 'Olympic Medals > Fehaid Al-Deehani', '["olympic-medals","fehaid-al-deehani"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('79ee2e73-6efe-4b40-b430-b14ad855f98f', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '227', '238', 'Model name: MX8 SCO Sideplates | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: SCO Sideplates | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX8 SCO Sideplates', 'Models > MX8 SCO Sideplates', '["model-details","mx8-sco-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('7a10dff4-d1fb-4004-a3df-f58e9f624aaa', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '7', '45', 'The **Metal Finishing & Bluing station** serves to:

- **Protect steel** against corrosion with bluing or alternative finishes.  
- **Enhance aesthetics** by creating smooth, visually coherent surfaces that complement wood finish and engraving.  
- **Preserve functional geometry** by avoiding over-polishing or finish buildup on critical fit surfaces.

This is one of the final operations on metal before final assembly; it defines much of the gun’s **visual and tactile character**.', null, '3.1.1 Purpose', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.1 Purpose', '["3-1-1-purpose","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-1-purpose"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('7a4ed5c2-cbf5-4b56-8b5a-a962c73bfcf2', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '36', '38', '- **Upstream:**  
  - **Design & Specification Station (Product Engineering)** – defines overall trigger type (inertia vs mechanical), pull weight targets, spring type choices, and safety/selector requirements.  
  - **Action & Receiver Machining Station** – provides the structural receiver geometry, pin hole locations, and surfaces that the trigger group interfaces with.

- **Lateral:**  
  - **Barrel Fabrication & Regulation Station** – while largely independent mechanically, interacts indirectly via second-shot behavior (e.g., load choice and recoil characteristics for inertia triggers).

- **Downstream:**  
  - **Stockmaking & Fitting Station** – integrates trigger reach and blade shape with hand position and stock dimensions.  
  - **Final Assembly & Test** – verifies the trigger group’s behavior under full-system conditions with barrels, stock, and live ammunition.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With the trigger and lockwork tuned to perfection, the action can now strike primers with precision. The barrels are complete, the action is machined, and the firing mechanism is alive. The next crucial element is the **woodwork: stock and fore-end**, which determine how the gun mounts, feels, and ultimately connects the shooter to the mechanical system.

---', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('7a72963d-4c70-4921-8b74-f0072a258f0a', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '4', '38', '- **Inertia Trigger**  
  - System where recoil from the first shot resets/arms the second sear.  
  - Simple and reliable but can be sensitive to very light loads that do not generate enough recoil to reset.

- **Mechanical Trigger**  
  - System where the second sear is reset by mechanical linkage instead of requiring recoil.  
  - More tolerant of very light loads or dry-fire; more complex mechanically.

- **Single vs Double Trigger**  
  - **Single Trigger** – One trigger fires both barrels sequentially; often with selector to choose firing order.  
  - **Double Trigger** – Two separate triggers, typically front then rear for first and second barrel; simpler mechanism with direct choice of barrel via trigger selection.

- **Release Trigger**  
  - Specialized trigger that fires when released rather than when pulled (particularly used in trap).  
  - More complex to design safely; often treated as a specialized case and sometimes aftermarket. (Mentioned as a specialized niche; not standard.)', null, '2.3 Trigger System Types', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Trigger System Types', '["2-3-trigger-system-types","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-trigger-system-types"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('7a8334c2-99be-4e14-bf44-80f2602a7ea0', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '25', '45', '- **Nickel-Plated Actions**  
  - Pros: high corrosion resistance; bright silver appearance.  
  - Cons: plating must be thin and well-adhered to preserve engraving and fit.

- **Gold-Plated Parts (e.g., Trigger Blades)**  
  - Pros: visual differentiation and perceived luxury.  
  - Cons: wear-prone; may require periodic re-plating after long use.

**Practical approach:**  
- Use plating sparingly and with careful pre-polish; ensure plating thickness does not interfere with assembly or operation.', null, '3.4.5 Plating & Decorative Details', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.5 Plating & Decorative Details', '["3-4-5-plating-decorative-details","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-5-plating-decorative-details"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('7acb5ed5-9f81-4a1c-bf8d-86e28de0b21c', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '22', '51', '- When a potential conflict arises:  
  - **Function and safety** override cosmetic considerations.  
  - Example: if making a lock‑up slightly tighter improves longevity but shifts top lever position, inspector evaluates whether cosmetic change is acceptable for functional benefit.  
- Typically, major functional adjustments occur earlier, but final inspector still weighs trade-offs when minor tweaks are considered.', null, '3.4.3 Functional vs Cosmetic Priorities', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Functional vs Cosmetic Priorities', '["3-4-3-functional-vs-cosmetic-priorities","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-functional-vs-cosmetic-priorities"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('7ae16a7b-5947-45fe-85c2-48ea8aab81e6', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '11', '58', 'All Perazzi shotguns derive from the **MX-style low-profile O/U action**, extended into several families:[16][18]

- **MX Platform (O/U)**  
  - Low-profile receiver; Boss-derived locking; monobloc barrels; interchangeable O/U barrel sets.  
  - Removable-trigger models (e.g. MX8) and fixed-trigger derivatives (e.g. MX12, MX2000S).  
  - Basis for most trap, skeet, sporting, and live-pigeon builds.

- **High Tech Platform (HT / HTS)**  
  - Widened receiver adds 3–4 ounces between the hands for improved balance and recoil management.[18][19]  
  - **High Tech (HT)**: removable trigger; **High Tech S (HTS)**: fixed trigger.  
  - Offered in 12 gauge and scaled small-gauge frames (20/28/.410).

- **TM Platform (Single Barrel)**  
  - Single-barrel trap guns (TM1, TMX, TM9, TM9X).  
  - Designed for ATA singles/handicap and similar disciplines.  
  - Typically fixed triggers with high combs and specialized ribs.

- **DC Platform**  
  - Emphasizes detachable trigger groups using coil mainsprings for rugged, high-volume use.

- **SHO Platform (Sidelock)**  
  - Sidelock designs with removable triggers; more aligned with traditional high-art gunmaking.

The core philosophy: **one fundamental action geometry**, many configurations tuned to discipline, gauge, balance, and aesthetic preferences.', null, '3.2.1 Platform Overview', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Product Platform Architecture > 3.2.1 Platform Overview', '["3-2-1-platform-overview","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-2-product-platform-architecture-3-2-1-platform-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('7b21bcf4-345f-4c35-8416-f31036865a30', '00375281-8620-478a-9e59-8b575d31fb83', '0', '1', '- **Pacific Sporting Arms - West**  
