  - Sticky safety.  
  - Slightly off spec trigger pull.  
  - Ejector misbehavior that slipped through earlier tests (rare).

- **Response:**  
  - Route gun back to assembly/mechanical QC for correction.  
  - Repeat relevant tests; then re-submit for final inspection.', null, '3.6.4 Functional Issues Discovered Late', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.4 Functional Issues Discovered Late', '["3-6-4-functional-issues-discovered-late","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-4-functional-issues-discovered-late"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('7f16ccdf-ab5c-40f8-989f-74e0b7f45bab', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '25', '38', 'Keith Ditto is portrayed as a dominant figure in ATA trapshooting, especially in Kentucky.

Key achievements:

- Earned his way to the 27-yard line as a teenager.  
- Completed the ATA Grand Slam in 2008 (200 straight singles, 100 straight doubles, 100 from 27 yards)[81][82].  
- Five-time Kentucky State HOA Champion (2019–2023)[83].  
- Maintained an “incredible” streak of state titles with aggregate scores near perfection (averaging over 1175×1200).  
- In each of those wins, hit well over 97% of all targets thrown.  
- At the 2023 Grand American, posted one of the highest overall averages (2556×2600) in the tournament[84].

Style and persona:

- Shooting style described as fast, aggressive, and confident.  
- Often “hits them faster and harder,” sometimes breaking targets before they peak[85].  
- This style stems from absolute trust in technique and equipment.  
- Known for calm focus at the trap line and for prevailing in epic shoot-offs, including a Kentucky State Singles shoot-off that extended 425 targets beyond the initial 200 straight[86].  
- Outside of competition, he is friendly and unassuming, willing to help newcomers.', null, '3.2.3.1 Biography & Background', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Supported Shooters > 3.2.3 Keith Ditto – American Trap (Supported Shooter) > 3.2.3.1 Biography & Background', '["3-2-3-1-biography-background","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-2-supported-shooters-3-2-3-keith-ditto-american-trap-supported-shooter-3-2-3-1-biography-background"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('7f25527b-0d42-45ad-8baf-ecc2e478442c', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '13', '53', '- Uses bending jigs safely to make **small changes** in cast or drop by heating the wrist and applying controlled pressure.  
- Understands wood behavior:  
  - Spring-back after bending.  
  - Grain direction and how it affects bending limits.  
- Knows approximate limits for safe bending (small millimeter‑level changes) and when bending becomes too risky for a finished stock.  
- Chooses alternatives (e.g., relying on adjustable comb, or more conservative changes) when bending risk outweighs benefit.', null, '3.3.3 Bending & Modification Skills', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.3 Bending & Modification Skills', '["3-3-3-bending-modification-skills","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-3-bending-modification-skills"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('7f47edb2-b89d-4e97-9572-b6ce17741cc0', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '32', '58', '1. **Choose platform and discipline**
   - Decide between MX, High Tech, TM, DC, or SHO.  
   - Choose intended use: trap, skeet, sporting clays, live pigeon, game, etc.[16]

2. **Select gauge and frame**
   - Common: 12 gauge.  
   - Optional: 20, 28, .410 – either on a **scaled frame** or as sub-gauge barrels for a 12-gauge frame.[27][31]

3. **Specify barrels**[27][28][70][71][72]
   - Length (e.g. 75, 78, 80 cm / 29.5", 30.75", 31.5").  
   - Barrel weight and profile (for desired balance).  
   - Chamber length (70mm or 76mm).  
   - Chokes: fixed constrictions or multi-choke system.  
   - Rib style: flat, semi-high, high, extra-high; adjustable vs fixed; rib width and surface; bead options.  
   - Side ribs: solid, ventilated, or deleted.

4. **Define stock and forend**[75][76][77][78][79][80]
   - Stock dimensions: drop at comb/heel, length of pull, cast, toe, pitch.  
   - Stock style: Monte Carlo, parallel comb, field-style, or game-specific shapes.  
   - Adjustable comb: optional hardware for vertical adjustment and fine tuning.  
   - Grip type: standard pistol, palm swell, or **glove grip** sculpted to the shooter’s hand.  
   - Forend style: slim beavertail, wide beavertail (trap), Schnabel, or rounded field forend.

5. **Choose wood grade and finish**[81][82][83][84][85]
   - Wood grades: standard (Grade 1), **SC2**, **SC3**, **SCO** (exhibition).  
   - Higher grades add visually striking figure and cost.  
   - Finish: oil, lacquer, or unfinished (for local finishing).  
   - Butt treatment: rubber recoil pad, leather-covered pad, or checkered wood butt.

6. **Select aesthetics and personalization**[86][87][88][89][90]
   - Receiver finish: blued or nickel/coin.  
   - Engraving pattern: from minimal scroll to SC3/SCO and custom commissions.  
   - Gold inlays, sideplates, personal monograms or crests.  
   - Colored logo lettering, flag inlays on High Tech receivers.  
   - Trigger blade shape and finish.

7. **Finalize and submit order**
   - Typically through an authorized dealer who helps optimize the configuration.[91]
   - Factory builds the gun to spec, then (optionally) the customer visits for fitting.', null, '3.6.2 Configuration Steps (High-Level)', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Customization and Ordering Process > 3.6.2 Configuration Steps (High-Level)', '["3-6-2-configuration-steps-high-level","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-6-customization-and-ordering-process-3-6-2-configuration-steps-high-level"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('7f4a73af-97f8-47b5-a7b3-7589d95a99da', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '22', '26', '- Confidence that:
  - The gun will remain meaningful and supportable over time.
  - The brand will still be there for **service, parts, and knowledge**.
- A story they can tell:
  - About why they chose this gun.
  - About what it meant in their life and shooting.', null, '3.5.3 What They Are Seeking', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.5 Legacy > 3.5.3 What They Are Seeking', '["3-5-3-what-they-are-seeking","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-5-legacy-3-5-3-what-they-are-seeking"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('7f51f6ba-923b-4c3f-b405-55533828f87e', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '102', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S SC3 | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S SC3', 'Models > High Tech S SC3', '["model-details","high-tech-s-sc3","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('7f571358-ac44-4efd-a6d8-00a0cee0a7d9', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '28', '58', '1. **Exclusivity & Prestige**[56]
   - Low-volume, high-quality production (~1,500 guns/year).  
   - Each gun is effectively custom-built, positioning ownership as entry into a selective community.  
   - Marketing focuses on selective sponsorships and presence at prestige events rather than mass-market saturation.

2. **Craftsmanship as Art**[57]
   - Guns are presented as functional art pieces: hand-fitted mechanics, high-grade walnut, and deep engraving.  
   - Options range from simple scroll to full-coverage game scenes with gold inlay.  
   - Perazzi highlights its artisans and maintains continuity of traditional skills.

3. **Emotional Connection & Storytelling**[53][58][59]
   - Ownership is framed as the culmination of a dream and an emotional journey.  
   - Marketing showcases champions and aspirants whose lives and identities are intertwined with their Perazzi.  
   - **The Champions Network (TCN)** is a structured storytelling strategy featuring long-form narratives and interviews.

4. **Mastery & Transformation**[62][63]
   - Perazzi positions itself as a catalyst for personal transformation: choosing a Perazzi signifies commitment to excellence and legacy.  
   - Taglines emphasize that a Perazzi is something you **earn**, not simply buy.  
   - Owning a Perazzi is described as joining an enduring lineage of champions.', null, '3.5.1 Core Brand Values', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Brand Philosophy and Ethos > 3.5.1 Core Brand Values', '["3-5-1-core-brand-values","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-5-brand-philosophy-and-ethos-3-5-1-core-brand-values"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('7f5cd8a9-f504-4fc0-823a-29f285ab1194', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '12', '238', 'Model name: High Tech | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech', 'Models > High Tech', '["model-details","high-tech","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('7f9c42b3-2553-43a2-8df1-d5eae6897902', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '28', '51', '- **Inspector’s Mark / Signature**  
