  - **Barrel Fabrication & Regulation (Part II.C)** – provides regulated barrel sets; pattern testing confirms their performance in the assembled gun.  
  - **Assembly & Mechanical QC (Part II.J)** – ensures mechanical reliability under dry tests; patterning verifies live-fire behavior.  
  - **Stock Inletting, Checkering, and Wood Finishing (Parts II.F–II.I)** – determine fit and feel; pattern testing helps finalize POI relative to the shooter.

- **Downstream / Related:**  
  - **Final Fitting & Customer-Specific Adjustments (Part III – Final Fit & Handover, conceptual)** – uses patterning results to fine-tune fit in the shooter’s hands.  
  - **Final Proof & Sign-Off** – after patterning and adjustments, the gun is ready for final administrative checks and delivery.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With patterning and performance testing complete—and any final POI adjustments made—the gun has proven itself both mechanically and ballistically. The next stages focus on **final fitting, customer handover, and long-term ownership considerations**, completing the journey from raw materials to a finished Perazzi shotgun.

