---', null, '3.5.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Legacy-Oriented Users', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.5 Legacy > 3.5.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Legacy-Oriented Users', '["3-5-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-legacy-oriented-users","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-5-legacy-3-5-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-legacy-oriented-users"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('82fc72fc-5e61-4cb9-ae51-b2ae11c72717', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '17', '32', '- **Goal**  
  Choose the ideal **walnut stock blank** and shape it roughly to the gun’s configuration and the customer’s dimensions.

- **Inputs**  
  - Dried walnut blank of the chosen **grade**.  
  - Stock design measurements (length of pull, cast, drop, grip style).  
  - Duplicating machine or CNC program for initial shaping.

- **Outputs**  
  - Rough-cut stock and matching fore-end wood with:
    - Excess material left for fine fitting.  
    - Approximate dimensions achieved (including cast, comb height, grip shape).

- **Owned by**  
  **Stock maker / stock inlet specialist** (often also involved in fitting).

---', null, '3.3.6 Stock Blank Selection & Rough Shaping', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.3 End-to-End Production Process Map > 3.3.6 Stock Blank Selection & Rough Shaping', '["3-3-6-stock-blank-selection-rough-shaping","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-3-end-to-end-production-process-map-3-3-6-stock-blank-selection-rough-shaping"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('8301cc8b-8b14-4216-8bf9-fbb70c94dd52', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '22', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 3 Palladium | Base model: high-tech-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 Palladium | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech 2020 3 Palladium', 'Models > High Tech 2020 3 Palladium', '["model-details","high-tech-2020-3-palladium","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('83b58c81-4801-4f96-b823-814aacd86388', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '24', '32', '> **Example (vignette, based on reported practices; speculative details noted as such):**
>
> Early morning in Botticino, the head of product design is at his bench, surrounded by measuring tools and previous day’s target sheets. A world champion shooter has flown in for a custom fitting. Through a translator, they discuss her recent performances. She mentions struggling with second targets in doubles because the gun lifts too much after the first shot.
>
> Instead of immediately suggesting recoil pads or barrel porting, the Perazzi specialist suspects a fit and pitch issue. Using a try-gun, he adjusts the **pitch angle** slightly and has her fire at the pattern plate. He sees a clear reduction in muzzle jump with the new setting.
>
> Based on this, he quietly decides that the final gun will have **approximately two degrees more pitch** and **a small increase in stock weight (around 10 grams)** to further calm the gun. These tweaks may never appear as explicit customer requests; they are added by the master’s judgment.
>
> Months later, when the shooter receives the finished gun, she may simply experience that the second target feels easier and more controlled. The seemingly minor design decisions made during this session were the keys to unlocking that performance.

This kind of invisible optimization—embedding the engineer’s experience into the specification—is the hallmark of mastery at this station.

