---', null, '3.2.2 Outputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.2 Outputs', '["3-2-2-outputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-2-outputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('84196ac6-d1de-486a-ba3a-9c0deeda38b5', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '31', '38', 'Amber English is described as the embodiment of Olympic poise and performance in international skeet.

Key achievements:

- Olympic Gold Medal in Women’s Skeet at the Tokyo 2020 Games (held in 2021).  
- Record-setting finals performance: hit 56/60, an Olympic Finals record for women’s skeet[103].  
- After narrowly missing the 2012 and 2016 U.S. Olympic teams, she persisted and ultimately triumphed in Tokyo.  
- First Lieutenant in the U.S. Army and member of the Army Marksmanship Unit.

Additional accolades:

- Multiple ISSF World Cup medals.  
- 2018 World Championship bronze medal[104].  
- 2023 Pan American Games gold (Mixed Team Skeet)[72].

Amber grew up in a family of shooters in Colorado, was winning national titles by her early 20s, and competed alongside other elite U.S. women’s skeet shooters. She balanced college, Army service, and demanding training, forging a character that combines authenticity and resilience. She openly paid tribute to her late father (her coach) after her Olympic gold and displayed strong sportsmanship with competitors.', null, '3.2.6.1 Biography & Background', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Supported Shooters > 3.2.6 Amber English – International Skeet (Supported Shooter) > 3.2.6.1 Biography & Background', '["3-2-6-1-biography-background","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-2-supported-shooters-3-2-6-amber-english-international-skeet-supported-shooter-3-2-6-1-biography-background"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('8422c4a8-3fc3-49da-8c47-97630921c864', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '20', '51', '- **Rework Bias:**  
  - For high-end guns, the default bias is toward **fixing any visible defect**, even if small.  
- **Trade-Off:**  
  - Sometimes tiny, nearly invisible marks (e.g., on undersides unlikely to be seen) may be accepted if rework would introduce more risk or if the mark will inevitably arise in first use.  
- Inspectors lean heavily toward perfection but use judgment in truly trivial cases.', null, '3.4.1 Cosmetic Perfection vs Risk of Rework', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Cosmetic Perfection vs Risk of Rework', '["3-4-1-cosmetic-perfection-vs-risk-of-rework","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-cosmetic-perfection-vs-risk-of-rework"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('8427b1a5-5465-491b-8f82-3bf16dab2d37', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '20', '38', '- **Trigger Pull Gauge**  
  - Mechanical or digital; measures pull weight to fine resolution (e.g., ±0.1–0.2 lbs).  
  - Used to verify both barrels’ pull weights.

- **Snap Caps / Dummy Rounds**  
  - Test firing pin strike depth and centering without live ammunition.

- **Firing Pin Protrusion Check**  
  - Though largely set by action design, hammer fall and linkages must deliver sufficient strike.  
  - Visual or gauged checks ensure adequate firing pin protrusion.

- **Safety and Jar Test Methods**  
  - Manual tests:  
    - Attempting to pull trigger with safety engaged.  
    - Bumping or striking the action/stock (often with a soft mallet) to simulate recoil or impact while cocked.', null, '3.5.2 Measurement & Test Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.2 Measurement & Test Tools', '["3-5-2-measurement-test-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-2-measurement-test-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('84611e31-fcee-46e8-90ec-67640f4c3b13', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '212', '238', 'Model name: MX8 SC3 | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX8 SC3', 'Models > MX8 SC3', '["model-details","mx8-sc3","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('8496c252-1ea8-44fe-bb4d-1c470b204eb1', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '39', '48', '> **Example vignette (composite, illustrative):**  
> A customer visits the wood room to choose a blank. The master stockmaker listens: “I like darker wood with strong marblecake figure, but I shoot heavy loads and don’t want it to crack.” From a wall of blanks, he pulls three candidates within minutes. To reveal the finished look, he lightly wets a section with alcohol or mineral spirits; the figure “pops” into view. The customer points to one, and the master nods—it is the same one he would have chosen. Later, as he lays out the pattern, he angles the stock so grain runs cleanly through the wrist while still placing the most dramatic figure across the butt and comb. The customer eventually shoulders the rough stock and feels it already sits correctly; the wood looks exactly as imagined. This ability to bridge customer preference, structural needs, and long-term experience is the hallmark of mastery at this station.

---', null, '3.7.6 Example Vignette: Matching Person to Wood', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.6 Example Vignette: Matching Person to Wood', '["3-7-6-example-vignette-matching-person-to-wood","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-6-example-vignette-matching-person-to-wood"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('8498badc-6be4-4c62-b1c0-18a4ac2f5d89', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '10', '38', '- **Assembled Trigger Mechanism**  
  - Removable trigger group (MX-style drop-out unit) or fixed trigger assembly built into the receiver.  
  - Fully installed safety and barrel selector.

- **Functional and Tuned System**  
  - Trigger pull weights documented (e.g., “3.5 / 3.75 lbs”).  
  - Verified function of first and second shots in both selector positions (where applicable).  
  - Safety and jar-off tests passed.

- **QC Records and Markings**  
  - Internal notes on trigger weights and configuration (e.g., leaf vs coil).  
  - Possible internal identifier marks for variants (e.g., notation if leaf springs used, or color-coded springs).

These outputs feed into final assembly and test, where the trigger group is integrated with the completed action, barrels, and stock.

