- Dislikes guesses and hand-waving; values **transparent trade-offs**.', null, '3.3.1 Core Motivation', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.3 Analyst > 3.3.1 Core Motivation', '["3-3-1-core-motivation","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-3-analyst-3-3-1-core-motivation"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('852c1b1d-5315-4a18-882f-96b31cc55d00', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '54', '56', '- **Upstream Stations (Conceptual Links):**  
  - **Design & Specification (Part II.A)** – defines mechanical and performance targets that assembly must achieve.  
  - **Action & Receiver Machining (Part II.B)** – determines underlying geometry for lock-up and internal fit.  
  - **Barrel Fabrication & Regulation (Part II.C)** – ensures barrels are safe and regulated; assembly confirms they integrate correctly.  
  - **Trigger Group & Lockwork Assembly (Part II.D)** – supplies tuned trigger mechanisms that must function correctly in assembled form.  
  - **Stock Selection, Shaping, Inletting, and Finishing (Parts II.E–II.I)** – provide fitted woodwork that must remain structurally sound after assembly.

- **Downstream / Related Sections:**  
  - **Pattern Testing & Regulation Confirmation (Part III – Patterning & Final Fit, conceptual)** – uses fully assembled gun to confirm POI and performance.  
  - **Customer Fitting & Handover (Part III)** – where fit and feel are finalized with the shooter, building on a mechanically sound platform.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With assembly and mechanical QC complete, the gun is now a **fully functional, finished shotgun**. The next phases of the handbook (Part III) focus on **pattern testing, final fit adjustments, and customer-facing aspects** that validate and personalize all the work done in the factory.

