- **Spring choices & High Tech vs MX context** – see Part III and Part IV.[4][8][9][15]', null, '5.1 Internal Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 5. References & Cross-Links > 5.1 Internal Cross-Links', '["5-1-internal-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-5-references-cross-links-5-1-internal-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('885a5b9e-0654-4a04-aa1e-c7c234619b2f', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '21', '39', '- Perazzi’s hand-rubbed oil finishes and hand-cut checkering are consistent with best-gun standards:
  - Multiple layers of oil built up over time.
  - At least ~20 LPI checkering, sometimes finer on high-art guns.
- Shared approach:
  - Italian and British stockers both:
    - Shape stocks to functional forms (e.g., Monte Carlo for trap).
    - Use oil finishes for depth and repairability.
- Adjustable features:
  - Adjustable combs and buttplates are now common across competition shotguns, not unique to Perazzi.
  - Reflects industry-wide adaptation to shooter needs.', null, '3.2.5 Oil Finishing and Stock Craft', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices > 3.2.5 Oil Finishing and Stock Craft', '["3-2-5-oil-finishing-and-stock-craft","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices-3-2-5-oil-finishing-and-stock-craft"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('88750543-a1c6-4098-864f-0310f553f074', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '18', '45', '- Understanding the chemistry of chosen finishes:  
  - Oil polymerization and the role of driers.  
  - Solvent systems and cure mechanisms for poly/varnish.

- Diagnosing and correcting issues:  
  - Slow-drying or tacky coats (too thick, low temperature, or old mixture).  
  - Cloudiness from trapped moisture.  
  - Remedying by thinning, increasing warmth/ventilation, or stripping and re-applying when necessary.', null, '3.3.8 Chemical Knowledge & Troubleshooting', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.8 Chemical Knowledge & Troubleshooting', '["3-3-8-chemical-knowledge-troubleshooting","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-8-chemical-knowledge-troubleshooting"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('8898d728-f62d-4016-bd02-982c51fd9050', '4ae532ea-bef9-47fe-9bd9-051858902e2f', '13', '23', 'This subsection provides **conceptual diagrams** you can hold in your head (or sketch) to organize knowledge.', null, '3.3 Mental Models & Diagrams', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Mental Models & Diagrams', '["3-3-mental-models-diagrams","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-3-main-content-3-3-mental-models-diagrams"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('88d4efc8-96b6-4a38-848d-326e641ef084', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '50', '51', '- **1. High-Level Overview** – Scope and purpose of the Final Inspection, Proof Marks & Sign-Off station.  
