- **5. References & Cross-Links** – Relationships to upstream QC, patterning, fitting, and downstream shipping/warranty systems.', null, 'Appendix A. Section Index', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > Appendix A. Section Index', '["appendix-a-section-index","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-appendix-a-section-index"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('89c2bb0f-7ba6-4b95-b9b4-b1d148fa8ae2', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '204', '238', 'Model name: MX410 SCO Gold | Base model: mx410 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 410ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX410 SCO Gold', 'Models > MX410 SCO Gold', '["model-details","mx410-sco-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('89f465e6-fc70-4a25-98ab-c187254d99ad', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '40', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - New scratches on metal or wood; marred screw slots.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Visual inspection under strong light.  
  - Lightly re-polish and re-blue tiny marks (e.g., screw head), or perform spot wood repairs where possible.  
  - Replace visibly damaged parts if necessary.', null, '3.6.10 Cosmetic Scuffs & Handling Damage', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.10 Cosmetic Scuffs & Handling Damage', '["3-6-10-cosmetic-scuffs-handling-damage","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-10-cosmetic-scuffs-handling-damage"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('8a8137e5-1300-4ab1-a07f-206630e15da5', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '32', '49', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Gun patterns at 50/50 when built for 70/30 high (or vice versa).

- **Diagnosis:**  
  - Compare patterns and ratios (above/below aim point) to customer spec.

- **Remedies:**  
  - Adjust **comb height** or **adjustable rib** to raise/lower POI.  
  - For fixed configurations, consider stock bending or modifying comb height.', null, '3.6.3 POI Mismatch vs Intended Use', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.3 POI Mismatch vs Intended Use', '["3-6-3-poi-mismatch-vs-intended-use","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-3-poi-mismatch-vs-intended-use"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('8a9604b4-f641-4432-96f1-81a52dd565e8', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '58', '238', 'Model name: High Tech Platinum | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: Platinum | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech Platinum', 'Models > High Tech Platinum', '["model-details","high-tech-platinum","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('8a99808a-5d1a-45d3-aa08-8c6c3f5e962c', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '2', '40', '- **Stock Inletting & Final Shaping Station (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Stock Fitting*, *Stock Inletting Bench*, *Final Stock Shaping*.  
  - Definition: Station where rough stock and fore-end are precisely fitted to the metalwork and sculpted to final external form and dimensions.

- **Stock Fitter / Stockmaker (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Stock Inletter*, *Shaper*, *Stock Craftsman/Craftswoman*.  
  - Definition: Craftsperson responsible for hand inletting, external shaping, ergonomic tuning, and pre-finishing of wood furniture.', null, '2.1 Roles and Station', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Station', '["2-1-roles-and-station","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-station"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('8adb32fd-e19f-4043-aa1a-bdddf5588d77', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '9', '32', 'Compared to high-volume, mass-market shotgun manufacturers:

- **Tolerances and Finishing**
  - Perazzi parts are **not** metal-injection-molded or cheaply cast.
  - Every component is **machined from quality steel**.
  - Parts are **hand-fitted** by skilled gunsmiths.
  - A factory tour shows craftspeople:
    - Filing, stoning, and sanding interfaces to achieve **exact fit**.
    - Checking alignment and function repeatedly.

- **Production Philosophy**
  - Mass-market plants:
    - Focus on **large-volume, identical units** with minimal human fitting.
    - Use high-speed assembly lines and more automation to reduce cost.
  - Perazzi:
    - Maintains **low volume** to preserve individual attention.
    - Accepts higher costs to achieve **precise mechanical integration**.

The result: Perazzi guns feel **tighter, smoother, and more bespoke** than mass-market alternatives, and are designed to be **rebuilt and maintained** over very long service lives.', null, '3.2.2 Perazzi vs. Mass-Market Shotguns', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Architectural Hallmarks and Brand Positioning > 3.2.2 Perazzi vs. Mass-Market Shotguns', '["3-2-2-perazzi-vs-mass-market-shotguns","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-2-architectural-hallmarks-and-brand-positioning-3-2-2-perazzi-vs-mass-market-shotguns"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('8b3e5b5d-e28a-450c-92b6-fb3dbaa77c92', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '32', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - First barrel fires; second does not, or trigger dead for second shot.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Inertia trigger: insufficient recoil to move inertia block (e.g., very light loads or too stiff inertia spring).  
  - Mechanical trigger: mis-timed selector or linkage.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Simulate recoil with mallet or sharp motion; test with different loads.  
  - Adjust inertia block mass/spring tension or mechanical linkage until second shot is reliable under realistic conditions.', null, '3.6.2 Failure to Fire Second Barrel', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.2 Failure to Fire Second Barrel', '["3-6-2-failure-to-fire-second-barrel","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-2-failure-to-fire-second-barrel"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('8c26f2df-c7bc-4416-9207-19928e98af41', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '121', '238', 'Model name: High Tech SCO Gold | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech SCO Gold', 'Models > High Tech SCO Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-sco-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('8c400be8-7994-4f99-be70-ab3eb244a502', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '16', '38', '- **Adjustable Trigger Shoe**  
  - Used to fine-tune reach for different hand sizes and stock lengths.  
  - Often placed in a neutral position by default if no specific request exists.

- **Blade Shape**  
  - Wider blades for comfort in high-volume competition shooting.  
  - Narrower, more traditional blades for certain field or game applications.

**Practical approach:**

- Choose blade type based on model and explicit customer instructions.  
- Coordinate with stock fitters so trigger position harmonizes with length of pull and grip geometry.', null, '3.4.4 Trigger Blade Position & Shape', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Trigger Blade Position & Shape', '["3-4-4-trigger-blade-position-shape","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-trigger-blade-position-shape"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('8c4f1c71-6b08-4fdd-8450-04cc7bef2f38', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '14', '38', 'David Radulovich is portrayed as synonymous with Perazzi.

Key statements and equipment details:

- He is quoted as saying a Perazzi isn’t just a shotgun, but “the tangible embodiment of my aspirations, dedication, and identity”[37][38].  
- He began his Perazzi journey as a teenager and now relies on a Perazzi High Tech Sporting gun at the highest level (including favored models such as the Perazzi MX12 and High Tech S, customized for his fit).  
- With this shotgun, he won the 2017 World FITASC in Budapest, using Gamebore Black Gold cartridges, and felt the equipment gave him an edge[39][40].  
- His current Perazzi is described as featuring bespoke stock dimensions and balanced 34″ barrels, chosen to match his smooth, methodical style.

The text characterizes David’s Perazzi as an “instrument of precision and quiet power.” When he shoulders it, he is said to embody the Perazzi brand tone – authentic, aspirational, and calmly confident – inviting others to feel excellence alongside him[41][42].

---', null, '3.1.4.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Sponsored Shooters (Perazzi USA Team) > 3.1.4 David Radulovich – Sporting Clays (Sponsored Shooter) > 3.1.4.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', '["3-1-4-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-1-sponsored-shooters-perazzi-usa-team-3-1-4-david-radulovich-sporting-clays-sponsored-shooter-3-1-4-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('8cacf166-18cb-4bd8-884e-84d859059868', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '25', '39', 'Perazzi often allows or encourages buyers to **shoot clays** with their guns on-site:

- Live-target evaluation reveals:
  - How the gun mounts in motion.
  - How it swings and recovers for doubles.
  - Whether target breaks are centered and authoritative (“smoked”).

Feedback loops:

- If a shooter consistently struggles with a second shot on a specific presentation, the fitter can consider:
  - Minor balance adjustments (e.g., adding subtle weight in the stock).
  - Rib or comb tweaks to refine POI.
  - Changes in trigger springs (for feel/lock time) or choke selection.

Because Perazzi guns are relatively **modular** (e.g., drop-out triggers, barrel weights, adjustable combs/ribs), targeted refinements can be made without rebuilding the entire gun.

However, if patterning and fitting are executed correctly, most shooters find **immediate on-range success**.', null, '3.3.4 Live Target Testing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Patterning & On-Range Performance > 3.3.4 Live Target Testing', '["3-3-4-live-target-testing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-3-patterning-on-range-performance-3-3-4-live-target-testing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('8cebb1d1-ca5d-49e2-9128-013d814c5a36', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '30', '38', 'This section consolidates scenarios that require extra care at the trigger station.', null, '4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', '["4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('8cf36dc6-5475-4645-aa29-f47f0e2f45e7', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '1', '39', 'This document compares **Perazzi-specific practices and innovations** with **general high-end gunmaking practices** and clarifies where information about Perazzi remains **proprietary or unknown**.

It is intended to help AI systems:

- Distinguish what is **unique to Perazzi** from what is shared across **other fine shotgun makers**.
- Understand where Perazzi’s design and production choices **depart from typical industry norms**.
- Identify which aspects of the process are **publicly documented** vs. **deliberately opaque or proprietary**.

The document is organized into three main sections:

1. **Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations** – what defines “a Perazzi” mechanically, operationally, and culturally.
2. **Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices** – where Perazzi aligns with the broader best-gun tradition.
3. **Unknowns & Respect for Proprietary Knowledge** – where the public record ends and speculation must stop.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('8d5b344f-faae-4a07-9302-566273edf548', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '46', '48', '- **Upstream:**  
  - **Design & Specification Station (Product Engineering)** – provides fit dimensions, stock style, and aesthetic grade requirements.  
  - **Trigger Group & Lockwork Assembly** – indirectly influences stock geometry (trigger reach, blade position).

- **Lateral:**  
  - **Barrel Fabrication & Regulation** – influences overall gun balance; barrel weight informs desired stock weight and density.

- **Downstream:**  
  - **Stock Inletting & Final Shaping Station** – performs precise metal-to-wood fit and sculpts final stock and fore-end contours.  
  - **Checkering & Finishing Station** – relies on stable, well-prepared surfaces and preserved figure.

- **Narrative Transition:**  
  - With stock and fore-end rough-shaped and oriented correctly in the wood, the next stage in the handbook follows the **inletting and final shaping** process, where wood and metal are married in a seamless fit and the rough block becomes the elegant furniture of a finished Perazzi shotgun.

