- Russell Mark (Top 20 Shotgunners) – Diamond’s continued use of MX8:contentReference[oaicite:32]{index=32}', null, '### Michael Diamond', 'Olympic Medals > Michael Diamond', '["olympic-medals","michael-diamond"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('9352c591-233b-440d-875d-dc773b69b903', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '36', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 3 Platinum | Base model: high-tech-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Platinum | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 3 Platinum', 'Models > High Tech 3 Platinum', '["model-details","high-tech-3-platinum","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('936e90c4-64a0-4ebc-820d-e1e06a9869c7', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '38', '39', '- **1. High-Level Overview** – Scope of cross-cutting systems in Part III.  
- **2. Key Concepts & Glossary** – Quality, fit, patterning, and aesthetic terminology.  
- **3.1 Quality Control & Tolerances** – QC mindset, in-process checks, proof testing, tolerance management, cosmetic QC.  
- **3.2 Fit, Balance & Handling Characteristics** – Stock geometry, fit, balance, recoil behavior, comparative philosophy, adjustability.  
- **3.3 Patterning & On-Range Performance** – Factory pattern tests, choke verification, fit diagnostics, live-target validation, ongoing performance.  
- **3.4 Aesthetics & Identity** – Engraving, wood selection, house style vs expression, legacy, emotional and brand identity cues.  
- **4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats** – Limits and contextual notes about tolerances, comparisons, and customization.  
- **5. References & Cross-Links** – Internal navigation and original reference markers.', null, 'Appendix A. Section Index', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > Appendix A. Section Index', '["appendix-a-section-index","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-appendix-a-section-index"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('939eedab-1e0b-4ac8-b338-a83e353b0473', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '4', '56', '- **Single Trigger with Selector**  
  - One trigger that fires both barrels sequentially; selector chooses which barrel fires first.

- **Inertia Trigger**  
  - Uses recoil from first shot to reset/arm second sear.  
  - Needs sufficient recoil to function reliably.

- **Mechanical Trigger**  
  - Second sear reset mechanically without relying on recoil; more tolerant of very light loads.

- **Doubling**  
  - Undesired discharge of both barrels at once when only one is intended to fire; must be eliminated in QC.

- **Safety**  
  - Manual mechanism that blocks trigger or sear motion.  
  - Some guns may have optional **auto-safety** (engages when gun is opened) depending on model/usage.', null, '2.3 Trigger & Safety Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Trigger & Safety Concepts', '["2-3-trigger-safety-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-trigger-safety-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('93eccc95-5bd8-490e-a627-427831fff88c', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '27', '39', 'Patterning and live performance testing serve as the **final validation** of:

- Precision barrel making.
- Correct stock fit and geometry.
- Effective QC across multiple departments.

A Perazzi that centers its patterns and crushes targets on the range is tangible proof that:

- The barrel maker.
- The action fitter.
- The stock maker.
- The QC inspector.

have all done their work to a high standard.

---', null, '3.3.6 Summary: Patterning as Final Systems Check', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Patterning & On-Range Performance > 3.3.6 Summary: Patterning as Final Systems Check', '["3-3-6-summary-patterning-as-final-systems-check","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-3-patterning-on-range-performance-3-3-6-summary-patterning-as-final-systems-check"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('93f08252-e1ba-4000-9ea3-c4e13360a1c5', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '32', '40', '- Internal inletting surfaces are often **beautifully smooth**, almost like a negative cast of the action, even though they are mostly hidden.  
- Some artisans may discreetly inscribe initials or a small mark in a hidden area (e.g., under buttplate or inside inletting) as a personal signature, unseen by most customers.', null, '3.7.4 Invisible Pride & Signature', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.4 Invisible Pride & Signature', '["3-7-4-invisible-pride-signature","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-4-invisible-pride-signature"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('93f6d9b4-f1d2-418c-a1e5-3621c46f4979', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '46', '51', '- Soft walnut tends to fuzz and tear; hard walnut can cause chatter or rapid tool wear.  
- Checkering technique must be tuned to each blank’s behavior.

**Caveat:**  
- Extra time may be needed to maintain crisp results; final recuts after finishing may be particularly important on softer wood.', null, '4.2 Very Soft or Very Hard Walnut Blanks', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.2 Very Soft or Very Hard Walnut Blanks', '["4-2-very-soft-or-very-hard-walnut-blanks","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-2-very-soft-or-very-hard-walnut-blanks"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('93ff205c-1939-45d7-b325-0b9990dcff20', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '34', '38', '- When adjustable trigger shoes are used, their position must harmonize with stock length and grip shape.  
- Misalignment can cause inconsistent trigger reach or feel.

**Caveat:**  
- Coordination with stockmakers and fitters is important; initial positions may be set conservatively, assuming later fine-tuning during fitting.', null, '4.4 Stock and Trigger Interface (Adjustable Shoes)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.4 Stock and Trigger Interface (Adjustable Shoes)', '["4-4-stock-and-trigger-interface-adjustable-shoes","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-4-stock-and-trigger-interface-adjustable-shoes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('9469e05a-4327-4d55-ba91-cd4708575154', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '28', '51', '- **Lighting & Magnification**  
  - Bright, oblique lighting to cast shadows in grooves.  
  - Optional head-mounted magnifiers for high-LPI or intricate areas.

- **Cleaning Tools**  
  - Small brushes or tack cloth to remove dust from grooves.  
  - Compressed air used carefully to avoid blowing away layout lines.', null, '3.5.3 Vision & Cleanliness', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.3 Vision & Cleanliness', '["3-5-3-vision-cleanliness","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-3-vision-cleanliness"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('94a1d54e-3afb-49b9-8739-c83ee5d5d929', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '15', '38', '- **Leaf Springs**  
  - Pros: extremely crisp feel; minimal lock time; the classic high-performance competition trigger feel.  
  - Cons: higher risk of sudden breakage; failure typically stops the trigger from functioning.

- **Coil Springs**  
  - Pros: very durable and forgiving; can sometimes continue working even if partially compromised.  
  - Cons: may feel less crisp; sometimes tuned lighter to achieve similar subjective feel.

**Practical approach:**

- Honor customer or model specification for spring type.  
- For high-stakes competition use, consider whether shooter will carry spare leaf-spring trigger groups or prefers coil for maximum reliability.  
- Balance lock time and feel against the risk and consequences of spring failure.', null, '3.4.3 Leaf vs Coil Springs[6]', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Leaf vs Coil Springs[6]', '["3-4-3-leaf-vs-coil-springs-6","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-leaf-vs-coil-springs-6"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('94cf47a0-1da0-4a65-b899-31e6b211a2a6', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '1', '45', 'This document describes the **Wood Finishing station** in the Perazzi factory.

At this station, the walnut **stock** and **fore-end** receive their final **surface treatment** (typically an oil or synthetic finish) to:

- Protect the wood from moisture, sweat, and handling.
- Enhance and stabilize the **color, figure, and depth** (“chatoyance”) of the walnut.
- Establish the final **sheen** (from matte to high gloss) and tactile feel.
- Seal and coordinate the transition between **smooth surfaces and checkering**.

The station covers:

- The **purpose** and **success criteria** for wood finishing.
- **Inputs and outputs** (parts, chemicals, tools, environment).
- The **core knowledge and skills** of the wood finisher.
- **Decisions and trade-offs** (oil vs polyurethane, pore filling, sheen level, timing).
- The **tools and measurements** used conceptually.
- Typical **failure modes** and how they are prevented or corrected.
- What **mastery** in wood finishing looks like, including an illustrative vignette.

The goal is wood that looks **alive**, feels **silky but not slick**, and is robust enough for real-world use while remaining serviceable over the gun’s life.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('94f842ef-bc71-4b9a-930d-1391a933c983', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '13', '45', '- Clear mental map of where aggressive polishing must be **avoided or minimized**, such as:  
  - Locking lugs, hooks, and bite surfaces.  
  - Hinge pin bores and bearing faces.  
  - Internal sear, hammer, and trigger surfaces.  
  - Forend iron interfaces.

- Ability to coordinate with fitting and assembly gunsmiths regarding how much polishing is safe on specific surfaces.', null, '3.3.2 Awareness of Critical Surfaces', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Awareness of Critical Surfaces', '["3-3-2-awareness-of-critical-surfaces","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-awareness-of-critical-surfaces"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('95ae23f1-5bf2-4a90-9863-909aa837f1a9', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '21', '36', '- Rather than straightforward advertisements, Perazzi builds **immersive storytelling arcs**.  
- The aim is for the audience to **feel, internalize, and live** the Perazzi experience.  
- Campaigns are designed as **emotional universes** the customer steps into, rather than one-off impressions.', null, '3.5.2 Narrative Over Visibility', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Strategic Brand Themes > 3.5.2 Narrative Over Visibility', '["3-5-2-narrative-over-visibility","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-5-strategic-brand-themes-3-5-2-narrative-over-visibility"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('95bb31e1-c0a2-4628-852f-3eb524db077d', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '51', '56', '- Converting inertia triggers to mechanical, changing ejector behavior, or altering balance after delivery can involve revisiting assembly/QC considerations.

**Caveat:**  
