- USA Shooting Hall of Fame (context on Carlisle’s gear, indirectly confirming Perazzi use):contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}', null, '### Daniel Carlisle', 'Olympic Medals > Daniel Carlisle', '["olympic-medals","daniel-carlisle"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('9d338d4c-41d3-453c-b139-4c32e071ee3e', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '25', '40', '- **Rulers & Tapes**  
  - For LOP and general linear dimensions.

- **Drop & Cast Gauges**  
  - May be simple references:  
    - Straightedge along rib + ruler to comb/heel for drop.  
    - Straightedge + lateral measurements at butt for cast.

- **Pitch Measuring Methods**  
  - Protractor-based or practical methods (e.g., measuring differences between top/bottom of butt against a vertical reference).

- **Torque Tools**  
  - Screwdrivers or Allen keys with awareness of appropriate force to tighten draw bolts without over-stressing wood.

- **Lighting & Magnification**  
  - Good lighting, possible use of magnifiers or mirrors to inspect inletting surfaces.', null, '3.5.3 Measuring & Alignment Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.3 Measuring & Alignment Tools', '["3-5-3-measuring-alignment-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-3-measuring-alignment-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('9d66578b-7640-4578-b354-f63c2f3731ae', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '24', '51', '- **Checkering Before Final Finish**  
  - Pros: finish flows into checkering; wood fully sealed.  
  - Cons: points risk slight softening as finish fills cuts.

- **Checkering After Finish**  
  - Pros: sharper-feeling points if finish is kept out of grooves.  
  - Cons: unsealed checkering can absorb sweat and dirt unless carefully sealed.

**Practical approach (conceptual as described):**  
- Often: cut checkering, apply finish, then perform a **final clean-up or recut** to restore crispness, balancing protection and sharp feel.', null, '3.4.6 Checkering Timing vs Finishing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.6 Checkering Timing vs Finishing', '["3-4-6-checkering-timing-vs-finishing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-6-checkering-timing-vs-finishing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('9dcfa1df-0ea6-4fa3-904e-80710e4c603a', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '11', '39', 'Perazzi maintains a library of **gauges and reference standards**, including:

- Bore size gauges.
- Chamber dimension gauges (e.g., CIP 70 mm go/no-go gauges).
- Firing pin protrusion gauges.
- Spring force testers.
- Reference master parts (e.g., perfectly straight bars for checking straightening machines).

These tools are **periodically calibrated**.

Spare parts (e.g., firing pins, locking bolts) are produced with **graded sizes**:

- Example: Locking bolts
  - Original bolt installs with very tight engagement.
  - After **tens of thousands of rounds**, wear may introduce slight play.
  - Gunsmith can fit the **next size up** bolt, restoring factory tightness.

This approach manages tolerances both:

- **At birth** (new gun build), and
- **Over time** (service life and rebuilds).', null, '3.1.6 Gauges, Standards, and Long-Term Tolerance Management', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Quality Control & Tolerances > 3.1.6 Gauges, Standards, and Long-Term Tolerance Management', '["3-1-6-gauges-standards-and-long-term-tolerance-management","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-1-quality-control-tolerances-3-1-6-gauges-standards-and-long-term-tolerance-management"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('9ddaf3e6-14f6-4a08-9151-fde2ae9bb871', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '19', '40', '- Decisions about when and how to:  
  - Trim butt to final LOP.  
  - Fit recoil pad vs thin buttplate vs checkered wooden butt.  
- Trade-offs:  
  - Thick pads can correct slightly short LOP or soften recoil; thin butts may look more elegant but offer less recoil mitigation.  
  - Checkering on wood butt often done later, requiring slight oversize allowances.', null, '3.4.3 Butt-End Handling & Recoil Solutions', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Butt-End Handling & Recoil Solutions', '["3-4-3-butt-end-handling-recoil-solutions","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-butt-end-handling-recoil-solutions"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('9e1b99d0-d85e-4d07-974f-974bfde00896', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '223', '238', 'Model name: MX8 SCO Gold | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX8 SCO Gold', 'Models > MX8 SCO Gold', '["model-details","mx8-sco-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('9e403df3-3d72-4f4d-a2af-75fc1f8c3fca', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '1', '36', 'This document defines the **Perazzi brand ethos and personality** so that AI systems can:

- Understand how Perazzi positions itself as more than a product brand.
- Apply the correct tone, emotional framing, and philosophical stance in generated content.
- Identify the core audience segments and how the brand should speak to each.
- Reuse signature phrases and themes consistently across campaigns, sites, and proposals.

It covers:

- Core brand identity and the idea of Perazzi as **identity and legacy**, not just hardware.
