- Brand tone and personality traits.
- Audience segments and how Perazzi connects with them.
- Strategic brand themes (exclusivity, narrative, and experience).
- The Perazzi brand experience and key storytelling vehicles.
- Signature language patterns and a canonical summary definition.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('9e641d34-8bd7-46ac-a608-d564939b4169', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '95', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 5 SCO Gold | Base model: high-tech-s-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S 5 SCO Gold', 'Models > High Tech S 5 SCO Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-s-5-sco-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('9e8593a7-ee8b-4848-b983-ce287c89fca2', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '9', '39', 'Tight control early in the process prevents downstream issues:

- **Monobloc barrel channels**
  - Must be extremely parallel; any deviation makes later regulation impossible.
  - Machined on precision jigs, then verified.
- **Action flats and hinge pin holes**
  - Kept square and true to ensure smooth pivoting and even bearing surfaces.

When **tolerance stack-up** occurs, assembly teams use selective fitting:

- Example: If the **top lever** sits too far to one side when the gun is closed:
  - They may:
    - Select a slightly **oversized locking bolt**, or
    - Hand-polish the locking bites until lever position is correct.
- Similar refinement happens at:
  - Forend-to-barrel fit.
  - Trigger group fit.
  - Ejector timing interfaces.

The outcome is a gun with:

- **No slop** where movement is not desired.
- **Smooth, lubricated freedom** where motion is required (e.g., hinge rotation).', null, '3.1.4 Tolerances, Stack-Up, and Corrective Fitting', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Quality Control & Tolerances > 3.1.4 Tolerances, Stack-Up, and Corrective Fitting', '["3-1-4-tolerances-stack-up-and-corrective-fitting","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-1-quality-control-tolerances-3-1-4-tolerances-stack-up-and-corrective-fitting"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('9ef7598d-629a-4ca5-ae84-19233142bdad', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '15', '45', '- For case-colored receivers (where used historically or by special order):  
  - Preparing surfaces to the correct pre-case finish.  
  - Understanding that case-hardening processes can distort parts, requiring careful fixturing and post-process checks.

- For plating (nickel, gold):  
  - Pre-polishing to a high finish.  
  - Masking areas that must not be plated (e.g., threads, critical fits).  
  - Ensuring plating thickness is thin enough to preserve engraving and fit.', null, '3.3.4 Case Hardening & Plating Awareness (When Applicable)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.4 Case Hardening & Plating Awareness (When Applicable)', '["3-3-4-case-hardening-plating-awareness-when-applicable","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-4-case-hardening-plating-awareness-when-applicable"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('9f09873f-afc4-4862-9661-01c4058bc68e', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '21', '51', '- When a shipping date is near, inspector may face pressure to accept borderline issues.  
- The high‑end standard is to prioritize **quality over schedule**:  
  - If necessary, inform dealer/customer of a slight delay to correct an issue.  
  - This honesty typically builds trust more than an on‑time but flawed delivery.', null, '3.4.2 Time vs Quality', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Time vs Quality', '["3-4-2-time-vs-quality","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-time-vs-quality"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('9f15c7bb-536d-4ff4-b2ff-1fa9bc61540d', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '22', '39', '- **Bore Micrometers and Gauges**  
  - Measure bore diameter along the length.  
  - Choke gauges measure constriction at muzzle.

- **Chamber Gauges**  
  - Verify chamber dimensions (length and diameter) against standards (e.g., CIP).

- **Straightness Checks**  
  - Visual inspection against a target line with backlight.  
  - Rolling on V-blocks or using a tight-fitting plug to detect bends.

- **Borescopes / Visual Aids**  
  - Used to inspect internal finish and tool marks.

- **Pattern Plates and Target Setup**  
  - For live-fire regulation and pattern evaluation.  
  - Often with fixtures or rests to remove shooter error.

- **Simple Acoustic Checks**  
  - Hanging barrels and lightly striking them to listen for a clear ring (indicating good solder joints) vs. dull thud (potential loose area).

