- **Events & community** – see §3.9.', null, '5.1 Internal Cross-Links', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 5. References & Cross-Links > 5.1 Internal Cross-Links', '["5-1-internal-cross-links","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-5-references-cross-links-5-1-internal-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('a08a3824-d7e2-461c-8ff9-d543ed3f9b77', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '12', '32', '- **Longer barrels (e.g., 32"–34")**  
  - Pros: smoother swing, longer sighting plane, often beneficial for trap and some FITASC applications.  
  - Cons: more forward weight; may feel slow to start or change direction.

- **Shorter barrels**  
  - Pros: quicker handling, easier to accelerate and redirect; often useful in sporting clays or field shooting.  
  - Cons: shorter sighting plane; can feel more “lively” or even “whippy” if not properly balanced.

**Design response:**

- Specify barrel profiles (e.g., lightened or fluted barrels) and stock weight choices to hit a target balance point.  
- Advise shooters based on discipline and style:  
  - Trap shooters may tolerate more front-heavy guns to reduce muzzle flip.  
  - Sporting or game shooters often want more neutral or slightly rear-biased balance.', null, '3.4.1 Barrel Length vs Handling', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Typical Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Barrel Length vs Handling', '["3-4-1-barrel-length-vs-handling","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-3-main-content-3-4-typical-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-barrel-length-vs-handling"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('a1037284-35e0-4115-b7c9-9857e5778779', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '5', '56', '- **Trigger Pull Weight**  
  - Force required to release each sear; measured with a trigger pull gauge.  
  - Target values may be set by internal spec or customer request (e.g., ~3.5–4 lb).

- **Firing Pin Protrusion**  
  - Extent to which pins project through breech face when fired; must be sufficient to ignite primers but not excessive.

- **“Perazzi Feel”**  
  - Informal description of the overall tactile qualities of a finished gun:  
    - Smooth opening and closing with controlled resistance.  
    - Solid, authoritative lock-up click.  
    - Crisp, consistent trigger breaks.  
    - Balanced weight and swing.

- **Balance & Total Weight**  
  - Overall gun weight and center of gravity; may need to match specific target values, especially in bespoke orders.

- **Screw Timing**  
  - Aligning screw slots in a consistent orientation (where practiced), often as a mark of meticulous assembly.', null, '2.4 Quality & Specification Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Quality & Specification Concepts', '["2-4-quality-specification-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-quality-specification-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('a10899bb-5ab2-4633-8fd6-c964dd1be41c', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '21', '39', 'Fit, balance, and handling result from collaboration between:

- **Stock makers**
- **Barrel makers**
- **Action/trigger specialists**
- **Final fitters and the shooter**

When executed well:

- The shooter’s view down the rib is correct.
- The gun neither wants to dip forward nor fall back.
- The barrels move as an extension of the shooter’s body during the swing.
- The gun “carries its weight invisibly,” feeling agile despite being solidly built.

---', null, '3.2.8 Summary: Fit & Balance as Shared Responsibility', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Fit, Balance & Handling Characteristics > 3.2.8 Summary: Fit & Balance as Shared Responsibility', '["3-2-8-summary-fit-balance-as-shared-responsibility","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-2-fit-balance-handling-characteristics-3-2-8-summary-fit-balance-as-shared-responsibility"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('a1094bcc-2295-43be-b8a0-23029fdcf314', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '43', '53', '- Experience fitting shooters of **different builds** (e.g., youth, women, unusual proportions).  
- Adjust LOP, pitch, cast, and grip feel to accommodate unique anatomies while preserving structural integrity.  
- When necessary, suggest or perform more significant modifications (e.g., slimmer grip radius) if time and context allow.', null, '3.7.5 Handling Diverse Anatomies & Use Cases', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.5 Handling Diverse Anatomies & Use Cases', '["3-7-5-handling-diverse-anatomies-use-cases","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-5-handling-diverse-anatomies-use-cases"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('a1223c2a-c718-4c2e-ac82-4385d01e64d4', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '54', '58', '- **Non-factory barrels on existing receivers**  
  - Always require expert fitting and POI verification.  
  - Unsafe combinations can appear to lock correctly but have poor headspace or regulation.

- **Release triggers**  
  - Widely used in trap but not installed by Perazzi at the factory.  
  - Quality and safety depend on the gunsmith’s expertise; issues may not be covered under warranty.

- **Extremely high round-count guns**  
  - Locking bolts, hinge pins, and monobloc surfaces can wear over 100k+ shells.  
  - Oversized locking bolts and other parts are designed for refurbishment.

- **Owner-applied modifications**  
  - Cosmetic or ergonomic changes (pads, comb hardware, etc.) usually benign if properly installed.  
  - Structural changes (porting, cone changes, re-chambering) should be entrusted only to experts familiar with Perazzi tolerances.

- **Ambiguities in model naming**  
  - Some historical model names (Comp I, Mirage, MT6) have overlapping or region-specific usage.  
  - When in doubt, resolve by **platform (MX/TM/HT)** and mechanical configuration rather than name alone.

---', null, '4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats', '["4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('a1724c3d-7684-4142-b6ef-9e3c907360a2', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '1', '35', 'This document describes the **Action & Receiver Machining station** in the Perazzi factory.

At this station, a forged steel blank is transformed into the **receiver (action body)** and related components that form the structural core of a Perazzi over-under shotgun. The receiver must:

- Withstand firing stresses over decades.
- Provide a precise foundation for barrel lock-up, trigger group, and stock inletting.
- Preserve enough material in critical interfaces for later **hand fitting**.

This document explains:

- The **purpose** and **success criteria** of the station.
- The **inputs and outputs** (material, programs, parts, and QC data).
- The **core skills and knowledge** required of the machinists.
- The **decisions and trade-offs** around tolerances, heat-treatment sequence, and material removal.
- The **tools and measurements** used (CNC, fixtures, gauges, etc.).
- The **failure modes**, how they are detected, and how they are mitigated.
- What **mastery** looks like at this station, including illustrative vignettes.

The focus is on how Perazzi integrates high-end CNC machining with traditional hand fitting to produce actions that lock up with the characteristic **"bank-vault" feel** and remain tight and safe over a long service life.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('a17405bc-a098-4480-915d-bbd82313baec', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '41', '51', '- Treat final sign‑off as a personal statement of quality:  
  - Many see their internal stamp or signature as a badge of honor.  
  - They will not sign a gun they are not personally proud of.

> **Example vignette (composite, illustrative):**  
> A final inspector begins with a new SC3‑grade Perazzi destined for an important client. He checks the barrels first: deep blue, choke marks correct, rib straight, beads secure. The fore-end latch closes with a precise click; wood and metal joints are flawless. He scans the engraving, comparing both sides for symmetry.  
>  
> When he opens the gun, the chambers shine like mirrors; he finds no stray fibers or flakes of metal. With snap caps in place, he tests the safety and triggers—everything feels crisp and familiar. The stock head fit is perfect; his fingernail finds no gap at the action junction. In the case, spare springs, firing pins, stock wrench, choke tubes, and manual are all in their spots.  
>  
> Finally, he matches serial number and proof marks to the certificate and order. Satisfied, he signs the inspection card. Later, when the client opens the case, everything appears immaculate and exactly as ordered—evidence that the inspector caught and resolved any issues before anyone else ever saw the gun.', null, '3.7.4 Pride & Ownership', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.4 Pride & Ownership', '["3-7-4-pride-ownership","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-4-pride-ownership"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('a1d0eb6d-9ef7-4602-b25a-ad987e16f31d', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '6', '32', '- **1964 Olympic Gold**: Ennio Mattarelli wins Olympic gold in trap with a Perazzi, propelling the brand to world prominence.  
- Since then, Perazzi has **dominated Olympic and world championship podiums**, especially in shotgun disciplines.  
- This competitive success is central to Perazzi’s identity: the guns are **validated in the highest-pressure environments** and optimized around elite-level performance.', null, '3.1.2 Breakthrough and Competitive Dominance', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi’s Competition Shotguns and Their Heritage > 3.1.2 Breakthrough and Competitive Dominance', '["3-1-2-breakthrough-and-competitive-dominance","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-s-competition-shotguns-and-their-heritage-3-1-2-breakthrough-and-competitive-dominance"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('a1d417ad-961b-41f1-8f77-04ead7c6b83e', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '23', '38', 'Mastery at the trigger bench is visible in **consistency**, **speed with precision**, and **deep diagnostic intuition**.', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('a1d8249f-32bb-4fd9-ade9-f98f8ddc24c8', '500269f5-9624-4f5b-9ded-8de9740793b2', '1', '7', 'Modifications to the receiver, such as unauthorized engraving or case color hardening, may not meet Perazzi''s craftsmanship standards and could compromise structural integrity, are considered counterfeit or fake and will diminish the firearm''s value. Ensure any engraving is performed by a Perazzi-authorized artisan to maintain authenticity and warranty coverage.', null, 'Aftermarket Engraving on Receivers', 'Consumer Warning Notice > Aftermarket Engraving on Receivers', '["aftermarket-engraving-on-receivers","consumer-warning-notice-aftermarket-engraving-on-receivers"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:16.184829+00', null), ('a1f536dc-97e2-4ba7-9529-fa2e239ab5ea', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '90', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 5 Gold | Base model: high-tech-s-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S 5 Gold', 'Models > High Tech S 5 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-s-5-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('a218a827-2fea-4cdc-abf8-f5d83af2a42f', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '18', '50', '### Suzanne Balogh
