---', null, '3.4.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Achievers', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.4 Achiever > 3.4.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Achievers', '["3-4-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-achievers","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-4-achiever-3-4-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-achievers"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('a2b34fb7-0dd2-4cd4-8bf9-da94c02757bd', '4ae532ea-bef9-47fe-9bd9-051858902e2f', '5', '23', 'This subsection provides a **roadmap for navigating the handbook**.', null, '3.1 Recommended Reading Order & Strategy', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Recommended Reading Order & Strategy', '["3-1-recommended-reading-order-strategy","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-3-main-content-3-1-recommended-reading-order-strategy"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('a2e40219-4d5f-4327-94e3-623ae6243bfb', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '30', '39', 'The **stock and fore-end** are the primary visual and tactile wood elements:

- **Walnut grades**:
  - Range from standard straight grain to dramatic exhibition-grade figure.
  - Choice reflects personality:
    - Conservative, straight grain: traditional, function-first sensibility.
    - Bold burl and flame: love of elegance and visual drama.

The finish:

- Typically **hand-rubbed oil** or similar, yielding:
  - Rich depth.
  - Natural, non-plastic sheen.
- Intended to:
  - Highlight grain and color.
  - Maintain a crafted, not mass-produced, look.

The **Perazzi Experience** of wood selection:

- Customers may personally choose their stock blank from Perazzi’s walnut stocks.
- This is often a **formative moment**:
  - Selecting “the piece of tree” that will become the heart of their gun.
- Checkering:
  - Usually precise flat-top diamonds, often wrap-around on the grip.
  - Executed by skilled craftswomen by hand.
  - Can be customized (e.g., special patterns or monograms), though competition guns usually keep it practical for grip.

Visual uniqueness arises from:

- No two walnut blanks being identical.
- Engraving and checkering variations.
- Finish choices.', null, '3.4.3 Wood Selection, Finish, and Emotional Impact', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Aesthetics & Identity > 3.4.3 Wood Selection, Finish, and Emotional Impact', '["3-4-3-wood-selection-finish-and-emotional-impact","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-4-aesthetics-identity-3-4-3-wood-selection-finish-and-emotional-impact"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('a2f36163-9cfe-4467-bf8a-b04719c76c0d', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '1', '38', 'This document is an internal reference on Perazzi USA team shooters and supported shooters.

It captures, for each athlete:

- Discipline(s) (e.g., Sporting Clays, American Trap, American Skeet, International Skeet).
- Biographical background and career trajectory.
- Major titles, records, and notable achievements (as described in the original text).
- Personality traits, coaching roles, and broader impact on the sport.
- Relationship with Perazzi shotguns, including preferred models and configurations where mentioned.', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('a31bd476-d033-4bb2-a257-5272117b73d6', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '3', '38', '- **Trigger Blade**  
  - The part the shooter’s finger contacts and pulls.

- **Hammer**  
  - Component that strikes the firing pin when released.

- **Sear**  
  - Part that holds the hammer under spring tension and releases it when the trigger is pulled.  
  - Sear angles (positive, neutral, negative) influence pull weight and feel.

- **Springs**  
  - **Leaf (V) Springs** – High-performance, fast-acting springs powering hammers; crisp feel but can break unexpectedly.[6]  
  - **Coil Springs** – Helical springs; generally more durable and forgiving; may feel slightly less crisp and can continue to function in a limited way even if partially compromised.[6]

- **Pins / Axles**  
  - Pivot and locating points for trigger, sear, hammer, and related components.

- **Safety Slide / Safety Bar**  
  - Mechanism that blocks triggers or sears to prevent firing when engaged.

- **Barrel Selector**  
  - Mechanism (often integrated into the safety slide) that chooses which barrel fires first in a single-trigger over-under.

- **Trigger Housing / Trigger Group**  
  - For drop-out designs, the self-contained unit that houses the entire trigger mechanism and can be removed from the action (e.g., MX8-style removable trigger).', null, '2.2 Core Components', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Core Components', '["2-2-core-components","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-core-components"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('a3350916-d56d-4366-a1f6-8ce57a65c21c', 'b06cfbad-6ed3-4ea2-aced-77b1d43c6fec', '0', '1', 'Each entry lists the model (or group of models), rib description, whether it is fixed or adjustable, and the nominal rib height in millimeters (MM).

