---', null, '3.3.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Analysts', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 3. Archetypes – Detailed Descriptions > 3.3 Analyst > 3.3.4 How the Brand Should Speak to Analysts', '["3-3-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-analysts","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-3-archetypes-detailed-descriptions-3-3-analyst-3-3-4-how-the-brand-should-speak-to-analysts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('a3d9252d-d67a-48d2-a6a0-eccb6b686388', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '32', '45', 'Mastery in metal finishing & bluing appears in both the **subtlety of the finish** and the **absence of problems**.', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('a3edfe1d-59df-4451-9862-840ae7af8ae9', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '11', '39', '- Many shotguns use either **leaf (V) springs** or **coil springs** exclusively; Perazzi’s triggers are designed to support **both**.[6][8]
- Features:
  - Trigger housings accept either leaf or coil spring assemblies.
  - Shooters can:
    - Choose spring type at purchase.
    - Convert between types later via specific kits.
- Trade-offs:
  - Leaf springs:
    - Faster lock time.
    - Very crisp feel (“glass rod” break).
    - Potentially more fragile if fatigued or improperly treated.
  - Coil springs:
    - Slightly slower lock time (in practice, often marginal).
    - High durability and predictable failure modes.
- Perazzi’s design choice:
  - Treats this as a **user-tunable variable** based on shooter preference and philosophy about redundancy and feel.
  - This level of trigger-spring configurability is unusual in general gunmaking.', null, '3.1.6 Coil vs Leaf Spring Option', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations > 3.1.6 Coil vs Leaf Spring Option', '["3-1-6-coil-vs-leaf-spring-option","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations-3-1-6-coil-vs-leaf-spring-option"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('a3f1281c-20ab-4f17-84d0-d1eaa748929e', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '32', '38', '- Leaf springs provide outstanding feel but can fail abruptly.  
- Competitive shooters may mitigate this by carrying spare trigger groups or springs.

**Caveat:**  
- When reliability is paramount and spare parts are not readily available (e.g., remote hunts or critical events without backup), coil springs may be preferable despite slightly different feel.', null, '4.2 Leaf Spring Breakage Risk', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.2 Leaf Spring Breakage Risk', '["4-2-leaf-spring-breakage-risk","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-2-leaf-spring-breakage-risk"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('a41981ea-4ac7-47e3-b49c-0acd0f27686a', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '23', '58', 'Perazzi has an unmatched record in Olympic and world-level shotgun sports.', null, '3.4 Athletes and Competitive Record', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Athletes and Competitive Record', '["3-4-athletes-and-competitive-record","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-4-athletes-and-competitive-record"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('a4541c8e-5431-48af-ba76-f2b85957fbc1', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '6', '48', '- **Centerline / Reference Line**  
  - Marked line used to align stock geometry to blank (often representing bore or rib axis).

- **Layout Lines**  
  - Chalk or pencil lines marking side and top profiles of the stock within the blank.

- **Oversize Allowance**  
  - Additional material left on surfaces (e.g., 2–4 mm) for later hand-fitting and shaping.

- **Natural Cast**  
  - Cast built into stock orientation within the blank (by tilting layout) rather than added later by bending.

---', null, '2.5 Measurement & Layout Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.5 Measurement & Layout Concepts', '["2-5-measurement-layout-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-5-measurement-layout-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('a46e1c81-e52f-40ad-9193-acf9952fc82e', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '36', '51', '- **Description:** Pattern appears tilted, misaligned, or ill-fitted to stock shape due to layout errors.  
- **Diagnosis:** Stepping back and visually checking; measuring distances from pattern edges to fixed stock landmarks.  
- **Mitigation & Repair:**  
  - Early detection allows border and spacing adjustments to visually correct.  
  - Late detection may be difficult or impossible to fully remedy; masters rely on initial layout discipline to avoid.', null, '3.6.7 Asymmetry & Layout Errors', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.7 Asymmetry & Layout Errors', '["3-6-7-asymmetry-layout-errors","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-7-asymmetry-layout-errors"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('a47c659d-518e-442e-94cd-ef2d8bae0c7e', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '30', '32', '- **To other handbook sections (conceptual cross-links):**  
  - **Receiver and Metalwork Station:** uses action, proof, and barrel-interface specifications from this document.  
  - **Barrel Making and Regulation Station:** relies heavily on barrel length, rib design, choke, and POI instructions set here.  
  - **Stockmaking and Fitting Station:** builds stock to the dimensions and behavioral goals defined here.  
  - **Engraving and Aesthetic Finishing Station:** depends on engraving grade, patterns, and custom motifs defined here.  
  - **Final Assembly and Test Station:** evaluates whether the finished gun aligns with the handling and POI intent originally captured at this design stage.

- **Within this document:**  
  - Stock-fit concepts are defined in **Section 2.3** and applied in **Sections 3.1–3.4**.  
  - Trigger system trade-offs are described in **Section 2.5** and detailed in **Section 3.4.3**.  
  - Non-standard requests and caveats are consolidated in **Section 4**.

---', null, '5. References & Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 5. References & Cross-Links', '["5-references-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-5-references-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('a49e47fb-724b-42fa-8755-84c687ddb419', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '8', '38', 'A trigger group is considered successful when:

- **Trigger feel**  
  - Minimal or controlled take-up (if any) and a “glass rod” break (crisp release).  
  - Pull weights set to specification (e.g., ~3.5 lbs first barrel, 4 lbs second barrel for a trap gun, or as requested).

- **Lock time and consistency**  
  - Fast, consistent lock time across both barrels.  
  - Hammers fall with adequate speed and force to ensure reliable primer ignition.

- **Second-shot function**  
  - Inertia or mechanical system reliably arms and fires the second barrel.  
  - No failures to reset under normal operating conditions and ammunition.

- **Safety**  
  - Trigger does **not** fire when the gun is jarred or dropped.  
  - Safety slide/bar fully blocks firing when engaged; cannot be overcome by a normal trigger pull.  
  - No doubling or unintended second-shot discharge.

- **Durability**  
  - Trigger group withstands tens of thousands of cycles without going out of adjustment or breaking.  
  - Springs, sear edges, and pins are robust under normal use.

- **QC Verification**  
  - Repeated dry-fire tests and, where applicable, dummy round tests confirm reliability.  
  - Live-fire and patterning tests show triggers behave as expected in real shooting.

When this station performs perfectly, the shooter experiences a **light, crisp, predictable trigger** that functions identically for both barrels and remains trustworthy over extended use.

---', null, '3.1.2 Success Criteria', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.2 Success Criteria', '["3-1-2-success-criteria","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-2-success-criteria"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('a4d362d1-a285-4e69-97ca-f1204a4bd27a', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '29', '36', '- "Quiet monuments to greatness."
- "A Perazzi is not something you own, it''s something you become."
- "Transformation, not transaction."
- "Legacy is no longer something you observe — it''s something you embody."
- "The hands of the artisan, the heart of the shooter."', null, '3.7.1 Core Phrases', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.7 Signature Language Patterns > 3.7.1 Core Phrases', '["3-7-1-core-phrases","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-7-signature-language-patterns-3-7-1-core-phrases"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('a510e029-3548-4dcf-bab3-8015cca69a1a', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '5', '39', '- **Regulation**  
  - Process of ensuring multiple barrels shoot to the desired **point of impact (POI)** at a specified distance (e.g., both barrels inside a 30-inch circle at 35 m at point of aim).

- **Point of Impact (POI)**  
  - Location where pattern centers relative to point of aim at a test distance.

- **Pattern**  
  - Distribution of shot pellets on a target at a given distance; used to evaluate choke performance and regulation.

- **Proof Testing**  
  - Firing barrels with over-pressure loads to verify safety and compliance with proof house standards. Perazzi is reported to perform **random destructive over-pressure tests** (e.g., up to 16× normal) as a quality check at the process level.

- **Barrel Wall Thickness**  
  - Thickness of steel around the bore. Influences safety, weight, heat handling, and dent resistance.

- **Back-Boring (conceptual)**  
  - Slightly increasing bore diameter compared to nominal gauge to influence pressure and pattern (mentioned as a possible practice).', null, '2.4 Performance and Safety Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Performance and Safety Concepts', '["2-4-performance-and-safety-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-performance-and-safety-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('a539e96f-f6b7-45e4-ab06-2abd697b4621', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '50', '238', 'Model name: High Tech Gold | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: Gold | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech Gold', 'Models > High Tech Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('a53cdf11-857d-46bf-af74-87bc8efabb6e', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '41', '48', '- If a blank appears slightly too green or unstable (by moisture reading or feel/sound), it may be:  
  - Set aside for further drying.  
  - Used only for non-critical parts (rare in a high-end context).

**Caveat:**  
Better to delay use than risk warp or cracking after shaping.', null, '4.1 Marginally Seasoned or “Suspicious” Blanks', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Marginally Seasoned or “Suspicious” Blanks', '["4-1-marginally-seasoned-or-suspicious-blanks","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-marginally-seasoned-or-suspicious-blanks"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('a59b79d8-9fa6-425c-8e62-1d77969fa8fe', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '10', '40', '- **Fully Inlet and Fitted Stock**  
  - Precise internal inletting for receiver, tangs, trigger guard, and through-bolt pathway.  
  - Stock bolted to action under proper torque with no visible gaps and no hidden stress points.

- **Fully Inlet and Fitted Fore-end**  
  - Internal fit to fore-end iron, latch, and barrel contact surfaces.  
  - Fore-end that snaps on/off with correct force and supports barrels as designed (without undue strain).

- **Final External Geometry**  
  - Stock shaped to final contours: comb, grip, wrist, butt, and any cheekpiece or Monte Carlo features.  
  - Fore-end shaped to final ergonomic form (flare near receiver, taper toward tip, etc.).  
  - Optional features implemented: palm swell, toe adjustments, adjustable comb/butt provisions if specified.

- **Pre-Finished Surfaces**  
  - Surfaces sanded to fine grit (e.g., around 220–320 or similar) and ready for finishing.  
  - Edges appropriately rounded or crisp according to design and comfort requirements.

- **Notes & Layout Lines for Downstream Work**  
  - Optional penciled checkering layout lines or notes for checkering patterns and finishing staff.  
  - Markings where additional features (e.g., adjustable comb hardware) will be added if not yet installed.

---', null, '3.2.2 Outputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.2 Outputs', '["3-2-2-outputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-2-outputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('a5b4cc10-ea47-4742-88bf-26ece9363194', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '10', '35', '- **Machined Receiver ("White" Action)**  
  - Receiver with all major cavities, holes, and surfaces machined, and critical surfaces left slightly oversize for hand fit.

- **Associated Machined Metal Parts**  
  - Components such as top latch, forend iron, and possibly trigger plate, produced in parallel operations.

- **Serialized Action**  
  - Serial number applied early in the process, often at or near this station, in accordance with Italian legal requirements.  
  - Serial number ties together receiver and later barrel/stock components.

- **Heat-Treated Receiver (when applicable)**  
  - If case hardening or other heat treatment is sequenced here, an output may be a hardened receiver ready for final fitting and finishing.

- **Quality Control Records**  
  - Measurement and inspection data (e.g., hinge pin spacing, locking bite depths, critical bore diameters).  
  - These may include measurement reports and internal inspection sheets.

---', null, '3.2.2 Outputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.2 Outputs', '["3-2-2-outputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-2-outputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('a6511a53-f9a2-4b00-b793-80259c916635', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '32', '45', 'Mastery in wood finishing resides in **subtle perfection** rather than flashy gestures.', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('a6950658-92a7-4e74-9778-175e231b2212', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '29', '53', '- Tape measure or rule for LOP and reference dimensions.  
- Inclinometer or pitch meter for pad angle.  
- Reference patterns or forms for standard stock geometries.', null, '3.5.3 Measurement Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.3 Measurement Tools', '["3-5-3-measurement-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-3-measurement-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('a6ba1b97-d49b-4af2-b179-de255146cc3a', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '16', '39', '- **Fixed Chokes**  
  - Pros: optimized patterning, less muzzle weight, no choke threads disrupting bore.  
  - Cons: less flexibility; pattern is fixed unless modified by reaming/honing.

- **Removable Chokes**  
  - Pros: high flexibility; shooters can change constrictions for different targets or conditions.  
  - Cons: added muzzle weight; potential influence on bore harmonics.

**Design response:**

- When fixed chokes are specified, choose exact constrictions and fine-tune via pattern testing and polishing if needed.  
- When removable chokes are specified, cut threads precisely so tubes seat correctly and align.', null, '3.4.3 Fixed vs. Removable Chokes', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Fixed vs. Removable Chokes', '["3-4-3-fixed-vs-removable-chokes","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-fixed-vs-removable-chokes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('a6ca694d-ddd7-45b5-aa0f-a096ef82a9a9', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '38', '45', '> A finisher has two Perazzi stocks on the bench: one for a presentation gun, one for a hard-use competition shooter.  
> For the presentation stock, he builds a deep, piano-like gloss using multiple coats of a catalyzed finish. Once cured, he lightly rubs it with ultra-fine abrasive to soften the harsh reflections, leaving a deep mirror that still looks like wood, not plastic. The owner later sees his reflection in the butt and smiles.  
> For the competition gun, he uses a traditional oil blend. He fills pores with an oil-and-dust slurry and stops when a soft satin appears. He then waxes lightly. Under bright sun on the range, there is no glare—only a gentle glow. The shooter shoulders the gun; it feels secure in the hands and comfortable against the cheek. The finisher nods; each stock reflects the life it is meant to live.

---', null, '3.7.6 Example Vignette (Composite, Illustrative)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.6 Example Vignette (Composite, Illustrative)', '["3-7-6-example-vignette-composite-illustrative","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-6-example-vignette-composite-illustrative"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('a6f66885-ab10-4df9-bdc4-3e80539b59ed', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '11', '51', 'Final inspectors combine **meticulous attention to detail** with **broad factory knowledge**.', null, '3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills', '["3-3-core-knowledge-skills","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('a6fbe87c-79de-4341-9f2c-7dc4cba38693', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '105', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S SC3 Gold | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SC3 Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S SC3 Gold', 'Models > High Tech S SC3 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-s-sc3-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('a70cf4f6-5628-449c-9cdd-062ea59d6e3b', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '22', '32', 'This subsection focuses on how each area behaves from a user-experience standpoint.', null, '3.3 How the Main Site Areas Work', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 3. Core Experiences & Main Site Areas > 3.3 How the Main Site Areas Work', '["3-3-how-the-main-site-areas-work","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-3-core-experiences-main-site-areas-3-3-how-the-main-site-areas-work"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('a73e20a6-52ce-4aac-8899-8ab8a1984686', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '16', '39', 'Balance is primarily controlled by:

- **Barrel weight and profiling**.
- **Stock wood density and internal hollowing**.
- **Receiver mass** (e.g., High Tech vs earlier MX designs).

Key principles:

- Perazzi competition O/Us are typically **slightly forward-balanced** (just in front of the hinge) to:
  - Provide front-end stability.
  - Smooth the swing.
  - Avoid a nervous, muzzle-light feel.
- The **High Tech** series:
  - Features a slightly **wider, heavier receiver**.
  - Moves more weight **between the hands**, shifting the balance slightly rearward relative to MX-series guns.
  - This yields a “smoother recoil and swing” between the hands.[9]

Fine-tuning methods:

- Selecting barrel sets of different **marked weights** (barrel weight is often stamped to 0.01 kg on the monobloc).
- Choosing denser or lighter walnut blanks.
- Slightly hollowing or weighting the stock (e.g., lead in the stock bolt hole).
- Adjusting fore-end wood or iron weight.

Craftsmen and fitters:

- Shoulder the gun themselves.
- Have the customer mount it (if present).
- Make subtle mass adjustments (tens of grams) to achieve the desired feel.

The target feel: **lively yet not twitchy**, with enough momentum to carry through the swing but not so much that it is sluggish.', null, '3.2.3 Balance and Mass Distribution', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Fit, Balance & Handling Characteristics > 3.2.3 Balance and Mass Distribution', '["3-2-3-balance-and-mass-distribution","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-2-fit-balance-handling-characteristics-3-2-3-balance-and-mass-distribution"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('a7a15896-5558-4fd5-927d-c3eda779cf36', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '5', '238', 'Model name: DC SC3 | Base model: dc | Platform: DC | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: side-by-side | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### DC SC3', 'Models > DC SC3', '["model-details","dc-sc3","platform:dc"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('a7b86ce8-4a27-4af5-8f18-6a14ea26bec7', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '149', '238', 'Model name: MX12 SCO Gold | Base model: mx12 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX12 SCO Gold', 'Models > MX12 SCO Gold', '["model-details","mx12-sco-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('a86c86e4-b354-4d7b-9717-3a4ccbe12935', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '15', '36', '- Communications regularly reference **identity, legacy, and soul**.  
- The language has a **thoughtful slowness**, evoking contemplation rather than urgency.  
- The gun is spoken of with reverence (e.g., "crafted patiently, waiting for the right hands to awaken it").', null, '3.3.3 Philosophical & Reverent', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Brand Tone & Personality > 3.3.3 Philosophical & Reverent', '["3-3-3-philosophical-reverent","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-3-brand-tone-personality-3-3-3-philosophical-reverent"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('a8720035-63ea-4a73-8692-70595be553ac', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '25', '51', '- Adjusting spacing slightly “on the fly” to preserve overall visual symmetry, especially near pattern edges or on asymmetrical surfaces.  
- Trade-off: small local variations in diamond size vs globally symmetrical pattern boundaries.

**Practical approach:**  
- Opt for what looks best overall to the eye; slight local deviations at pattern edges are preferred to global misalignment.

---', null, '3.4.7 Spacing Adjustments for Symmetry', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.7 Spacing Adjustments for Symmetry', '["3-4-7-spacing-adjustments-for-symmetry","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-7-spacing-adjustments-for-symmetry"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('a8c81e44-ba68-4a19-8273-5dd99ebe20d0', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '10', '53', '- **Final Adjusted Gun**  
  - Comb height and (if applicable) comb cast set and locked.  
  - Stock cast and drop finalized, via adjustable comb or bending as needed.  
  - LOP set with spacers or pad choice; trigger shoe position adjusted to match.  
  - Pitch refined (via tapered spacers or pad trimming) to improve pad contact and recoil feel.  
  - Balance tuned, with weights added/removed if needed.

- **Comfort & Mount Improvements**  
  - Pad edges and toe/heel shaped or softened so the gun mounts smoothly without catching clothing.  
  - Minor ergonomic refinements such as small comb edge rounding or subtle cheek comfort tweaks.

- **Documentation & Records**  
  - Final geometry recorded (LOP, drop at comb/heel, cast at heel/toe, pitch, comb hardware settings, trigger shoe position).  
  - Notes on subjective feedback and how it was addressed (e.g., “preferred slightly heavier butt; added stock weight”).

- **Shooter Instructions & Expectations**  
  - Guidance on current adjustment settings (e.g., comb post marks) so the shooter can restore them if hardware is removed.  
  - Discussion of any reversible vs permanent changes and advice on potential future tweaks after a break‑in period.

- **Optional Cosmetic Touch-Ups**  
  - Local refinish where small adjustments (bending, light sanding) might have affected finish.  
  - Cleaned and ready gun for final inspection and sign‑off.

When the customer is not physically present, outputs may be limited to **baseline settings** based on measurements and the expectation that a local gunsmith can make small adjustments later if necessary.

---', null, '3.2.2 Outputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.2 Outputs', '["3-2-2-outputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-2-outputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('a928680b-b2e1-4f90-bc61-8f82b47adf88', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '34', '45', '- Finisher maintains **multiple stocks in rotation**, each at different stages of oiling or curing.  
- Coats are logged (formally or mentally), and no stock is rushed before proper cure.  
- Environment, timing, and coat thickness are consistent, yielding a repeatable “house look.”', null, '3.7.2 Process Discipline & Rotation', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.2 Process Discipline & Rotation', '["3-7-2-process-discipline-rotation","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-2-process-discipline-rotation"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('a935a857-1438-4e08-9fd0-6902991ad132', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '45', '51', '- For guns intended more as **presentation pieces** than hard-use competition tools, finer LPI and more elaborate patterns may be employed.  
- These require even greater tool control and visual planning.

**Caveat:**  
- Such patterns can wear more quickly and are less forgiving in daily use.', null, '4.1 Extremely Fine or Decorative Checkering', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Extremely Fine or Decorative Checkering', '["4-1-extremely-fine-or-decorative-checkering","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-extremely-fine-or-decorative-checkering"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('aa461ea0-2e4b-40fc-9ed1-3631e5cbded0', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '29', '35', '- When introducing a new receiver family (e.g., wider or heavier action):  
  - Fixturing, CNC programs, and tool paths may need redesign.  
  - Past practice from models like the MX8 is used as a starting point but must be validated for the new geometry.  
  - Early runs may involve tighter collaboration between machinists, engineers, and fitters to tune allowances.', null, '4.1 New Models and Prototype Runs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 New Models and Prototype Runs', '["4-1-new-models-and-prototype-runs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-new-models-and-prototype-runs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('aa9cd8e0-2a79-422f-8948-d7a5b2d0e78d', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '62', '238', 'Model name: High Tech RS | Base model: high-tech-rs | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: unsingle | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 10.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech RS', 'Models > High Tech RS', '["model-details","high-tech-rs","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('aac3491e-7ef6-4fa5-a0be-a2000b08884f', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '15', '39', 'Fit and POI are tightly linked:

- During the **pattern-testing phase**, Perazzi verifies:
  - The gun shoots to the intended POI (e.g., 60/40, 70/30).
  - The shooter’s mount aligns with that POI.
- If a customer desires a **60/40** pattern (60% pellets above, 40% below):
  - Stock drop and cast are shaped to produce this for their build and shooting style.
- Final fitting may involve:
  - Bending the stock slightly (for cast or drop).
  - Adjusting an **adjustable comb**.
  - Changing recoil pad thickness or angle.', null, '3.2.2 Fit, POI, and Patterning', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Fit, Balance & Handling Characteristics > 3.2.2 Fit, POI, and Patterning', '["3-2-2-fit-poi-and-patterning","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-2-fit-balance-handling-characteristics-3-2-2-fit-poi-and-patterning"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('aac65b5f-7fa9-4a4f-baba-d6a1c26eca32', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '44', '48', '- For customers ordering multiple guns with matched wood, selection and layout must consider:  
  - Matching tone and figure across multiple stocks and fore-ends.  
  - Consistency in wrist strength across the set.', null, '4.4 Matching Multiple Guns or Sets', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.4 Matching Multiple Guns or Sets', '["4-4-matching-multiple-guns-or-sets","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-4-matching-multiple-guns-or-sets"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('aae2f4a6-0592-44ef-80e7-35715ea085ae', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '5', '32', 'At a high level, the site can be thought of as:

- **Home** – The cinematic welcome and brand overview.
- **Shotguns / Platforms** – The structured way to understand Perazzi platforms, disciplines, and configurations.
- **Bespoke Build / Concierge** – The guided experience for exploring or imagining a custom build.
- **Heritage** – History, factory, champions, and timeline.
- **Experience / Stories** – Articles, interviews, behind-the-scenes, and event coverage.
- **Service & Support** – Service centers, parts, care guidance, and ownership support.
- **Dealers & Events** – Where to see, handle, and shoot Perazzi in the real world.

PerazziGPT should use these buckets when answering questions like:

- "Where do I go to read about Perazzi history?"
- "Where can I compare platforms for sporting clays?"
- "Where do I find service info for my gun?"', null, '2.2 Navigation Summary', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 2. Site Structure & Area Concepts > 2.2 Navigation Summary', '["2-2-navigation-summary","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-2-site-structure-area-concepts-2-2-navigation-summary"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('ab9d0415-4a2a-49df-be33-798698568be4', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '11', '38', 'Tom Seay is described as part of the new wave of sporting clays champions – young, driven, and already battle-tested. A Tennessee native who trained under legendary coaches, Tom grew up on clay ranges and learned to compete with both heart and mind.

By his early twenties, he had amassed several major titles, signaling that a “prodigy” had come of age in the sport. The original text lists significant achievements, including:

- Two-time Northeast Regional Champion.  
- 2018 South Central Regional Champion.  
- PSCA Tour Stop Champion.  
- Back-to-back Gamaliel Cup HOA winner[16][17].

These victories, against some of the toughest fields in the nation, are presented as evidence of Tom’s consistency and competitive grit.

The source notes that those who know Tom describe him as:

- Extremely driven and motivated.  
- “Never satisfied with the status quo” – a mindset he himself embraces[18].

Additional milestones:

- Multiple-time USA Junior Team Captain.  
- World junior titles before transitioning successfully to the open/professional level[19][20].  
- In 2017, at just 21, Tom won the North East Regional Championship and a PSCA Tour stop in a dramatic shoot-off[21].  
- By 2019, he was a fixture on Team USA and a multiple National Junior Champion[19].

The text also highlights Tom’s roles beyond competition, including coaching and guest podcast hosting – reflecting a maturity in giving back to the sport[22][23].', null, '3.1.3.1 Biography & Background', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Sponsored Shooters (Perazzi USA Team) > 3.1.3 Tom Seay – Sporting Clays (Sponsored Shooter) > 3.1.3.1 Biography & Background', '["3-1-3-1-biography-background","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-1-sponsored-shooters-perazzi-usa-team-3-1-3-tom-seay-sporting-clays-sponsored-shooter-3-1-3-1-biography-background"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('ab9f3516-75b0-4fe5-a2b7-c8400cf4675b', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '3', '53', '- **Length of Pull (LOP)**  
  - Distance from trigger face to center of butt/pad; strongly affects mount comfort, trigger reach, and recoil distribution.

- **Drop (Comb & Heel)**  
  - Vertical distance between the sighting plane and the comb/heel; determines eye height and basic point of impact (POI) for a given sight picture.

- **Cast (Cast-Off / Cast-On)**  
  - Lateral offset of the stock from the barrel/action centerline.  
  - Cast-off (right-handed) moves stock to the right; cast-on (left-handed) to the left.  
  - Affects lateral eye alignment and how the recoil pad seats in the shoulder pocket.

- **Pitch**  
  - Angle of the butt/pad relative to the bore; influences how pad contacts the shoulder and how recoil is distributed (toe vs heel dig, muzzle rise).

- **Toe & Heel**  
  - Toe: lower rear corner of the butt/pad.  
  - Heel: upper rear corner.  
  - Toe angle and pad shape impact how smoothly the gun mounts and whether the pad catches on clothing.

- **Comb Height & Thickness**  
  - Height: influences vertical POI and sight picture (how much rib the shooter sees).  
  - Thickness/edge shape: affects cheek comfort and bruising risk.', null, '2.2 Fit & Geometry Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Fit & Geometry Concepts', '["2-2-fit-geometry-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-fit-geometry-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('abb5c4da-940b-4abc-8eb9-2bcdaedc3d4f', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '17', '48', '- Selecting and orienting fore-end blanks to minimize warp and ensure strength near latch and iron.  
- Matching color and figure to the butt stock (often from the same log, set, or visually matched blank).  
- Roughing the fore-end concurrently so style and proportion match the stock.', null, '3.3.6 Fore-end-Specific Considerations', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.6 Fore-end-Specific Considerations', '["3-3-6-fore-end-specific-considerations","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-6-fore-end-specific-considerations"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('ac28a604-3b95-463d-81c3-2b3ad9e8cabb', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '140', '238', 'Model name: MX12 SC2 | Base model: mx12 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SC2 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX12 SC2', 'Models > MX12 SC2', '["model-details","mx12-sc2","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('ac640bff-6f6b-4280-94b1-91fa1e2bf150', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '21', '56', '- **Tighter Lock-Up / Stiffer Opening**  
  - Pros: longer service life before looseness; perception of robustness.  
  - Cons: can be fatiguing, especially for shooters opening the gun thousands of times (e.g., trap shooters).

- **Easier Opening / Softer Lock-Up**  
  - Pros: more comfortable for frequent use; easier to operate for shooters with less hand strength.  
  - Cons: reduced wear margin if too loose; earlier need for tightening or service.

**Practical approach:**  
- Target a **slightly stiff but smooth** feel at delivery:  
  - Top lever comfortably right-of-center.  
  - Action firm but not resistant in an abrupt or gritty way.', null, '3.4.1 Tightness vs User-Friendliness', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Tightness vs User-Friendliness', '["3-4-1-tightness-vs-user-friendliness","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-tightness-vs-user-friendliness"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('ad0cd73c-ef39-4702-8b8d-a4adcc5e1f56', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '17', '39', 'Perazzi offers barrel lengths from **short (e.g., ~26")** up to **long trap barrels (~34")**, with handling implications:

- **Longer barrels**
  - More forward weight.
  - Longer sighting plane.
  - Often favored for:
    - Trap (steady swing on rising targets).
    - Longer sporting targets.
- **Shorter barrels**
  - Faster to start and stop.
  - Favored for:
    - Skeet.
    - Driven game.
    - Very fast target presentations.

Perazzi’s approach:

- Let the shooter choose length by discipline and preference.
- Then adjust barrel profiles and stock balance so:
  - A given model line retains a **consistent character** across lengths, where physics allows.
- For example:
  - A **34" trap barrel** may be profiled slightly lighter to avoid being overly front-heavy.
  - A **30" sporting barrel** might be a touch heavier to carry momentum.', null, '3.2.4 Barrel Length and Handling', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Fit, Balance & Handling Characteristics > 3.2.4 Barrel Length and Handling', '["3-2-4-barrel-length-and-handling","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-2-fit-balance-handling-characteristics-3-2-4-barrel-length-and-handling"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('adb08b3d-1ebb-44cb-b11e-f48d7db2e251', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '25', '38', '- Maintains a personal set of stones and tools worn into precise shapes for particular sear notches.  
- Guards these tools as “signature instruments,” used to impart a distinct, consistent feel to all triggers from their bench.', null, '3.7.2 Customized, Ultra-Fine Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.2 Customized, Ultra-Fine Tools', '["3-7-2-customized-ultra-fine-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-2-customized-ultra-fine-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('adb8cb5c-77ab-471e-8e83-7058ea3b12db', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '33', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2024 5 | Base model: high-tech-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2024 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 2024 5', 'Models > High Tech 2024 5', '["model-details","high-tech-2024-5","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('adda30bc-9277-4f9f-87cb-bdf86495e7e3', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '169', '238', 'Model name: MX20 SC3 Gold Sideplates | Base model: mx20 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 Gold Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX20 SC3 Gold Sideplates', 'Models > MX20 SC3 Gold Sideplates', '["model-details","mx20-sc3-gold-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('ade0979f-bbb0-4843-8fa9-3b4a37d7ae85', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '1', '51', 'This document describes the **Final Inspection, Proof Marks & Sign-Off** station in the Perazzi factory.

At this station, a **fully assembled, test‑fired, and fitted shotgun** receives a last, comprehensive inspection before leaving the factory. The final inspector:

- Verifies that **every feature** matches the order (model, barrel length, chokes, engraving pattern and grade, stock dimensions, handedness, accessories, etc.).
- Confirms that all **serial numbers and proof marks** are present, correct, and legible.
- Performs a final **fit, finish, and function** check, correcting any remaining cosmetic or minor mechanical issues.
- Ensures the gun is **immaculately clean, properly lubricated, and correctly cased** with all required accessories and documents.
- Signs off the gun in **internal records**, completing the manufacturing journey.

The output is a shotgun that conforms **exactly** to Perazzi standards and to the customer’s specification, ready to delight the owner without the factory ever seeing it returned for flaws.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('ae1b7836-97fd-4083-8f94-d6e1d634b0ad', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '33', '38', 'Josh Poole is portrayed as a standout in American skeet with a dramatic early rise.

