- Daniele’s children, **Mauro** and **Roberta Perazzi**, join the business and progressively assume leadership roles.
- **2012** – Daniele Perazzi dies at age 80, shortly after the **London 2012 Olympics**, where shooters using Perazzi shotguns win **12 of 15 shotgun medals**.[11]
  - Mauro becomes company president, and the family continues to lead the company.[3][15]
- **2023** – **CSG Group** acquires an **80% stake** in Perazzi; Mauro and Roberta retain **20% ownership** and operational control. The partnership is framed as securing Perazzi’s long-term future while preserving its family-led philosophy.[12][13][14]', null, '3.1.4 Consolidation, Medals, and Modern Era', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Company History and Ownership Timeline > 3.1.4 Consolidation, Medals, and Modern Era', '["3-1-4-consolidation-medals-and-modern-era","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-1-company-history-and-ownership-timeline-3-1-4-consolidation-medals-and-modern-era"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('b1f99a0f-9980-4bd2-8488-1f547438d736', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '35', '39', '- Using soft solder for ribs constrains finishing options (e.g., requiring rust bluing to avoid melting solder).  
- Changing solder alloys without adjusting finishing processes can lead to joint failures.

**Caveat:** All joining and finishing decisions must be coordinated to protect both structural integrity and corrosion resistance.', null, '4.4 Solder and Finishing Interactions', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.4 Solder and Finishing Interactions', '["4-4-solder-and-finishing-interactions","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-4-solder-and-finishing-interactions"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('b21af1b4-b779-42ae-ac95-992bde7b3c6b', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '6', '45', '- **Uniform Color and Tone**  
  - Matching blue-black shade across barrels, action, and other parts (unless intentionally contrasted).

- **Mirror Polish vs Satin Finish**  
  - Mirror: extremely smooth, reflective surfaces, especially on barrels.  
  - Satin: controlled, fine texture that diffuses light, often preferred on glare-prone surfaces like top ribs.

- **“Wet-Looking” Blue**  
  - Deep, lustrous blue-black appearance commonly associated with high-quality rust bluing, especially on polished barrels.

- **White-Glove Standard**  
  - Informal benchmark indicating that finished parts have no burrs, residual compounds, or overlooked defects; they withstand scrutiny under bright light and touch.

---', null, '2.5 Quality & Aesthetic Terms', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.5 Quality & Aesthetic Terms', '["2-5-quality-aesthetic-terms","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-5-quality-aesthetic-terms"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('b23a7ac8-e39f-4388-b044-81415a357b40', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '33', '45', '- Barrel and action surfaces show **no waves or ripples**; reflections move smoothly.  
- Flats truly look flat; curves are continuous without kinks or flats.  
- Design lines remain crisp, enhancing the gun’s overall architecture.', null, '3.7.1 Perfect Surfaces & Lines', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.1 Perfect Surfaces & Lines', '["3-7-1-perfect-surfaces-lines","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-1-perfect-surfaces-lines"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('b2c31236-ae9e-4a9d-be36-a904f1f6e255', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '4', '51', '- **Checkering Cutters**  
  - Small saw- or file-like tools with multiple teeth used to cut lines.  
  - Types include single-line cutters, double-line (spacing) cutters, and safe-sided cutters with one smooth edge for border work.

- **V-Tool / Veiner**  
  - Small V-shaped cutting tool used to start lines, deepen grooves, or cut border lines.

- **Safe-Sided Cutter**  
  - Cutter with one smooth edge that can ride against a border without cutting past it.

- **Checkering Cradle / Stock Holder**  
  - Padded fixture that holds the stock or fore-end securely and can rotate to present surfaces at comfortable angles.

- **Lighting & Magnification**  
  - Strong, often oblique light and sometimes magnifiers to highlight groove shadows and fine details.', null, '2.3 Tools & Fixtures Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Tools & Fixtures Concepts', '["2-3-tools-fixtures-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-tools-fixtures-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('b2ed3b95-394b-47f5-871c-a36e251e1abd', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '1', '49', 'This document describes the **Patterning & Performance Testing station** in the Perazzi factory.

At this station, the **fully assembled shotgun** is test-fired with **live ammunition** to verify:

- **Point of impact (POI)** and barrel **regulation** (how the two barrels’ POIs relate).
- **Pattern distribution and density** for each barrel vs. its choke designation.
- **Live-fire behavior** of mechanical systems already checked in dry tests:
  - Ejectors/extractors.
  - Trigger reset and second-shot function (especially inertia triggers).
  - Overall recoil feel and functioning under real conditions.

This station provides the final **performance proof** that the gun:

- Shoots where it is supposed to shoot (for the intended discipline and customer specification).
- Produces patterns that match choke expectations.
- Behaves mechanically under recoil as expected.

The output is a **test‑fired, performance-verified shotgun**, often with pattern data that can be shared with the customer or used for final fitting.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('b2ef8076-1b9b-4ca0-a4d9-029e7170a981', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '31', '40', '- Masters can fit and shape a stock in a fraction of the time an apprentice needs—without sacrificing precision.  
- They know exactly which areas to adjust to shift POI slightly:  
  - For example, moving shot pattern slightly left or right through tiny cast or toe changes achieved by careful shaving on one side.  
- They can make small corrections after test-firing and incorporate them seamlessly.', null, '3.7.3 Efficiency with Care & Micro Corrections', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.3 Efficiency with Care & Micro Corrections', '["3-7-3-efficiency-with-care-micro-corrections","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-3-efficiency-with-care-micro-corrections"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('b306cc9d-23b4-48cd-b882-2943f4d3b735', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '3', '51', '- **Serial Number**  
  - Unique identifier stamped (and sometimes engraved) on major parts: barrel monobloc, action/receiver, fore-end iron, etc.  
  - Must match across all serialised parts and records.

- **Proof Marks**  
  - Stamps applied by the official proof house (e.g., Brescia) verifying that barrels (and sometimes actions) passed pressure tests.  
  - Include symbols such as:
    - Proof house stamp.  
    - Year code/date mark.  
    - Gauge designation and bore measurement (e.g., “18.4”).  
    - Chamber length marking (e.g., “CAM 70” for 70 mm).  
    - Marks indicating superior proof (e.g., for steel shot), where applicable.

- **Order Specification Sheet**  
  - Document describing all ordered features (e.g., model, barrel length, chokes, engraving pattern, wood grade, stock dimensions, handedness, accessories).  
  - Used as the primary reference for final verification.

- **Proof Certificate / Ballistic Test Document**  
  - Official documentation from the proof house (and/or internal test targets) accompanying the gun, used for legal and assurance purposes.', null, '2.2 Identity & Legal Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Identity & Legal Concepts', '["2-2-identity-legal-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-identity-legal-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('b3441652-3b22-4fed-be3a-db47f5360e30', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '46', '51', '- Final inspector may coordinate with shipping/export staff to ensure that:  
  - Gun details on export papers match actual markings.  
  - Serial numbers, model names, and descriptions are accurate.  
- Errors here can cause customs delays; extra care is needed.', null, '4.3 Export & Customs Documentation', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.3 Export & Customs Documentation', '["4-3-export-customs-documentation","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-3-export-customs-documentation"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('b382b84e-de8f-4593-af5f-883b04c9cc14', '500269f5-9624-4f5b-9ded-8de9740793b2', '5', '7', 'Aftermarket parts are not produced to the same precision, tolerances, hardness and metallurgy as factory produced parts. Use of aftermarket parts could compromise performance, functionality, reliability and accelerate wear. Perazzi USA and authorized gunsmiths have the right to refuse any service on guns with these parts. Beware of gunsmiths that do not disclose the use of these parts.', null, 'Aftermarket Parts', 'Consumer Warning Notice > Aftermarket Parts', '["aftermarket-parts","consumer-warning-notice-aftermarket-parts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:16.184829+00', null), ('b3d1c04c-ebc7-4bef-8c8a-f8cdcfe51f44', '4ae532ea-bef9-47fe-9bd9-051858902e2f', '18', '23', 'Mauro Perazzi remarked that **“the hand assembly is where the gun’s soul is born.”**

As a model:

- Visualize all parts as **lifeless pieces** arriving at final assembly.  
- Through careful tuning by master gunsmiths, the gun becomes a **cohesive whole**:
  - Trigger feel set.  
  - Action opening and closing tuned.  
  - Stock and barrels balanced.

This is the **culmination point** where all previous stages feed into a single outcome: a gun with a recognizable “character” in the hands of the shooter.

Thinking of assembly as the moment where all flows (**materials, information, craftsmanship**) converge helps unify the entire handbook.

---', null, '3.3.5 “Gun’s Soul” Convergence Model', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Mental Models & Diagrams > 3.3.5 “Gun’s Soul” Convergence Model', '["3-3-5-gun-s-soul-convergence-model","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-3-main-content-3-3-mental-models-diagrams-3-3-5-gun-s-soul-convergence-model"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('b3d94497-4466-45a0-ad31-762f7188c6f8', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '34', '53', '- **Symptoms:** Scratches, dull spots, or crazing of finish caused by tools, bending, or sanding.  
- **Response:**  
  - Local re‑oiling, polishing, or small refinishing patches to blend defects.  
  - Prevent by protecting surfaces during mechanical operations and using careful tool handling.', null, '3.6.3 Finish Damage During Adjustments', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.3 Finish Damage During Adjustments', '["3-6-3-finish-damage-during-adjustments","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-3-finish-damage-during-adjustments"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('b4500fb3-5b91-4f2f-b9e7-f246684a52d9', '177a681e-a602-4d92-af07-b17c98816feb', '4', '13', '- **Definition:** The specific stylistic and structural patterns used to express the tone of voice, including word choice, narrative structure, and use of repetition and layering.', null, '2.3 Style and Language Choices', 'Perazzi Writing Style and Tone (AI-Optimized Reference) > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Style and Language Choices', '["2-3-style-and-language-choices","perazzi-writing-style-and-tone-ai-optimized-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-style-and-language-choices"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:49.998824+00', null), ('b45519c0-d592-4ad5-ab51-79a6b93e0e1d', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '34', '58', '- Typical end-to-end timeline: **6–9 months**, sometimes up to a year for complex orders.[68]
- Completed guns are shipped with a Perazzi case; customers may choose case styles and colors (e.g., traditional red ABS).[96]
- Many guns serve as **multi-decade competition tools and family heirlooms**, supported by long-term parts availability.[97]

---', null, '3.6.4 Delivery and Lifecycle', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Customization and Ordering Process > 3.6.4 Delivery and Lifecycle', '["3-6-4-delivery-and-lifecycle","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-6-customization-and-ordering-process-3-6-4-delivery-and-lifecycle"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('b4b636c5-ef1e-41e8-9ecd-1d3bdbf12f2c', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '39', '45', '- Some customers request extremely high gloss for showpieces.  
- These require additional coats, meticulous leveling, and often a final rub-out to keep the finish looking **deep rather than plastic**.

**Caveat:**  
- These finishes are more prone to visible scratches and may require careful handling and maintenance.', null, '4.1 Exhibition-Grade, High-Gloss Finishes', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Exhibition-Grade, High-Gloss Finishes', '["4-1-exhibition-grade-high-gloss-finishes","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-exhibition-grade-high-gloss-finishes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('b4c01b48-211f-43a7-b86b-32704c113ac7', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '28', '38', 'Michael initially shot with other brands, including Kolar Arms[92], but now shoots a Perazzi trap shotgun.

Key equipment details:

- Perazzi MX-series combo with high-profile rib barrels.  
- Preferred for sustained leads and hard trap angles.  
- He notes that he loves the trigger feel and hammer speed of his Perazzi, which suits his quick style.

The source states that shortly after switching to Perazzi, he:

- Shot a perfect 400×400 to win the Texas State HOA as a visitor.  
- Posted his career-best year for averages.

On the firing line, he is depicted as in total harmony with his Perazzi: natural fit to shoulder and cheek, decisive calls for the target, and smooth transitions between posts. His ongoing career is framed as a bright future for American Trap with Perazzi as a key partner.

---', null, '3.2.4.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Supported Shooters > 3.2.4 Michael Wengard (Wengerd) – American Trap (Supported Shooter) > 3.2.4.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', '["3-2-4-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-2-supported-shooters-3-2-4-michael-wengard-wengerd-american-trap-supported-shooter-3-2-4-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('b4cdb0a8-9ece-434f-a050-287efd9fc137', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '24', '36', 'The Perazzi brand experience is defined by several recurring elements:', null, '3.6 The Perazzi Experience', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.6 The Perazzi Experience', '["3-6-the-perazzi-experience","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-6-the-perazzi-experience"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('b4f3e0ab-302f-4e1b-a2c3-700d273feabe', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '15', '35', '- **Machine-Then-Harden vs. Harden-Then-Finish**  
  - If receivers are case-hardened to create a hard outer skin, the process can cause slight warping.  
  - Machinists must decide which operations to perform **before** hardening and which to reserve for **after** to restore final dimensions.

**Typical approach (conceptual):**

- Rough out and partially finish the receiver.  
- Apply case hardening.  
- Perform final machining and/or hand fitting to account for any distortion.', null, '3.4.3 Heat Treatment Sequence', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Heat Treatment Sequence', '["3-4-3-heat-treatment-sequence","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-heat-treatment-sequence"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('b65f56cc-e81b-4fe4-83c2-ec6d783922c0', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '4', '45', '- **Polishing**  
  - Progressive removal of tool marks using files, abrasives, and buffing to achieve smooth or mirror-like surfaces.

- **Critical Fit Surfaces**  
  - Areas whose geometry must not be altered by polishing or finishing, such as:
    - Locking lugs and hooks.
    - Hinge pin bores and bearing surfaces.
    - Internal sear/hammer interfaces.
    - Forend iron contact surfaces.

- **Edges and Design Lines**  
  - Intentional sharp lines that define the shape of the receiver, trigger guard, and other parts.  
  - Must be preserved (or only gently broken) to maintain crisp design and good wood-to-metal fit.

- **Matte vs Gloss Texture**  
  - Gloss: high reflectivity, mirror-like finish (e.g., barrel sides).  
  - Matte: reduced reflectivity to reduce glare (e.g., top ribs, top tangs), achieved by file cuts, bead blasting, or controlled polishing.', null, '2.3 Surface & Geometry Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Surface & Geometry Concepts', '["2-3-surface-geometry-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-surface-geometry-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('b68c16e1-928e-450d-944a-9d68d91e4a05', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '54', '238', 'Model name: High Tech P | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: P | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech P', 'Models > High Tech P', '["model-details","high-tech-p","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('b6fb4f3e-fd1b-4c50-9418-b913643d7768', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '30', '49', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Barrel patterns consistently separated in POI (e.g., one high, one low, or one left/right of the other) beyond acceptable tolerance.

- **Diagnosis:**  
  - Multiple patterns per barrel to confirm consistent offset.  
  - Testing at shorter and standard distances to see how separation scales.

- **Potential Causes:**  
  - Barrel regulation error not fully corrected earlier.  
  - Slight misalignment introduced during later work.

- **Remedies:**  
  - **Minor offsets**: barrel bending to bring POIs together.  
  - **Significant mis-regulation**: may require barrel disassembly/re‑regulation (major rework, avoided unless necessary).', null, '3.6.1 Mis-Regulation (Barrels Not Shooting Together)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.1 Mis-Regulation (Barrels Not Shooting Together)', '["3-6-1-mis-regulation-barrels-not-shooting-together","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-1-mis-regulation-barrels-not-shooting-together"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('b7543c69-51ba-470a-85f1-ad2755f8875a', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '36', '40', '- Some heavy-recoil or high-volume guns may benefit from reinforcing elements (e.g., cross-bolts or rods in the wrist, depending on brand practices).  
- While not explicitly detailed in this text for Perazzi, the general principle is that reinforcement must not undermine aesthetics or create stress risers.', null, '4.3 Reinforcement Strategies', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.3 Reinforcement Strategies', '["4-3-reinforcement-strategies","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-3-reinforcement-strategies"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('b764e602-502e-4607-88d2-26e9662d9735', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '109', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S SCO Gold | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S SCO Gold', 'Models > High Tech S SCO Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-s-sco-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('b76b24fc-fdc1-4c0f-a4dc-f2fe57e4b9e8', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '29', '56', '- **Bore Light / Borescope**  
  - Final internal barrel inspection (cleanliness, residues).

