  - Fore-end difficult to latch or remove; or loose and rattling.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Over-tight or under-tight latch engagement; misfitted fore-end iron.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Evaluate closing force and fit; check for gaps or movement.  
  - Slightly adjust internal metal surfaces (stoning, peening) for proper fit.', null, '3.6.8 Fore-end Latch Problems', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.8 Fore-end Latch Problems', '["3-6-8-fore-end-latch-problems","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-8-fore-end-latch-problems"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('b8d5d681-b258-4d58-a4e6-9d76565c30f3', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '43', '45', '- **Upstream:**  
  - **Stock Inletting & Final Shaping Station (Part II.F)** – provides fully shaped and fitted stock and fore-end with final geometry.  
  - **Checkering Station (Part II.G)** – provides crisp checkered surfaces that must be protected and respected during finishing.

- **Parallel / Lateral:**  
