  - **Also referred to as:** “Supported Shooters.”  
  - **Definition:** An athlete listed in the original text under the “Supported Shooters” heading; still closely associated with Perazzi but distinguished from primary team shooters by category label.', null, '2.1 Athlete Categories', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Athlete Categories', '["2-1-athlete-categories","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-athlete-categories"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('bb541de0-d457-4ee9-9c37-860be6524fee', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '7', '53', 'The **Final Fitting & Customer-Specific Adjustments** station:

- Takes a gun built to **initial measurements or standard spec** and aligns it with the **actual shooter** using it.  
- Fine‑tunes stock geometry (LOP, drop, cast, pitch, toe angle, comb height/width) and trigger reach/feel.  
- Adjusts **balance and weight** with small additions or removals.  
- Tailors subjective details such as pad type, pad edge rounding, and minor ergonomics so the gun mounts and swings naturally.  
- Confirms real‑world shooting comfort and performance via pattern board checks or shooting clay targets.', null, '3.1.1 Purpose', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.1 Purpose', '["3-1-1-purpose","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-1-purpose"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('bb74f5ce-d773-4138-ad0e-403e4ed9c2d3', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '35', '45', '- Rust-blued barrels exhibit a **deep, inky blue-black** with uniform tone end-to-end.  
- There are no “holidays” (missed spots) or color blotches; even under strong light, color appears smooth.  
- The finish balances mirror gloss and functional matte zones exactly where intended.', null, '3.7.3 Consistent, Deep Bluing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.3 Consistent, Deep Bluing', '["3-7-3-consistent-deep-bluing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-3-consistent-deep-bluing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('bba4750b-f7bb-4896-9b46-48a612ebcf77', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '11', '38', 'The trigger specialist combines **fine mechanical understanding** with **watchmaker-level hand skills**.

Key domains:

- **Trigger Mechanics**  
  - Detailed understanding of how sear geometry (angle and depth) influences:  
    - Pull weight.  
    - Creep vs crisp break.  
    - Safety margins against jar-off.  
  - Familiarity with inertia vs mechanical systems:  
    - Inertia block mass and spring behavior.  
    - Mechanical linkages that reset sears without recoil.

- **Fine Hand-Fitting and Polishing**  
  - Using magnification and ultra-fine stones to polish sear and hammer contact surfaces to near-mirror finish.  
  - Understanding that removing a few microns of material can radically change behavior.  
  - Achieving the “glass rod break” feel without compromising safety.

- **Spring Behavior and Tuning**  
  - Knowing how to fit and seat coil springs correctly.  
  - Handling leaf springs carefully and understanding their higher performance and breakage risk.  
  - Occasionally adjusting leaf springs (e.g., slight bending) when necessary for consistent force, while respecting design limits.

- **Safety Systems Knowledge**  
  - Fitting and testing manual safety: ensuring full block when engaged, with positive detent feel.  
  - Understanding and fitting barrel selector: consistent switching of first-barrel preference without inducing misfires or doubles.  
  - Awareness of concepts like intercepting sears (even if not used in a specific design) and general best practices for safe lockwork.

- **Diagnostic and Testing Skills**  
  - Performing systematic tests:  
    - Cocking, snapping, and resetting repeatedly.  
    - Jar/bump tests to check for accidental release.  
    - Testing safety engagement under deliberate attempts to fire.  
  - Reading subtle rub marks and soot/marking patterns on sear noses and hammer notches to understand engagement.

- **Terminology and Communication**  
  - Using terms like sear engagement, creep, over-travel, reset, take-up, pull weight, and lock time precisely.  
  - Communicating with stock fitters (e.g., about adjustable trigger shoes) and others for coordinated fitting.

- **Microscopic Tolerances Awareness**  
  - Working at tolerances in hundredths of millimeters.  
  - Adjusting pin fit (polishing pins lightly) to remove play without binding.  
  - Selecting from multiple nominally identical parts to get the best combination of geometry and feel.

A master triggersmith has a **mental catalog** of part behaviors and knows how to combine and tune components to get consistent, safe trigger feel across many guns.

---', null, '3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills', '["3-3-core-knowledge-skills","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('bbed97cc-d0b3-4e5b-afe7-b616a1f44fc5', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '36', '49', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Test shooter notices misalignment of front bead or mid-bead with rib line.

- **Diagnosis:**  
  - Visual inspection of beads and rib: off-center beads, canted threads.

- **Remedies:**  
  - Re-align or replace beads; ensure proper centering and orientation.

---', null, '3.6.7 Sight & Bead Alignment Issues', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.7 Sight & Bead Alignment Issues', '["3-6-7-sight-bead-alignment-issues","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-7-sight-bead-alignment-issues"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('bc317780-1cfb-4731-84ef-51288833b566', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '18', '58', '- Material: Proprietary high-grade **chromoly steel**; exact composition is closely guarded.[24]
- Manufacturing philosophy:  
  - Perazzi rejects **cold hammer forging** for top-tier barrels, arguing it can over-harden steel and induce stress.[25]  
  - Barrels are machined, honed, and hand-lapped to achieve desired elasticity and harmonics.
- Bores:  
  - Polished, non-chrome-lined bores; this is a deliberate choice for pattern consistency and feel rather than ease of cleaning.[26]  
  - Available bore diameters (12 gauge) typically range from **18.3–18.9 mm**, often customer-specified.[27]
- Lengths & profiles:  
  - Common lengths: approx. **29.5"**, **30.75"**, **31.5"** (metric equivalents 75, 78, 80 cm).[28]  
  - Barrel weights can be ordered heavier or lighter to tune swing and balance.[37][38]
- Ribs:  
  - Flat, semi-high, high, and extra-high ribs, including adjustable designs with three to five POI positions.[29][72]  
  - High-rib and adjustable-rib designs are common on trap and bunker guns (e.g. MX10, MX2000/3, HT RS).  
  - Sporting models typically use lower ribs for a 50/50 POI.  
  - Rib widths and profiles (e.g. 11x7, 11x11, 7x7) are selectable.[72]
- Chokes and side ribs:  
  - Fixed chokes are standard; constrictions can be specified per barrel (e.g. Skeet/Improved Cylinder, IM/Full).[70][71]  
  - Screw-in multi-chokes available as an option, with sets of tubes.  
  - Side ribs can be solid, ventilated, or deleted (skeet or lightweight configurations).[30][74]
- Regulation:  
  - Each O/U barrel set is soldered and regulated so both barrels shoot to the same POI.  
  - Regulation is verified on a pattern plate and in test tunnels at the factory.[43]', null, '3.3.2 Barrels', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Technical Design and Manufacturing > 3.3.2 Barrels', '["3-3-2-barrels","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-3-technical-design-and-manufacturing-3-3-2-barrels"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('bc3b60c0-4ec0-4506-ad87-1e770f2359c5', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '26', '32', '- **Goal**  
  Fine-tune fit and personalization for the individual shooter (when possible), so the gun feels like an **extension of the shooter**.

- **Inputs**  
  - Assembled, test-fired shotgun.  
  - Customer feedback or fitter’s observations.  
  - Tools for minor adjustments:
    - Trigger shoe position.  
    - Adjustable comb hardware.  
    - Recoil pad shims.  
    - Bending tools for stock cast.

- **Outputs**  
  - Gun customized to the shooter’s feel:
    - Subtle stock bends for perfect cast.  
    - Comb height adjusted to refine point of impact.  
  - Last-minute refinements completed.

- **Owned by**  
  **Gun fitter** (may be the stock specialist or a dedicated fitter, often working directly with the customer).

---', null, '3.3.15 Final Fitting & Customer Adjustments', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.3 End-to-End Production Process Map > 3.3.15 Final Fitting & Customer Adjustments', '["3-3-15-final-fitting-customer-adjustments","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-3-end-to-end-production-process-map-3-3-15-final-fitting-customer-adjustments"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('bc3d1f78-c58f-4a28-b974-390a88fa97b4', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '16', '39', 'This section describes methods that Perazzi shares with other **top-tier shotgun makers**, particularly in the European best-gun tradition.', null, '3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices', '["3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('bc517400-479f-4854-9e25-2fd6063dbec8', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '8', '39', '- Many manufacturers buy barrel tubes from specialized mills; Perazzi instead **produces its own barrels end-to-end**.
- Benefits:
  - Tight control over **steel sourcing, alloy composition, and internal dimensions**.
  - Barrels can be:
    - Straightened by skilled specialists.
    - Custom-choked and honed to spec.
- Observations:
  - Factory tours (e.g., AllOutdoor coverage) note that in-house barrel making is a **distinct point of pride and differentiation** for Perazzi.
- Performance implications:
  - Supports Perazzi’s claims of **pattern consistency, strength, and long-term endurance**.', null, '3.1.3 Barrel Making In-House', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations > 3.1.3 Barrel Making In-House', '["3-1-3-barrel-making-in-house","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations-3-1-3-barrel-making-in-house"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('bc93131f-8cbb-487b-8903-99e55fa603bb', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '15', '58', '- **Mirage** – Historically, an MX8 variant marketed as the “Ithaca Perazzi Mirage” in some markets.[20]
- **Comp I (Competition I)** – Early O/U model name used before MX naming fully standardized.
- **MT6** – 1970s fixed-trigger O/U, associated with the 1976 Montreal Olympics, seen as a forerunner of MX12.[16]
- **MXS** – Modern fixed-trigger sporting model line, often positioned as a more accessible sporting clays gun.
- **Pigeon grade guns** – Configurations optimized for live-pigeon and helice shooting, usually heavier, tight-choked, and with no safety.', null, '3.2.5 Other Notable Model Names', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Product Platform Architecture > 3.2.5 Other Notable Model Names', '["3-2-5-other-notable-model-names","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-2-product-platform-architecture-3-2-5-other-notable-model-names"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('bc9e53ab-8f1c-43ee-ae1a-4c70c37e3082', '500269f5-9624-4f5b-9ded-8de9740793b2', '2', '7', 'Some firearms may be altered with non-original sideplates to mimic higher-grade models. These additions may not meet Perazzi’s quality standards, be potentially dangerous and can misrepresent the shotgun’s authenticity and value. Always confirm authenticity through Perazzi’s official verification process. As stated above, guns with aftermarket sideplates are counterfeits.', null, 'False Sideplates', 'Consumer Warning Notice > False Sideplates', '["false-sideplates","consumer-warning-notice-false-sideplates"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:16.184829+00', null), ('bcba2b59-3e5c-4214-974d-73bce10eb644', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '4', '53', '- **Adjustable Comb**  
  - Hardware allowing comb to move up/down (height) and sometimes sideways (cast at comb).  
  - Adjusted with hex keys or screwdrivers; often includes posts, locking screws, and optional spacers/shims.

- **Stock Bending**  
  - Controlled bending of the finished stock (typically at the wrist) using heat and a bending jig to change cast and/or drop by small amounts.  
  - Requires knowledge of wood behavior and finish tolerance.

- **Recoil Pad & Spacers**  
  - Pad: rubber or synthetic butt piece that softens recoil and defines butt shape.  
  - Spacers: flat or tapered inserts between stock and pad to adjust LOP and/or pitch (e.g., 1/8", 1/4").

- **Weight & Balance Adjustments**  
  - Additional weight (e.g., inserted in stock bolt hole) to shift balance rearward or change total gun weight.  
  - Sometimes barrel weights if needed.

- **Adjustable Trigger Shoe**  
  - Trigger blade that can slide fore/aft on a rail to adjust trigger reach relative to LOP and grip size.', null, '2.3 Adjustment & Hardware Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Adjustment & Hardware Concepts', '["2-3-adjustment-hardware-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-adjustment-hardware-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('bcf0a73e-eaae-475f-95b4-20f01b7e4068', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '17', '39', '- Like other fine makers (e.g., London best-gun houses, Beretta SO series), Perazzi guns involve extensive **hand fitting** of parts.
- Practices:
  - Machined surfaces left slightly “proud.”
  - Contact points marked with soot or marker.
  - Carefully filed and scraped to achieve:
    - Invisible joints.
    - Smooth, bank-vault lock-up.
- Rationale:
  - Hand fitting ensures **stress is evenly distributed** over bearing surfaces.
  - Promotes long-term durability and a characteristic “feel” when opening/closing the gun.', null, '3.2.1 Hand Fitting', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices > 3.2.1 Hand Fitting', '["3-2-1-hand-fitting","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices-3-2-1-hand-fitting"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('bd0e27eb-5716-4d48-bcf8-a4b8f3766c0f', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '34', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 3 | Base model: high-tech-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 3', 'Models > High Tech 3', '["model-details","high-tech-3","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('bd6be57b-3727-4187-a420-e1a9056f6830', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '18', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: 2020 | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech 2020', 'Models > High Tech 2020', '["model-details","high-tech-2020","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('bd8b3037-5545-4954-9ba6-5c6e43139f63', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '89', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 5 | Base model: high-tech-s-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S 5', 'Models > High Tech S 5', '["model-details","high-tech-s-5","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('bda9b4e3-d2bf-49fd-a9ce-cdcf98047b36', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '35', '38', '- **Citation markers `[n]`:**  
