4. Check **Dealers & Events** for real-world engagement.', null, '3.2.3 Enthusiast Journey (Fan, Researcher, or Collector)', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 3. Core Experiences & Main Site Areas > 3.2 User Journeys Through the Site > 3.2.3 Enthusiast Journey (Fan, Researcher, or Collector)', '["3-2-3-enthusiast-journey-fan-researcher-or-collector","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-3-core-experiences-main-site-areas-3-2-user-journeys-through-the-site-3-2-3-enthusiast-journey-fan-researcher-or-collector"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('c7bc7c00-4c04-42a1-a271-90afbe2fb261', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '2', '26', 'Perazzi’s audience can be understood through a set of **five motivational archetypes**. These are not boxes or rigid labels; they are patterns in what people value, what they are seeking, and how they relate to a gun that is more than equipment.

The archetypes described here are:

- **Loyalist**  
- **Prestige**  
- **Analyst**  
- **Achiever**  
- **Legacy**

Each archetype represents:

- A **core drive** (What do they want from their gun and brand?).  
- A **relationship posture** (How do they show up toward Perazzi?).  
- A set of **resonant messages** (What language, stories, and emphasis feel natural to them?).

Most real people are a **blend** of these archetypes. The goal is not to label individuals, but to recognize patterns so that:

- Brand communication feels like it “gets” them.  
- Guidance from Perazzi (human or digital) can meet them where they are, while still pulling them toward the deeper ethos of the brand.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'V2_Audience-Psychology-and-Archetypes.md > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","v2-audience-psychology-and-archetypes-md-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:40.516062+00', null), ('c80b545f-3362-45a0-846a-8dbb25aca6db', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '2', '32', '- **Perazzi**  
  Italian maker of high-end, bespoke over-under competition shotguns, founded in 1957 by **Daniele Perazzi**. The company focuses on clay target disciplines such as Olympic trap, skeet, and sporting clays. Its mission is to blend best-of-British craft principles with modern manufacturing to create shotguns of exceptional performance and durability.

- **Perazzi Competition Shotgun**  
  A Perazzi O/U purpose-built for high-volume competitive use. Designed as a long-lived “competition workhorse” capable of firing hundreds of thousands of rounds over its lifetime, not as a fragile museum piece.[1]', null, '2.1 Core Entities', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Core Entities', '["2-1-core-entities","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-core-entities"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('c82fc273-c384-4f0a-8fe4-e181ed0cdd90', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '41', '51', '- Under magnification, each diamond looks sharply defined with **neatly intersecting grooves**.  
- There are no random flats or ragged edges.  
- The pattern has a subtle, lively sparkle as light hits the many micro-facets.', null, '3.7.3 Micro-Level Precision & Sparkle', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.3 Micro-Level Precision & Sparkle', '["3-7-3-micro-level-precision-sparkle","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-3-micro-level-precision-sparkle"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('c8371e6c-e3f1-4ec8-97cd-e5d5a71d5b83', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '1', '51', 'This document describes the **Checkering station** in the Perazzi factory.

At this station, the fully shaped stock and fore-end are given **hand-cut checkering**: a criss-cross pattern of fine grooves that:

- Provides a **secure, non-slip grip** for the shooter’s hands under sweat and recoil.
- Adds a **classic decorative element** that signals craftsmanship and quality.

The focus is on:

- Where checkering is placed.
- How the pattern is laid out and cut.
- What “perfect” checkering looks and feels like.
- The decision-making around lines-per-inch (LPI), pattern coverage, borders, and depth.
- Common failure modes and how experts avoid or repair them.
- The defining traits of mastery in checkering at Perazzi.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('c84a3222-2c17-49c8-851a-dd523f55476c', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '23', '51', '- After substantial final fit adjustments (e.g., bending, major mechanical tweaks), inspector may decide whether **additional test firing** is needed.  
- In many cases, earlier patterning and test firing suffice; in others, a final shot or two may provide extra assurance.', null, '3.4.4 Post‑Adjustment Test Firing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Post‑Adjustment Test Firing', '["3-4-4-post-adjustment-test-firing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-post-adjustment-test-firing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('c84c2e7b-ae8b-4eb0-960d-d2a7faf05e57', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '1', '56', 'This document describes the **Assembly & Mechanical Quality Control (QC) station** in the Perazzi factory.

At this station, all **finished components** of the shotgun are:

- Brought together into the **fully assembled firearm**.
- **Function-tested** and tuned so that all mechanisms work together smoothly.
- Checked to ensure the gun meets **mechanical, safety, and feel** criteria before pattern testing and delivery.

This station:

- Confirms that work from **all upstream stations** (design, machining, barrel fabrication, trigger assembly, stocking, finishing) integrates correctly.
- Performs detailed **mechanical QC** on:
  - Lock-up and headspace.
  - Triggers, safety, and barrel selector.
  - Ejectors and extraction.
  - Firing pin protrusion and strike quality.
  - Balance, weight, and general “Perazzi feel”.
- Sends any issues back to the relevant station for correction as needed.

The output is a **mechanically flawless, fully assembled shotgun** that is ready for pattern testing, final fitting, and delivery.

