  - Cons: edges may look less defined; stray lines can be more noticeable.

**Practical approach:**  
- On Perazzi competition guns, straightforward checkering with **clean borders** is common, reinforcing a precise, purposeful aesthetic.', null, '3.4.3 Borders vs Borderless Edges', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.3 Borders vs Borderless Edges', '["3-4-3-borders-vs-borderless-edges","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-3-borders-vs-borderless-edges"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('c8b516c0-3a88-451b-ab51-5ea6e8efa6e7', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '22', '38', 'In her competitive journey, Dania has chosen Perazzi shotguns as trusted partners.

Key equipment details:

- Early use of a Perazzi MX2000 for national and world titles[75].  
