  - Pros: fast unloading, ideal for competition.  
  - Cons: shells fly away; less suitable for some hunters who prefer to retain shells.

- **Extractor-Only Configuration**  
  - Pros: more controlled shell removal; preferred by some game shooters.  
  - Cons: slower operation for high-volume shooting.

**Practical approach:**  
- Configure according to **model and customer order**:  
  - Competition models typically fully eject.  
  - Some builds may have ejector sears disabled or omitted for extractor-only behavior.', null, '3.4.2 Ejectors vs Extractors', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Ejectors vs Extractors', '["3-4-2-ejectors-vs-extractors","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-ejectors-vs-extractors"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('c8de4c1a-a1f8-431a-a4d2-9b7c567cbd56', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '23', '35', 'A master action machinist:

- Programs and runs CNC cycles that remove metal efficiently without shocking tools or the workpiece.  
- Produces surfaces that feel satin-smooth to the touch, especially on action bars and internal walls.  
- Knows which curves (e.g., fences around the standing breech, trigger guard tang transitions) should be subtly refined by hand to remove any hint of "machine" pattern.', null, '3.7.1 Machine Mastery and Surface Finesse', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.1 Machine Mastery and Surface Finesse', '["3-7-1-machine-mastery-and-surface-finesse","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-1-machine-mastery-and-surface-finesse"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('c8e04215-a3c1-4300-a112-5f176d0899e8', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '5', '38', '- **Trigger Pull Weight**  
  - Force required to fire the gun (e.g., ~3.5–4 lbs for many competition triggers, with variations based on shooter preference and discipline).

- **Creep**  
  - Unwanted movement of the trigger before break; minimized in a “crisp” trigger.

- **Over-Travel**  
  - Movement after the sear releases; often minimized or controlled for feel.

- **Reset**  
  - Trigger returning to a position where it can fire again; must be positive and reliable.

- **Lock Time**  
  - Time from trigger break to primer ignition; shorter is generally better for performance.  
  - Perazzi actions are known for fast lock times (reported in the range of ~1.5–2 ms; this is maintained by design rather than measured for each gun).

- **Jar-Off / Bump Safety**  
  - Undesired discharge if the gun is jarred or dropped; proper sear engagement and safety systems prevent this.

- **Doubling**  
  - Both barrels firing at once or unintentionally; a serious safety and competition issue.', null, '2.4 Performance and Safety Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Performance and Safety Concepts', '["2-4-performance-and-safety-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-performance-and-safety-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('c92b1e36-cb1c-43e4-8cbc-63a42b17bc8e', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '7', '32', 'Key differentiator: **extreme customization and fit**.

- Every Perazzi is essentially **made-to-order**. The customer (and/or fitter) can specify:
  - **Stock dimensions** (length of pull, cast, drop, grip shape).
  - **Barrel length** and configuration.
  - **Choke type** (fixed or multi-choke, constriction values).
  - **Rib style** (height, profile).
  - **Trigger configuration** (drop-out vs fixed, spring type).
  - **Aesthetic details** (engraving level, wood grade, finish).[2]

Factory organization reflects this:

- Location: **Botticino, Brescia**, Italy.
- Scale: About **70 specialists** producing roughly **7 shotguns per day** (approx. 1,500–3,000 per year).
- Each gun is built to a **specific shooter’s blueprint**, rather than to a generic spec.

Perazzi explicitly **forgoes economies of scale**. As **Mauro Perazzi** (Daniele’s son) puts it:

> “We are not interested in increasing production. The most important part of the process is the hand assembly, where the gun’s soul is born.”

This philosophy underpins every department in the factory.

---', null, '3.1.3 Custom Fit and Individualization', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi’s Competition Shotguns and Their Heritage > 3.1.3 Custom Fit and Individualization', '["3-1-3-custom-fit-and-individualization","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-s-competition-shotguns-and-their-heritage-3-1-3-custom-fit-and-individualization"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('c936e6fd-faa8-4af8-8a7a-284f9531ee39', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '1', '50', '### Rustam Yambulatov
**Country:** Soviet Union (RUS)
