- ISSF Athlete Profile (indirect confirmation of equipment through Perazzi events):contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}', null, '### Rustam Yambulatov', 'Olympic Medals > Rustam Yambulatov', '["olympic-medals","rustam-yambulatov"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('c979b797-bc4a-487a-af1b-e4de5311b30a', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '35', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Detectable movement between barrels and action when closed.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Insufficient locking bolt engagement; improper bite geometry.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Check lock-up contact pattern; verify top lever position.  
  - Fit slightly oversize locking bolt or adjust bite surfaces.  
  - Ensure new guns leave with zero perceptible play.', null, '3.6.5 Loose on Face (Play at Breech)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.5 Loose on Face (Play at Breech)', '["3-6-5-loose-on-face-play-at-breech","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-5-loose-on-face-play-at-breech"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('c992dedf-05a2-4d2a-b07b-28f07a81fec0', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '4', '32', 'The site is designed to make sense for three primary user types:

- **Prospect** – A shooter who is curious about Perazzi and may be considering a first purchase.
- **Owner** – Someone who already owns a Perazzi and is looking for service, parts, upgrades, or deeper connection.
- **Enthusiast / Fan** – Someone interested in the history, factory, champions, or simply the world around Perazzi.

The same pages may serve more than one audience, but they should always feel coherent through these lenses.', null, '2.1 Primary Audiences', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 2. Site Structure & Area Concepts > 2.1 Primary Audiences', '["2-1-primary-audiences","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-2-site-structure-area-concepts-2-1-primary-audiences"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('c9f63fea-15be-4762-8e13-0d28015f3bb5', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '45', '56', '- Experienced assemblers can build a gun quickly, but they **do not rush QC**.  
- They maintain a mental or written “multi-point check” (e.g., a “12-point” routine) repeated identically for every gun.  
- They prefer to **over-test** rather than risk a missed fault.', null, '3.7.3 Efficiency with Thoroughness', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.3 Efficiency with Thoroughness', '["3-7-3-efficiency-with-thoroughness","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-3-efficiency-with-thoroughness"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('ca56fc48-d0eb-4dde-9672-7c5f2ab0ac21', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '195', '238', 'Model name: MX28 SCO Gold | Base model: mx28 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 28ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX28 SCO Gold', 'Models > MX28 SCO Gold', '["model-details","mx28-sco-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('ca644788-f4a5-422b-acbd-5f9f42a28d07', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '15', '32', '- **Goal**  
  Build a precise, reliable **trigger mechanism and firing system** tuned for crisp release and fast lock times.

- **Inputs**  
  - Machined trigger plate.  
  - Sears, hammers, pins.  
  - Springs (coil or leaf, as specified).  
  - Safety and barrel-selector parts (if applicable).

- **Outputs**  
  - Fully assembled **trigger group** (often detachable).  
  - Firing mechanism tested for:
    - Correct trigger pulls.  
    - Proper sear engagement.  
    - Safety operation.

- **Owned by**  
  **Lockwork specialist** (gunsmith specializing in triggers/locks).

---', null, '3.3.4 Trigger Group & Lockwork Assembly', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.3 End-to-End Production Process Map > 3.3.4 Trigger Group & Lockwork Assembly', '["3-3-4-trigger-group-lockwork-assembly","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-3-end-to-end-production-process-map-3-3-4-trigger-group-lockwork-assembly"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('ca99f0dc-bab3-4b87-8b1b-21d78cfcbf3a', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '94', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 5 SCO | Base model: high-tech-s-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S 5 SCO', 'Models > High Tech S 5 SCO', '["model-details","high-tech-s-5-sco","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('cb19a8c4-fc8e-4cf5-a6fa-8e58a4f1e68d', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '17', '36', '- Lifelong shooters with deep roots in the sport.  
- View Perazzi as a **badge of authenticity and legacy**.  
- Often already emotionally invested in the brand or its history.', null, '3.4.1 Loyalists', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Audience Connection > 3.4.1 Loyalists', '["3-4-1-loyalists","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-4-audience-connection-3-4-1-loyalists"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('cba18663-1a83-4c3a-84b3-2676719fc223', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '3', '49', '- **Point of Impact (POI)**  
  - The center of the shot pattern relative to the **point of aim** at a given distance.

- **Regulation (for Over/Under)**  
  - Relationship of POI between the two barrels:  
    - For most clay guns, both barrels are regulated to essentially the **same POI**.  
    - For specialized use (e.g., trap), bottom barrel might be set slightly higher per customer specification.

- **Pattern Percentage**  
  - Approximate percentage of pellets within a defined circle (e.g., **30" circle at 40 yards**).  
  - Example: a “Full” choke might give ~70% of pellets in that circle; a more open choke might give ~55%.

- **Pattern Evenness / Uniformity**  
  - How evenly pellets are spread within the pattern circle; absence of large “holes” (voids).

- **POI Ratios (e.g., 60/40)**  
  - Describes how much of the pattern is above vs. below the point of aim at test distance.  
  - Example: **60/40 high** for trap means ~60% of the pellets above and 40% below the aiming point.', null, '2.2 Pattern & POI Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Pattern & POI Concepts', '["2-2-pattern-poi-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-pattern-poi-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('cbae72e2-f0f9-4da4-8ffe-03e0c42834d4', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '37', '45', '- Finishes are chosen and executed with **long-term behavior** in mind:  
  - Oil finishes that look better with time and occasional renewal.  
  - Thin, robust film finishes that resist chipping and are not overly brittle.

- Masters can advise owners on **maintenance** (e.g., light re-oiling over years, cleaning practices).', null, '3.7.5 Aging & Client Guidance', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.5 Aging & Client Guidance', '["3-7-5-aging-client-guidance","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-5-aging-client-guidance"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('cbb3c729-d359-42bb-8283-8422afccf037', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '9', '40', '- **Rough-Formed Wood Components**  
  - Rough-shaped stock and fore-end from the previous “Stock Blank Selection & Rough Shaping” stage, including basic geometry and oversize allowances.

- **Specific Metal Components**  
  - Receiver/action (with top and bottom tangs).  
  - Trigger guard and related metalwork.  
  - Fore-end iron, latch mechanism, and any other fore-end metal.  
  - Screws, through-bolt/draw bolt, tang screws, and related hardware.  
  - (As applicable) buttplate or recoil pad parts.

- **Fit & Design Specifications**  
  - Shooter’s fit metrics: LOP, drop at comb/heel, cast at heel/toe, pitch, grip style, palm swell preferences, etc.  
  - Style notes: trap vs sporting vs field geometry, cheekpiece or Monte Carlo comb, special toe-in/out, or palm swell instructions.

- **Tools & Materials**  
  - Inletting black (lampblack, soot smoker, or transfer paste).  
  - Chisels, gouges, scrapers, hook scrapers, rifflers, rasps, spokeshaves, and sandpapers.  
  - Mallet, clamps, padded vises, and stock cradles.  
  - Measuring tools (rulers, protractors, pitch gauges, drop/cast gauges).  
  - Clean cloths, solvents (if needed), and potentially glues/epoxy for micro repairs.', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('ccb94841-7b3e-401e-90cc-7573bf9a502a', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '12', '36', '- Perazzi owners are portrayed as part of an **elite lineage**.  
- The gun forms a bridge between **Olympic champions, aspiring amateurs, and future generations**.  
- Wear marks and scratches are not flaws; they are treated as **evidence of a story unfolding** — history in the making.  
- To own a Perazzi is to join an **unbroken chain of excellence**.', null, '3.2.3 Legacy and Belonging', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Emotional & Philosophical Brand Pillars > 3.2.3 Legacy and Belonging', '["3-2-3-legacy-and-belonging","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-2-emotional-philosophical-brand-pillars-3-2-3-legacy-and-belonging"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('ccee501c-e2e2-47f4-8071-0ba4e0950e91', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '30', '40', '- They ensure the **lines of the gun flow** from butt to muzzle:  
  - Grip transitions gracefully into trigger guard.  
  - Comb lines align elegantly into receiver.  
- Even on relatively straightforward competition stocks, they maintain subtle, pleasing curves and avoid awkward bulges or flat spots.', null, '3.7.2 Flow of Lines & Visual Harmony', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.2 Flow of Lines & Visual Harmony', '["3-7-2-flow-of-lines-visual-harmony","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-2-flow-of-lines-visual-harmony"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('cd2a9dd2-2613-46a8-940e-94b38ca88af8', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '197', '238', 'Model name: MX28 SCO Sideplates | Base model: mx28 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 28ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX28 SCO Sideplates', 'Models > MX28 SCO Sideplates', '["model-details","mx28-sco-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('cd332601-a4e6-44f0-99ba-46b72271a19e', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '31', '51', '- **Description:** Line drifts from straight path or duplicates an adjacent line irregularly.  
- **Diagnosis:** Diamonds appear uneven; lines converge or diverge unexpectedly.  
- **Mitigation & Repair:**  
  - Detect early at shallow depth and steer line back gradually.  
  - In severe cases, pattern may need partial re-layout or recutting; masters avoid reaching this point through careful initial layout and steady technique.', null, '3.6.2 Wandering Lines / Double Cuts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.2 Wandering Lines / Double Cuts', '["3-6-2-wandering-lines-double-cuts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-2-wandering-lines-double-cuts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('cd710a07-f75f-4e0a-a3a8-31ba3563e2aa', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '24', '49', '- Interpreting patterns vs choke expectations:

- If patterns look too open or too tight relative to the stamped choke, check:
    - Choke constriction measurements.  
    - Ammunition type.

- Deciding whether to:

- Accept minor pattern differences as normal ammo variation.  
  - Re‑check choke dimensions.  
  - In rare cases, adjust choke cutting.', null, '3.4.6 Choke Evaluation', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.6 Choke Evaluation', '["3-4-6-choke-evaluation","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-6-choke-evaluation"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('cd8ebb8d-695a-48b4-b916-fa101b4a7150', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '24', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 5 | Base model: high-tech-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 2020 5', 'Models > High Tech 2020 5', '["model-details","high-tech-2020-5","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('cdc412be-7bdc-4c38-938e-3c29e4325ef0', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '151', '238', 'Model name: MX12 SCO Gold Sideplates | Base model: mx12 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX12 SCO Gold Sideplates', 'Models > MX12 SCO Gold Sideplates', '["model-details","mx12-sco-gold-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('ce4af3b1-c6b8-414a-b4d9-3c8396849627', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '221', '238', 'Model name: MX8 SCO Gold | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX8 SCO Gold', 'Models > MX8 SCO Gold', '["model-details","mx8-sco-gold","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('ce706ae6-3d7e-40ec-a568-76deff93733b', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '20', '32', '- **Goal**  
  Smooth all metal surfaces and prepare them for protective finishing (bluing, case hardening, plating) without disturbing critical fits.

- **Inputs**  
  - All machined metal parts (action, barrels, trigger guard, fore-end metal, small parts).  
  - Polishing stones, files, emery cloth.  
  - Measuring gauges.

- **Outputs**  
  - Metal with:
    - Mirror-smooth finish where required.  
    - Correctly broken or preserved edges.  
    - Manufacturing/tooling marks removed, without altering fits.

- **Owned by**  
  **Metal finisher / polisher**.

---', null, '3.3.9 Metal Polishing & Preparation for Finishing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.3 End-to-End Production Process Map > 3.3.9 Metal Polishing & Preparation for Finishing', '["3-3-9-metal-polishing-preparation-for-finishing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-3-end-to-end-production-process-map-3-3-9-metal-polishing-preparation-for-finishing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('ce8b36ff-95c7-4308-b076-3b3ee8758128', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '3', '58', '- **MX Platform**  
  - Canonical term: **MX platform**.  
  - Description: Core low-profile over/under (O/U) receiver design with a Boss-type locking system and monobloc barrels. Includes removable-trigger models (e.g. MX8) and fixed-trigger derivatives (e.g. MX12). Underpins most Perazzi competition guns.[16]

- **High Tech Platform**  
  - Canonical terms: **High Tech**, **HT**.  
  - Description: Modernized MX evolution with a wider, heavier receiver to shift weight between the hands and reduce muzzle flip. Retains removable trigger (High Tech), while **High Tech S (HTS)** is the fixed-trigger counterpart.[18][19]

- **TM Platform**  
  - Canonical term: **TM series**.  
  - Description: Single-barrel trap/live-bird guns derived from the MX-style action but configured as single-barrel guns for American trap and similar disciplines (e.g. TM1, TMX, TM9, TM9X).

- **DC Platform**  
  - Canonical term: **DC series**.  
  - Description: “Detachable coil” builds where the removable trigger group uses coil mainsprings; emphasizes rugged use and serviceability.

- **SHO Platform**  
  - Canonical term: **SHO series**.  
  - Description: Hand-built sidelock guns with distinct sidelock metalwork; still use a removable trigger group.

- **Model Name Prefixes / Suffixes**  
  - **MX**: Core O/U family (e.g. MX1–MX14, MX8, MX12, MX20, MX28, MX410, MX2000).[16]  
  - **HT / HTS**: High Tech platform, removable- vs fixed-trigger respectively.  
  - **TM**: Single-barrel trap/live-bird models.  
  - **SC2 / SC3 / SCO**: Wood and engraving **grades**, not model types.  
  - **Lusso**: Italian for “luxury”; indicates higher cosmetic grade.  
  - **RS**: Often indicates a rib/stock configuration (e.g. MX2000/RS unsingle named for Ray Stafford).[7]  
  - **S**: Often indicates fixed trigger on models otherwise similar to removable-trigger siblings (e.g. MX2000S, HTS).[16]', null, '2.2 Platform Families & Model Prefixes', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Platform Families & Model Prefixes', '["2-2-platform-families-model-prefixes","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-platform-families-model-prefixes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('ceee6566-54ff-40a7-b589-a20e1e0f0fc4', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '20', '39', '- **Gun Drill Machines**  
  - Deep-hole drills with internal lubrication, used to create bores in solid bar stock.

- **Reamers**  
  - Long reamers for bringing bores and chambers to final diameter (including forcing cones).

- **Honing / Lapping Tools**  
  - Hones or lead laps with fine abrasive for final bore smoothing and finish.

- **Mandrels / Profiling Tools**  
  - Used to shape or support barrels during contouring operations (if applicable).', null, '3.5.1 Machining & Forming Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Machining & Forming Tools', '["3-5-1-machining-forming-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-machining-forming-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('cef05f54-4eeb-44ea-924e-3531d4089329', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '14', '39', '- **Thinner Barrels**  
  - Pros: lower weight, quicker handling; desirable for some field and driven game guns.  
  - Cons: heat up faster, more dent-prone, potentially more barrel whip.

- **Thicker Barrels**  
  - Pros: more durable, smoother swing, better recoil handling (often used in competition guns or heavier models like some High Tech variants).  
  - Cons: greater weight, potentially slower to start and redirect.

**Design response:**

- Adjust wall thickness and profiling based on discipline and customer goals (e.g., leave more metal on trap barrels, less on ultra-light field barrels).  
- Inform customers (when they are directly engaged) about trade-offs between responsiveness and recoil/heat behavior.', null, '3.4.1 Barrel Wall Thickness vs. Weight', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Barrel Wall Thickness vs. Weight', '["3-4-1-barrel-wall-thickness-vs-weight","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-barrel-wall-thickness-vs-weight"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('cef6d61b-28ff-4a88-a7b8-d4f8974b477a', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '31', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Both firing pins show fresh strikes after a single trigger pull.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Too light sear engagement or incorrect sear geometry.  
  - Inertia block issues (inertia trigger) that fail to isolate the second sear properly.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Use snap caps and simulate recoil, watching for simultaneous drops.  
  - Increase sear engagement or adjust spring forces; correct inertia block behavior.  
  - Retest until doubling is eliminated.', null, '3.6.1 Doubling (Both Barrels Fire at Once)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.1 Doubling (Both Barrels Fire at Once)', '["3-6-1-doubling-both-barrels-fire-at-once","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-1-doubling-both-barrels-fire-at-once"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('cf464407-72e8-405d-b9fd-355f7b9d4cc0', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '40', '49', '- Masters may pattern **many guns daily**, yet maintain:

- Routine test distances and targets.  
  - Simple but effective notes or logs.  
  - A repeatable sequence: bottom barrel → top barrel, etc.

- They rely on upstream quality and are vigilant for anomalies rather than over‑testing every gun unnecessarily.', null, '3.7.3 Efficient, Structured Workflow', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.3 Efficient, Structured Workflow', '["3-7-3-efficient-structured-workflow","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-3-efficient-structured-workflow"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('cf9605de-f782-4dec-a04f-8b4b6622d527', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '18', '39', '- Perazzi uses **high-grade steels** and **premium walnut**, consistent with other best-gun makers:
  - Barrel steels are comparable to those used by other top Italian makers (e.g., Boehler-type steels).
  - Stock wood is often **Turkish or Circassian walnut** with good density and figure.
- Shared principle:
  - At the high end, makers do **not compromise** on core materials.
  - Performance and longevity are bounded by the quality of steel and wood.', null, '3.2.2 Quality Materials', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Shared High-End Gunmaking Practices > 3.2.2 Quality Materials', '["3-2-2-quality-materials","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-2-shared-high-end-gunmaking-practices-3-2-2-quality-materials"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('cfa36bdc-1f4b-449f-99b8-327c940ee915', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '165', '238', 'Model name: MX20 | Base model: mx20 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX20', 'Models > MX20', '["model-details","mx20","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('cfe09a69-43e2-4dbc-bdf0-07d36fce28be', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '41', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 5 | Base model: high-tech-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 5', 'Models > High Tech 5', '["model-details","high-tech-5","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, 