Perazzi is committed to the quality and satisfaction of our customers. If you have concerns or need to verify the authenticity of your shotgun, contact our official customer service team.', null, 'Protect Your Investment', 'Consumer Warning Notice > Protect Your Investment', '["protect-your-investment","consumer-warning-notice-protect-your-investment"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:16.184829+00', null), ('d30a2108-d677-4a90-a17f-f097f66d40a9', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '21', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 3 Gold | Base model: high-tech-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2020 Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 2020 3 Gold', 'Models > High Tech 2020 3 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-2020-3-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('d4323fec-c61d-409f-b49c-ddf3f44989b9', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '12', '40', '- Shapes exterior with rasps, spokeshaves, scrapers, and sandpaper, working both sides alternately to maintain symmetry.  
- Maintains design language:  
  - Fuller combs for trap vs slimmer combs for sporting.  
  - Grip shapes appropriate for discipline and shooter (e.g., more vertical for trap).  
- Blends wood into the **metal scallops and curves** of the receiver so transitions feel continuous and aesthetically cohesive.  
- Controls proud vs shy wood:  
  - Avoids proud wood standing above metal or shy wood that sits noticeably below metal at joints, except where tiny margins are intentionally left for finishing.', null, '3.3.2 Symmetry & External Shaping', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Symmetry & External Shaping', '["3-3-2-symmetry-external-shaping","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-symmetry-external-shaping"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('d4472c39-28e3-4f64-b940-30e62f04aad1', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '40', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 3 SCO Gold | Base model: high-tech-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 3 SCO Gold', 'Models > High Tech 3 SCO Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-3-sco-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('d4c28a64-1e19-463f-b1bf-a18b04be5e7d', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '26', '48', '- Cutting cast and drop directly from the blank:  
  - Pros: clean geometry, uses natural grain and avoids later bending stress.  
  - Cons: limited by blank dimensions; may not reach extreme adjustments.

- Bending (post-shaping heat/steam/oil) for fine-tuning:  
  - Pros: adds flexibility to adjust cast/drop after test shooting.  
  - Cons: introduces internal stress and requires care; best used as a fine adjustment, not major offset.

**Practical approach:**  
- Build in most of the cast and drop in the cut layout, using blank orientation, and reserve bending for smaller corrections after the shooter tests the gun.', null, '3.4.5 Cutting Geometry vs Later Bending', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.5 Cutting Geometry vs Later Bending', '["3-4-5-cutting-geometry-vs-later-bending","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-5-cutting-geometry-vs-later-bending"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('d4c62165-4539-4642-9d32-093b5b0bc3f5', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '16', '58', '- The **MX8 action** remains the core architecture for over 50 years.  
- Innovations focus on:  
  - Adjustable ribs (3–5-position systems) for tunable POI.[29]  
  - Adjustable combs and buttplates.  
  - Alternate spring systems (leaf vs coil).  
  - Wider receivers (High Tech) for balance and recoil control.  
  - Cosmetic and ergonomic customization rather than wholesale mechanical redesign.
- Cross-compatibility: Many parts (e.g. triggers, barrels) are compatible across generations, though proper fitting is critical for safety.

