92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '22', '48', '- Highly figured blanks (burl, strong curl) can have irregular grain that weakens the wrist.  
- Trade-off:  
  - **Favor strength** by orienting the stock so grain runs through the wrist, even if it sacrifices some striking figure.  
  - Seek blanks where figure and grain strength coincide to minimize compromise.  
- Example: If strong cast-off is required, the stockmaker may retain slightly more wrist thickness to compensate for thinner sections created by cast geometry.', null, '3.4.1 Grain Strength vs Figure Display', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Grain Strength vs Figure Display', '["3-4-1-grain-strength-vs-figure-display","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-grain-strength-vs-figure-display"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('d62f936e-29ab-4200-8811-85a6b9e20f9b', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '131', '238', 'Model name: High Tech X RS | Base model: high-tech-rs | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: X | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: unsingle | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 10.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech X RS', 'Models > High Tech X RS', '["model-details","high-tech-x-rs","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('d661df76-e48f-4daf-ba67-d3638b9adef7', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '2', '32', 'The Perazzi USA site is designed as a **digital atelier**—a place where a shooter, owner, or enthusiast can explore:

- Who Perazzi is and what the brand stands for.
- Which platforms and configurations might fit their discipline and style.
- What it means to commission or configure a Perazzi gun.
- How to care for, service, and live with a Perazzi over decades.

From a user’s perspective, the site is organized around a few core questions:

1. **"What is Perazzi, really?"** → Brand, heritage, champions, factory.
2. **"Which gun or platform is right for me?"** → Shotguns / platforms / concierge.
3. **"How do I build or configure my own Perazzi?"** → Bespoke build / concierge.
4. **"How do I look after my gun?"** → Service, parts, recommended centers.
5. **"Where do I shoot, watch, or connect with other Perazzi owners?"** → Events, athletes, stories.

Everything else flows from these core experiences.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('d68c7223-6948-4eee-827e-e9226caa42a7', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '12', '45', '- Use files and abrasives to remove tool marks while **preserving design geometry**:  
  - Draw-filing on barrels to keep planes straight.  
  - Using sanding blocks/sticks to maintain flats and avoid waves.  
  - Using wheels only on appropriate curves, with care not to round edges.

- Transition through **progressively finer grits** (e.g., from ~320 up to 600 or finer) to achieve a surface that will take a uniform, mirror-like or satin finish.

- Always polish **along the axis** of barrels and major surfaces to avoid visible cross-scratches after bluing.', null, '3.3.1 Expert Polishing Technique', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.1 Expert Polishing Technique', '["3-3-1-expert-polishing-technique","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-1-expert-polishing-technique"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('d6e6766b-3589-415b-91d7-a36be068b87e', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '29', '32', '- **Heritage and philosophy** – see §3.1.  
- **Architectural hallmarks and positioning** – see §3.2.  
- **End-to-end production process map** – see §3.3.', null, '5.1 Internal Cross-Links', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 5. References & Cross-Links > 5.1 Internal Cross-Links', '["5-1-internal-cross-links","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-5-references-cross-links-5-1-internal-cross-links"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('d824d9e7-c450-4b6e-a0ee-3e5723bdb117', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '3', '40', '- **Seamless Wood-to-Metal Fit**  
  - Condition where wood meets metal with hairline joints, no daylight visible, and surfaces feel like a continuous plane when touched.

- **Bearing Surfaces**  
  - Critical contact areas between stock and action (e.g., recoil shoulders, tangs) designed to transmit recoil forces safely.

- **Relieved Areas**  
  - Non-critical regions intentionally cut slightly away from metal to avoid random stress points.

- **Length of Pull (LOP)**  
  - Distance from trigger face to center of butt; finalized at this station (often via trimming butt and fitting pad/plate).

- **Drop (Comb/Heel)**  
  - Vertical distance from sighting plane/rib to comb or heel; comb height is finalized here by shaping.

- **Cast-Off / Cast-On**  
  - Lateral offset of stock relative to bore/action; refined here via asymmetric shaping and, if needed, mild bending in adjacent stages.

- **Pitch**  
  - Angle of butt relative to bore; checked and fine-tuned in combination with butt-shaping.

- **Monte Carlo Comb**  
  - Raised comb with step at heel, often used in trap stocks to keep a high eye line while preserving heel drop for recoil clearance.', null, '2.2 Fit & Geometry Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 Fit & Geometry Concepts', '["2-2-fit-geometry-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-fit-geometry-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('d83cb409-ea4b-47ed-8a85-598841504121', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '12', '56', '- Understand how all subsystems interact:  
  - Locking bolt engagement with barrel bites and monobloc.  
  - Cocking system: how opening the gun cocks hammers or strikers.  
  - Ejector system: how ejector sears are set when shots are fired and tripped on opening.  
  - Trigger system (inertia or mechanical) and safety/selector linkage.  
- Interpret symptoms:  
  - Stiff opening may indicate issues with cocking cams or ejector springs.  
  - Top lever behavior may reflect lock-up geometry.', null, '3.3.1 Comprehensive Mechanism Knowledge', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.1 Comprehensive Mechanism Knowledge', '["3-3-1-comprehensive-mechanism-knowledge","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-1-comprehensive-mechanism-knowledge"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('d8a1aad2-8655-4a74-9ec6-a1dc7dca6c84', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '26', '38', 'Keith joined the ranks of Perazzi-supported shooters after years of success.

Key equipment details:

- Uses a Perazzi trap combo tuned to his preferences.  
- Unsingle barrel for handicap and doubles barrels for two-shot events.  
- Fitted with a Precision Fit Stock (PFS), allowing fine-tuning of fit[87].

This setup has supported multiple 100-straights and his run of state titles. Keith values the balance and crisp trigger of his Perazzi, which supports his quick shooting style. The source describes him as a marksman at peace with his craft and his gun, his synergy with Perazzi enabling extraordinary consistency in a demanding sport.

---', null, '3.2.3.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Supported Shooters > 3.2.3 Keith Ditto – American Trap (Supported Shooter) > 3.2.3.2 Relationship with Perazzi & Equipment', '["3-2-3-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-2-supported-shooters-3-2-3-keith-ditto-american-trap-supported-shooter-3-2-3-2-relationship-with-perazzi-equipment"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('d8aeff53-ad92-48a2-a8eb-f5b6fb9267c2', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '16', '32', '- **Examples of non-standard requests**:  
  - Very heavy barrel profiles.  
  - Extremely tight chokes (e.g., extra full ~0.040" constriction).  
  - Unusual combinations of short stocks with heavy barrels.

**Design response:**

- Confirm that monobloc, barrel wall thickness, and chamber design remain within safe proof limits.  
- If necessary, adjust barrel blanks or specifications so final muzzle wall thickness remains safe after choking.  
- Plan for additional weight or balance corrections in stock to avoid extremely front-heavy or unstable guns.  
- When needed, advise the client that certain combinations are inadvisable or require modification.

In all cases, the product engineer uses experience and, when required, prototypes or test rigs (e.g., temporarily pairing components) to feel what a proposed combination will be like in practice.

---', null, '3.4.5 Safety Margins, Proof, and Non-Standard Requests', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Typical Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.5 Safety Margins, Proof, and Non-Standard Requests', '["3-4-5-safety-margins-proof-and-non-standard-requests","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-3-main-content-3-4-typical-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-5-safety-margins-proof-and-non-standard-requests"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('d8c416cf-7864-47c3-8d78-ba1954391bf3', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '10', '50', '### Zemfira Meftakhetdinova
