- Check that hammer/striker springs provide sufficient energy without excessive cocking effort.  
- Understand and correct potential misalignment or weak strikes.', null, '3.3.5 Firing Pin & Hammer Performance', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.5 Firing Pin & Hammer Performance', '["3-3-5-firing-pin-hammer-performance","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-5-firing-pin-hammer-performance"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('d9bcdf53-29f5-412a-b973-4634ab5cddb5', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '157', '238', 'Model name: MX16 | Base model: mx16 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 16ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX16', 'Models > MX16', '["model-details","mx16","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('d9db987e-62a3-47a3-aa03-7cb897e87c6f', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '19', '51', '- **Finer LPI (24–28)**  
  - Pros: highly refined appearance, delicate texture.  
  - Cons: more prone to wear, may feel less aggressive; can clog more easily.

- **Coarser LPI (16–18)**  
  - Pros: very strong grip; durable under heavy use.  
  - Cons: can feel rough or harsh; less visually refined.

- **Medium LPI (around 18–22)**  
  - Common choice for competition guns like a Perazzi; balances grip, comfort, and visual quality.

**Practical approach:**  
- For **hard-used competition guns**, choose medium-coarse LPI.  
- For **showpiece or lighter-use guns**, finer LPI may be selected when aesthetics are prioritized.', null, '3.4.1 LPI vs Grip, Comfort, & Durability', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 LPI vs Grip, Comfort, & Durability', '["3-4-1-lpi-vs-grip-comfort-durability","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-lpi-vs-grip-comfort-durability"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('da10ad50-07da-4e7f-bd96-1aa3442f56a0', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '12', '49', '- Interpreting pattern boards or papers to determine:

- **Pattern center**:  
    - Locating densest area or using simple techniques (visual estimation; folding paper, etc.).

- **Offset from aiming point**:  
    - Measuring horizontal and vertical distances from aim to pattern center.

- **Pattern density & distribution**:  
    - Judging whether the pattern is appropriate for the choke designation (tight vs open).  
    - Spotting large voids or unusual shapes (e.g., “donut” patterns).

- Distinguishing between **ammo-related anomalies** and **barrel-related issues** by:
  - Re-shooting with the same load.  
  - Testing another brand or load if needed.', null, '3.3.2 Pattern Analysis', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.2 Pattern Analysis', '["3-3-2-pattern-analysis","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-2-pattern-analysis"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('da5ff286-e87b-4756-80bc-b20c04db78c6', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '27', '35', '- Delivers receivers that are nearly identical in critical dimensions across batches, making Perazzi’s modularity possible (e.g., swapping barrels or trigger groups within the same family).  
- Uses experience from decades of production and feedback to refine tolerances and allowances over time.

Mastery here is partly visible (in clean surfaces and precise geometry) and partly invisible (in the absence of problems downstream and in the gun’s long-term durability).

---', null, '3.7.5 Consistency and Long-Term Perspective', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.5 Consistency and Long-Term Perspective', '["3-7-5-consistency-and-long-term-perspective","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-5-consistency-and-long-term-perspective"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('da8fd083-0f22-4517-b491-0c1701315962', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '48', '51', '- For bespoke guns, fitting and final inspection include verifying personalized aspects.  
- For stock guns shipped to dealers, final inspection focuses on factory spec conformance and presentation, with final fit adjustments left to dealer or local gunsmith when needed.

---', null, '4.5 Post-Fit vs Factory-Default Guns', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.5 Post-Fit vs Factory-Default Guns', '["4-5-post-fit-vs-factory-default-guns","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-5-post-fit-vs-factory-default-guns"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('daef7f20-0873-4967-ae12-7fa1d63205c0', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '27', '51', '- **Layout Tools**  
  - Pencils or scribers for guide lines.  
  - Simple angle references (e.g., paper or plastic angle gauges) to maintain pattern angle on curved surfaces.  
  - Flexible straightedges for drawing initial long lines.

- **Support & Cradles**  
  - Checkering cradle or padded vise that allows rotation and locking at various angles.  
  - Non-skid padding or sandbag supports to prevent stock movement during cutting.', null, '3.5.2 Layout & Support Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.2 Layout & Support Tools', '["3-5-2-layout-support-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-2-layout-support-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('db4b5097-06af-48ab-8b17-0780f66a286a', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '7', '39', '- Perazzi O/Us use a low-profile action inspired by the **Boss** design.[4]
- Key characteristics:
  - Shallow receiver height brings barrels close to the hinge.
  - Full-width locking bolt engages bites on the monobloc from beneath (and, on some models, supplemented by a top latch).
- Distinct from:
  - Browning’s under-bolt system.
  - Beretta’s dual-cone locking approach.
- Functional impact:
  - Lower bore axis reduces muzzle flip.
  - Action geometry contributes to **between-hands balance** and agility.
- Philosophical fit:
  - Emphasizes **strength with agility**, consistent with Perazzi’s competition focus.', null, '3.1.2 Boss-Style Low-Profile Action', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations > 3.1.2 Boss-Style Low-Profile Action', '["3-1-2-boss-style-low-profile-action","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations-3-1-2-boss-style-low-profile-action"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('db56a253-c091-40f9-8c9f-f95838b0a221', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '27', '45', '- **Files**  
  - Smooth and fine-cut files for removing machining marks while controlling surface geometry.

- **Abrasives (Sandpapers)**  
  - Various grits on blocks, sticks, and flexible backers for progressive smoothing.

- **Buffing Motors & Wheels**  
  - Wheels of varying hardness and shape; compounds ranging from cutting to finishing.  
  - Used primarily on curved surfaces; flats and edges often done by hand to avoid distortion.', null, '3.5.1 Polishing Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Polishing Tools', '["3-5-1-polishing-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-polishing-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('dc06c3a2-1983-43ae-b997-130cbb1e24ff', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '34', '49', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Ejectors fail to throw shells clear or behave inconsistently under live fire.  
  - Trigger issues such as:
    - Failure to reset second shot.  
    - Doubling that did not appear in dry tests.

- **Diagnosis & Remedies:**  
  - Inspect and adjust ejector springs, channels, and trip mechanisms; polish where necessary.  
  - Adjust inertia block or sear engagement; increase safety margins to prevent doubling.  
  - Confirm fixes with further live-fire tests.', null, '3.6.5 Ejection or Trigger Issues Under Recoil', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.5 Ejection or Trigger Issues Under Recoil', '["3-6-5-ejection-or-trigger-issues-under-recoil","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-5-ejection-or-trigger-issues-under-recoil"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('dc26b928-d3e0-4173-b010-7958c8f294e8', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '33', '39', '- Requests for unusual regulation (e.g., specific crossing patterns at non-standard distances) require more calculation and sometimes trial-and-error.  
- Although shotgun tolerances are more forgiving than double-rifle regulation, these requests still demand careful setup and testing.

**Caveat:** Complex regulation goals may increase the risk of re-soldering cycles or fine bending adjustments.', null, '4.2 Atypical Regulation Requests', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.2 Atypical Regulation Requests', '["4-2-atypical-regulation-requests","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-2-atypical-regulation-requests"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('dc97c612-977d-45a7-b021-4beecdc4398d', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '35', '50', '### Anders Golding
**Country:** Denmark
**Event:** Men’s Skeet
**Medal:** Silver
**Olympics:** 2012 London
**Perazzi platform:** MX2000/8
**Highlights:** Golding claimed skeet silver at London 2012 with a Perazzi MX2000/8:contentReference[oaicite:124]{index=124}. He set a then-Olympic finals record in skeet. His choice of Perazzi (over the Scandinavian-favored shotguns like Krieghoff) illustrated the MX2000’s appeal for its excellent pointability, which Golding cited as key to his success in the windy conditions of the final.
**Sources:**
- Wikipedia – Olympic use (Perazzi):contentReference[oaicite:125]{index=125}
- Danmarks Idrætsforbund (Danish Olympic Committee) – Golding’s post-match remarks:contentReference[oaicite:126]{index=126}', null, '### Anders Golding', 'Olympic Medals > Anders Golding', '["olympic-medals","anders-golding"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Loyalist","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:20.792823+00', null), ('dca29cea-8ce0-438b-8d95-397b7e842184', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '3', '39', '- **Best Gun / Best Work**  
  Term used (especially in the British tradition) for guns built to the highest standard of craftsmanship and materials, usually with extensive hand fitting, engraving, and long service life.

- **Hand Fitting / Smoke Fitting**  
  Technique of leaving metal “proud” from machining and then carefully filing and scraping it to fit using soot/marker to reveal high spots. Common to high-end shotguns and doubles.

- **Proof & Regulation**  
  - **Proof**: Legal high-pressure testing of barrels/actions at an official proof house (e.g., CIP proof in Europe).[12]  
  - **Regulation**: Adjusting double-barrel guns so both barrels shoot to a desired point of impact.

- **Oil Finish**  
  Traditional hand-rubbed stock finish built up with layers of oil, producing a satin or semi-gloss sheen and highlighting walnut figure.', null, '2.2 General High-End Gunmaking Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.2 General High-End Gunmaking Concepts', '["2-2-general-high-end-gunmaking-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-2-general-high-end-gunmaking-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('dccdde7b-5101-4fc5-ba79-5fff7a7ba7bf', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '130', '238', 'Model name: High Tech X Gold | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: X Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech X Gold', 'Models > High Tech X Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-x-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('dcd43e9c-2ea7-4010-b3d0-e1aa0671dfad', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '47', '51', '- For matched pairs or sets, checkering must be **visually identical** across guns: same LPI, coverage, line counts, and border positions.

**Caveat:**  
- Requires systematic layout checks, line counting, and careful comparison between stocks.', null, '4.3 Matched Pairs & Pattern Uniformity', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.3 Matched Pairs & Pattern Uniformity', '["4-3-matched-pairs-pattern-uniformity","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-3-matched-pairs-pattern-uniformity"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('dcd8d6a6-b0be-4cb5-8016-51190ae5aea9', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '103', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S SC3 | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S SC3', 'Models > High Tech S SC3', '["model-details","high-tech-s-sc3","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('dce5b8ec-05f5-4a15-80e8-26a2d39cb118', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '19', '35', '- **Precision Measuring Tools**  
  - Calipers and micrometers for general dimensions.  
  - Plug and ring gauges or go/no-go gauges for specific holes and slots (e.g., locking bolt slots).

- **Surface Plate and Height Gauges**  
  - Used to verify flatness (e.g., water table) and squareness (e.g., standing breech vs. action bar).

- **Coordinate Measuring Machine (CMM)**  
  - Employed for process qualification and random QC checks on critical receiver features.

- **Hardness Testers**  
  - Rockwell or similar testers to confirm surface hardness after case hardening.

- **Master Templates or Golden Samples**  
  - Reference receivers or dummy parts that represent ideal geometry and fit.', null, '3.5.2 Gauges and Inspection Equipment', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.2 Gauges and Inspection Equipment', '["3-5-2-gauges-and-inspection-equipment","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-2-gauges-and-inspection-equipment"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('dce90b01-5b3c-40b9-b234-e2c40e992c8f', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '27', '32', '- Extremely tight chokes beyond typical catalog values.  
- Atypical barrel lengths, rib heights, or custom rib designs.  
- Very unusual stock geometries for medical or idiosyncratic reasons.  
- Requests for add-on devices (e.g., hypothetical electronic sensors) integrated into the stock or rib.

**Caveats:**

- Must verify structural safety and proof compliance (especially for barrel and choke designs).  
- Must evaluate impact on balance and handling and plan compensations.  
- May require custom CAD work or special machining sequences.', null, '4.2 Non-Standard Functional Requests', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.2 Non-Standard Functional Requests', '["4-2-non-standard-functional-requests","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-2-non-standard-functional-requests"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('dcf8d539-f9c3-4143-8f35-763a701bb08d', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '210', '238', 'Model name: MX8 | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX8', 'Models > MX8', '["model-details","mx8","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('dd08bd77-3a15-49c7-9122-782d27df549f', '177a681e-a602-4d92-af07-b17c98816feb', '12', '13', '- **1. High-Level Overview** – Summarizes the purpose of this document and what it describes.  
- **2. Key Concepts & Glossary** – Defines core terms: Perazzi Writing Style, Tone of Voice, Style and Language Choices, Reader Perception & Psychological Impact.  
- **3.1 Tone of Voice** – Detailed breakdown of emotional and philosophical tone characteristics.  
- **3.2 Style and Language Choices** – Describes the structural and linguistic patterns (poetic language, intimacy, repetition, layering, sophistication).  
- **3.3 Reader Perception & Psychological Impact** – Outlines how readers are meant to feel and what they should infer about Perazzi ownership.  
- **3.4 Canonical One-Sentence Definition** – Provides the canonical, one-sentence summary of the Perazzi Writing Style.  
- **4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats** – Notes the absence of explicit exceptions in the source and flags the need for separate guidelines where necessary.  
- **5. References & Cross-Links** – Indicates related documents and conceptual links for broader brand documentation.', null, 'Appendix A. Section Index', 'Perazzi Writing Style and Tone (AI-Optimized Reference) > Appendix A. Section Index', '["appendix-a-section-index","perazzi-writing-style-and-tone-ai-optimized-reference-appendix-a-section-index"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:49.998824+00', null), ('dda169fb-eb8c-47d8-9c8b-15390f7029a7', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '16', '48', '- Removing bulk material with band saw and machines without causing splits or large chips.  
- Anticipating grain direction and cutting “with the grain” where possible to reduce tear-out.  
- Knowing how much material to leave on:  
  - Exterior surfaces (e.g., a few millimeters on comb, cheekpiece, and grip).  
  - Inletting surfaces (e.g., leaving undersize for tight fit).', null, '3.3.5 Efficient, Safe Material Removal', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.5 Efficient, Safe Material Removal', '["3-3-5-efficient-safe-material-removal","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-5-efficient-safe-material-removal"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('dde97ba3-2e75-4f6c-a039-3700c30ab974', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '44', '51', '- In rare cases, serious mis‑spec (wrong engraving, model, or barrel length) may be discovered only at final inspection.  
- These require **high-level decisions**:  
  - Offer to remake.  
  - Negotiate alternative solutions with the customer.  
- Final inspector’s role is to detect and escalate promptly, not to minimize or hide such issues.', null, '4.1 Major Errors Discovered at Final Inspection', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Major Errors Discovered at Final Inspection', '["4-1-major-errors-discovered-at-final-inspection","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-major-errors-discovered-at-final-inspection"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('ddf34379-ff2d-42d1-b5df-f7602ea16e64', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '29', '40', '- Master stockmakers may trial-fit an action dozens of times, removing only tiny slivers of wood each time.  
- They rarely force assemblies; each seating of the action is gentle and deliberate.  
- Their tactile sense is so refined that they can detect asymmetry or flat spots that are invisible to casual observers, sometimes checking with eyes closed.', null, '3.7.1 Process & Tactile Sensitivity', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.1 Process & Tactile Sensitivity', '["3-7-1-process-tactile-sensitivity","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-1-process-tactile-sensitivity"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('de2b1b2a-475a-4086-8ba0-a1b71386e984', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '8', '39', 'Every gun must pass **official proof** at the **Italian proof house in Brescia**:

- Barrels and action are tested with **high-pressure proof loads**.
- Guns are inspected for:
  - Signs of stress.
  - Permanent dimensional changes.
- Successful guns receive proof marks on barrels and action.[12]

Perazzi also conducts **internal stress testing**:

- Random barrels are subjected to **ultra-high pressure tests** (reportedly up to ~16x normal pressure) as QA audits.
- Desired failure mode:
  - If a barrel fails, it should do so **mid-tube**, away from the breech and receiver.
- Perazzi’s tests confirmed this behavior, validating:
  - Steel quality.
  - Fabrication integrity.
  - Safe failure characteristics beyond regulatory minimums.', null, '3.1.3 Proof Testing and Extreme QA', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Quality Control & Tolerances > 3.1.3 Proof Testing and Extreme QA', '["3-1-3-proof-testing-and-extreme-qa","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-1-quality-control-tolerances-3-1-3-proof-testing-and-extreme-qa"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('de2f098d-9f71-4e1b-84a4-33741137f450', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '26', '32', '- Unique engraving motifs (e.g., portraits of a dog, family scenes).  
- Mixed or non-catalog engraving styles.  
- Unusual inlays, stock carving, or hybrid finishes.

**Caveats:**

- May require specific engravers or stock specialists, which can significantly lengthen delivery time.  
- Design must explicitly record:  
  - Motif details and references.  
  - Whether initials or monograms should be gold inlaid.  
  - Placement of key decorative elements.', null, '4.1 Non-Standard Aesthetic Requests', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Non-Standard Aesthetic Requests', '["4-1-non-standard-aesthetic-requests","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-non-standard-aesthetic-requests"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('de5b53fb-4ecf-4138-b312-c4e25fe5a3d2', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '5', '48', '- **Band Saw**  
  - Used to rough cut blank along layout lines for profile and plan views.

- **Stock Duplicator / Pantograph Copy Carver**  
  - Machine that traces a **pattern stock** with a stylus while a cutter reproduces the shape in the blank, often leaving extra material.

- **CNC Router / CNC Stock Machine**  
  - Computer-controlled machine that carves stock based on 3D CAD models, with parameters for drop, cast, LOP, etc.

- **Pattern Stock / Master Pattern**  
  - Reference stock used in duplicators as the shape template.

- **Templates / Layout Patterns**  
  - Flat templates used to mark stock outlines on blank surfaces.

- **Sacrificial Blocks**  
  - Extra wood pieces temporarily attached for clamping or fixturing, protecting the actual stock surfaces.', null, '2.4 Tools & Machine Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Tools & Machine Concepts', '["2-4-tools-machine-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-tools-machine-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('deb7a4db-ffaf-4ac1-8998-22b801809d48', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '23', '48', '- High-grade walnut is expensive and scarce.  
- Decisions include:  
  - Whether to cut fore-end from same blank (perfect color match) or from a separate but matching blank (better structural layout).  
  - How to position the stock within the blank to minimize waste while preserving safety margins and aesthetics.', null, '3.4.2 Blank Usage vs Waste', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Blank Usage vs Waste', '["3-4-2-blank-usage-vs-waste","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-blank-usage-vs-waste"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('def65eb1-d9b5-4436-8a5b-c5e715f9d859', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '154', '238', 'Model name: MX12/3 | Base model: mx12-3 | Platform: MX | Category: mixed | Disciplines: Sporting, Game | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### MX12/3', 'Models > MX12/3', '["model-details","mx12-3","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('df008ead-4f43-4588-8ceb-14bbad0c1e4c', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '134', '238', 'Model name: MX10 | Base model: mx10 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: top-single | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 17.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### MX10', 'Models > MX10', '["model-details","mx10","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('df0b7cb3-bc78-4389-a5d7-8682c1220845', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '39', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Audible crack sound; visible line in stock head or wrist when tightening stock.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Hidden defect in wood; over-tightened stock bolt; stress concentration from inletting.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Inspect for crack extent; assess structural risk.  
  - For minor internal cracks, high-quality repair (glue and possibly hidden reinforcement).  
  - For significant structural cracks, likely re-stock with a new blank.', null, '3.6.9 Cracks During Assembly', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.9 Cracks During Assembly', '["3-6-9-cracks-during-assembly","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-9-cracks-during-assembly"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('dfdb4c67-fc9e-4198-9337-7f20b4e3aff0', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '50', '51', '- **1. High-Level Overview** – Scope and purpose of the Checkering station.  
