- Third-party parts may be cheaper but can cause:  
  - Inconsistent trigger feel.  
  - Premature breakage.  
  - Safety issues.  
- Use of non-genuine parts can **void warranty** if failures are linked to such components.', null, '3.10.1 Authentic Parts and Aftermarket Risk', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.10 Counterfeits, Grey Market, and Service Integrity > 3.10.1 Authentic Parts and Aftermarket Risk', '["3-10-1-authentic-parts-and-aftermarket-risk","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-10-counterfeits-grey-market-and-service-integrity-3-10-1-authentic-parts-and-aftermarket-risk"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('e27d20cf-ef42-4125-afde-eaa01918cfdc', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '200', '238', 'Model name: MX410 SC3 | Base model: mx410 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 410ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX410 SC3', 'Models > MX410 SC3', '["model-details","mx410-sc3","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('e292a47a-5df6-47f5-a811-999312baf042', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '48', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 8 Gold | Base model: high-tech-8 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Gold | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 34.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 8 Gold', 'Models > High Tech 8 Gold', '["model-details","high-tech-8-gold","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('e2b82f13-550e-4671-a76e-a20ce7d84b46', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '60', '238', 'Model name: High Tech RS | Base model: high-tech-rs | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 10.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech RS', 'Models > High Tech RS', '["model-details","high-tech-rs","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('e2e72423-9fc6-497e-9c27-7d5973bc302c', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '1', '45', 'This document describes the **Metal Finishing & Bluing station** in the Perazzi factory.

At this station, all major **steel components** of the shotgun—barrels, receiver/action, trigger guard, fore-end iron, top lever, and small fittings—are:

- **Polished** to remove machining marks and prepare surfaces.
- **Protected** from corrosion via finishes such as:
  - Rust bluing (especially for soft-soldered barrels).
  - Hot salt bluing for compatible parts (where applicable).
  - Coin (bright steel) finish with protective coating.
  - Case-hardened finishes (on some models/eras).
  - Plating (nickel, gold) for specific parts or models.
- Matched in **color, gloss, and texture** according to model and specification.

This document explains:

- The **purpose** and **success criteria** of metal finishing & bluing.
- The **inputs and outputs** handled at this station.
- The **core knowledge and skills** of the metal finisher.
- The main **decisions and trade-offs** (process choice, polish level, edge preservation, etc.).
- The **tools and measurements** used at a conceptual level.
- Typical **failure modes** and their diagnosis.
- What **mastery** looks like in this role, including an illustrative vignette.

The focus is on how Perazzi produces the **deep, polished blue-black barrels** and coherent metal finishes that define the visual first impression of the gun, while preserving all functional geometry.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('e2e8472b-2984-47bd-bb0f-daf0247106fa', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '31', '38', '- Very light recoil loads can fail to reset inertia triggers.  
- For shooters insisting on ultra-light loads, standard inertia setups may require careful tuning or may remain marginal.

**Caveat:**  
- The triggersmith must decide whether to:  
  - Lighten inertia-block springs,  
  - Adjust mass, or  
  - Recommend mechanical trigger configurations (where available) to ensure reliable second-shot function.', null, '4.1 Ultra-Light Loads and Inertia Triggers', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.1 Ultra-Light Loads and Inertia Triggers', '["4-1-ultra-light-loads-and-inertia-triggers","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-1-ultra-light-loads-and-inertia-triggers"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('e2ee61d1-1bb0-444c-aa37-cacb442e6614', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '17', '58', '- **Locking system**: Low-profile, Boss-type design:[21][22]  
  - Monobloc with locking bites and side lugs.  
  - Dual locking bolts emerging from the receiver engage the monobloc bites.  
  - Broad hinge pins and hook surfaces distribute stress.  
- Design goals:  
  - Exceptional durability under very high round counts.  
  - Low bore axis relative to the hands to minimize muzzle flip.  
  - Weight concentrated under the bore line to drive recoil straight into the shoulder.  
- **High Tech variant**: Adds 3–4 ounces of receiver mass directly in line with the chambers, further reducing muzzle rise and smoothing handling.[18]', null, '3.3.1 Action and Locking Mechanism', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Technical Design and Manufacturing > 3.3.1 Action and Locking Mechanism', '["3-3-1-action-and-locking-mechanism","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-3-technical-design-and-manufacturing-3-3-1-action-and-locking-mechanism"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('e335b7c7-3686-4f9e-b767-669b8c6f96ba', '40639b0a-dab7-48fe-8f4f-a017a331ec3e', '22', '45', '- **High Mirror Polish**  
  - Pros: visually striking; resists corrosion better due to fewer micro-crevices; classic high-end look.  
  - Cons: can create glare, especially on top surfaces; reveals any remaining scratches.

- **Satin / Matte Finish**  
  - Pros: reduces glare (important for top ribs, tangs, and some competition actions); can hide minor surface imperfections.  
  - Cons: may hold dirt/oil more; less “luxury” appearance on some surfaces.

**Practical approach:**  
- High gloss on barrel sides and key visible flats.  
- Matte or file-cut top ribs and other glare-prone surfaces.  
- Receiver finish chosen per model: from polished blue to matte or coin, balancing aesthetics and function.', null, '3.4.2 Polish Level vs Glare & Maintenance', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.2 Polish Level vs Glare & Maintenance', '["3-4-2-polish-level-vs-glare-maintenance","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-2-polish-level-vs-glare-maintenance"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('e3410c84-cf21-4b28-aacf-47ff79d1600a', '5eba6cac-e507-407b-80c3-b76bdb3f3e89', '6', '32', 'This subsection defines each major area concept more explicitly.', null, '2.3 Site Area Concepts', 'PerazziGPT v2 – Source Corpus Manifest (User-Facing Site Overview) > 2. Site Structure & Area Concepts > 2.3 Site Area Concepts', '["2-3-site-area-concepts","perazzigpt-v2-source-corpus-manifest-user-facing-site-overview-2-site-structure-area-concepts-2-3-site-area-concepts"]', '["Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:59:09.736657+00', null), ('e362fca9-dd07-4502-8e04-c43b3b5e257b', '8078a4a0-2d04-41fd-bd01-ecfc4c710fbb', '25', '50', '### Wang Zheng
