  - Wrong serial number recorded on shipping or legal documents.  
  - Incorrect model code or description.

- **Response:**  
  - Correct records and paperwork before shipping; double‑check against gun.  
  - Recognize that such errors can create serious legal and logistic problems; treat as critical.

---', null, '3.6.8 Documentation Errors', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.8 Documentation Errors', '["3-6-8-documentation-errors","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-8-documentation-errors"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('e4b42887-1e38-4381-a9b5-f47629c833aa', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '44', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 5 SC3 | Base model: high-tech-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech 5 SC3', 'Models > High Tech 5 SC3', '["model-details","high-tech-5-sc3","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('e4f4640e-d6fa-4bc7-ac88-c418e95494be', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '5', '39', 'This section captures practices and design choices that are either **distinctive to Perazzi** or significantly more emphasized by Perazzi than by general shotgun makers.', null, '3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations', '["3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('e53c80d0-5423-41c5-9b2f-24b9ea478ce9', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '25', '39', 'A master barrel maker:

- Consistently drills bores that stay straight where others might see drift.  
- Intuitively adjusts feed, speed, and chip clearing to "coax" the drill to follow a true path.  
- Reads very subtle visual cues when sighting a barrel and can immediately identify where and how far it is bending.', null, '3.7.1 Command of Drilling and Straightness', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.1 Command of Drilling and Straightness', '["3-7-1-command-of-drilling-and-straightness","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-1-command-of-drilling-and-straightness"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('e59b6d43-c118-4186-b55f-ec463a12abc9', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '17', '35', 'When a new model is introduced (e.g., a wider *High Tech* receiver compared to an *MX8*):

- **Reusing Processes vs. Investing in New Tooling**  
  - Decide whether to adapt existing machining routines or develop new fixtures and programs.  
  - Balancing consistency with legacy models versus optimizing for the new geometry.

In day-to-day work, machinists also make smaller decisions, such as removing forging flash in an extra step if it could interfere with fixturing or alignment.

---', null, '3.4.5 Prototype vs. Tradition (New Models)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.5 Prototype vs. Tradition (New Models)', '["3-4-5-prototype-vs-tradition-new-models","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-5-prototype-vs-tradition-new-models"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('e720cb86-c230-4e05-b5e2-da1c9c6adc64', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '2', '32', '- **Design & Specification Stage (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Product Engineering*, *Spec Definition*, *Design Phase*.  
  - Definition: The factory station that translates customer requirements and model options into a complete build sheet and technical dossier before production begins.

- **Product Engineer / Designer (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Spec Specialist*, *Design Specialist*, *Order-Definition Specialist*.  
  - Definition: The person responsible for interpreting orders and fitting data, choosing compatible options, resolving trade-offs, and issuing build instructions that downstream stations will follow.

- **Downstream Stations (cross-reference)**  
  - Examples: receiver/metal machining, barrel making and regulation, stock making, engraving, final assembly, testing, and inspection.  
  - The design stage ensures each of these receives clear, compatible instructions.', null, '2.1 Roles and Stages', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Stages', '["2-1-roles-and-stages","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-stages"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('e78281dd-6191-43eb-9362-4746e6482a79', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '12', '51', '- Work from order sheet and internal spec, verifying line by line:  
  - Model, gauge, barrel length, choke configuration, engraving pattern/grade, wood grade.  
  - Stock hand, cast, LOP, adjustable comb, pad type.  
  - Special requests (initials, special trigger, custom guard shape, etc.).  
- Recognize small deviations (e.g., 32" barrels fitted when order calls for 30") and escalate immediately.', null, '3.3.1 Checklist Discipline & Order Verification', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.1 Checklist Discipline & Order Verification', '["3-3-1-checklist-discipline-order-verification","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-1-checklist-discipline-order-verification"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('e7d609ff-b016-403a-a98a-c4d723622e48', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '2', '48', '- **Stock Blank Selection & Rough Shaping Station (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Wood Room*, *Stock Roughing Station*, *Stock & Fore-end Rough Shaping*.  
  - Definition: Station where walnut blanks for stock and fore-end are selected, oriented, cut, and rough-shaped to incorporate customer dimensions while leaving material for final fitting.

- **Stockmaker / Stock Blank Selector (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Stock Cutter*, *Wood Specialist*, *Stock Rougher*.  
  - Definition: Craftsperson who selects blanks, lays out patterns, operates duplicators/CNC for rough shaping, and ensures structural and aesthetic suitability.', null, '2.1 Roles and Station', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Station', '["2-1-roles-and-station","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-station"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('e8041bd4-7c20-4aed-91ec-e72327b3d65a', '6a033257-810e-408f-bcd1-5e0ba6cb7594', '1', '32', 'This document describes the **Design & Specification Definition** station (also called **Product Engineering** or **Spec Definition**) in the Perazzi factory.

This station converts customer needs and model options into a **complete, feasible, and unambiguous build specification** before any metal is cut or wood is shaped. It is the bridge between:

- The customer/fitting experience (including dealer orders and Perazzi Experience fittings), and
- The downstream factory stations (machining, barrel making, stocking, engraving, finishing, regulation, and final inspection).

This document explains:

- The **purpose** and **success criteria** of the station.
- The **inputs and outputs** handled here.
- The **core knowledge and skills** required.
- The **decisions and trade-offs** typically made.
- The **tools and measurements** used (conceptually).
- The **failure modes** and how they are prevented or diagnosed.
- What **mastery** in this role looks like, including an example vignette.

The focus is on how Perazzi integrates **shooter fit**, **model architecture**, **safety**, **balance**, and **aesthetics** into a coherent specification that the rest of the factory can build against with confidence.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.A > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-a-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:25.67313+00', null), ('e838dda6-686b-4c79-b937-f756db1811aa', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '155', '238', 'Model name: MX14 | Base model: mx14 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: unsingle | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib height: 4.0 mm | Rib style: ramp', null, '### MX14', 'Models > MX14', '["model-details","mx14","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('e89c353e-c026-4eec-b66b-85ec2ecc5d3b', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '37', '53', '- **Symptoms:** After major LOP or pad changes, trigger reach or feel becomes suboptimal.  
- **Response:**  
  - Re‑position trigger shoe to restore comfort.  
  - Confirm triggers still reset correctly and remain within safe pull weight ranges.', null, '3.6.6 Trigger & Action Issues After Fit Changes', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.6 Trigger & Action Issues After Fit Changes', '["3-6-6-trigger-action-issues-after-fit-changes","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-6-trigger-action-issues-after-fit-changes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('e8afae30-2520-4a3f-9358-72b0511faea4', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '20', '58', '- Perazzi uses a mix of **leaf and coil springs** depending on model and function:  
  - Main hammer springs: leaf or coil, customer-selectable on many MX8 triggers.[33]  
  - Ancillary functions (ejectors, top lever, sears): small coil springs.[36]
- Typical wear-and-service guidance:[35][36]  
  - Routine inspection recommended periodically for high-volume shooters.  
  - Major overhauls (springs, firing pins, etc.) often considered around **30,000–40,000 rounds** or as needed.  
  - There is **no mandated annual factory service**; the guns are designed for long intervals between major work.', null, '3.3.4 Springs and Service Intervals', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Technical Design and Manufacturing > 3.3.4 Springs and Service Intervals', '["3-3-4-springs-and-service-intervals","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-3-technical-design-and-manufacturing-3-3-4-springs-and-service-intervals"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('e8d6ded7-3faf-474d-a4de-4c21077371a3', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '92', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 5 SC3 | Base model: high-tech-s-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SC3 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S 5 SC3', 'Models > High Tech S 5 SC3', '["model-details","high-tech-s-5-sc3","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('e8e9808b-f90e-4c4d-944d-a0c6c426a2ce', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '27', '53', '- Adjustable comb hardware tools (hex keys, screwdrivers).  
- Spacers and shims (flat for LOP, tapered for pitch).  
- Bending jack for the stock wrist, with associated heat source (infrared lamp, heat gun, steam, hot oil).', null, '3.5.1 Stock & Comb Adjustment Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.1 Stock & Comb Adjustment Tools', '["3-5-1-stock-comb-adjustment-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-1-stock-comb-adjustment-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('e90fefe7-cd57-4771-b4b8-bc029531a77e', '4ae532ea-bef9-47fe-9bd9-051858902e2f', '1', '23', 'This part of the handbook is a **learning map**. It explains **how to read and internalize** the rest of the series:

- Recommends a **reading order** for Parts I–IV.
- Shows how to **layer understanding** from big-picture overview → station-level detail → cross-cutting systems → comparisons.
