The goal is to help a reader (or AI) build a **coherent mental model** of the Perazzi factory system and the shotgun itself, instead of memorizing disconnected facts.

---', null, '1. High-Level Overview', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 1. High-Level Overview', '["1-high-level-overview","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-1-high-level-overview"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('e9180d89-344c-4212-bb53-a6212a8efe12', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '5', '51', '- **Runover**  
  - Cutter accidentally crosses the intended border line or extends past the pattern boundary.

- **Double Cut / Wandering Line**  
  - Line that drifts from its intended path or doubles back, causing irregular diamonds.

- **Flat-Topped Diamonds**  
  - Diamonds with flattened instead of sharp peaks, indicating insufficient depth or uneven cutting.

- **Tear-Out / Chip-Out**  
  - Small pieces of wood breaking away in or near the checkered area due to grain behavior or tool issues.

- **Sparkle**  
  - Visual effect from many small facets catching light slightly differently; characteristic of well-executed hand checkering.

---', null, '2.4 Process & Quality Terms', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Process & Quality Terms', '["2-4-process-quality-terms","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-process-quality-terms"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('e9202f2f-5e19-4aa3-8b6a-12c8bfdc499e', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '24', '39', 'Mastery in Perazzi’s barrel shop is a combination of precision engineering, sensory acuity, and long-term experience.', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('e9717bbc-9729-4b42-88ca-7f8c9c220a80', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '7', '51', 'Checkering is considered successful when:

- **Lines**  
  - Straight and evenly spaced.  
  - Cleanly cut with no fuzzy edges or chatter.  
  - Intersect accurately to form **sharp, consistent diamonds**.

- **Pattern Placement**  
  - Symmetric and correctly located on both sides of grip and fore-end.  
  - Coverage corresponds to contact areas of the shooter’s hands.  
  - Design layout complements the gun’s style and wood figure.

- **Borders**  
  - Crisp and even, typically single or double lines framing the pattern.  
  - No runovers or wavering border lines.

- **Depth & Feel**  
  - Diamonds are cut to **uniform depth**, with points neither excessively sharp nor too flat.  
  - Grip feels consistently “raspy” – grippy without being painfully abrasive.  
  - Medium-coarse LPI (often ~18–22 for competition use) yields a balance of grip and comfort.

- **Overall Impression**  
  - Pattern may appear almost machined in regularity, yet under magnification reveals slight individual variations that create a **lively sparkle**.  
  - In hand, there are no smooth “bald” patches or areas noticeably rougher than others.

---', null, '3.1.2 Success Criteria', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.G > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Station Purpose & Success Criteria > 3.1.2 Success Criteria', '["3-1-2-success-criteria","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-g-3-main-content-3-1-station-purpose-success-criteria-3-1-2-success-criteria"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:44.833658+00', null), ('e99ba1df-d721-4c41-9670-70667eccb0c1', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '30', '32', '- [1] Statement that Perazzi competition guns are built as workhorses capable of firing hundreds of thousands of rounds.  
- [2] Description of Perazzi’s made-to-order approach and customer specification options.  
