- **Perazzi Classic** (1998–2005): special handicap event at the Grand American, often awarding a new Perazzi shotgun as the top prize.[142]
- Perazzi continues to sponsor specific events (e.g. President’s Handicap) and maintain a high-profile vendor presence.[143]
- Daniele Perazzi was inducted into the **Trapshooting Hall of Fame** in 2019 for his contributions to ATA trap.[144][11]', null, '3.9.2 American Trap – Grand American & ATA', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.9 Events, Community, and Legacy > 3.9.2 American Trap – Grand American & ATA', '["3-9-2-american-trap-grand-american-ata","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-9-events-community-and-legacy-3-9-2-american-trap-grand-american-ata"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('ec7e6ced-285e-4381-945a-ede9ae612e69', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '189', '238', 'Model name: MX28 | Base model: mx28 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SC2 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 28ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX28', 'Models > MX28', '["model-details","mx28","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('ec9d6121-112e-4585-a503-6734793b588c', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '22', '49', '- **Standard Factory Load**  
  - Pros: consistent reference; easy to compare performance across guns.  
  - Cons: may not reflect specific customer ammunition choices.

- **Customer-Specified Load**  
  - Pros: reveals how the gun behaves with the shooter’s real-world ammo.  
  - Cons: more variables; results specific to that load.

**Practical approach:**  
- Use a **trusted, consistent target load** for QC.  
- Add customer-specific ammo tests if required, recording any notable differences.', null, '3.4.4 Ammunition Selection', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Ammunition Selection', '["3-4-4-ammunition-selection","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-ammunition-selection"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('eca541d0-460a-4dcc-a6dd-adfd2a442cc9', '00ee41e2-2a64-4498-9321-fde7e5df53f0', '27', '51', '- **Rags & Oiled Cloths**  
  - For final wipe-down; often branded silicone cloths or similar.

- **Case & Packaging Inspection**  
  - Visual and tactile inspection of case interior (no debris, correct inserts, accessories in place).', null, '3.5.3 Cleaning & Preservation Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.M > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.3 Cleaning & Preservation Tools', '["3-5-3-cleaning-preservation-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-m-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-3-cleaning-preservation-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:55.761534+00', null), ('ecb3fcf9-df8c-406c-8dd0-4ac71a2006e3', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '5', '35', '- **Dimensional Tolerance**  
  - Allowable deviation from nominal dimension (expressed in thousandths of an inch or hundredths of a millimeter).  
  - Critical for hinge spacing, locking surfaces, trigger and sear pin locations, and firing pin alignment.

- **Datum Surfaces**  
  - Reference surfaces (e.g., standing breech, water table) from which other measurements are taken.

- **Allowance for Hand Fit**  
  - Intentional extra material (e.g., ~0.1 mm or a few thousandths of an inch) left on critical surfaces so later craftspeople can hand-fit components to a perfect final interface.', null, '2.4 Measurement and Tolerance Concepts', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.4 Measurement and Tolerance Concepts', '["2-4-measurement-and-tolerance-concepts","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-4-measurement-and-tolerance-concepts"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('ed1694f0-df27-4393-9f2c-7abf6f36082b', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '4', '58', '- **Trap / ATA Trap**  
  - Governing body: ATA (Amateur Trapshooting Association).  
  - Typical Perazzi models: TM series, MX trap models, Grand America 1 & 2, High Tech trap combos.

- **Olympic Trap / Bunker Trap**  
  - Governing body: ISSF.  
  - Perazzi association: Major platform for Olympic success since 1964.

- **Skeet**  
  - Disciplines: Olympic skeet, national skeet models.  
  - Typical models: MX and High Tech sporting/skeet configurations.

- **Sporting Clays / FITASC**  
  - Governing body: FITASC for international disciplines.  
  - Typical models: MX8, MX2000, MXS, High Tech sporting builds, small-gauge models.

- **Live Pigeon / Helice (ZZ)**  
  - Use case: High-reliability competition requiring heavy, tight-choked O/Us.', null, '2.3 Disciplines & Organizations', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Disciplines & Organizations', '["2-3-disciplines-organizations","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-disciplines-organizations"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('ed22feb8-7304-4f3c-aeeb-cb55c11cbf31', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '33', '38', '- Release triggers (fire on release instead of pull) are complex to design safely.  
- They often require specialized knowledge and are treated as niche or aftermarket in many contexts.

**Caveat:**  
- These systems may be handled by specific specialists or under special procedures, with heightened focus on safety and fail-safes.', null, '4.3 Release Triggers (Specialized, Niche)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.D > 4. Edge Cases, Exceptions, and Caveats > 4.3 Release Triggers (Specialized, Niche)', '["4-3-release-triggers-specialized-niche","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-d-4-edge-cases-exceptions-and-caveats-4-3-release-triggers-specialized-niche"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:05.619789+00', null), ('ed2aa5d4-f392-44e2-aa57-446d60a5e603', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '16', '238', 'Model name: High Tech 2020 | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: 2020 | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech 2020', 'Models > High Tech 2020', '["model-details","high-tech-2020","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('ed469960-51f8-41a2-98f6-46bb98e6b5d4', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '11', '35', 'Workers at this station combine **advanced machining skill** with **traditional gunsmithing awareness**.

Key domains of knowledge and skill include:

- **Machining and Metallurgy**  
  - Understanding how Perazzi’s steels behave under cutting and heat.  
  - Sequencing rough, semi-finish, and finish cuts to control stress relief and warpage.  
  - Managing tool wear to maintain consistent surface finishes, especially on critical interfaces (e.g., locking surfaces, breech face).

- **CNC and Manual Machine Operation**  
  - Programming and setting up multi-axis CNC mills (e.g., 4- or 5-axis) to cut complex receiver geometries.  
  - Using manual mills or other machines for follow-up adjustments.  
  - Knowing exactly where to stop machining and **leave material** for hand fitting (e.g., extra 0.1 mm on locking bite surfaces).

- **Blueprint Reading and Metrology**  
  - Reading digital and paper drawings with tolerances, datum schemes, and surface finish requirements.  
  - Using micrometers, calipers, gauges, and potentially coordinate measuring machines (CMMs) to verify dimensions.

- **Firearm-Specific Geometry and Function**  
  - Understanding how hinge geometry sets barrel angle and headspace.  
  - Knowing how locking lug cuts and bolt recesses affect lock-up feel and longevity.  
  - Recognizing which dimensions are safety-critical versus primarily cosmetic.

- **Problem-Solving and Adaptation**  
  - Diagnosing issues such as tool breakage, variable forging stock, or small programming errors.  
  - Adjusting offsets or process steps to maintain tolerance without compromising downstream fitting.

- **Shared Vocabulary and Culture**  
  - Using terms like *trunnions*, *locking bites*, *water table*, *standing breech*, and *two thou* fluently.  
  - Maintaining a culture of measuring precisely and "leaving something" for the next craftsman.

A master at this station anticipates how each dimensional choice will affect the work of barrel fitters, stockmakers, and assemblers later.

---', null, '3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills', '["3-3-core-knowledge-skills","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('ed4f7b67-2249-47ee-bb96-b29ab1f01369', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '6', '49', '- **Ejector/Extractor Function**  
  - Ejectors must throw fired hulls clear; unfired shells should extract without ejection.  
  - Live fire confirms behavior under realistic pressure and vibration.

- **Trigger Reset & Doubling**  
  - Inertia triggers must reset reliably under actual recoil.  
  - Any **doubling** (both barrels firing on one pull) under live fire is unacceptable and triggers rework.

- **Recoil Feel**  
  - Overall recoil “sharpness” and balance under typical shooting conditions.  
  - Not a pass/fail metric alone, but one of the cues used in evaluating the gun.

---', null, '2.5 Mechanical Behavior Under Live Fire', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.5 Mechanical Behavior Under Live Fire', '["2-5-mechanical-behavior-under-live-fire","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-5-mechanical-behavior-under-live-fire"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('ed683dca-45e6-45ca-b77d-be4ccaf0350b', '0894113c-c061-44ea-aa24-5dbe961f9a09', '0', '51', '- Source: Internal Perazzi USA Document - The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun
