---', null, '0. Metadata', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.H > 0. Metadata', '["0-metadata","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-h-0-metadata"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:02.508279+00', null), ('f4a77ef4-d8ae-428e-95b7-195d8542b6f3', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '14', '32', '- **Goal**  
  Produce perfectly straight, durable barrel sets that **shoot to the same point of aim**.

- **Inputs**  
  - Chromium-molybdenum steel bars for barrel tubes.  
  - Steel **monobloc** forging (breech block).  
  - Reamers and deep-drill tools.  
  - Sight rib material.  
  - Solder and related joining materials.

- **Outputs**  
  - A matched pair of barrel tubes fitted into a monobloc, forming an **O/U barrel set**.  
  - Ribs soldered on.  
  - Bores polished and straightened.  
  - Barrels **regulated** so both patterns converge correctly.

- **Owned by**  
  - Barrel maker (drilling/reaming specialist).  
  - Barrel fitter (soldering, straightening, regulating).

---', null, '3.3.3 Barrel Fabrication & Fitting', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.3 End-to-End Production Process Map > 3.3.3 Barrel Fabrication & Fitting', '["3-3-3-barrel-fabrication-fitting","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-3-end-to-end-production-process-map-3-3-3-barrel-fabrication-fitting"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('f4b284d1-28d2-45be-9ef8-01f0bdfb09e2', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '33', '53', '- **Symptoms:** Audible crack; visible fracture in the stock, especially at the wrist.  
- **Cause:** Excessive bending force, insufficient heat/conditioning, or unfavorable grain.  
- **Response:**  
  - For minor cracks, carefully repair (e.g., adhesive and refinish) if structurally acceptable.  
  - For serious damage, stock replacement and restarting fit on a new blank.  
  - Prevention via conservative bends and respect for wood limits.', null, '3.6.2 Over-Bending or Stock Breakage', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.2 Over-Bending or Stock Breakage', '["3-6-2-over-bending-or-stock-breakage","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-2-over-bending-or-stock-breakage"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('f4dabcd2-17f4-4789-b24c-ce20640ccba0', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '17', '40', '- **Very Tight Fit**  
  - Pros: extremely solid feel; action and stock may stay together from friction alone.  
  - Cons: risk of splitting wood during assembly/disassembly; harder maintenance.

- **Slightly Looser Fit**  
  - Pros: easier to service; less risk of stress-induced cracking.  
  - Cons: potential for subtle movement if contact is not controlled.

**Practical approach:**

- Aim for **snug, stress-free seating**:  
  - May relieve non-critical areas slightly so main recoil shoulders take the load.  
  - Allow disassembly without hammering while still preventing any perceptible movement under recoil.', null, '3.4.1 Fit Tightness vs Ease of Disassembly', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.1 Fit Tightness vs Ease of Disassembly', '["3-4-1-fit-tightness-vs-ease-of-disassembly","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-1-fit-tightness-vs-ease-of-disassembly"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('f4e3a239-a773-418a-8c36-6008f73ee5f5', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '112', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S X 5 | Base model: high-tech-s-5 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: X | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S X 5', 'Models > High Tech S X 5', '["model-details","high-tech-s-x-5","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('f4ee5733-5b56-4663-a10f-50256991d334', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '17', '49', '- Working with fitters and shooters to:

- Fine-tune adjustable combs and ribs.  
  - Perform multiple pattern tests as necessary to reach the shooter’s preferred POI.

- Remembering approximate rules of thumb for how much adjustment is needed to move POI by a given amount at distance.', null, '3.3.7 Iterative Final Fitting Support', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.7 Iterative Final Fitting Support', '["3-3-7-iterative-final-fitting-support","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-7-iterative-final-fitting-support"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('f5b1b3af-12f6-4e35-bce2-6ab9954d2e16', 'ea11bfa6-bea4-49fe-a9c8-e2f8d739eec6', '6', '38', '- **Intercepting Sear (conceptual)**  
  - A secondary sear designed to catch a hammer if the primary sear releases unexpectedly.  
  - The source text notes uncertainty on whether Perazzi uses intercepting sears; this concept is included as general background.

- **Jar Test / Bump Test**  
  - Manual test where the action or stock is bumped or struck to verify that hammers do not fall accidentally.

- **Snap Cap / Dummy Round**  
  - Non-live cartridge used for testing firing pin strike and function without risk of discharge.

