---', null, '5.2 External Reference Markers (from original text)', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 5. References & Cross-Links > 5.2 External Reference Markers (from original text)', '["5-2-external-reference-markers-from-original-text","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-5-references-cross-links-5-2-external-reference-markers-from-original-text"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('f6574553-0bb4-4ec9-ad27-90d9bf19b2a9', 'fae85afb-4054-48f2-a2a6-8d756c851b62', '10', '32', 'Compared to traditional English “best gun” makers (e.g., Purdey, Holland & Holland):

- **Primary Use Case**
  - English best guns:
    - Often **side-by-side** designs.
    - Traditionally optimized for **game hunting**.
    - Built for **field use**, not necessarily massive clay-target volume.
  - Perazzi:
    - Focused on **competition** (trap, skeet, sporting).
    - Designed explicitly for **high-volume shooting** and repeated recoil cycles.

- **Construction Techniques**
  - English best guns:
    - May rely heavily on **traditional case-hardening**.
    - Feature fully hand-cut parts, with extensive manual shaping.
  - Perazzi:
    - Leverages **CNC machining** and modern steels to achieve precision.
    - Retains hand-fitting where it matters (action, lockwork, stock fit).

- **Aesthetic & Ethos**
  - English guns:
    - Often prioritize **lavish engraving**, ornate detailing, and classic luxury.
  - Perazzi:
    - Emphasizes **understated, sporty elegance**.
    - Offers high-level engraving and exhibition-grade walnut, but aligns aesthetics with **performance-first** ethos.

In practical ownership terms:

- A Perazzi owner gets:
  - A gun that can be **rebuilt indefinitely** (wear parts replaceable).
  - A build tailored **exactly** to their shooting style and physical dimensions.
- The brand’s ethos can be summarized as:  
  **“Performance first, without compromise in aesthetics or feel.”**

---', null, '3.2.3 Perazzi vs. English “Best Gun” Makers', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part I: Product & System Overview > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Architectural Hallmarks and Brand Positioning > 3.2.3 Perazzi vs. English “Best Gun” Makers', '["3-2-3-perazzi-vs-english-best-gun-makers","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-i-product-system-overview-3-main-content-3-2-architectural-hallmarks-and-brand-positioning-3-2-3-perazzi-vs-english-best-gun-makers"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:11.853745+00', null), ('f6724992-0f92-4863-a8ac-69b804559d04', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '15', '45', '- Spraying multiple **thin coats** to avoid runs and orange peel.  
- Controlling viscosity and air pressure for fine atomization.  
- Leveling and sanding between coats:  
  - Cutting back orange peel or minor defects with fine paper.  
  - Avoiding cutting through at edges.

- Final rub-out:  
  - Using fine abrasives or compounds to reach uniform satin or high gloss without swirl marks.  
  - For matte finishes, deliberately knocking down gloss uniformly.', null, '3.3.5 Application Techniques – Polyurethane / Lacquer', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.5 Application Techniques – Polyurethane / Lacquer', '["3-3-5-application-techniques-polyurethane-lacquer","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-5-application-techniques-polyurethane-lacquer"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('f685f90d-969d-4ba8-99e9-07901375f5b4', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '42', '49', '- Masters clean the gun after patterning:

- Remove powder residue from bores and action.  
  - Lightly re‑oil and wipe external surfaces.

- They also:

- Note recurring patterns in QC (e.g., if a model is consistently a little high or left).  
  - Communicate these trends back to barrel regulators, fitters, or engineering for possible process adjustments.

---', null, '3.7.5 Care After Testing & Feedback to Factory', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.5 Care After Testing & Feedback to Factory', '["3-7-5-care-after-testing-feedback-to-factory","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-5-care-after-testing-feedback-to-factory"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('f69aef75-c90b-4ee5-b9f3-94b77b89d30a', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '66', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S | Base model: high-tech-s | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: Standard | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech S', 'Models > High Tech S', '["model-details","high-tech-s","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('f6bd423e-b65b-4102-a9a7-47b62fd24548', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '4', '39', '- **Pattern Board / Pattern Plate**  
  A large board used to visualize shot distribution at a set range (typically ~32–40 yards).

- **Pattern Uniformity**  
  Evenness of pellet distribution in a defined circle (often 30") at a specific distance. Voids and “donut” patterns are undesirable.

- **Choke**  
  Constriction at the muzzle that shapes pattern density and range (e.g., Improved Cylinder, Modified, Improved Modified). Can be fixed or via choke tubes.', null, '2.3 Patterning & Performance', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.3 Patterning & Performance', '["2-3-patterning-performance","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-3-patterning-performance"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('f6cbeacd-9f8c-46f2-aad3-3079d2e30348', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '6', '36', '- **Exclusivity Over Accessibility**  
  Perazzi does **not** compete on price, volume, or advertising saturation. It emphasizes rarity, elite access, and personalized experiences (e.g., Bespoke Build, Perazzi Invitational).

- **Narrative Over Visibility**  
  Instead of conventional ads, the brand prefers immersive storytelling arcs. The audience is meant to **feel, internalize, and live** the Perazzi experience rather than passively watch it.

- **Experience Over Sponsorship**  
  While competitors buy visibility through broad sponsorships, Perazzi focuses on signature events that act as transformative experiences (e.g., Perazzi Invitational, where participation equals belonging).', null, '2.5 Strategic Brand Themes', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.5 Strategic Brand Themes', '["2-5-strategic-brand-themes","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-5-strategic-brand-themes"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('f79f4cf5-d70e-4cf7-a30e-88359d8570b4', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '158', '238', 'Model name: MX16 SC2 | Base model: mx16 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SC2 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 16ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX16 SC2', 'Models > MX16 SC2', '["model-details","mx16-sc2","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('f8139901-5711-43f2-ab2a-88c0de61b05a', '30dc5da6-b9ed-450e-8736-4a6dfce0983a', '11', '40', '- Uses **inletting black**: metal is coated with soot or paste, pressed into wood, leaving marks where wood is high.  
- Removes only the shiny/high spots with small, razor-sharp chisels and scrapers.  
- Understands which surfaces are **primary bearing surfaces** (e.g., stock head contacting action shoulders) and which should be slightly relieved.  
- Aims for a fit where action settles fully with even contact at intended bearing points and slight relief in non-critical areas.  
- Avoids prying or levering cuts that could chip or crack the wood, especially around tangs and thin sections.', null, '3.3.1 Precision Hand Inletting', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.F > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Core Knowledge & Skills > 3.3.1 Precision Hand Inletting', '["3-3-1-precision-hand-inletting","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-f-3-main-content-3-3-core-knowledge-skills-3-3-1-precision-hand-inletting"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:32.068221+00', null), ('f8249ee4-a8df-4512-bcbe-1288369d2927', '1ae4b60f-6ad5-4475-9eb9-cabf6b0e829c', '34', '56', '- **Symptoms:**  
  - Excessive resistance when opening or closing; grinding feel.  
- **Likely Causes:**  
  - Over-tight lock-up, burrs on bites or locking surfaces.  
  - Cocking cams or rods binding.  
  - Ejector springs or sears causing excess friction.  
- **Diagnosis & Correction:**  
  - Inspect with marking compounds (e.g., contact blue) to reveal high spots.  
  - Lightly stone or polish offending surfaces; adjust springs as needed.  
  - Aim for firm but smooth motion.', null, '3.6.4 Hard Opening or Closing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.J > 3. Main Content > 3.6 Failure Modes & Diagnosis > 3.6.4 Hard Opening or Closing', '["3-6-4-hard-opening-or-closing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-j-3-main-content-3-6-failure-modes-diagnosis-3-6-4-hard-opening-or-closing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:46.826724+00', null), ('f86ea85a-67a8-4911-8948-e422a930d345', '536080f1-89e0-4124-9514-2ba022ce8a4b', '9', '36', 'Perazzi is positioned as **more than a product manufacturer**:

- It is framed as a **creator of personal legacies**, not simply a maker of shotguns.
- Ownership is described as **entering a legacy of mastery, artistry, and emotional transformation**, rather than acquiring a tool.
- A Perazzi is characterized as something you **earn, embody, and become**, aligning the gun with the shooter’s identity and life story.
- The brand targets individuals who demand **meaning, depth, and performance** from the objects they choose.', null, '3.1 Core Brand Identity', 'Perazzi Brand Ethos & Personality – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Core Brand Identity', '["3-1-core-brand-identity","perazzi-brand-ethos-personality-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-1-core-brand-identity"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:25.853025+00', null), ('f885fbcc-7beb-482b-ab9e-d9235c5326ff', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '2', '53', '- **Final Fitting & Customer-Specific Adjustments Station (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Final Fitting Bench*, *Customer Fitting*, *Personal Fit Station*.  
  - Definition: Station where the nearly finished shotgun is adjusted to match the individual shooter’s physique, preferences, and real‑world performance.

- **Fitter / Final Fitting Specialist (canonical)**  
  - Synonyms: *Gun Fitter*, *Stock Fitter*, *Perazzi Experience Fitter*.  
  - Definition: Craftsperson who interprets shooter feedback and pattern results, makes small but critical mechanical and stock adjustments, and coaches the shooter through the fitting process.', null, '2.1 Roles and Station', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Roles and Station', '["2-1-roles-and-station","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-roles-and-station"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('f8c784d7-3edb-4ab5-9f31-46222f78f551', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '187', '238', 'Model name: MX2005 | Base model: mx2005 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: 2000 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: unsingle | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 5-notch adjustable | Rib height: 24.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### MX2005', 'Models > MX2005', '["model-details","mx2005","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('f8fc67d3-35ea-49b2-8215-adceeba383d5', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '52', '58', '- Common third-party modifications: barrel porting, forcing-cone lengthening, aftermarket adjustable combs, recoil reducers, and release-trigger conversions.  
- Factory disclaimers:  
  - Such modifications are at the owner’s risk.  
  - Perazzi may decline warranty or certain services on heavily modified barrels or actions.  
  - If necessary, the factory may charge to replace non-factory parts back to original spec.', null, '3.10.5 Aftermarket Modifications and Factory Service', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.10 Counterfeits, Grey Market, and Service Integrity > 3.10.5 Aftermarket Modifications and Factory Service', '["3-10-5-aftermarket-modifications-and-factory-service","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-10-counterfeits-grey-market-and-service-integrity-3-10-5-aftermarket-modifications-and-factory-service"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('f9048eb2-9cd1-4ef6-9ae2-f45ae161f7db', 'dadad96d-904b-4c92-af84-aba4f15f7e85', '9', '48', '- **Walnut Blanks**  
  - Stock blanks and fore-end blanks, often from high-grade Turkish or French walnut.  
  - Air-dried and then conditioned (e.g., 3–4 months in controlled humidity rooms) with thousands of blanks in inventory.

- **Customer & Design Specifications**  
  - Fit data: LOP, drop at comb/heel, cast at heel/toe, pitch, grip size/shape, presence of Monte Carlo comb.  
  - Aesthetic grade: SC2, SC3, SCO, etc.  
  - Handedness: right- or left-handed (affects cast direction and grain considerations).

- **Patterns & Models**  
  - Pattern stocks for different disciplines (trap, skeet, sporting, field).  
  - CAD/CAM models or parametric templates for CNC-based shaping.

- **Machines & Tools (conceptual)**  
  - Band saws for rough cutting.  
  - Stock duplicators/pantograph carvers.  
  - CNC routers for advanced shaping.  
  - Clamps, vises, and fixturing systems (including sacrificial blocks for mounting).  
  - Layout tools: templates, straightedges, rulers, protractors, chalk/pencils.

- **Reference Fitting Data**  
  - Try-gun or adjustable prototype stock set to the customer’s fitted dimensions.  
  - Notes from fitting sessions.

- **Environmental & Wood Data**  
  - Moisture measurements or inferred dryness based on blank age and storage.', null, '3.2.1 Inputs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.E > 3. Main Content > 3.2 Inputs & Outputs > 3.2.1 Inputs', '["3-2-1-inputs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-e-3-main-content-3-2-inputs-outputs-3-2-1-inputs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:55:17.919795+00', null), ('f93ec497-d7e7-4b5b-8c2a-826dcb22f89f', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '80', '238', 'Model name: High Tech S 2024 3 | Base model: high-tech-s-3 | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: 2024 | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 3-notch adjustable | Rib height: 8.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### High Tech S 2024 3', 'Models > High Tech S 2024 3', '["model-details","high-tech-s-2024-3","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('f958bce7-69c8-4ad2-9d91-36108b16b510', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '21', '39', '- **Straightening Bench**  
  - Bench with rollers or V-blocks to support the barrel, plus a controlled press or lever.  
  - Used alongside a visual reference (target with line) to find and correct bends.

- **Regulation Jigs**  
  - Fixtures to hold tubes and monobloc in precise relationship while setting muzzle spacing and alignment.  
  - May use collimators, lasers, or visual targets to align bores.

- **Soldering/Brazing Equipment**  
  - Gas torches, induction heaters, or furnaces as appropriate.  
  - Clamps and fixtures for holding barrels and ribs while solder flows and cools.

- **Files and Scrapers**  
  - Used to remove excess solder, clean joints, and refine external surfaces prior to polishing.

- **Choke Laps and Reamers**  
  - Tools for fine-tuning choke constriction and pattern behavior.', null, '3.5.2 Alignment, Straightening & Joining Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.2 Alignment, Straightening & Joining Tools', '["3-5-2-alignment-straightening-joining-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-2-alignment-straightening-joining-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:47.674361+00', null), ('f9a6b1a0-f796-4498-a436-bd1937f1db77', '67ca387d-48bc-4047-9404-209a02645c52', '9', '39', '- All double guns require regulation; Perazzi’s approach is **labor-intensive and traditional**:
  - Barrels are straightened by eye and press by experienced barrel straighteners.
  - Indoor ranges and pattern plates are used to confirm regulation and POI.
- Distinctive elements:
  - Manual straightening and regulation are retained even as some volume makers use wider allowances or more automated methods.
- Culture of mastery:
  - Barrel straightening is described as taking **years to master**.
  - Reflects Perazzi’s willingness to **invest skilled labor where it impacts performance**.', null, '3.1.4 Barrel Regulation Philosophy', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part IV: Perazzi vs General Gunmaking > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Perazzi-Specific Practices and Innovations > 3.1.4 Barrel Regulation Philosophy', '["3-1-4-barrel-regulation-philosophy","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iv-perazzi-vs-general-gunmaking-3-main-content-3-1-perazzi-specific-practices-and-innovations-3-1-4-barrel-regulation-philosophy"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:41.686758+00', null), ('f9e0881e-9b1c-4e98-b48c-f8dec9f8e681', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '52', '238', 'Model name: High Tech Lusso | Base model: high-tech | Platform: HT | Category: competition | Disciplines: Skeet, Sporting | Engraving Grade: Lusso | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### High Tech Lusso', 'Models > High Tech Lusso', '["model-details","high-tech-lusso","platform:ht"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('fab4bb27-8a3c-49eb-9f67-a5faaa8116bf', 'e71c2213-11d3-4fbb-ad08-12dd9cb1fbe1', '37', '49', 'Mastery at this station lies in **rapid, accurate interpretation** of patterns, efficient corrections, and collaboration with fitters and customers.', null, '3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.K > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like', '["3-7-what-mastery-looks-like","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-k-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:15.866317+00', null), ('faba973f-2330-4359-b9e4-b0d0ec202fb3', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '201', '238', 'Model name: MX410 SC3 Gold Sideplates | Base model: mx410 | Platform: MX | Category: game | Disciplines: Game | Engraving Grade: SC3 Gold Sideplates | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 410ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: fixed | Trigger springs: coil | Rib: fixed', null, '### MX410 SC3 Gold Sideplates', 'Models > MX410 SC3 Gold Sideplates', '["model-details","mx410-sc3-gold-sideplates","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('faecf435-3828-4a19-b339-d4b874f67933', 'c5b4fa4d-9f28-4908-a706-fbdc7cefdf94', '45', '53', '- Ultimate sign of success: the shooter mounts the gun, shoots, and says some version of  
  **“It feels like a part of me.”**  
- At that point, the fitter has aligned decades of craft and factory work with the individual shooter’s body and style.

---', null, '3.7.7 The “Part of Me” Test', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.L > 3. Main Content > 3.7 What Mastery Looks Like > 3.7.7 The “Part of Me” Test', '["3-7-7-the-part-of-me-test","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-l-3-main-content-3-7-what-mastery-looks-like-3-7-7-the-part-of-me-test"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:57:33.590816+00', null), ('fb6b4327-8b3f-4066-ab83-6712356c1bc4', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '181', '238', 'Model name: MX2000/RS | Base model: mx10rs | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: Trap | Engraving Grade: 2000 | Combo configuration: yes | Gauges: 12ga | Barrel configuration style: unsingle | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: adjustable | Rib notches: 4-notch adjustable | Rib height: 10.0 mm | Rib style: notch', null, '### MX2000/RS', 'Models > MX2000/RS', '["model-details","mx2000-rs","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('fb7eed02-1740-423c-94cb-1030ccb016fb', '053bd335-5ad7-49ba-a915-991f3ed97590', '34', '39', 'Aesthetics in Perazzi guns:

- Express brand identity (modern Italian craftsmanship with competition heritage).
- Give owners a **visual language** to express their own identity and legacy.
- Support performance by:
  - Strengthening emotional bond to the gun.
  - Enhancing confidence.

Form and function converge so that:

