- The Perazzi in the shooter’s hands becomes:
  - An extension of their will.
  - A reflection of their character.

---', null, '3.4.7 Summary: Aesthetics as Functional Identity', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part III: Cross-Cutting Systems > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Aesthetics & Identity > 3.4.7 Summary: Aesthetics as Functional Identity', '["3-4-7-summary-aesthetics-as-functional-identity","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-iii-cross-cutting-systems-3-main-content-3-4-aesthetics-identity-3-4-7-summary-aesthetics-as-functional-identity"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:22.014078+00', null), ('fc09aff6-8e05-43dd-88ad-c34dab4dd2f8', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '21', '58', '- Barrel weights, stock dimensions, and receiver mass are tuned to achieve a desired balance point.[37][38]  
- Customers can specify their preferred balance (e.g. slightly muzzle-heavy vs. neutral).  
- High Tech receivers place more mass between the hands for smoother, more "centered" swing characteristics.[18][39]
- Stocks may be hollowed or weighted to fine-tune balance; many are fitted with cast-off and palm swell for ergonomics.[40][41]', null, '3.3.5 Balance and Handling', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 3. Main Content > 3.3 Technical Design and Manufacturing > 3.3.5 Balance and Handling', '["3-3-5-balance-and-handling","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-3-main-content-3-3-technical-design-and-manufacturing-3-3-5-balance-and-handling"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('fca5c990-9134-40c5-98bb-46d16d6adb34', '82a899f9-2019-4029-b599-221316624acd', '7', '38', 'Wendell Cherry’s journey to the pinnacle of sporting clays is described as unique and inspiring. A professional musician in his early life, Wendell performed at iconic venues like the Grand Ole Opry and Ryman Auditorium before discovering clay shooting in the mid-1990s. Trading guitar strings for shotgun shells, he quickly proved a natural talent – shooting competitively by 2002 and never looking back[1].

Wendell’s background instilled in him a quiet confidence and discipline; he balances a prolific competitive career with a passion for coaching, guiding countless shooters with the same calm, focused demeanor that defines his own style[2][3].

Over a career spanning decades, Wendell has amassed a resume described as one few can rival. Inducted into the NSCA Hall of Fame in 2012[4], he is a multi-time U.S. Open Sporting Clays Champion, most recently claiming the 2023 HOA title after a dramatic shoot-off in Arizona[5]. He has represented the United States internationally, earning a World Sporting Clays Silver Medal as the top American in 2015[6]. Wendell has shot a perfect 100-straight in competition on five separate occasions – presented as a testament to his precision and composure under pressure[7].

His championship tally in the source includes:

- Numerous NSCA regional wins.  
- National FITASC titles.  
- Over a dozen Team USA appearances[8].

These achievements collectively position him as one of the most decorated sporting clays shooters of his generation. Despite these accolades, the source emphasizes that Wendell remains grounded and approachable, serving as a mentor as much as a champion.', null, '3.1.1.1 Biography & Background', 'Perazzi USA Team & Supported Shooters (AI-Optimized Reference) > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Sponsored Shooters (Perazzi USA Team) > 3.1.1 Wendell Cherry – Sporting Clays (Sponsored Shooter) > 3.1.1.1 Biography & Background', '["3-1-1-1-biography-background","perazzi-usa-team-supported-shooters-ai-optimized-reference-3-main-content-3-1-sponsored-shooters-perazzi-usa-team-3-1-1-wendell-cherry-sporting-clays-sponsored-shooter-3-1-1-1-biography-background"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:56.586148+00', null), ('fcadb263-b534-44df-9225-c15cb404c56b', '4ae532ea-bef9-47fe-9bd9-051858902e2f', '10', '23', '- After absorbing Parts III–IV, **circle back** to specific Part II chapters:
  - Now you have better perspective on:
    - How each station supports cross-cutting systems (quality, fit, performance).  
    - How specific details influence handling and longevity.

- Example:
  - After understanding in Part III how fit and balance impact performance, re-read **Stock Inletting & Shaping**.  
  - The previously minor detail “they left 2 mm extra here” now makes sense as a deliberate choice that allows later bending or adjustment.', null, '3.1.5 Step 5 – Revisit Part II as Needed', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 3. Main Content > 3.1 Recommended Reading Order & Strategy > 3.1.5 Step 5 – Revisit Part II as Needed', '["3-1-5-step-5-revisit-part-ii-as-needed","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-3-main-content-3-1-recommended-reading-order-strategy-3-1-5-step-5-revisit-part-ii-as-needed"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('fcdfd989-a5c2-4089-9f92-513eaae256de', '226d9a88-7f09-43b1-983c-d236d935dd77', '220', '238', 'Model name: MX8 SCO | Base model: mx8 | Platform: MX | Category: competition | Disciplines: All Disciplines | Engraving Grade: SCO | Combo configuration: no | Gauges: 12ga, 20ga | Barrel configuration style: over-under | Trigger: removable | Trigger springs: flat, coil | Rib: fixed | Rib style: flat, step, ramp', null, '### MX8 SCO', 'Models > MX8 SCO', '["model-details","mx8-sco","platform:mx"]', '["Prospect","Owner"]', '["Analyst","Achiever","Prestige"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:52:48.829876+00', null), ('fcf36a9b-fd00-4be7-800d-8102080d384f', 'f8b0315e-200b-46a7-afda-d38cc89aff71', '13', '39', 'Barrel makers continuously balance safety, performance, weight, and durability.', null, '3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.C > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs', '["3-4-decisions-trade-offs","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-c-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever"