---', null, '0. Metadata', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part V: Learning Map for the Reader > 0. Metadata', '["0-metadata","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-v-learning-map-for-the-reader-0-metadata"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:58:59.884559+00', null), ('fd8d8c9b-8c78-4657-8a3f-229919a97052', '70499c1f-6a48-44b7-804a-fc63b2ea9317', '16', '35', '- **Sequence of Operations**  
  - Removing too much supporting material too early risks flexing or distortion during later cuts.  
  - Keeping excess material too long may prevent access to certain features.

**Station practice:**

- Rough internal cavities early to relieve internal stresses.  
- Maintain adequate support in the forging during critical cuts.  
- Use specialized fixtures to hold the action at angles required for each operation (e.g., top latch recess, firing pin holes).', null, '3.4.4 Material Removal Strategy and Fixturing', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.B > 3. Main Content > 3.4 Decisions & Trade-Offs > 3.4.4 Material Removal Strategy and Fixturing', '["3-4-4-material-removal-strategy-and-fixturing","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-b-3-main-content-3-4-decisions-trade-offs-3-4-4-material-removal-strategy-and-fixturing"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:54:34.806094+00', null), ('fde6d958-00e1-44bb-ba42-dbef8f1153b2', 'a265cd6c-d21f-4b6d-a4d3-4aa569a508a9', '2', '58', '- **Perazzi**  
  - Canonical name: **Perazzi**.  
  - Legal name: **Armi Perazzi S.p.A.**  
  - Description: Italian manufacturer of high-end competition and game shotguns, founded by Daniele Perazzi in 1957 in Brescia, Italy. Specializes in low-volume, high-quality, highly customizable guns.

- **Perazzi USA**  
  - Role: Official U.S. importer and service hub for Perazzi shotguns and parts. Headquartered in Azusa, California.  
  - Function: Import, distribution, service, parts, and customer support for the U.S. market.

- **CSG Group (Czechoslovak Group)**  
  - Canonical name: **CSG**.  
  - Role: Industrial holding company that acquired an 80% stake in Perazzi in 2023 while Mauro and Roberta retained 20% and operational control.[1]

- **The Champions Network (TCN)**  
  - Canonical name: **The Champions Network**.  
  - Aliases: **TCN**. 
  - Description: Storytelling and content ecosystem focused on champions and aspirants using Perazzi shotguns. Used as a narrative and marketing vehicle (e.g., long-form proposals, phased campaigns, and potential events like the Perazzi Invitational).[53][58][65]', null, '2.1 Core Entities', 'Perazzi Brand Bible – AI Reference > 2. Key Concepts & Glossary > 2.1 Core Entities', '["2-1-core-entities","perazzi-brand-bible-ai-reference-2-key-concepts-glossary-2-1-core-entities"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:51:07.263026+00', null), ('fe25f6ec-2eee-4b48-a180-8be1e18fefe4', '1e2052a5-ee5e-4421-83c1-cf4e7172cbf2', '28', '45', '- **For Oil Finishes**  
  - Lint-free rags, fingers, or rubber/cloth pads for rubbing-in.  
  - Small containers for controlled oil portions.  
  - Drying racks or stands to prevent resting on finished areas.

- **For Sprayed Finishes**  
  - Spray guns, compressors, and regulators.  
  - Viscosity cups for thinning adjustments.  
  - Spray booth or ventilated area.

- **Curing Environment**  
  - Warm, low-dust room or cabinet.  
  - Hooks or supports for hanging stocks and fore-ends.', null, '3.5.2 Application & Curing Tools', 'The Making of a Perazzi Over-Under Shotgun – Part II.I > 3. Main Content > 3.5 Tools & Measurements (Conceptual Level) > 3.5.2 Application & Curing Tools', '["3-5-2-application-curing-tools","the-making-of-a-perazzi-over-under-shotgun-part-ii-i-3-main-content-3-5-tools-measurements-conceptual-level-3-5-2-application-curing-tools"]', '["Prospect","Owner","Navigation"]', '["Loyalist","Prestige","Analyst","Achiever","Legacy"]', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '2025-12-11 21:56:22.593132+00', null), ('fe40e599-9c33-442e-818c-c786213ed659', 'afb5cf00-70cd-49aa-b1ee-096c29e9674e', '0', '26', '> Version: 1.0  
> Owner: David Radulovich  
